"sanskrit\":\"\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"skyor chu skyes\"}},{\"uuid\":\"1f8feedb-2537-40b9-a8c6-52aaf91b0433\",\"authority\":\"87a4d541-deb9-4ac3-8ed7-ae9590000e2a\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eAn area in \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-9398\\\"\u003eKuru\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Born Round\",\"tibetan\":\"ཀུན་ནས་ཟླུམ་པར་སྐྱེས་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"kun nas zlum par skyes pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"71de96cf-2fb8-41d0-964d-b7f33b4dceae\",\"authority\":\"4927235b-321a-43bf-9ba2-cf06017a7368\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eAn area in \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-9398\\\"\u003eKuru\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Born Triangular\",\"tibetan\":\"གྲུ་གསུམ་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"gru gsum pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"9f45e79e-6407-48c1-b4a5-d72e2b1c3011\",\"authority\":\"7a108cff-501a-4289-bacf-ed7df02d60c6\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eOne of sixteen realms that surround the \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-9235\\\"\u003eGreat Howling Hell\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Boundless Torture\",\"tibetan\":\"ཚོར་བ་དབག་ཏུ་མེད།\",\"sanskrit\":\"aparimita­vedana\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"tshor ba dbag tu med\"}},{\"uuid\":\"22aacecd-ce8a-432e-af83-30700bb49bcd\",\"authority\":\"e1dec481-25d1-45ac-9634-9f6b97138a4b\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eA mountain in the sea west of \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-9338\\\"\u003eJambudvīpa\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Brāgajyotiṣa\",\"tibetan\":\"བྲཱ་ག་ཛྱོ་ཏི་ཥ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"brāgajyotiṣa\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"brA ga dz+yo ti Sha\"}},{\"uuid\":\"e4d3cd20-fd11-455c-844e-c5bb18b89e36\",\"authority\":\"db36127a-581c-4efe-9ebf-172706c136f8\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp\u003eA high-ranking deity presiding over a divine world; he is also considered to be the lord of the Sahā world (our universe). Though not considered a creator god in Buddhism, Brahmā occupies an important place as one of two gods (the other being Indra/Śakra) said to have first exhorted the Buddha Śākyamuni to teach the Dharma. The particular heavens found in the form realm over which Brahmā rules are often some of the most sought-after realms of higher rebirth in Buddhist literature. Since there are many universes or world systems, there are also multiple Brahmās presiding over them. His most frequent epithets are “Lord of the Sahā World” (\u003cem class=\\\"foreign break text-sa\\\" lang=\\\"sa-LATN\\\"\u003esahāṃpati\u003c/em\u003e) and Great Brahmā (\u003cem class=\\\"foreign break text-sa\\\" lang=\\\"sa-LATN\\\"\u003emahābrahman\u003c/em\u003e).\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Brahmā\",\"tibetan\":\"ཚངས་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"brahmā\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"tshangs pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"fbf14623-8bc4-49b3-82cc-09f81616c9c6\",\"authority\":\"55a600c9-c2f9-48a7-9b19-39a5ff3282f4\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eThe lower realm within the first \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-9969\\\"\u003econcentration\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Brahmā Realm\",\"tibetan\":\"ཚངས་རིས།\",\"sanskrit\":\"brahmakāyika\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"tshangs ris\"}},{\"uuid\":\"d2beaf90-2596-4dcc-b765-8064c0cba1f3\",\"authority\":\"47bce8c5-ec29-4bea-8b8a-a459224f0ba6\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eA member of the \u003cspan class=\\\"ignore\\\"\u003ebrahmin\u003c/span\u003e caste.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"brahmin\",\"tibetan\":\"བྲམ་ཟེ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"brāhmaṇa\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"bram ze\"}},{\"uuid\":\"27f641b5-8b75-40a5-92a7-5faaed828004\",\"authority\":\"e3e52d3f-bf22-4