y White Clouds\u003c/span\u003e (\u003cem class=\\\"foreign text-wy\\\" lang=\\\"bo-LATN\\\"\u003engang ngur rnams kyis rjes su bsgrags par byed pa\u003c/em\u003e). (2) A river on \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-9657\\\"\u003eSaṅkāśa\u003c/span\u003e (\u003cem class=\\\"foreign text-wy\\\" lang=\\\"bo-LATN\\\"\u003engang pa kun sgra ’byin pa\u003c/em\u003e). \u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Calling Geese\",\"tibetan\":\"ངང་ངུར་རྣམས་ཀྱིས་རྗེས་སུ་བསྒྲགས་པར་བྱེད་པ།, ངང་པ་ཀུན་སྒྲ་འབྱིན་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"ngang ngur rnams kyis rjes su bsgrags par byed pa, ngang pa kun sgra ’byin pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"6857822b-45e2-4813-a82c-b2789d9d6ffd\",\"authority\":\"f2cbdf52-fb59-48b9-ab78-dba315b9aed3\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eRefers to the meditative practice of calming the mind to rest free from the disturbance of thought. One of the two basic forms of Buddhist meditation, the other being \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-9923\\\"\u003especial insight\u003c/span\u003e (\u003cem class=\\\"foreign break text-sa\\\" lang=\\\"sa-LATN\\\"\u003evipaśyanā\u003c/em\u003e, \u003cem class=\\\"foreign text-wy\\\" lang=\\\"bo-LATN\\\"\u003elhag mthong\u003c/em\u003e).\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"calm abiding\",\"tibetan\":\"ཞི་གནས།\",\"sanskrit\":\"śamatha\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"zhi gnas\"}},{\"uuid\":\"acda2250-5859-4485-b5e2-032f3b06a140\",\"authority\":\"88c6e169-7694-4147-8fd8-758224c7c0e0\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eA land in the east of \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-9338\\\"\u003eJambudvīpa\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Camel Face\",\"tibetan\":\"རྔ་མོའི་བཞིན།\",\"sanskrit\":\"\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"rnga mo’i bzhin\"}},{\"uuid\":\"881b31c8-c966-4d59-aaa7-b7d00a6150c9\",\"authority\":\"5a540000-776f-48df-9c69-1767ce7a05bb\",\"definition\":\"\u