hting in Flower Garlands\",\"tibetan\":\"མེ་ཏོག་ཕྲེང་དགའ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"me tog phreng dga’\"}},{\"uuid\":\"fa4e5a30-cd2d-4dfe-b724-8d07a9a9dd19\",\"authority\":\"59d84cc9-5977-4228-ac09-b899a2c1866b\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eA realm of the \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-8516\\\"\u003eever-infatuated gods\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Delighting in Objects\",\"tibetan\":\"ཡུལ་ལ་འདོད་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"yul la ’dod pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"8c4df26d-3a5e-4879-a42e-02d77d8a29f6\",\"authority\":\"02164a3d-85f1-4992-a53a-1ac602f524d0\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eA pond on \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-9078\\\"\u003eEqual Peaks\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Delighting the People\",\"tibetan\":\"སྐྱེ་བོ་རྣམས་མངོན་པར་དགའ་བ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"skye bo rnams mngon par dga’ ba\"}},{\"uuid\":\"391da7bf-5c0b-4dfb-aab1-7dcfc40fe04a\",\"authority\":\"5e4917f5-ae42-4920-b668-f29b134322a9\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eAn emanated forest created upon the shoulders of \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-8636\\\"\u003eAirāvaṇa\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Desirable\",\"tibetan\":\"འདོད་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"’dod pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"20bb1d6b-75d3-4021-a466-36269d16ec8c\",\"authority\":\"3634ec82-1909-48e7-a3ae-28323794f324\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eA city in the \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-8489\\\"\u003easura\u003c/span\u003e realm called \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-9481\\\"\u003eMoon Garland\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Desired Wind\",\"tibetan\":\"འདོད་པའི་ཀླུང་།\",\"sanskrit\":\"\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"’dod pa’i klung\"}},{\"uuid\":\"ed04b085-14fb-4ba7-952e-758baccad7d0\",\"authority\":\"efcebac0-3384-491b-9a0c-df6112967ba8\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eA cousin of the Buddha \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-10026\\\"\u003eŚākyamuni\u003c/span\u003e who broke with him and established his own community. His tradition was still continuing during the first millennium \u003cspan class=\\\"small-caps\\\"\u003eᴄᴇ\u003c/span\u003e. He is portrayed as engendering evil schemes against the Buddha and even succeeding in wounding him. He is usually identified with wicked beings in accounts of previous lifetimes.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Devadatta\",\"tibetan\":\"ལྷས་བྱིན།\",\"sanskrit\":\"devadatta\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"lhas byin\"}},{\"uuid\":\"a40034a3-e020-4c00-b967-5757173a5b0f\",\"authority\":\"d8cfde35-d1b1-4dee-af18-43f066d1ddce\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eThe Indian king who established \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-9851\\\"\u003eVikramaśīla\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Devapāla\",\"tibetan\":\"དེ་བ་ཕཱ་ལ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"devapāla\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"de ba phA la\"}},{\"uuid\":\"d82e3613-3ecd-459b-90e4-dff460e353dd\",\"authority\":\"16dfb0f1-2232-4fdd-a01b-103387db83f7\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eOne of the twenty-seven realms in the \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-9266\\\"\u003eHeaven Free from Strife\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Devoid of the Sound of Concentration\",\"tibetan\":\"བསམ་གཏན་སྒྲའི་བྱ་བས་དབེན་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"bsam gtan sgra’i bya bas dben pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"b98e0a0a-e4b2-408a-b1d0-d27d91224b0c\",\"authority\":\"4d12900d-2415-48bc-a1e6-345d7c3f55a3\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eA \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-8562\\\"\u003enāga\u003c/span\u003e who visits \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-9657\\\"\u003eSaṅkāśa\u003c/span\u003e Mountain.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Dharma Master Surrounded by Clouds\",\"tibetan\":\"སྤྲིན་གྱི་ཉེ་འཁོར་ཆོས་ལ་དབང་བ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"sprin gyi nye ’khor chos la dbang ba\"}},{\"uuid\":\"c8f3d188-2996-4689-9f87-c02f70f2e31e\",\"authority\":\"034c6bd3-2bb0-49a9-84c3-21d487f4a7fc\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eAn early term to denote the Buddha’s teaching. “Dharma” refers to the \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-9986\\\"\u003esūtras\u003c/span\u003e and “\u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-9974\\\"\u003eVinaya\u003c/span\u003e” to the rules of discipline.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Dharma-Vinaya\",\"tibetan\":\"ཆོས་འདུལ་བ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"dharmavinaya\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"chos ’dul ba\"}},{\"uuid\":\"51956966-be91-4b65-9d33-f7cf5c25811e\",\"authority\":\"1d0cad53-f093-4c7a-9c5c-4272a0ff52d4\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eA mountain in the eastern sea beyond \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-9338\\\"\u003eJambudvīpa\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Dhiriko\",\"tibetan\":\"དྷི་རི་ཀོ\",\"sanskrit\":\"dhiriko\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"dhi ri ko\"}},{\"uuid\":\"9d2ca8fb-2e60-4709-9745-53737dc6a8ad\",\"authority\":\"b14e9896-8b44-45ed-9b7d-5692e266740f\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eOne among the \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-8526\\\"\u003eFour Great Kings\u003c/span\u003e, guardian of the east.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Dhṛtarāṣṭra\",\"tibetan\":\"ཡུལ་འཁོར་སྐྱོང་།\",\"sanskrit\":\"dhṛtarāṣṭra\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"yul ’khor skyong\"}},{\"uuid\":\"9b88d71e-8b13-4788-acb4-b0111033853a\",\"authority\"