\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"za ba po\"}},{\"uuid\":\"cbc7fa66-921d-48f4-82a9-e65f01e472e7\",\"authority\":\"25954d86-13d6-449a-8e47-06ecdb5cb335\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eA forest on \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-9771\\\"\u003eTamer of Deer Enemies\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Egg-Born Infatuation\",\"tibetan\":\"མྱོས་པ་སྒོ་ང་ལས་སྐྱེས་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"myos pa sgo nga las skyes pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"db9e6de6-2f04-48a1-aba6-52d196525b4e\",\"authority\":\"ccf427f1-a6cc-446b-91af-183c91173f91\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eEight factors constituting the path of cultivation, namely: right view, right intention, right speech, right activity, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, and right absorption.. These are further explained in this text, see \u003ca href=\\\"UT22084-068-021-section-6.xhtml#UT22084-068-021-4043\\\" data-pointer-type=\\\"id\\\"\u003e4.B.1101\u003c/a\u003e–\u003ca href=\\\"UT22084-068-021-section-6.xhtml#UT22084-068-021-4044\\\" data-pointer-type=\\\"id\\\"\u003e4.B.1102\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"eight branches of the noble path, eightfold path, eightfold path of the noble ones\",\"tibetan\":\"འཕགས་པའི་ལམ་ཡན་ལག་བརྒྱད།\",\"sanskrit\":\"āryāṣṭāṅga­mārga\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"’phags pa’i lam yan lag brgyad\"}},{\"uuid\":\"e15669a4-c64d-4734-a4df-5f50fe1f2f2e\",\"authority\":\"5f766d84-7400-44ea-a135-ade139e0a698\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eHoping for happiness, fame, praise and gain and fearing suffering, insignificance, blame and loss.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"eight mundane concerns\",\"tibetan\":\"འཇིག་རྟེན་གྱི་ཆོས་བརྒྱད།\",\"sanskrit\":\"aṣṭa­loka­dharma\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"’jig rten gyi chos brgyad\"}},{\"uuid\":\"898be4c2-0729-4590-8d9e-5040e2552a46\",\"authority\":\"8ad4e903-8811-483a-9bc5-1ae411fced9a\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eSee \u003ca href=\\\"UT22084-068-021-chapter-2.xhtml#UT22084-068-021-206\\\" data-pointer-type=\\\"id\\\"\u003e2.4\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"eighteen categories of discernment, eighteen discernments, eighteen forms of discernment, eighteen types of discernment\",\"tibetan\":\"ཡིད་ཀྱི་དཔྱོད་པ་བཅོ་བརྒྱད།\",\"sanskrit\":\"\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"yid kyi dpyod pa bco brgyad\"}},{\"uuid\":\"979a8df9-464d-4d79-9bda-299dc188c053\",\"authority\":\"e5de4a74-1aec-4917-8034-ee47c1d63741\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eThe objects, sense \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-9924\\\"\u003efaculties\u003c/span\u003e, and forms of consciousness that are associated with form, sound, smell, taste, touch, and mental phenomena. See also “\u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-9921\\\"\u003eelement\u003c/span\u003e.”\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"eighteen elements\",\"tibetan\":\"ཁམས་བཅོ་བརྒྱད།\",\"sanskrit\":\"aṣṭā­daśa­dhātu\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"khams bco brgyad\"}},{\"uuid\":\"87b038b7-dc28-4897-bc8e-03a757675733\",\"authority\":\"e2fca84d-1615-4318-856b-db1a886d3fab\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eEighteen special features of a buddha’s behavior, realization, activity, and wisdom that are not shared by other beings.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"eighteen floods of unique qualities\",\"tibetan\":\"ཡོན་ཏན་གྱི་ཀླུང་རང་གི་ཡོན་ཏན་བཅོ་བརྒྱད།\",\"sanskrit\":\"\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"yon tan gyi klung rang gi yon tan bco brgyad\"}},{\"uuid\":\"b00d6211-3c02-40c0-bd29-4805807c4d34\",\"authority\":\"4659bc58-3135-4a2d-a890-69f39530d845\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eOne among the twelve sections of scripture.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"elaborate teachings\",\"tibetan\":\"ཤིན་ཏུ་རྒྱས་པའི་སྡེ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"vaipulya\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"shin tu rgyas pa’i sde\"}},{\"uuid\":\"1364ded3-bd82-4c3b-8f35-1ded727bca81\",\"authority\":\"e3685c95-a735-4cb3-a0e7-d0d5dc0b3295\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eIn the context of Buddhist philosophy, one way to describe experience and the world is in terms of \u003cspan class=\\\"ignore\\\"\u003eeighteen elements\u003c/span\u003e (eye, form, and eye consciousness; ear, sound, and ear consciousness; nose, smell, and nose consciousness; tongue, taste, and tongue consciousness; body, touch, and body consciousness; mind, mental phenomena, and mind consciousness).\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eThe \u003cspan class=\\\"ignore\\\"\u003eelements\u003c/span\u003e also refer to the \u003cspan class=\\\"ignore\\\"\u003eelements\u003c/span\u003e of the physical world, which are the four main \u003cspan class=\\\"ignore\\\"\u003eelements\u003c/span\u003e: earth, water, fire, and \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-100021\\\"\u003ewind\u003c/span\u003e. Sometimes two extra \u003cspan class=\\\"ignore\\\"\u003eelements\u003c/span\u003e are added to this list: space and consciousness.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"element\",\"tibetan\":\"ཁམས།\",\"sanskrit\":\"dhātu\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"khams\"}},{\"uuid\":\"66f34608-5e08-44d3-9e82-ba8371c66ed0\",\"authority\":\"ff230a68-c1f4-4225-babf-9e4441e731f9\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eA class of \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-8622\\\"\u003evidyādharas\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"elephant chariot\",\"tibetan\":\"གླང་པོའི་ཤིང་རྟ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"glang po’i shing rta\"}},{\"uuid\":\"c8d2d850-bb9c-459b-ba93-07b9084bc015\",\"authority\":\"1160f36d-7f80-4c94-b6aa-cd32156346bd\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eA forest on \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-9128\\\"\u003eFlocking Peacocks\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Elevated Sounds\",\"tibetan\":\"སྒྲ་འཕང་མཐོན་པོ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"sgra ’phang mthon po\"}},{\"uuid\":\"347b557f-1661-4647-bd04-75e0e1980c51\",\"authority\":\"c4ea2609-dab7-4ece-b7cd-7828a94bd5fd\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eOne of sixteen realms that surround the \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-9235\\\"\u003eGreat Howling Hell\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Eleven Flames\",\"tibetan\":\"མེ་ལྕེ་བཅུ་གཅིག\",\"sanskrit\":\"ekādaśārcis\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"me lce bcu gcig\"}},{\"uuid\":\"54af20b7-0e14-4541-9262-a1271d95c47f\",\"authority\":\"c4f9cca3-7483-4464-9c39-3626bace545d\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eA land in the east of \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-9338\\\"\u003eJambudvīpa\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Eliminating Ailing Deer\",\"tibetan\":\"ཤ་བ་ན་འཆང་བ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"sha ba na ’chang ba\"}},{\"uuid\":\"01375a25-c07a-4d07-9428-bf1a1960c1fa\",\"authority\":\"1fe42549-bbe7-4d8a-a857-c0e6001fe39f\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eA previous ruler of the \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-9276\\\"\u003eHeaven of the Thirty-Three\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Emanated Śakra\",\"tibetan\":\"སྤྲུལ་པའི་བརྒྱ་བྱིན།\",\"sanskrit\":\"\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"sprul pa’i brgya byin\"}},{\"uuid\":\"521b40c6-eaa8-4a8a-9eee-de3be23a0655\",\"authority\":\"0f0d8809-c4a8-43e2-9ec7-03c89037c7c7\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eOne of the twenty-seven realms of the \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-9266\\\"\u003eHeaven Free from Strife\u003c/span\u003e.\u003