:\"b40e108b-6978-49f5-bced-880748027844\",\"authority\":\"be8e8fea-d313-4b07-9c13-cc9433d1c874\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eA pleasure grove in \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-9668\\\"\u003eShaded by Garlands\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Forest of White Lotus Petals\",\"tibetan\":\"པད་མ་དཀར་པོའི་ཚལ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"pad ma dkar po’i tshal\"}},{\"uuid\":\"06448c53-2966-4033-be7e-7934df9b3dbd\",\"authority\":\"1c120dd2-bd53-48ed-989b-5765f22a59ac\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e\u003cspan class=\\\"ignore\\\"\u003eFour ages\u003c/span\u003e of human life in \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-9338\\\"\u003eJambudvīpa\u003c/span\u003e including the \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-8483\\\"\u003eage of perfection\u003c/span\u003e, \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-8485\\\"\u003eage of threefold endowment\u003c/span\u003e, age of twofold endowment, and \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-8484\\\"\u003eage of strife\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"four ages\",\"tibetan\":\"དུས་བཞི།\",\"sanskrit\":\"caturyuga\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"dus bzhi\"}},{\"uuid\":\"04ff888f-51c9-49c8-983c-060adfa89c4d\",\"authority\":\"13bed90e-9b81-4b91-adae-6614d77a40d7\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eThe four levels of the realm of form.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"four concentrations\",\"tibetan\":\"བསམ་བཏན་བཞི།\",\"sanskrit\":\"caturdhyāna\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"bsam btan bzhi\"}},{\"uuid\":\"a7f049cb-5f1d-456f-8313-b7348eaf54a1\",\"authority\":\"907d8e58-4bcc-4dc3-b466-c744321bf96c\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eTaking what is impermanent to be permanent, what is painful to be delightful, what is unclean to be clean, and what is no self to be a self.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"four errors\",\"tibetan\":\"ཕྱིན་ཅི་ལོག་བཞི།\",\"sanskrit\":\"caturviprayāsa\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"phyin ci log bzhi\"}},{\"uuid\":\"ebe1e705-276e-4952-b683-2842163bdaae\",\"authority\":\"bb33d68b-14a3-4413-b73c-7ba5c306b5dc\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eThe four results of the \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-8536\\\"\u003ehearer\u003c/span\u003e’s path.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"four fruitions\",\"tibetan\":\"འབྲས་བུ་བཞི།\",\"sanskrit\":\"caturphala\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"’bras bu bzhi\"}},{\"uuid\":\"a2bcf0ed-8865-4c0f-b74b-ede745904d1b\",\"authority\":\"d0099514-8ec5-4014-9139-eb47d42c74a0\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eThe divine kings who rule the four directions: Vaiśravaṇa (who in this text appears under his alternative name \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-8702\\\"\u003eKubera\u003c/span\u003e), \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-8775\\\"\u003eVirūḍhaka\u003c/span\u003e, \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-8658\\\"\u003eDhṛtarāṣṭra\u003c/span\u003e, and \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-8776\\\"\u003eVirūpākṣa\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Four Great Kings\",\"tibetan\":\"རྒྱལ་ཆེན་བཞི།\",\"sanskrit\":\"caturmahārāja\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"rgyal chen bzhi\"}},{\"uuid\":\"be885a17-3d78-4aa1-a10a-62568e066302\",\"authority\":\"096296b3-676b-4289-8ef7-d65068aa68fc\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eThis seems to refer to the four continents around Mount Meru.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"four human abodes\",\"tibetan\":\"མིའི་གནས་བཞི།\",\"sanskrit\":\"\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"mi’i gnas bzhi\"}},{\"uuid\":\"9d287c52-6bfd-45ad-9db4-d2f2a5804a2f\",\"authority\":\"235580a4-d7fa-46de-9f28-040432b1aa02\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e