Lotuses\",\"tibetan\":\"པད་མས་ཁྱབ་པར་གྱུར་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"pad mas khyab par gyur pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"a14c0e16-b041-4032-aaed-0c94f1bc2808\",\"authority\":\"6da0112b-97cc-4c6d-ab53-621629184f02\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eOne of sixteen realms that surround the \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-8975\\\"\u003eCrushing Hell\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Furnace\",\"tibetan\":\"མེ་ཐབ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"agnikuṇḍa\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"me thab\"}},{\"uuid\":\"4b5fff0a-a58b-4b08-b00d-7c8a73e9e40f\",\"authority\":\"d641c10d-c475-4263-b511-4dcd82e06a7b\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eA virtuous \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-8562\\\"\u003enāga\u003c/span\u003e king.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Gajānana\",\"tibetan\":\"གླང་པོའི་གདོང་།\",\"sanskrit\":\"gajānana\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"glang po’i gdong\"}},{\"uuid\":\"e228c566-ae6d-491d-89fb-fa8b720b9505\",\"authority\":\"16eceb46-2f00-4d02-a95d-4eee5b8fddfe\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eA lake in \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-9209\\\"\u003eGodānīya\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Gambhīrajala\",\"tibetan\":\"གམ་བྷི་ར་ཛ་ལང་།\",\"sanskrit\":\"gambhīrajala\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"gam bhi ra dza lang\"}},{\"uuid\":\"7dc69e3c-5fe0-42ea-b9cc-9b2721770cf6\",\"authority\":\"003d4426-ed2d-4601-82c4-3d55b4cf61a1\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eA land to the north of \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-9338\\\"\u003eJambudvīpa\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Gandhara\",\"tibetan\":\"གན་དྷ་ར།\",\"sanskrit\":\"gandhara\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"gan d+ha ra\"}},{\"uuid\":\"b74ef150-7f77-412e-9bb2-1b4c5052267f\",\"authority\":\"74461fd0-5ed8-4923-b6bb-16bb40dfa426\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp\u003eA class of generally benevolent nonhuman beings who inhabit the skies, sometimes said to inhabit fantastic cities in the clouds, and more specifically to dwell on the eastern slopes of Mount Meru, where they are ruled by the Great King Dhṛtarāṣṭra. They are most renowned as celestial musicians who serve the gods. In the Abhidharma, the term is also used to refer to the mental body assumed by sentient beings during the intermediate state between death and rebirth. Gandharvas are said to live on fragrances (\u003cem class=\\\"foreign break text-sa\\\" lang=\\\"sa-LATN\\\"\u003egandha\u003c/em\u003e) in the desire realm, hence the Tibetan translation \u003cem class=\\\"foreign text-wy\\\" lang=\\\"bo-LATN\\\"\u003edri za\u003c/em\u003e, meaning “scent eater.”\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"gandharva\",\"tibetan\":\"དྲི་ཟ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"gandharva\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"dri za\"}},{\"uuid\":\"57ba503f-9dc3-4e38-8b29-3730482f0770\",\"authority\":\"3c2353af-4852-4412-aaea-3ccf82db4cd6\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eA river on \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-9657\\\"\u003eSaṅkāśa\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Gandharva Melody\",\"tibetan\":\"དྲི་ཟའི་དབྱངས་ཅན།\",\"sanskrit\":\"\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"dri za’i dbyangs can\"}},{\"uuid\":\"aa13dec1-b1a9-46bd-9d62-44afb78f7e12\",\"authority\":\"062f7b7f-39dc-4bcc-a998-f5cf2636a853\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp\u003eThe Gaṅgā, or Ganges in English, is considered to be the most sacred river of India, particularly within the Hindu tradition. It starts in the Himalayas, flows through the northern plains of India, bathing the holy city of Vārāṇasī, and meets the sea at the Bay of Bengal, in Bangladesh. In the sūtras, however, this river is mostly mentioned not for its sacredness but for its abundant sands‍—noticeable still today on its many sandy banks and at its delta‍—which serve as a common metaphor for infinitely large numbers.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eAccording to Buddhist cosmology, as explained in the \u003ccite class=\\\"title text-en\\\" lang=\\\"en\\\"\u003eAbhidharmakośa\u003c/cite\u003e, it is one of the four rivers that flow from Lake Anavatapta and cross the southern continent of Jambudvīpa‍—the known human world or more specifically the Indian subcontinent. \u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Gaṅgā\",\"tibetan\":\"གང་གཱ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"gaṅgā\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"gang gA\"}},{\"uuid\":\"3c127884-956e-4412-84c1-9cff014a49e6\",\"authority\":\"731bf4f6-e21e-4881-8e9d-563522073092\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eA city in \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-9209\\\"\u003eGodānīya\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Gaṅkara\",\"tibetan\":\"གང་ཀ་ར།\",\"sanskrit\":\"gaṅkara\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"gang ka ra\"}},{\"uuid\":\"b8f9da69-1b67-426f-af9c-5917a3f308d5\",\"authority\":\"ca8a4f59-65e5-4e09-930f-c5f3aee84197\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eA park in \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-8867\\\"\u003eBorn in a Tank\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Garland\",\"tibetan\":\"ཕྲེང་།\",\"sanskrit\":\"\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"phreng\"}},{\"uuid\":\"5ec5f729-08fa-4651-a8b2-127e0ae5a7c9\",\"authority\":\"476fa6b0-92b0-42d8-b06b-60bac59bbd22\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eAn area in \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-9398\\\"\u003eKuru\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Garland Abode\",\"tibetan\":\"ཕྲེང་བ་གནས་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"phreng ba gnas pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"78440e64-13f2-4861-994f-df808b947674\",\"authority\":\"59fd2e08-2c95-4122-b4f4-57158995111f\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eA class of \u003cs