2084-068-021-9338\\\"\u003eJambudvīpa\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Kailāśa\",\"tibetan\":\"ཏི་སེ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"kailāśa\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"ti se\"}},{\"uuid\":\"cda6967c-d0f6-49c1-9a61-ddc6004ccb90\",\"authority\":\"03649153-3c83-4d8a-ae81-8f64ab82398d\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eA mountain north of \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-9338\\\"\u003eJambudvīpa\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Kailāśa Horn\",\"tibetan\":\"ཏི་སེའི་རྭ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"ti se’i rwa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"f2457bfd-2bfc-40be-b0f7-038cbb56cb20\",\"authority\":\"d57850df-a25a-4a46-aa5b-dd47b1677d7f\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eAn unvirtuous \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-8562\\\"\u003enāga\u003c/span\u003e king.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Kāla\",\"tibetan\":\"ནག་པོ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"kāla\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"nag po\"}},{\"uuid\":\"3e9f5fb3-f861-4757-aac5-848d744cf086\",\"authority\":\"8aba21a4-783b-4280-ba83-432dce7d1bef\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eAn island in the sea west of \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-9338\\\"\u003eJambudvīpa\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Kālaka\",\"tibetan\":\"ཀཱ་ལ་ཀོ\",\"sanskrit\":\"kālaka\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"kA la ko\"}},{\"uuid\":\"7efaaf8e-0744-4ca0-b258-48fa13dc0ad0\",\"authority\":\"fb6e8152-4f57-433b-a23e-2e11c967c688\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eA deadly poison that originated when the \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-8531\\\"\u003egods\u003c/span\u003e and \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-8489\\\"\u003easuras\u003c/span\u003e churned the oceans to create the nectar of immortality.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"kālakūṭa\",\"tibetan\":\"ཀཱ་ལ་ཀུ་ཊ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"kālakūṭa\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"kA la ku Ta\"}},{\"uuid\":\"8b09a86f-030e-48b6-a2f7-32387be173f8\",\"authority\":\"752c8e45-09fe-4b4d-8cc0-d1a07eb0fbb2\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eA land to the north of \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-9338\\\"\u003eJambudvīpa\u003c/span\u003e, corresponding to the northern Afghanistan\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Kamboja\",\"tibetan\":\"ཀམ་པོ་ཛཱི།\",\"sanskrit\":\"kamboja\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"kam po dzI\"}},{\"uuid\":\"22ed69b2-7e51-4f3d-a4a9-e61d967dfd3c\",\"authority\":\"758ab9c9-399e-48a1-a1af-fd9e86918965\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eThe name of a previous buddha.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Kanakamuni\",\"tibetan\":\"གསེར་ཐུབ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"kanakamuni\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"gser thub\"}},{\"uuid\":\"9f5ca546-6149-44fb-8ac3-81d8067885b3\",\"authority\":\"586e5934-ec66-4659-852a-227c683e7529\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eKing of the “\u003cspan\u003e\u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-8564\\\"\u003enecklaces\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e” (a class of \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-8489\\\"\u003easuras\u003c/span\u003e).\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Kaṇṭhamāla\",\"tibetan\":\"མགུལ་ཕྲེང་།\",\"sanskrit\":\"kaṇṭhamāla\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"mgul phreng\"}},{\"uuid\":\"3f828789-569b-475e-936d-f593aa04c57d\",\"authority\":\"ae9f5d79-3cb8-417c-a285-6c9606e1c3c9\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eA bird of a red color whose voice has been described as like thunder or the sound of a drum.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"karada\",\"tibetan\":\"ཀ་ར་ད།\",\"sanskrit\":\"karada\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"ka ra da\"}},{\"uuid\":\"2b16e93c-570a-49f0-a0a9-2fcd483b50e3\",\"authority\":\"08542357-a76f-4cf7-b3dd-1cf01842c485\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eA stone sometimes identified as cat’s eye.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"karketana\",\"tibetan\":\"ཀེ་ཀེ་རུ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"karketana\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"ke ke ru\"}},{\"uuid\":\"44394edb-98b3-4e82-b0d6-d9fa66ff4226\",\"authority\":\"5a7e8a58-228c-423a-b3d2-aabf5fe3b53c\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e(1284–1339). An important master in the Karma Kagyu lineage of Tibetan Buddhism (\u003cem class=\\\"foreign text-wy\\\" lang=\\\"bo-LATN\\\"\u003ekarma bka’ brgyud\u003c/em\u003e). He is considered the third master in the lineage to have the title of Karmapa.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Karmapa III, Rangjung Dorjé\",\"tibetan\":\"རང་འབྱུང་རྡོ་རྗེ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"rang ’byung rdo rje\"}},{\"uuid\":\"5cb1014d-c618-472e-928d-0be854478200\",\"authority\":\"13153320-dcb9-46f7-b704-d0437fee728f\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eOne of the three types of karma whose results are experience neither in the present nor the next, but the subsequent lives. The other two types are the “karma that ripens in this life” (\u003cem class=\\\"foreign break text-sa\\\" lang=\\\"sa-LATN\\\"\u003edṛṣṭa­dharma­vipāka\u003c/em\u003e or \u003cem class=\\\"foreign break text-sa\\\" lang=\\\"sa-LATN\\\"\u003edṛṣṭa­dharma­vedanīya\u003c/em\u003e) and the “karma that is to be experienced in the immediately following life” (\u003cem class=\\\"foreign break text-sa\\\" lang=\\\"sa-LATN\\\"\u003eupapadya­vedanīya\u003c/em\u003e).\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"karmic actions to be experienced in other lives\",\"tibetan\":\"ལན་གྲངས་གཞན་ལ་མྱོང་བར་འགྱུར་བའི་ལས།\",\"sanskrit\":\"apara­paryāya­vedanīya\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"lan grangs gzhan la myong bar ’gyur ba’i las\"}},{\"uuid\":\"9dbb7f4f-7b7f-4173-a879-c90f7203c679\",\"authority\":\"bbea74ca-d19c-4ab7-90b9-77300e20333b\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eA land in the east of \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-9338\\\"\u003eJambudvīpa\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Karṇika\",\"tibetan\":\"ཀརྞྞི་ཀ\",\"sanskrit\":\"karṇika\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"kar+N+Ni ka\"}},{\"uuid\":\"39e256f1-6af9-440b-b3f5-91d28a413331\",\"authority\":\"d30b95e3-bc0c-4dca-8305-bd91015ca00a\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eThe grass \u003cem class=\\\"foreign\\\"\u003eSaccharum spontaneum\u003c/em\u003e, native to Indian subcontinent.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"kāsa\",\"tibetan\":\"ཀ་ས།\",\"sanskrit\":\"kāsa\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"ka sa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"16af352f-99c6-4b59-bb18-15e65eee3728\",\"authority\":\"0054a2e8-a50e-45b9-a77d-c1d2cfc6334b\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eAncient name for \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-10019\\\"\u003eVārāṇasī\u003c/span\u003e, the holy city on the banks of the \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-9182\\\"\u003eGaṅgā\u003c/span\u003e, this name can be applied also to the surrounding country or district. It lies in modern day Uttar Pradesh, India.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Kāśī\",\"tibetan\":\"ཀ་ཤི་ཀ, ཀ་ཤི།, ཀཱ་ཤི།\",\"sanskrit\":\"\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"kA shi, ka shi, ka shi ka\"}},{\"uuid\":\"a7964590-bdae-4ad7-9f3a-29bf9f4c739d\",\"authority\":\"c9571afc-2255-4c00-9268-432006dbdd35\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eA previous buddha.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Kāśyapa\",\"tibetan\":\"འོད་སྲུང་།\",\"sanskrit\":\"kāśyapa\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"’od srung\"}},{\"uuid\":\"cc862b30-e334-4f17-a19f-cc1988720588\",\"authority\":\"273809d4-74d3-4298-992f-b87c44666916\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eA land to the north of \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-9338\