ition\\\"\u003eOne among the twelve sections of scripture.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"past-life stories\",\"tibetan\":\"སྐྱེས་པ་རབས་ཀྱི་སྡེ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"jātaka\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"skyes pa rabs kyi sde\"}},{\"uuid\":\"5326689d-97db-4c80-b715-c82ad9426bdd\",\"authority\":\"6a8a6338-9729-4033-af40-44209e4a0df1\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eA city in \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-9338\\\"\u003eJambudvīpa\u003c/span\u003e; present day Patna.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Pāṭaliputra\",\"tibetan\":\"པཱ་ཊཱ་ལི་པུ་ཏྲ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"pāṭaliputra\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"pA TA li pu tra\"}},{\"uuid\":\"a520d09f-0cab-429d-9dea-46460cc85598\",\"authority\":\"5b2b2115-9219-40b3-b984-e942eb35c3e2\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eThe name of a Tibetan family to which belonged the renowned translator Patshap Nyima Drakpa.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Patshap\",\"tibetan\":\"པ་ཚབ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"pa tshab\"}},{\"uuid\":\"06eeafb3-6e7a-45a9-a148-46d8a8e4fd64\",\"authority\":\"f7b5d707-5e89-4ebc-bf32-f0fa12a7327f\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eThe primary translator of this scripture.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Patshap Tsultrim Gyaltsen, Tsultrim Gyaltsen\",\"tibetan\":\"པ་ཚབ་ཚུལ་ཁྲིམས་རྒྱལ་མཚན།\",\"sanskrit\":\"\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"pa tshab tshul khrims rgyal mtshan\"}},{\"uuid\":\"3eeb7f6a-2dcd-4030-89bd-df482de901b4\",\"authority\":\"3c1a285a-882d-4f8c-9629-edeb7ab7a03e\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eA class of \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-8622\\\"\u003evidyādharas\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"paurva\",\"tibetan\":\"པཽ་རྭ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"paurva\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"pau rwa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"43e192de-5bce-49dd-ba69-485cefe0f4bf\",\"authority\":\"cca53940-8e1c-4ee0-976f-601caf29854c\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eAn area in \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-9398\\\"\u003eKuru\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Peacock Call\",\"tibetan\":\"རྨ་བྱའི་སྒྲ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"rma bya’i sgra\"}},{\"uuid\":\"039ba75c-bc93-454a-94f0-9fa26b2fed0b\",\"authority\":\"aba75a39-31ba-467b-a4c4-9aa7588c2384\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eAn island in the vicinity of \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-9338\\\"\u003eJambudvīpa\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Peacock Forest\",\"tibetan\":\"རྨ་བྱའི་ནགས།\",\"sanskrit\":\"\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"rma bya’i nags\"}},{\"uuid\":\"1f964bff-73e5-429a-a211-94ce0a9df997\",\"authority\":\"5b91d280-d3b9-4f21-952f-1c914d09f81c\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eAn island in the vicinity of \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-9338\\\"\u003eJambudvīpa\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Pearl\",\"tibetan\":\"མུ་ཏིག\",\"sanskrit\":\"\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"mu tig\"}},{\"uuid\":\"02ac1e5e-243d-4bc8-bd26-7c36ccc266f8\",\"authority\":\"eb9881d7-0197-4f76-812a-6f6068d7f85a\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eA river in \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-9519\\\"\u003eMutual Liking\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Pearl Stream\",\"tibetan\":\"མུ་ཏིག་འབབ་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"mu tig ’bab pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"bc6e0567-0267-443c-88e8-1946f51adfd2\",\"authority\":\"4c522ef5-a51c-41da-a268-5f1fe195835c\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eA river on \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-9657\\\"\u003eSaṅkāśa\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Pearly Sand\",\"tibetan\":\"མུ་ཏིག་གི་བྱེ་མ་དང་ལྡན་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"mu tig gi bye ma dang ldan pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"c5ae4358-5887-4fb1-ab8b-fbb95298da6b\",\"authority\":\"e50a5132-170b-4676-8053-639028a96c11\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eA realm inhabited by \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-8530\\\"\u003egarland-bearer gods\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Peripheral\",\"tibetan\":\"ཟུར་ལ་གནས་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"zur la gnas pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"c56f12f3-a1a3-4d11-8f28-cc820090a120\",\"authority\":\"557bd24b-c51e-4d50-9015-2247092b8f75\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eA class of \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-8622\\\"\u003evidyādharas\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"pervasive attachment\",\"tibetan\":\"ཀུན་ཏུ་ཁྱབ་པའི་ཞེན་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"kun tu khyab pa’i zhen pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"28520a62-5ad3-4f69-92a1-92605be7ca2c\",\"authority\":\"cd055ef5-916f-4dd6-9e17-59c4e8a4a8cb\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eA forest in \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-9796\\\"\u003eTotal Pleasure\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Pervasive Fragrance\",\"tibetan\":\"དྲི་འཐུལ་བ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"dri ’thul ba\"}},{\"uuid\":\"a1478969-2a92-4ec9-9a37-9683889b7748\",\"authority\":\"246800a7-e7ca-495a-93be-e41681b68a48\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eAn ocean between \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-9398\\\"\u003eKuru\u003c/span\u003e and \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-9209\\\"\u003eGodānīya\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Pervasive Waters\",\"tibetan\":\"ཆུས་ཁྱབ་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"chus khyab pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"6af4c99a-3f38-484d-88d3-e794470f9260\",\"authority\":\"938158a6-039e-40fb-8af2-dde051c447e6\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e(1) A river on \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-9657\\\"\u003eSaṅkāśa\u003c/span\u003e (\u003cem class=\\\"foreign text-wy\\\" lang=\\\"bo-LATN\\\"\u003ertse mo\u003c/em\u003e). (2) One of four parks that surround the city of \u003cspan data-ref=\\\"UT22084-068-021-9605\\\"\u003e\u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-9605\\\"\u003eRadiant\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/span\u003e (\u003cem class=\\\"foreign text-wy\\\" lang=\\\"bo-LATN\\\"\u003ertse mo can\u003c/em\u003e).\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Pinnacle\",\"tibetan\":\"རྩེ་མོ་ཅན།, རྩེ་མོ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"rtse mo, rtse mo can\"}},{\"uuid\":\"02559a9d-b6dd-4119-bc9a-77e18e40ec84\",\"authority\":\"5830463c-615e-4a92-a4cd-68f3a648081d\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp\u003eA class of nonhuman beings that, like several other classes of nonhuman beings, take spontaneous birth. Ranking below rākṣasas, they are less powerful and more akin to pretas. They are said to dwell in impure and perilous places, where they feed on impure things, including flesh. This could account for the name \u003cem class=\\\"foreign break text-sa\\\" lang=\\\"sa-LATN\\\"\u003epiśāca\u003c/em\u003e, which possibly derives from \u003cem class=\\\"foreign break text-sa\\\" lang=\\\"sa-LATN\\\"\u003e√piś\u003c/em\u003e, to carve or chop meat, as reflected also in the Tibetan \u003cem class=\\\"foreign break text-sa\\\" lang=\\\"sa-LATN\\\"\u003esha za\u003c/em\u003e, “meat eater.” They are often described as having an unpleasant appearance, and at times they appear with animal bodies. Some possess the ability to enter the dead bodies of humans, thereby becoming so-called \u003cem class=\\\"foreign break text-sa\\\" lang=\\\"sa-LATN\\\"\u003evetāla\u003c/em\u003e, to touch whom is fatal.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"engli