cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-9511\\\"\u003eMoving in Vast Environments\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Radiant Streams\",\"tibetan\":\"ཆུ་ཀླུང་འོད་འབྱིན།\",\"sanskrit\":\"\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"chu klung ’od ’byin\"}},{\"uuid\":\"7753a90f-1fbc-496c-a768-753a1a8f1412\",\"authority\":\"df74b2cc-e30a-4a58-8507-4dd54e98becf\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eAn \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-8489\\\"\u003easura\u003c/span\u003e king.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Rāhu\",\"tibetan\":\"སྒྲ་གཅན།, སྒྲ་ཅན།\",\"sanskrit\":\"rāhu\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"sgra can, sgra gcan\"}},{\"uuid\":\"06cfc474-eb9a-4a14-8928-77aca3e176e6\",\"authority\":\"3a1e72fc-0622-435d-8622-b9dc3ec81ce7\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eOne of sixteen realms that surround the \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-9298\\\"\u003eHowling Hell\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Rain of Burning Stones\",\"tibetan\":\"རྡོ་མེ་འབར་བ་ཆར་ལྟར་འབབ་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"rdo me ’bar ba char ltar ’bab pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"f064b151-88cb-4ab1-9ede-d64a7a710654\",\"authority\":\"b7f31ac2-017b-4724-a68e-ea373729da99\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eA forest in \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-8866\\\"\u003eBorn in a Lap\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Rain of Jambu Gold\",\"tibetan\":\"འཛམ་བུ་ན་ད་ཆར་འབེབས།\",\"sanskrit\":\"\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"’dzam bu na da char ’bebs\"}},{\"uuid\":\"6f3f7fc6-be4f-4826-893b-9c656936e0ab\",\"authority\":\"02a20d35-7fbf-493f-92e9-20103308cbc1\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eOne of sixteen realms that surround the \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-9630\\\"\u003eReviving Hell\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Rain of Weapons\",\"tibetan\":\"མཚོན་འབབ་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"śastrasāmpāti\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"mtshon ’bab pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"7cafc4d7-7e87-4f63-a54a-f0278790a80d\",\"authority\":\"ab26e3ba-6b1f-4bbd-a2c9-2d632ec43ae0\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eA river on \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-9657\\\"\u003eSaṅkāśa\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Rain River\",\"tibetan\":\"ཆར་དང་ཆར་གྱི་རྗེས་སུ་འབྱུང་བའི་ཆུ་ཀླུང་།\",\"sanskrit\":\"\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"char dang char gyi rjes su ’byung ba’i chu klung\"}},{\"uuid\":\"d1537ccc-2fde-4f33-82a7-ea483c9593d9\",\"authority\":\"3cfae3b6-85f3-43bd-abdd-8756a9da3faa\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eA virtuous \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-8562\\\"\u003enāga\u003c/span\u003e king.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Rainfall\",\"tibetan\":\"ཆར་འབེབས།\",\"sanskrit\":\"\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"char ’bebs\"}},{\"uuid\":\"a5d6cdd3-67d3-4718-a63d-0028f40baee2\",\"authority\":\"b5a161b5-2aa7-4c37-a473-82556d4a3e8b\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp\u003eThe ancient capital of Magadha prior to its relocation to Pāṭaliputra during the Mauryan dynasty, Rājagṛha is one of the most important locations in Buddhist history. The literature tells us that the Buddha and his saṅgha spent a considerable amount of time in residence in and around Rājagṛha‍—in nearby places, such as the Vulture Peak Mountain (Gṛdhrakūṭaparvata), a major site of the Mahāyāna sūtras, and the Bamboo Grove (Veṇuvana)‍—enjoying the patronage of King Bimbisāra and then of his son King Ajātaśatru. Rājagṛha is also remembered as the location where the first Buddhist monastic council was held after the Buddha Śākyamuni passed into parinirvāṇa. Now known as Rajgir and located in the modern Indian state of Bihar.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Rājagṛha\",\"tibetan\":\"རྒྱལ་པོའི་ཁབ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"rājagṛha\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"rgyal po’i khab\"}},{\"uuid\":\"49187835-c54b-429a-9eb0-87d756187fd9\",\"authority\":\"3385409e-ddeb-43a2-8907-41c6c6657cf1\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eA lake in \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-9413\\\"\u003eLiving by Rājanina\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Rājanina\",\"tibetan\":\"རཱ་ཛ་ནི་ན།\",\"sanskrit\":\"rājanina\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"rA dza ni na\"}},{\"uuid\":\"b21f414a-955c-4574-a5e2-4dfc51ccfb88\",\"authority\":\"876d2af6-1945-40b0-a434-a0a06775fa7e\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp\u003eA class of nonhuman beings that are often, but certainly not always, considered demonic in the Buddhist tradition. They are often depicted as flesh-eating monsters who haunt frightening places and are ugly and evil-natured with a yearning for human flesh, and who additionally have miraculous powers, such as being able to change their appearance.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"rākṣasa, rākṣasa/rākṣasī, rākṣasī\",\"tibetan\":\"སྲིན་པོ།, སྲིན་མོ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"rākṣasa, rākṣasī\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"srin mo, srin po\"}},{\"uuid\":\"4b8909e7-501c-4557-9629-a34e5f2a025d\",\"authority\":\"ff522a28-cc10-4b47-b0ad-55ee14c80dad\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eA \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-8581\\\"\u003erākṣasī\u003c/span\u003e living on \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-8813\\\"\u003eArdhamaru\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Rāmā\",\"tibetan\":\"རཱ་མ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"rāmā\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"rA ma\"}},{\"uuid\":\"1dd25731-ca1a-41d6-8bc5-e3d2888ecfd0\",\"authority\":\"f4de7f34-9077-44c3-897d-414d1798189f\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e(1) A king of the Pāla dynasty who ruled from 1077–1120 \u003cspan class=\\\"small-caps\\\"\u003eᴄᴇ\u003c/span\u003e (\u003cem class=\\\"foreign text-wy\\\" lang=\\\"bo-LATN\\\"\u003erA ma phA la\u003c/em\u003e). (2) The alternate spelling, \u003cem class=\\\"foreign text-wy\\\" lang=\\\"bo-LATN\\\"\u003ene bai pA la\u003c/em\u003e, is tentatively identified to be the very same king of the Pāla dynasty. See \u003ca href=\\\"end-notes.xhtml#UT22084-068-021-8447\\\" data-pointer-type=\\\"id\\\"\u003en.640\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Rāmapāla\",\"tibetan\":\"ནེ་བཻ་པཱ་ལ།, རཱ་མ་ཕཱ་ལ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"rāmapāla\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"ne bai pA la, rA ma phA la\"}},{\"uuid\":\"77ab151e-ee21-426d-9fe3-826a2194d60f\",\"authority\":\"140fd7ea-d939-4676-bf30-74561b2eadf4\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eA sea to the west of \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-9338\\\"\u003eJambudvīpa\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Ramayo\",\"tibetan\":\"ར་མ་ཡོ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"ramayo\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"ra ma yo\"}},{\"uuid\":\"9b704838-9f50-4caa-a288-3efd9be9860c\",\"authority\":\"a686fa34-1ec4-46ef-8032-22b64fd89795\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eOne of sixteen realms that surround the \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-9279\\\"\u003eHell of Ultimate Torment\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Raven Mouths\",\"tibetan\":\"བྱ་རོག་ཁ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"kākāsyaka\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"bya rog kha\"}},{\"uuid\":\"04427c94-4845-458a-86d7-a0c73b723e8c\",\"authority\":\"3fce7a66-1fac-4b24-9de1-ecfb349bfcc2\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eOne of sixteen realms that surround the \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-9279\\\"\u003eHell of Ultimate Torment\u003c/span\u003e. Also called \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-8845\\\"\u003eBlack Belly\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Raven’s Belly\",\"tibetan\":\"བྱ་རོག་ལྟོ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"bya rog lto\"}},{\"uuid\":\"76d0e7a3-9382-45c1-b5c2-9954ef579cdb\",\"authority\":\"1d6267c2-f9b1-4746-911d-899886104b0c\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eOne of sixteen realms that surround the \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-9235\\\"\u003eGreat Howling Hell\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Ravens with Vajra-Like Beaks\",\"tibetan\":\"ཁྭའི་ཆུ་རྡོ་རྗེ་ལྟ་བུ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"vajra­vāyasa­tuṇḍa\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"khwa’i chu rdo rje lta bu\"}},{\"uuid\":\"ff8539fc-1f2d-4265-baad-8433a0b1dc30\",\"authority\":\"287ffd3f-70c4-4b55-92a3-2bbdeea7c712\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eA mountain in the hell called \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-9859\\\"\u003eWailer\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Ravens’ Peak\",\"tibetan\":\"ཁྭ་སྤུངས།\",\"sanskrit\":\"vāyasakūṭa\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"khwa spungs\"}},{\"uuid\":\"0e1f9b7a-915d-4d6d-8123-4e54f6da60e0\",\"authority\":\"eb53097b-b589-4f8b-b326-7599edbaa79f\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eLiterally “thatness.” This term refers to the ultimate nature of things, the way things are in \u003cspan class=\\\"ignore\\\"\u003ereality\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eNote that the term “reality” has also been used to render terms of similar meaning such as \u003cem class=\\\"foreign text-wy\\\" lang=\\\"bo-LATN\\\"\u003eyang dag nyid\u003c/em\u003e and others.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"reality\",\"tibetan\":\"དེ་ཁོ་ན་ཉིད།, དེ་ཉིད།\",\"sanskrit\":\"tattva\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"de kho na nyid, de nyid\"}},{\"uuid\":\"46a75ee1-0292-48b5-8944-e2558c4ca296\",\"authority\":\"8d2a3d9a-1589-4425-beb8-a05ca95a501d\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003e(1) An ocean between \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-9847\\\"\u003eVideha\u003c/span\u003e and \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-9338\\\"\u003eJambudvīpa\u003c/span\u003e. (2) An ocean off \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-9338\\\"\u003eJambudvīpa\u003c/span\u003e. (3) A river in \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-9338\\\"\u003eJambudvīpa\u003c/span\u003e. (4) An ephemeral hell to the north of \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-9338\\\"\u003eJambudvīpa\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Red\",\"tibetan\":\"དམར་པོ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"dmar po\"}},{\"uuid\":\"019447fb-d77d-4fb5-8d90-3c08cf699525\",\"authority\":\"afd2f36b-a39b-492c-bb49-fd61bfafd7fe\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eA realm of the \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-8516\\\"\u003eever-infatuated gods\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Red City\",\"tibetan\":\"གྲོང་ཁྱེར་དམར་གནས།\",\"sanskrit\":\"\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"grong khyer dmar gnas\"}},{\"uuid\":\"b4cc6b7a-fb37-4274-a1d2-88750b8dd8f5\",\"authority\":\"0e4fed26-aa14-43cd-b00d-22533257ed87\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eAn island in the vicinity of \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-9338\\\"\u003eJambudvīpa\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Red Conches and Pearls\",\"tibetan\":\"དུང་དང་མུ་ཏིག་དམར་པོ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"dung dang mu tig dmar po\"}},{\"uuid\":\"677b43c5-d5e2-4ba8-b0fa-bfa64556f253\",\"authority\":\"45113b93-f3bb-4f48-b029-b8de6dbefe86\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eA forest in \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-9506\\\"\u003eMoving in Mixed Environments\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Red Forest\",\"tibetan\":\"ནགས་དམར་པོ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"nags dmar po\"}},{\"uuid\"