":\"ཤུཀྟིའི་གནས།\",\"sanskrit\":\"śukti\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"shuk+ti’i gnas\"}},{\"uuid\":\"22a54d38-181b-4b0a-a5c1-eca5bc803cd0\",\"authority\":\"dfac8357-c5bb-432d-92a8-bd42fc151718\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eA previous ruler of the \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-9276\\\"\u003eHeaven of the Thirty-Three\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Sumanyu\",\"tibetan\":\"སུ་མ་ནྱུམ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"sumanyu\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"su ma n+yum\"}},{\"uuid\":\"ec554dcc-896f-47fc-befa-ed29ccc75a6f\",\"authority\":\"edde8dbf-1922-4296-9a09-e4582788077f\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eA mountain in the sea west of \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-9338\\\"\u003eJambudvīpa\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Sumegha\",\"tibetan\":\"སུ་མེ་གྷོ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"sumegha\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"su me gho\"}},{\"uuid\":\"2014c001-ec4d-45a4-ba8c-d283853d6949\",\"authority\":\"00c9880b-c835-42e4-8a54-7f9d0c52c4a4\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp\u003eAccording to ancient Buddhist cosmology, this is the great mountain forming the axis of the universe. At its summit is Sudarśana, home of Śakra and his thirty-two gods, and on its flanks live the asuras. The mount has four sides facing the cardinal directions, each of which is made of a different precious stone. Surrounding it are several mountain ranges and the great ocean where the four principal island continents lie: in the south, Jambudvīpa (our world); in the west, Godānīya; in the north, Uttarakuru; and in the east, Pūrvavideha. Above it are the abodes of the desire realm gods. It is variously referred to as Meru, Mount Meru, Sumeru, and Mount Sumeru.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Sumeru\",\"tibetan\":\"རི་རབ་ལྷུན་པོ།, རི་རབ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"sumeru\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"ri rab, ri rab lhun po\"}},{\"uuid\":\"5bd87759-fd74-42a8-8949-e54dfbd90110\",\"authority\":\"0b48021c-fab0-4cdc-ac0f-b9dafe2dfed3\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eA class of \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-8622\\\"\u003evidyādharas\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Sumeru dweller\",\"tibetan\":\"རི་རབ་ལྷུན་པོ་ལ་གནས་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"ri rab lhun po la gnas pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"f184f2a7-fe3e-4199-831b-753ad0c8887d\",\"authority\":\"10750ac1-0d14-4a34-989c-b151c5d668ca\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eA mountain to the north of \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-9338\\\"\u003eJambudvīpa\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Sumeru Rival\",\"tibetan\":\"རི་རབ་ལྷུན་པོ་ལ་འགྲན་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"ri rab lhun po la ’gran pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"cc4063d1-0adb-4ca6-bf06-cd650c8c8acf\",\"authority\":\"b758f21c-8abb-4d61-8c7e-e78b93314063\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eA river on \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-9657\\\"\u003eSaṅkāśa\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Summer Joy\",\"tibetan\":\"དབྱར་དགའ་བ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"dbyar dga’ ba\"}},{\"uuid\":\"89b4d3b0-be3b-477b-b703-383d5c0e408d\",\"authority\":\"06b9c4d3-5b1b-4e0d-a845-cd32c7bcfbce\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eA river on \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-9142\\\"\u003eForest Garlands\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Summit Encircler\",\"tibetan\":\"རྩེ་མོ་ལ་འཁོར་བ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"rtse mo la ’khor ba\"}},{\"uuid\":\"ac5610b8-3a1a-426c-ae11-80e3b4f22203\",\"authority\":\"4a89c792-3ce8-43c2-9e9a-d36fa70e899b\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eA lake on \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-9078\\\"\