87f-4f26-95c6-e1fd97778836\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eA class of semi-divine beings that are famous for wielding (\u003cem class=\\\"foreign break text-sa\\\" lang=\\\"sa-LATN\\\"\u003edhara\u003c/em\u003e) spells (\u003cem class=\\\"foreign break text-sa\\\" lang=\\\"sa-LATN\\\"\u003evidyā\u003c/em\u003e). Loosely understood as “sorcerers,” these magical beings are frequently petitioned through dhāraṇī and kriyātantra ritual to grant magical powers to the supplicant. The later Buddhist tradition, playing on the dual valences of \u003cem class=\\\"foreign break text-sa\\\" lang=\\\"sa-LATN\\\"\u003evidyā\u003c/em\u003e as “spell” and “knowledge,” began to apply this term to realized figures in the Buddhist pantheon.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"vidyādhara\",\"tibetan\":\"རིག་པ་འཛིན་པ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"vidyādhara\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"rig pa ’dzin pa\"}},{\"uuid\":\"2bc29893-6085-42d1-958b-51e516268a65\",\"authority\":\"28fab2bb-7516-4735-bc0b-6e2aecf945b7\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eA realm of the \u003cspan data-glossary-id=\\\"UT22084-068-021-8621\\\"\u003evessel-bearer gods\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Viewing\",\"tibetan\":\"ཀུན་ཏུ་ལྟ་བ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"kun tu lta ba\"}},{\"uuid\":\"71c477d7-26a5-4379-a115-28a05113726e\",\"authority\":\"effbc033-8237-4946-81db-3caca2668a42\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eA renowned monastic complex in India.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"Vikramaśīla\",\"tibetan\":\"བི་ཀྲ་མ་ཤཱི་ལ།\",\"sanskrit\":\"vikramaśīla\",\"pali\":\"\",\"chinese\":\"\",\"wylie\":\"bi kra ma shI la\"}},{\"uuid\":\"5f282b3e-2104-4c5c-b471-eb70cf7247af\",\"authority\":\"0bf5f807-1786-42f0-890a-d9cbcee0c065\",\"definition\":\"\u003cp class=\\\"definition\\\"\u003eA family of Indian chordophone instruments.\u003c/p\u003e\",\"names\":{\"english\":\"vīṇā\",\"ti