"italic">mu tig dang byi ru ’bab pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མུ་ཏིག་དང་བྱི་རུ་འབབ་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river in the realm of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8526">Four Great Kings</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="6c73b468-b63b-4955-939f-69d6658f009c" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_jkt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.467</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Flow of Red Rivers</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">chu bo dmar po ’bab pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཆུ་བོ་དམར་པོ་འབབ་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">lohita­nadī­pravāha</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of the sixteen realms that surround the <span><span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9277">Hell of Heat</span></span>. </p></div></div></div></div><div id="a1590176-5b74-44d3-bb93-5e129ebbd692" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_jl55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.468</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Flow of Wine</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">chang chu ltar ’bab pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཆང་ཆུ་ལྟར་འབབ་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9752">Supreme Splendor</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="bc7f617f-f613-4755-90ad-d8742daa8053" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_jld5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.469</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Flower Homes</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">me tog gi khang pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མེ་ཏོག་གི་ཁང་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A part of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9153">Forest of Joy</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="84049ab4-3576-407a-97d0-5fcefa53bfca" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_jll5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.470</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">flower-garland draped</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">me tog gi phreng ba ’phyang ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མེ་ཏོག་གི་ཕྲེང་བ་འཕྱང་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A class of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8622">vidyādharas</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="6d0e4db7-86bf-436b-b1dc-5b1f2473d1f5" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_jlt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.471</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Flowing above the Gaṅgā</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gang gA’i steng du rgyu</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གང་གཱའི་སྟེང་དུ་རྒྱུ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9035">Dwelling on Summits</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="92070014-d454-47e3-a704-bdf256dc12b0" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_jm55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.472</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Flowing Colors of Melody</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dbyangs can gyi mdog tu ’bab pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དབྱངས་ཅན་གྱི་མདོག་ཏུ་འབབ་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9657">Saṅkāśa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="81c1e980-a90e-4435-86db-91fe5adac57f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_jmd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.473</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Foam Garlands</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dbu ba’i phreng ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དབུ་བའི་ཕྲེང་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9657">Saṅkāśa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="0bd0c43c-aafb-45ac-aaed-48d2a70fb722" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_jml5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.474</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">food of contact</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">reg pa’i kha zas, reg pa’i zas</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རེག་པའི་ཁ་ཟས།, རེག་པའི་ཟས།</span></li><li class="italic">sparśāhāra</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">Sustenance obtained through consciousness being in contact with an object; one of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9889">four kinds of food</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="650db816-b718-4543-881c-dd54f136a3d5" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_jmt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.475</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">food of joy</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dga’ ba’i zas</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དགའ་བའི་ཟས།</span></li><li class="italic">prītyāhāra</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9889">four kinds of food</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="3f1ddc76-d0f7-4456-9c90-fa8922c6e55c" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_jn55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.476</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">food of volition</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">yid la sems pa’i zas</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཡིད་ལ་སེམས་པའི་ཟས།</span></li><li class="italic">manaḥsañcetanāhāra</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9889">four kinds of food</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="671a70a1-e152-4883-a1f5-cb77c7ac180a" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_jnd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.477</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Forest Course</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">nags na ’byung ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ནགས་ན་འབྱུང་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9241">Great Slope</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="564c29f9-4117-40c3-9c99-fb7115835009" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_jnl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.478</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Forest Fires Like an Enveloping Darkness</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">nags tshal gyi me mun pa ltar ’khrigs pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ནགས་ཚལ་གྱི་མེ་མུན་པ་ལྟར་འཁྲིགས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">tamo’gniṣaṇḍaḥ</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of the sixteen realms that surround the <span><span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9277">Hell of Heat</span></span>. </p></div></div></div></div><div id="be26ad27-7dc7-439f-a2a2-86979d0cfdcc" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_jnt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.479</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Forest Garlands</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">nags kyi phreng ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ནགས་ཀྱི་ཕྲེང་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9847">Videha</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="72a84e48-eb24-42d8-b3f2-d0567c17a106" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_jo55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.480</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Forest Joy</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">nags mngon par dga’ ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ནགས་མངོན་པར་དགའ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A city in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9847">Videha</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="7b2b9f84-7aa1-4210-aaa2-51ff9e63927e" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_jod5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.481</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Forest of Amusements</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rtsed mo’i nags</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྩེད་མོའི་ནགས།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">(1) A forest in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8956">Continuous Movement</span>. (2) A forest in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9509">Moving in the Stream</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="997f07df-eaca-48a7-bcca-1e3090ba52a1" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_jol5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.482</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Forest of Armor</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">go cha’i tshal</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གོ་ཆའི་ཚལ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">Where the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8531">gods</span> receive their armor before battle.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="be53d5d2-6e70-4eaf-887c-c58da2dd8e2f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_jot5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.483</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Forest of Cascading Water Sounds</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’bab chu’i sgra dang ldan pa’i nags</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འབབ་ཆུའི་སྒྲ་དང་ལྡན་པའི་ནགས།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9241">Great Slope</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="b67b0008-152b-40a0-ab1f-76634b7d4d55" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_jp55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.484</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Forest of Continuous Flames</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">nags tshal mes mched pa’i rgyud lta bu</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ནགས་ཚལ་མེས་མཆེད་པའི་རྒྱུད་ལྟ་བུ།</span></li><li class="italic">dava­mālāgni­sama, davāgni­mālā­sama</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of sixteen realms that surround the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9235">Great Howling Hell</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="bf98d112-c466-434f-97b1-7d934b327411" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_jpd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.485</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Forest of Divine Joys</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">lha’i nyams dga’ bar byed pa’i tshal</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ལྷའི་ཉམས་དགའ་བར་བྱེད་པའི་ཚལ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest in <span><span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9913">Happiness</span></span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="98e2397a-9285-4e12-a6de-e8dd5a85ba32" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_jpl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.486</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Forest of Drinks</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">btung ba’i nags</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བཏུང་བའི་ནགས།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9506">Moving in Mixed Environments</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="39bef344-be02-4b23-96fe-8305286d47fb" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_jpt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.487</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Forest of Enjoyment</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dga’ ba’i tshal</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དགའ་བའི་ཚལ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">Another name for the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9144">Forest of Amusements</span> in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9509">Moving in the Stream</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="a16239cd-220f-42c2-90b3-736eb7d0623f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_jq55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.488</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Forest of Fiery Mist</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">glog gi na bun tshal</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གློག་གི་ན་བུན་ཚལ།</span></li><li class="italic">abhrāgni­nīhāra­vana</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of sixteen realms that surround the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9298">Howling Hell</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="9c207301-69c9-4c5a-a4de-197ef9790b2b" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_jqd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.489</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Forest of Flowing Rivers</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">chu bo ’bab pa’i tshal</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཆུ་བོ་འབབ་པའི་ཚལ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A part of the forest known as <span><span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9310">Incomparable</span></span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="913f6af1-f143-4770-ace0-f57f7805fba4" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_jql5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.490</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Forest of Incense</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">spos kyi tshal</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྤོས་ཀྱི་ཚལ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">Alternative name for <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9157">Forest of Music</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="413842dc-90a9-437a-bc00-8769b83d775f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_jqt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.491</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Forest of Joy</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mngon par dga’ ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མངོན་པར་དགའ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9890">Emanation of Light Rays</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="c10096f1-435d-45a7-b877-f1d84470f8d8" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_jr55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.492</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Forest of Laughter</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dgod par gyur pa’i nags</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དགོད་པར་གྱུར་པའི་ནགས།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9840">Vast Garlands of Bliss</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="bbb8e56c-39ce-42f5-9265-198611612bcd" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_jrd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.493</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Forest of Marvelous Lotuses</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">pad ma rmad byung gi tshal</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">པད་མ་རྨད་བྱུང་གི་ཚལ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9027">Dwelling in One Direction</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="e2bf3e24-1c06-427d-a4b8-a4831ba3a7f9" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_jrl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.494</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Forest of Multistoried Mansions</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">khang pa brtsegs pa’i tshal</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཁང་པ་བརྩེགས་པའི་ཚལ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A park in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9772">Tamer of Madness</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="28a59f43-7370-419a-b9e2-1155d2f48d88" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_jrt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.495</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Forest of Music</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rol mo’i tshal</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རོལ་མོའི་ཚལ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8819">Attached to Sound</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="4b89f4fc-53cf-406e-84d1-1f7af8339a41" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_js55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.496</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Forest of Palaces</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">zhal med khang gi tshal</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཞལ་མེད་ཁང་གི་ཚལ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9505">Moving on Springy Ground</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="fcc7b9d9-d37c-451a-959e-58be455cd4a1" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_jsd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.497</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Forest of Silver Trees</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dngul gyi ljon zhing gi nags</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དངུལ་གྱི་ལྗོན་ཞིང་གི་ནགས།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">Part of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9153">Forest of Joy</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="aac690d6-e4e5-4f84-ae2f-84eec2adcf87" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_jsl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.498</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Forest of Splendor</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gzi brjid kyi nags</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གཟི་བརྗིད་ཀྱི་ནགས།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9753">Supreme Strength</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="8adf7724-9d9c-420b-b6b0-d5b5cb2b55da" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_jst5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.499</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Forest of the Assembly of Kubera</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ku be ra’i tshogs kyi nags</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀུ་བེ་རའི་ཚོགས་ཀྱི་ནགས།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9753">Supreme Strength</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="6a2cb892-c44f-4b3f-89ca-e0cab32c1e25" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_jt55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.500</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Forest of Vines</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ljon zhing kun tu ’khril ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ལྗོན་ཞིང་ཀུན་ཏུ་འཁྲིལ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9506">Moving in Mixed Environments</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="b40e108b-6978-49f5-bced-880748027844" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_jtd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.501</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Forest of White Lotus Petals</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">pad ma dkar po’i tshal</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">པད་མ་དཀར་པོའི་ཚལ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A pleasure grove in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9668">Shaded by Garlands</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="06448c53-2966-4033-be7e-7934df9b3dbd" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_jtl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.502</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">four ages</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dus bzhi</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དུས་བཞི།</span></li><li class="italic">caturyuga</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition"><span class="ignore">Four ages</span> of human life in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span> including the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8483">age of perfection</span>, <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8485">age of threefold endowment</span>, age of twofold endowment, and <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8484">age of strife</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="04ff888f-51c9-49c8-983c-060adfa89c4d" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_jtt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.503</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">four concentrations</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bsam btan bzhi</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བསམ་བཏན་བཞི།</span></li><li class="italic">caturdhyāna</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">The four levels of the realm of form.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="a7f049cb-5f1d-456f-8313-b7348eaf54a1" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ju55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.504</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">four errors</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">phyin ci log bzhi</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཕྱིན་ཅི་ལོག་བཞི།</span></li><li class="italic">caturviprayāsa</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">Taking what is impermanent to be permanent, what is painful to be delightful, what is unclean to be clean, and what is no self to be a self.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="ebe1e705-276e-4952-b683-2842163bdaae" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_jud5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.505</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">four fruitions</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’bras bu bzhi</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འབྲས་བུ་བཞི།</span></li><li class="italic">caturphala</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">The four results of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8536">hearer</span>’s path.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="a2bcf0ed-8865-4c0f-b74b-ede745904d1b" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_jul5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.506</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Four Great Kings</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rgyal chen bzhi</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྒྱལ་ཆེན་བཞི།</span></li><li class="italic">caturmahārāja</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">The divine kings who rule the four directions: Vaiśravaṇa (who in this text appears under his alternative name <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8702">Kubera</span>), <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8775">Virūḍhaka</span>, <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8658">Dhṛtarāṣṭra</span>, and <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8776">Virūpākṣa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="be885a17-3d78-4aa1-a10a-62568e066302" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_jut5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.507</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">four human abodes</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mi’i gnas bzhi</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མིའི་གནས་བཞི།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">This seems to refer to the four continents around Mount Meru.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="9d287c52-6bfd-45ad-9db4-d2f2a5804a2f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_jv55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.508</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">four kinds of food</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">zas rnam pa bzhi</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཟས་རྣམ་པ་བཞི།</span></li><li class="italic">caturāhāra</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">The four types of food on which beings subsist: <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9888">coarse food</span>, the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8523">food of contact</span>, the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9886">food of volition</span>, and the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9887">food of joy</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="e39aafcd-f6f3-4367-b548-ccfd70bb026a" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_jvd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.509</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">four truths of noble beings</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’phags pa’i bden pa bzhi</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འཕགས་པའི་བདེན་པ་བཞི།</span></li><li class="italic">caturāryasatya</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">The first teaching of the Buddha covering suffering, the origin of suffering, the cessation of suffering, and the path to the cessation of suffering.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="4dd4bbec-82e7-414c-93f0-cac409aed87c" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_jvl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.510</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">four types of fearlessness</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mi ’jigs pa bzhi</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མི་འཇིགས་པ་བཞི།</span></li><li class="italic">caturabhaya</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">Fearlessness in declaring that one has (1) awakened, (2) ceased all illusions, (3) taught the obstacles to awakening, and (4) shown the way to liberation.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="33c80214-d2c6-4b8d-bdc3-e8f9cfdda199" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_jvt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.511</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Fragrant</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">spos ’byung</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྤོས་འབྱུང་།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A grove in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9403">Lateral</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="7dd80a92-cd68-4bd6-88e0-c48e4987844f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_k055anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.512</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Fragrant Flowers</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">me tog dri zhim pa ’byung ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མེ་ཏོག་དྲི་ཞིམ་པ་འབྱུང་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A lotus pond on the fifth minor mountain on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9423">Lofty Summit</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="f62057e5-6956-4ece-bd81-c662febde0fc" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_k0d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.513</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Fragrant Forest</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dri zhim pa’i tshal</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དྲི་ཞིམ་པའི་ཚལ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9513">Moving Mind</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="7a579516-5dae-4f01-aff0-ad255a3c415a" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_k0l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.514</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Fragrant Garlands</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dri’i phreng ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དྲིའི་ཕྲེང་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">An island in the vicinity of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="9d457433-3d01-4891-9dcb-eca73b5e0897" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_k0t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.515</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Fragrant Stream</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dri’i chu</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དྲིའི་ཆུ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9657">Saṅkāśa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="ee5db1a5-b12f-456f-b6cc-debcd23be175" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_k155anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.516</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Free from Action</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bya ba med pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བྱ་བ་མེད་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A city in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9209">Godānīya</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="597c328e-a689-4959-995a-953932301164" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_k1d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.517</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Free from Anger</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">khro ba bral ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཁྲོ་བ་བྲལ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8562">nāga</span> who visits <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9657">Saṅkāśa</span> Mountain.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="c7231732-9f18-4551-9b18-0415e0eda326" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_k1l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.518</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Free from Sand</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bye mas ma bcom pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བྱེ་མས་མ་བཅོམ་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A lake on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9078">Equal Peaks</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="51ea6bef-2574-4728-a987-a2d2c53e8fd3" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_k1t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.519</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Free from Strife, Heaven Free from Strife, Yāma Heaven</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mtshe ma, ’thab bral</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མཚེ་མ།, འཐབ་བྲལ།</span></li><li class="italic">yāma, yāma</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of the six heavens of the desire realm.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="16ff9862-f57c-4f50-a856-4949d24f439a" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_k255anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.520</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Free from Strife, Heaven Free from Strife, Yāma Heaven</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mtshe ma, ’thab bral</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མཚེ་མ།, འཐབ་བྲལ།</span></li><li class="italic">yāma, yāma</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">Another name for the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9266">Heaven Free from Strife</span>, this is the third of the six heavens of the desire realm. The Tibetan literally means “twins.” The Sanskrit for this heaven is <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">Yāma</em> or <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">Suyāma</em>, the precise meaning of which is uncertain.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="3cf703fc-46f9-478a-ab11-0cb931dbe0ed" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_k2d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.521</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Free from Weeds</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">chu bal dang rnam par bral ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཆུ་བལ་དང་རྣམ་པར་བྲལ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A pond on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9078">Equal Peaks</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="5fee832a-c04b-4e96-8455-721f60cc4eaa" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_k2l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.522</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Freedom from Suffering</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">myang ngan bral</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མྱང་ངན་བྲལ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mansion in the forest <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9054">Endowed with Everything</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="001dcbb1-10e2-47f7-81f9-28122eb8e25d" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_k2t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.523</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Frolicking</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rab tu rtse bar byed pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རབ་ཏུ་རྩེ་བར་བྱེད་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A pond on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9078">Equal Peaks</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="7e0609a2-2c35-4cdf-8ee4-bef1107d929d" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_k355anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.524</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Fruits of Constant Beauty</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’bras bu rtag tu mdzas</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འབྲས་བུ་རྟག་ཏུ་མཛས།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8489">asuras</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="db53fd46-07b9-4b00-b144-d1ddf1fa85df" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_k3d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.525</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Fulfillment of Wishes</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bsams ’gro, yid bzhin sna tshogs</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བསམས་འགྲོ།, ཡིད་བཞིན་སྣ་ཚོགས།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">(1) A lake near <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9734">Sudharma</span> (<em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">bsams ’gro</em>). (2) A lotus pool in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9403">Lateral</span> (<em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">yid bzhin sna tshogs</em>).</p></div></div></div></div><div id="3ee40464-068d-459c-8727-7beaf8c3d1f8" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_k3l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.526</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Full of Hundreds of Birds</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bya brgya phrag gis kun tu gang ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བྱ་བརྒྱ་ཕྲག་གིས་ཀུན་ཏུ་གང་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A lake on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9078">Equal Peaks</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="84884741-7ede-4528-a363-ff734fda1b9c" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_k3t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.527</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Full of Lotuses</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">pad mas khyab par gyur pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">པད་མས་ཁྱབ་པར་གྱུར་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A lotus pond on the fifth minor mountain on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9423">Lofty Summit</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="a14c0e16-b041-4032-aaed-0c94f1bc2808" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_k455anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.528</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Furnace</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">me thab</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མེ་ཐབ།</span></li><li class="italic">agnikuṇḍa</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of sixteen realms that surround the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8975">Crushing Hell</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="4b5fff0a-a58b-4b08-b00d-7c8a73e9e40f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_k4d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.529</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Gajānana</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">glang po’i gdong</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གླང་པོའི་གདོང་།</span></li><li class="italic">gajānana</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A virtuous <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8562">nāga</span> king.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="e228c566-ae6d-491d-89fb-fa8b720b9505" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_k4l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.530</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Gambhīrajala</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gam bhi ra dza lang</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གམ་བྷི་ར་ཛ་ལང་།</span></li><li class="italic">gambhīrajala</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A lake in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9209">Godānīya</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="7dc69e3c-5fe0-42ea-b9cc-9b2721770cf6" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_k4t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.531</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Gandhara</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gan d+ha ra</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གན་དྷ་ར།</span></li><li class="italic">gandhara</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A land to the north of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="b74ef150-7f77-412e-9bb2-1b4c5052267f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_k555anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.532</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">gandharva</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dri za</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དྲི་ཟ།</span></li><li class="italic">gandharva</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p>A class of generally benevolent nonhuman beings who inhabit the skies, sometimes said to inhabit fantastic cities in the clouds, and more specifically to dwell on the eastern slopes of Mount Meru, where they are ruled by the Great King Dhṛtarāṣṭra. They are most renowned as celestial musicians who serve the gods. In the Abhidharma, the term is also used to refer to the mental body assumed by sentient beings during the intermediate state between death and rebirth. Gandharvas are said to live on fragrances (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">gandha</em>) in the desire realm, hence the Tibetan translation <em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">dri za</em>, meaning “scent eater.”</p></div></div></div></div><div id="57ba503f-9dc3-4e38-8b29-3730482f0770" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_k5d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.533</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Gandharva Melody</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dri za’i dbyangs can</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དྲི་ཟའི་དབྱངས་ཅན།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9657">Saṅkāśa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="aa13dec1-b1a9-46bd-9d62-44afb78f7e12" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_k5l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.534</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Gaṅgā</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gang gA</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གང་གཱ།</span></li><li class="italic">gaṅgā</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p>The Gaṅgā, or Ganges in English, is considered to be the most sacred river of India, particularly within the Hindu tradition. It starts in the Himalayas, flows through the northern plains of India, bathing the holy city of Vārāṇasī, and meets the sea at the Bay of Bengal, in Bangladesh. In the sūtras, however, this river is mostly mentioned not for its sacredness but for its abundant sands‍—noticeable still today on its many sandy banks and at its delta‍—which serve as a common metaphor for infinitely large numbers.</p><p>According to Buddhist cosmology, as explained in the <cite class="title text-en" lang="en">Abhidharmakośa</cite>, it is one of the four rivers that flow from Lake Anavatapta and cross the southern continent of Jambudvīpa‍—the known human world or more specifically the Indian subcontinent. </p></div></div></div></div><div id="3c127884-956e-4412-84c1-9cff014a49e6" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_k5t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.535</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Gaṅkara</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gang ka ra</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གང་ཀ་ར།</span></li><li class="italic">gaṅkara</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A city in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9209">Godānīya</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="b8f9da69-1b67-426f-af9c-5917a3f308d5" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_k655anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.536</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Garland</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">phreng</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཕྲེང་།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A park in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8867">Born in a Tank</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="5ec5f729-08fa-4651-a8b2-127e0ae5a7c9" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_k6d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.537</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Garland Abode</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">phreng ba gnas pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཕྲེང་བ་གནས་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">An area in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9398">Kuru</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="78440e64-13f2-4861-994f-df808b947674" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_k6l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.538</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">garland bearer, garland-bearer gods</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">phreng thogs lha</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཕྲེང་ཐོགས་ལྷ།</span></li><li class="italic">mālādhara</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A class of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8531">gods</span> associated with the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8526">Four Great Kings</span>. </p></div></div></div></div><div id="a618b72b-909d-45e1-bd15-f073adf24831" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_k6t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.539</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Garland of Bathing Ponds</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">khrus kyi rdzing bu’i phreng ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཁྲུས་ཀྱི་རྫིང་བུའི་ཕྲེང་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A lake on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9078">Equal Peaks</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="524d2c59-3688-4fc9-a355-c493d8f67b8b" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_k755anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.540</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Garland of Bell Bangles</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">g.yer kha’i phreng ba’i tshal</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གཡེར་ཁའི་ཕྲེང་བའི་ཚལ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">Forest on the third <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8489">asura</span> level, <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9087">Excellent Abode</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="70da04eb-4c0c-4bde-99ac-3d858a2f8ff2" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_k7d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.541</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Garland of Celestial Cottages</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gzhal yas khang gi khang bu’i phreng ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གཞལ་ཡས་ཁང་གི་ཁང་བུའི་ཕྲེང་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A location in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9753">Supreme Strength</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="fceb903e-9c5d-4413-927a-c0539bf22cdf" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_k7l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.542</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Garland of Golden Trees</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">shing ljon pa’i phreng ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཤིང་ལྗོན་པའི་ཕྲེང་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A grove in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9030">Dwelling in Essence of Jewels</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="1335eefb-2a69-47a6-b2b4-bb299b76131b" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_k7t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.543</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Garland of Lightning</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">glog gi phreng ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གློག་གི་ཕྲེང་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8562">nāga</span> who visits <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9657">Saṅkāśa</span> Mountain.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="15ed1764-bc66-4b7f-86a8-110852f8fa33" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_k855anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.544</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Garland of Lotus Ponds</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">pad ma’i rdzing bu’i phreng ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">པད་མའི་རྫིང་བུའི་ཕྲེང་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">Ponds in the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9144">Forest of Amusements</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="e3019605-3444-415f-8fde-43ec395e140b" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_k8d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.545</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Garland of Lotuses</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">pad ma’i phreng ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">པད་མའི་ཕྲེང་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">padmamālin</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of sixteen realms that surround the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9630">Reviving Hell</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="59b10194-92af-418b-b54c-cf94b54d1c23" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_k8l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.546</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Garland of Mansions</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">khang bzangs kyi phreng ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཁང་བཟངས་ཀྱི་ཕྲེང་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A realm in which <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8720">Musulundha</span> resides.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="f1838f1e-10f7-42c5-8bf0-4f695d4bcc12" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_k8t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.547</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Garland of Parks</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">nye ba’i tshal gyi phreng ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཉེ་བའི་ཚལ་གྱི་ཕྲེང་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A palace visited by King <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8754">Sudarśana</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="94664318-6bbd-45cf-b2fa-59a4c131fc6f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_k955anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.548</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Garland of Planets</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rgyu skar phreng</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྒྱུ་སྐར་ཕྲེང་།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of the seven golden mountains that surround Mount <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9739">Sumeru</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="ecd9c16e-65f1-4d08-b866-f99ada2f9c06" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_k9d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.549</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Garland of Plantains</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">tA la’i phreng ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཏཱ་ལའི་ཕྲེང་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain in the sea south of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="1e669fe2-e2f0-46e2-b764-003218a7eb37" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_k9l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.550</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Garland of Play</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rtsed mo’i phreng ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྩེད་མོའི་ཕྲེང་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain between <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9398">Kuru</span> and <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9209">Godānīya</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="30eab565-1328-4f5d-adaf-25007019a22b" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_k9t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.551</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Garland of Pleasure Groves</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">skyed mos tshal gyi phreng ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྐྱེད་མོས་ཚལ་གྱི་ཕྲེང་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A grove in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9753">Supreme Strength</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="a722cb8a-2c02-4b1e-bdb7-2ea70bd75dcb" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ka55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.552</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Garland of Pools</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">lteng ka phreng</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ལྟེང་ཀ་ཕྲེང་།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A lotus pool in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9403">Lateral</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="92f9cd54-585b-4d97-bef5-336d3e5f5608" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_kad5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.553</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Garland of Splendor</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gzi brjid phreng</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གཟི་བརྗིད་ཕྲེང་།</span></li><li class="italic">tejojālinī</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A realm in the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9276">Heaven of the Thirty-Three</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="1517b2f5-feda-433d-91c8-e35a0fe859fd" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_kal5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.554</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Garland of Stars</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">skar ’phreng, ’gram dngar</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འགྲམ་དངར།, སྐར་འཕྲེང་།</span></li><li class="italic">tārāmāla</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of sixteen realms that surround the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9279">Hell of Ultimate Torment</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="ac96e5fd-f44e-470b-9a56-5d68c069afc5" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_kat5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.555</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Garland of Tortures</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gnod pa’i rgyun</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གནོད་པའི་རྒྱུན།</span></li><li class="italic">kāraṇāmāla</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A realm that neighbors the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9278">Hell of Intense Heat</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="05521f71-2458-477e-8c7a-7d8f9deebecb" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_kb55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.556</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Garland-Draped</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">phreng ba’i nyes ’khor</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཕྲེང་བའི་ཉེས་འཁོར།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9398">Kuru</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="e7b719b7-f503-4e4f-9a95-2630c8bb1990" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_kbd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.557</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Garlands of Flowers</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">me tog gi phreng ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མེ་ཏོག་གི་ཕྲེང་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">Part of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9153">Forest of Joy</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="ed427784-180d-4632-9164-e09772150bfd" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_kbl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.558</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Garlands of Foam</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dbu ba’i phreng ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དབུ་བའི་ཕྲེང་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9803">Triple Horns</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="06246652-cd17-4520-8ccc-52da84a1863a" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_kbt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.559</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Garlands of Lightning</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">glog gi phreng ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གློག་གི་ཕྲེང་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A sea to the north of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="ceb227ad-db0f-417e-88e2-fabbad65a95b" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_kc55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.560</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">garuḍa</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">nam mkha’ lding</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ནམ་མཁའ་ལྡིང་།</span></li><li class="italic">garuḍa</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p>In Indian mythology, the garuḍa is an eagle-like bird that is regarded as the king of all birds, normally depicted with a sharp, owl-like beak, often holding a snake, and with large and powerful wings. They are traditionally enemies of the nāgas. In the Vedas, they are said to have brought nectar from the heavens to earth. <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">Garuḍa</em> can also be used as a proper name for a king of such creatures.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="292bd234-d0ca-4097-ab4d-99b6548b74e2" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_kcd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.561</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Gathered</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">tshogs pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཚོགས་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">An area in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9398">Kuru</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="06065a04-f338-4331-bceb-5fd705891843" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_kcl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.562</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Gautama</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gau ta ma</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གཽ་ཏ་མ།</span></li><li class="italic">gautama</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">Appellation for the Buddha, primarily used by <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8567">non-Buddhists</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="0b4d17d9-00ba-4362-a099-ba31e8d3fb01" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_kct5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.563</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Giver of Stones</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rdo sbyin par byed pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྡོ་སྦྱིན་པར་བྱེད་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9825">Uttara</span> Mountain.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="48c4b503-a64b-4e40-b3af-e7d46b2bce09" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_kd55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.564</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Glowing Hot Embers</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">me mdag tsha ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མེ་མདག་ཚ་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">rūkṣāṅgāra­nibha</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain range surrounding the hell of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9043">Embers Within</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="001a0a5f-1d64-4686-98cb-d50f70cca517" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_kdd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.565</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">god</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">lha</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ལྷ།</span></li><li class="italic">deva</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p>In the most general sense the devas‍—the term is cognate with the English <em class="emph">divine</em>‍—are a class of celestial beings who frequently appear in Buddhist texts, often at the head of the assemblies of nonhuman beings who attend and celebrate the teachings of the Buddha Śākyamuni and other buddhas and bodhisattvas. In Buddhist cosmology the devas occupy the highest of the five or six “destinies” (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">gati</em>) of saṃsāra among which beings take rebirth. The devas reside in the <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">devalokas</em>, “heavens” that traditionally number between twenty-six and twenty-eight and are divided between the desire realm (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">kāmadhātu</em>), form realm (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">rūpadhātu</em>), and formless realm (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">ārūpyadhātu</em>). A being attains rebirth among the devas either through meritorious deeds (in the desire realm) or the attainment of subtle meditative states (in the form and formless realms). While rebirth among the devas is considered favorable, it is ultimately a transitory state from which beings will fall when the conditions that lead to rebirth there are exhausted. Thus, rebirth in the god realms is regarded as a diversion from the spiritual path. </p></div></div></div></div><div id="8b6d8b7b-2b27-4edd-9145-c1acaa70d4aa" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_kdl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.566</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Godānīya</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ba lang spyod</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བ་ལང་སྤྱོད།</span></li><li class="italic">godānīya</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">The continent to the west of Mount <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9739">Sumeru</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="dad6145c-0143-4fb9-977f-fb00e0377ac7" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_kdt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.567</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Godāvarī</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">go dA ba rI</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གོ་དཱ་བ་རཱི།</span></li><li class="italic">godāvarī</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river in the south of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="594dacf7-525a-4187-9a8b-977fc57c5fc5" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ke55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.568</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Gold Garland</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gser gyi phreng ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གསེར་གྱི་ཕྲེང་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river at <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9606">Radiant Streams</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="b5b6a0f7-feac-4c3d-a7a5-39a29a989bfd" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ked5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.569</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Gold Water</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gser gyi chu</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གསེར་གྱི་ཆུ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9657">Saṅkāśa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="ffa05416-657c-418b-ab46-f1c30e271bda" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_kel5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.570</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Golden Garland</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gser phreng</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གསེར་ཕྲེང་།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">Forest on the third <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8489">asura</span> level, <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9087">Excellent Abode</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="58f62811-1c47-4a33-9870-12a9afb21e55" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ket5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.571</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Golden Ground</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gser gyi sa gzhi dang ldan pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གསེར་གྱི་ས་གཞི་དང་ལྡན་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">An island in the vicinity of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="02eea943-f4df-4763-ab69-0eed60a75113" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_kf55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.572</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Golden Shadow</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gser gyi grib ma</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གསེར་གྱི་གྲིབ་མ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A park in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9757">Sustained by Fruition</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="feb2aae8-1a61-4a7f-ae2d-f455bd5d04cc" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_kfd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.573</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Golden Walls</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gser gyi rtsig pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གསེར་གྱི་རྩིག་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">An island in the eastern sea beyond <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="42ecd130-56e8-4431-9d15-8ad0924b7736" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_kfl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.574</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Golden Waters</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gser gyi mdog gi chu</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གསེར་གྱི་མདོག་གི་ཆུ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">(1) A river on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8890">Cakravāḍa</span>. (2) A sea between <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9209">Godānīya</span> and <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9398">Kuru</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="355a94ba-76b1-4745-bd13-96bb0e15a9e5" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_kft5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.575</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Gonakī</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">go na kI</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གོ་ན་ཀཱི།</span></li><li class="italic">gonakī</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A location in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span> renowned for soft cotton.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="3259130a-c7ff-4755-a37d-87ecb7d54766" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_kg55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.576</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Gorgeous Gold Summit</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rtse mo yid ’ong gser</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྩེ་མོ་ཡིད་འོང་གསེར།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain near the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8489">asura</span> city <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9012">Double Pleasure</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="6b5f67ba-875b-4e47-bb6e-d012723a34d4" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_kgd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.577</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Gorgeous Mount</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ri mdzes pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རི་མཛེས་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A part of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9495">Mountainous Garland</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="75ba2471-25b5-486c-a3f8-c4e81e80aeaa" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_kgl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.578</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Gorgeous, Gorgeous Heaven</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">shin tu mthong</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཤིན་ཏུ་མཐོང་།</span></li><li class="italic">sudarśana</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">The fourth of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9927">five realms</span> associated with the fourth <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9969">concentration</span> into which only noble beings are born. </p></div></div></div></div><div id="0d02e1ee-a13a-4f3a-aab0-ad8e93bd2fb9" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_kgt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.579</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Gośīrṣaka</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">go shiR+Sha pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གོ་ཤིཪྵ་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">gośīrṣaka</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A minor mountain on <span><span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9422">Lofty Peak</span></span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="b6a4da21-46a4-4535-a177-d9bde5639997" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_kh55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.580</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Grape Water</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rgun ’bru’i chu</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྒུན་འབྲུའི་ཆུ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9657">Saṅkāśa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="fa02cb7d-3ec5-4601-8085-deacbf1718c7" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_khd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.581</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Great Action</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">las chen po</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ལས་ཆེན་པོ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A ruler of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9266">Heaven Free from Strife</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="fdc47c5f-8e87-42a5-923d-601d7cdfb3b3" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_khl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.582</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Great and Utter Joy</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rab dga’ chen po</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རབ་དགའ་ཆེན་པོ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A lake near <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9734">Sudharma</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="aec6a5db-8b26-4291-a593-a86dd8bbd8a0" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_kht5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.583</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Great Belly</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">lto chen po</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ལྟོ་ཆེན་པོ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain off <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9847">Videha</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="bca99826-22d1-4b24-bb0d-5dc305ebc19c" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ki55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.584</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Great Brahmā</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">tshangs chen</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཚངས་ཆེན།</span></li><li class="italic">mahābrahma</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">The highest level of the first <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9969">concentration</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="51106fc7-10a2-4ae1-bffd-f4b74ffc4598" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_kid5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.585</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Great Bright Light</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rab tu dang bar snang ba chen po</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རབ་ཏུ་དང་བར་སྣང་བ་ཆེན་པོ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A part of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9495">Mountainous Garland</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="770fceef-1ef9-4f31-aa3b-b3fd88b980fd" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_kil5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.586</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Great Buoyancy</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rab tu dang ba chen po</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རབ་ཏུ་དང་བ་ཆེན་པོ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain range in the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9266">Heaven Free from Strife</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="812114f7-78e5-4500-bc9f-6c772e79b1c0" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_kit5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.587</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Great Darkness</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mun nag chen po</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མུན་ནག་ཆེན་པོ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A hell in the vicinity of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9279">Ultimate Torment</span></p></div></div></div></div><div id="5eb156b9-45af-4730-8166-d79847d34514" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_kj55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.588</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Great Depth</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gting zab</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གཏིང་ཟབ།</span></li><li class="italic">āgādha</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain range surrounding the hell of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9043">Embers Within</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="c91e4214-b888-43a0-89dd-9c1d8b08241c" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_kjd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.589</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Great Flow</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">chen po rab tu ’bab pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཆེན་པོ་རབ་ཏུ་འབབ་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A lake on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9078">Equal Peaks</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="cf8e7a59-819b-4f4c-ba45-425a37deac75" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_kjl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.590</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Great Fruition</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’bras bu che ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འབྲས་བུ་ཆེ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">The third level of the fourth <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9969">concentration</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="b026a8fd-4a7f-414c-98e0-507f032ddcef" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_kjt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.591</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Great Howling, Great Howling Hell</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ngu ’bod chen po</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ངུ་འབོད་ཆེན་པོ།</span></li><li class="italic">mahāraurava</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of the eight hot hells.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="219a87bb-8f4e-4feb-9c7b-7b4eb2896244" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_kk55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.592</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Great Joy</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dga’ ba chen po</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དགའ་བ་ཆེན་པོ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9056">Endowed with Increasing Bliss</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="eb0341b1-0309-406b-8689-0e55a2c2bd9f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_kkd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.593</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Great Power</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dbang chen</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དབང་ཆེན།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain in the sea beyond <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span></p></div></div></div></div><div id="b63c7b1e-6e07-4c3b-bc28-1fe63b76c91f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_kkl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.594</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Great Rodhā</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ro dhA chen po</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རོ་དྷཱ་ཆེན་པོ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river to the south of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="03dfc92a-b8c3-495f-bcfc-db3ab0cd7733" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_kkt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.595</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Great Śālmali Forest, Śālmali Forest</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">shing shal ma la’i tshal chen, shing shal ma li chen po’i tshal, shing shal ma li’i tshal</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཤིང་ཤལ་མ་ལའི་ཚལ་ཆེན།, ཤིང་ཤལ་མ་ལི་ཆེན་པོའི་ཚལ།, ཤིང་ཤལ་མ་ལིའི་ཚལ།</span></li><li class="italic">mahā­śālmali­vana, śālmalivana</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of sixteen realms that surround the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9235">Great Howling Hell</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="0c9aad12-4844-4711-b448-a7d0d2a420cb" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_kl55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.596</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Great Śālmali Forest, Śālmali Forest</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">shing shal ma la’i tshal chen, shing shal ma li chen po’i tshal, shing shal ma li’i tshal</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཤིང་ཤལ་མ་ལའི་ཚལ་ཆེན།, ཤིང་ཤལ་མ་ལི་ཆེན་པོའི་ཚལ།, ཤིང་ཤལ་མ་ལིའི་ཚལ།</span></li><li class="italic">mahā­śālmali­vana, śālmalivana</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of sixteen realms that surround the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9235">Great Howling Hell</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="2a0aef08-fa4f-4a5e-9f34-ef958576b674" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_kld5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.597</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Great Scorching</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rab tu sreg pa chen po</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རབ་ཏུ་སྲེག་པ་ཆེན་པོ།</span></li><li class="italic">mahāpradāha</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of the sixteen realms that surround the <span><span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9277">Hell of Heat</span></span>. </p></div></div></div></div><div id="522384c3-3dce-48a8-8638-78a852eb3c78" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_kll5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.598</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Great Slope</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">logs chen po</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ལོགས་ཆེན་པོ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9847">Videha</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="c040798f-f3d8-4bfa-b3bd-2f4296867559" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_klt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.599</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Great Sound</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sgra chen</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྒྲ་ཆེན།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river in the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9278">Hell of Intense Heat</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="6ffa1fed-94a0-4d24-9c07-c9a02a707cff" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_km55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.600</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Great Summit</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rtse mo rgya chen po</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྩེ་མོ་རྒྱ་ཆེན་པོ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9511">Moving in Vast Environments</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="a67d34ba-7a37-470d-9d35-8853758f778f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_kmd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.601</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Great Tangible Darkness</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mun nag thibs</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མུན་ནག་ཐིབས།</span></li><li class="italic">tamonicaya­sparśa</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain range surrounding the hell of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9043">Embers Within</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="83c8bfe0-2709-42f4-adea-d7a17f6e61fe" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_kml5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.602</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Great Trees</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ljon shing, shing chen po</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ལྗོན་ཤིང་།, ཤིང་ཆེན་པོ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">(1) A forest in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9025">Dwelling in Excellent View</span> (<em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">shing chen po</em>). (2) A lotus pond on the fifth minor mountain on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9423">Lofty Summit</span> (<em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">ljon shing</em>).</p></div></div></div></div><div id="3d148261-4c45-4bc4-acec-1f9d03ee71ae" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_kmt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.603</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Great Waters</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">chu chen po</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཆུ་ཆེན་པོ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9544">Ornament of the Mind</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="586792d6-4aef-4957-b43e-4380b988e136" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_kn55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.604</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Great Waves</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rlabs chen, rlabs chen po</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རླབས་ཆེན་པོ།, རླབས་ཆེན།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">(1) An ocean far off the coast of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span> (<em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">rlabs chen po</em>). (2) A river in the south of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span> (<em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">rlabs chen</em>).</p></div></div></div></div><div id="7ba84e0a-0b64-404d-8d57-0f20cb443c30" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_knd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.605</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">ground</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ས།</span></li><li class="italic">bhūmi</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">Stage of spiritual maturation or realization on the path to awakening, serving as the <span class="ignore">ground</span> for the growth of noble qualities. </p></div></div></div></div><div id="6ef4ded9-b4fe-413e-bf37-074d841f1667" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_knl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.606</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Ground of Constant Joy</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">kun dga’ gzhi</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀུན་དགའ་གཞི།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A park in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9757">Sustained by Fruition</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="3427eeab-654c-4444-b95f-8c08633cdda2" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_knt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.607</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">ground traveler</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sa gzhi la rgyu ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ས་གཞི་ལ་རྒྱུ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A class of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8622">vidyādharas</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="3f0d07f7-384f-4dff-9110-1045b33dc9bb" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ko55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.608</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Grove</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">kun nas tshal</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀུན་ནས་ཚལ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A grove in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9034">Dwelling on Mixed Riverbanks</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="5d378ab1-0347-4532-a9d3-4f0b5d1a0771" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_kod5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.609</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Grove of Beauty</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">nags tshal mdzes</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ནགས་ཚལ་མཛེས།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A queen of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8731">Rāhu</span>, king of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8489">asuras</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="5be3a3a9-c36f-421a-868d-51ec54c0396a" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_kol5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.610</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Grove of Delicious Wine</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">chang zhim po’i tshal</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཆང་ཞིམ་པོའི་ཚལ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9505">Moving on Springy Ground</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="a4630c51-6783-4122-9137-b9ce89cddae6" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_kot5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.611</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Grove of Infatuation</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">myos byed kyi tshal</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མྱོས་བྱེད་ཀྱི་ཚལ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A grove in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9519">Mutual Liking</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="43ff96d9-3414-4a74-93d1-0f24e86a5b9e" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_kp55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.612</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Grove of Utter Joy, grove known as Utter Joy</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">tshal rab tu dga’ ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཚལ་རབ་ཏུ་དགའ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A grove in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9197">Garland of Splendor</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="398255ac-22f9-4438-ac87-7e6d5d5478dc" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_kpd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.613</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Growing Utpalas</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ud pa la skye</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཨུད་པ་ལ་སྐྱེ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9035">Dwelling on Summits</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="76849504-74b0-4384-ac86-e3e58678f3b1" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_kpl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.614</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">guardians of the world</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’jig rten skyong ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འཇིག་རྟེན་སྐྱོང་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">This refers to the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8526">Four Great Kings</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="298a66bc-1e2b-4352-b555-a94e2ee3f82f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_kpt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.615</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">guhyaka</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gsang ba pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གསང་བ་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">guhyaka</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A subclass of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8629">yakṣas</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="40b7b71a-462f-4697-a28b-84fe5b72c227" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_kq55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.616</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">halāhala</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ha la ha la</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཧ་ལ་ཧ་ལ།</span></li><li class="italic">halāhala</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mythological poison said to have been produced by demonic forces in their fight against the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8531">gods</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="873e97ed-60bf-4a59-ae45-6e614ecb617e" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_kqd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.617</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Hanging Leaves</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">lo ma shin tu ’phyang ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ལོ་མ་ཤིན་ཏུ་འཕྱང་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9142">Forest Garlands</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="c747787a-1ac3-40be-9d37-c04eced26246" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_kql5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.618</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Happiness</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rtag tu dga’ ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྟག་ཏུ་དགའ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A realm of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8621">vessel-bearer gods</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="8cbbc6d9-a880-4dd7-8e8e-3c87d1ac5f50" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_kqt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.619</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Happy Bees</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bung ba mngon dga’</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བུང་བ་མངོན་དགའ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A grove in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9403">Lateral</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="27e4f408-2a83-4544-bae7-58c260fcfbf2" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_kr55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.620</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Happy Flow</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">yid bde bar ’bab pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཡིད་བདེ་བར་འབབ་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9657">Saṅkāśa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="aee7db3c-3a2e-4851-92bd-e72b3f22f976" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_krd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.621</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Happy Mind</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">yid bde ba, yid dga’</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཡིད་དགའ།, ཡིད་བདེ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">(1) A forest in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9413">Living by Rājanina</span> (<em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">yid dga’</em>). (2) A mountain in the eastern sea between <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span> and <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9847">Videha</span> (<em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">yid bde ba</em>).</p></div></div></div></div><div id="d4cd314d-1814-4c28-bbeb-799d1d6e6435" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_krl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.622</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Harmed by Pain</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sdug bsngal gyis gnod pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྡུག་བསྔལ་གྱིས་གནོད་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">duḥkhataḍāga</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of sixteen realms that surround the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9630">Reviving Hell</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="3726be32-a663-4eef-bf46-ff0252c07e0a" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_krt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.623</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Harmful Forest</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gnod pa’i nags</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གནོད་པའི་ནགས།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A town in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9847">Videha</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="ec8f7f40-6c08-41c1-abc2-6cce205065e8" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ks55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.624</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">harsh words</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">tshig rtsub</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཚིག་རྩུབ།</span></li><li class="italic">pāruṣya</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">The third among the four verbal misdeeds.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="c9f11341-559b-494a-8878-0248ae23ef8d" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ksd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.625</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Heap in the Stream</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">klung na brtsegs pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀླུང་ན་བརྩེགས་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9417">Living on the Peak</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="60f195d8-5e68-4c45-ad04-fc5bff26712d" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ksl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.626</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Heap of Incense</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">spos brtsegs</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྤོས་བརྩེགས།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A peak upon Mount <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9739">Sumeru</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="ab1dc604-693c-4013-9047-1f9f17f7b945" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_kst5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.627</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Heap of Iron</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">lcags kyi phung po</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ལྕགས་ཀྱི་ཕུང་པོ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain off <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9847">Videha</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="ec2af397-5749-42d6-8613-53aeadf43ef5" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_kt55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.628</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Heap of Live Coals of Iron-dust</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">lcags kyi phye ma me mdag gi ra ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ལྕགས་ཀྱི་ཕྱེ་མ་མེ་མདག་གི་ར་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">ayaś­cūrṇāṅgāra­nikara</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of sixteen realms that surround the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8975">Crushing Hell</span>. Alternatively referred to as <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9468">Metallic Fire</span> (<em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">lcags kyi me</em>).</p></div></div></div></div><div id="e19490fe-96ef-407f-8605-6b8e15d6c0fb" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ktd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.629</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Heaps of Fresh Butter</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mar sar gyi gong bu</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མར་སར་གྱི་གོང་བུ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A lake on the mountain called “<span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9085">Excellence of Exquisite Intelligence</span>.”</p></div></div></div></div><div id="5a90184b-4c5f-424b-8a34-4d859dc83b2f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ktl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.630</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">hearer</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">nyan thos</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཉན་ཐོས།</span></li><li class="italic">śrāvaka</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">The term is most simply interpreted as “those who hear” the Buddha’s teaching, i.e. his disciples, but the additional <span class="ignore">element</span> that they then “make it heard” to others is often present in canonical glosses. In a Mahāyāna context it refers to those disciples of the Buddha who aspire to attain the state of a <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8627">worthy one</span> (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">arhat</em>), and not to embark on the path of a bodhisattva (with buddhahood as its ultimate goal).</p></div></div></div></div><div id="7914a74a-dcb8-4c66-80f4-6948756ba88a" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ktt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.631</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Heartbreaking Cries</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">snying rje rje skad sgra ’byin pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྙིང་རྗེ་རྗེ་སྐད་སྒྲ་འབྱིན་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">karuṇānināda</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A realm that neighbors the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9278">Hell of Intense Heat</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="01cf2171-1722-4bd1-be63-0cf55b101a24" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ku55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.632</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Heat, Hell of Heat</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">tsha ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཚ་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">tapana</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of the eight hot hells.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="edb6d2f3-3f74-4ea3-866d-d369436fbbd4" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_kud5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.633</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Heaven of Increased Merit, Increased Merit</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bsod nams skyes</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བསོད་ནམས་སྐྱེས།</span></li><li class="italic">puṇyaprasava</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">The second level of the fourth <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9969">concentration</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="46213ef2-d436-4f60-8508-a7ba72502ab3" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_kul5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.634</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Heaven of Joy</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dga’ ldan</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དགའ་ལྡན།</span></li><li class="italic">tuṣita</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p>Tuṣita (or sometimes Saṃtuṣita), literally “Joyous” or “Contented,” is one of the six heavens of the desire realm (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">kāmadhātu</em>). In standard classifications, such as the one in the <cite class="title break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">Abhidharmakośa</cite>, it is ranked as the fourth of the six counting from below. This god realm is where all future buddhas are said to dwell before taking on their final rebirth prior to awakening. There, the Buddha Śākyamuni lived his preceding life as the bodhisattva Śvetaketu. When departing to take birth in this world, he appointed the bodhisattva Maitreya, who will be the next buddha of this eon, as his Dharma regent in Tuṣita. For an account of the Buddha’s previous life in Tuṣita, see <cite class="title text-en" lang="en">The Play in Full</cite> (Toh 95), <a target="_blank" href="/entity/passage/943039c8-c5ca-4a10-a536-2dd2c725aba6" title="2.12">2.12</a>, and for an account of Maitreya’s birth in Tuṣita and a description of this realm, see <cite class="title text-en" lang="en"><a target="_blank" href="/entity/work/61476bf4-b4db-4e4d-9993-60d347cf1769" title="The Sūtra on Maitreya’s Birth in the Heaven of Joy">The Sūtra on Maitreya’s Birth in the Heaven of Joy</a></cite>, (Toh 199).</p></div></div></div></div><div id="b8b39106-75e2-421e-aefe-42823367ccb8" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_kut5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.635</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Heaven of Limited Virtue</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dge chung</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དགེ་ཆུང་།</span></li><li class="italic">parīttaśubha</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">The first level of the third <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9969">concentration</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="ff1831f1-ef0c-4439-a310-65808c3d2c24" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_kv55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.636</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Heaven of Limitless Virtue, Limitless Virtue</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">tshad med dge</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཚད་མེད་དགེ</span></li><li class="italic">apramāṇaśubha</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">The third level within the third <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9969">concentration</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="d4e75f68-8e45-4473-ac6a-2ad7f89e2825" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_kvd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.637</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Heaven of Making Use of Others’ Emanations, Making Use of Others’ Emanations</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gzhan ’phrul dbang byed pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གཞན་འཕྲུལ་དབང་བྱེད་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">para­nirmita­vaśa­vartin</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of the six heavens of the desire realm.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="3ca8faf7-6e08-42a4-be38-986cb344c304" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_kvl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.638</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Heaven of No Hardship, No Hardship</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mi gdung ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མི་གདུང་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">atapa</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">The second of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9927">five realms</span> associated with the fourth <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9969">concentration</span> into which only noble beings are born. </p></div></div></div></div><div id="8c5181be-ba55-4de6-8963-268f4ea0ae65" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_kvt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.639</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Heaven of Perfected Virtue, Perfected Virtue</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dge rgyas</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དགེ་རྒྱས།</span></li><li class="italic">śubhakṛtsna</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">The second level of the third <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9969">concentration</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="5395cc84-679f-4260-8e1a-39c1fe9d002a" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_l055anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.640</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Heaven of the Four Great Kings</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rgyal chen bzhi’i ris</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྒྱལ་ཆེན་བཞིའི་རིས།</span></li><li class="italic">caturmahā­rājika</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of the six heavens of the desire realm.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="0446cfb8-b505-4839-b40c-cb2de27fd0c5" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_l0d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.641</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Heaven of the Thirty-Three</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sum cu rtsa gsum</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སུམ་ཅུ་རྩ་གསུམ།</span></li><li class="italic">trāyastriṃśa</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of the six heavens of the desire realm.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="75490385-7dc4-45eb-a8ee-660e965e39a8" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_l0l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.642</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">hell being</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sems can dmyal ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སེམས་ཅན་དམྱལ་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">naraka</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of the five or six classes of sentient beings, engendered by anger and powerful negative actions. They are dominated by great suffering and said to dwell in different hells with specific characteristics.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="1160cf2d-5e09-4ed0-b863-8c83c862567d" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_l0t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.643</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">hell of Destructive Wood Fire</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">shing skam ltar ’jigs par ’tshed</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཤིང་སྐམ་ལྟར་འཇིགས་པར་འཚེད།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A realm that neighbors the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9278">Hell of Intense Heat</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="f3ab1c4a-402f-4e85-917a-eee362258ec3" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_l155anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.644</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Hell of Intense Heat, Intense Heat</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rab tu tsha ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རབ་ཏུ་ཚ་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">pratāpana</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of the eight hot hells.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="3d3649dd-8aa0-47cd-a66e-f5af7b1e1fb0" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_l1d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.645</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Hell of the Lump, Lump</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bsdus pa, ’khums pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བསྡུས་པ།, འཁུམས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">piṇḍonaraka</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of sixteen realms that surround the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8975">Crushing Hell</span>. </p></div></div></div></div><div id="8f5efab1-1d55-410b-b89a-af49ca7d6f7d" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_l1l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.646</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Hell of Ultimate Torment, Ultimate Torment</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mnar med</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མནར་མེད།</span></li><li class="italic">avīci</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">The most severe among the eight hot hells.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="d97690e4-9c44-4a8b-9c7e-3609404682f7" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_l1t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.647</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">High and Low</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dma’ ba dang mtho ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དམའ་བ་དང་མཐོ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A park in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9757">Sustained by Fruition</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="d99867eb-bf50-4fd9-8ff6-e3fd719a7bca" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_l255anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.648</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">High and Seen by Everyone</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">kun mthong mtho</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀུན་མཐོང་མཐོ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9601">Promotion</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="1c904477-7c77-42ad-9881-395d768a77bb" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_l2d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.649</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">High Brahmins of Brahmā, High Priests of Brahmā</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">tshangs pa’i mdun na ’don, tshangs pa’i mdun na ’don</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཚངས་པའི་མདུན་ན་འདོན།, ཚངས་པའི་མདུན་ན་འདོན།</span></li><li class="italic">brahmapurohita</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">The second level of the first among the realms of form.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="787d87c0-59f2-4e9e-9c43-01875b5b8c4c" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_l2l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.650</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">High Brahmins of Brahmā, High Priests of Brahmā</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">tshangs pa’i mdun na ’don, tshangs pa’i mdun na ’don</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཚངས་པའི་མདུན་ན་འདོན།, ཚངས་པའི་མདུན་ན་འདོན།</span></li><li class="italic">brahmapurohita</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">The intermediate level of the first <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9969">concentration</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="62e94bcb-1483-4d3f-afc0-b080637152e9" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_l2t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.651</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">High Conduct</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mtho bar spyod pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མཐོ་བར་སྤྱོད་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">utkarṣacārinī</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A realm in the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9276">Heaven of the Thirty-Three</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="fcfb75db-f3ea-48a7-b81b-5efb356b00bc" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_l355anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.652</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Highest Heaven</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’og min</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འོག་མིན།</span></li><li class="italic">akaniṣṭha</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">The fifth of <span class="ignore">five realms</span> associated with the fourth <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9969">concentration</span> into which only noble beings are born. </p></div></div></div></div><div id="31d7bacd-f3f4-4ee3-95dc-ffd773df9d33" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_l3d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.653</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">highway possessors</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">lam chen ldan</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ལམ་ཆེན་ལྡན།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A class of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8489">asuras</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="405a8540-d5b2-4f00-bf18-0ae88f8273a6" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_l3l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.654</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Himalayas</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">kha ba can</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཁ་བ་ཅན།</span></li><li class="italic">himālaya</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">The Himalayan mountain range</p></div></div></div></div><div id="dcf3ef05-7792-4926-852d-3fecef722b45" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_l3t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.655</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Himavat</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gangs can</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གངས་ཅན།</span></li><li class="italic">himavat</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">Mountains in the north of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="ce8ed6b9-9f12-4b31-8a20-85219997640c" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_l455anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.656</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Holder of Joy</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">kun dga’ ba ’dzin pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀུན་དགའ་བ་འཛིན་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9398">Kuru</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="fba80677-f3e5-43e7-b321-3f31d31a56c6" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_l4d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.657</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Holder of Supreme Gifts</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mchog sbyin ’dzin</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མཆོག་སྦྱིན་འཛིན།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A previous ruler of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9276">Heaven of the Thirty-Three</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="35d3817a-64e4-4286-a2cc-6986ec453d00" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_l4l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.658</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Hole Marked by Spinning Wheels</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’khor lo ltar yongs su bskor ba mtshan ma’i bar</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འཁོར་ལོ་ལྟར་ཡོངས་སུ་བསྐོར་བ་མཚན་མའི་བར།</span></li><li class="italic">paribhrāmita­cakrāṅka­vivara</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A place in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9279">Ultimate Torment</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="140c1d11-b9b0-4833-b761-d3bb7482055f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_l4t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.659</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Home of Birds</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bya nges par gnas pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བྱ་ངེས་པར་གནས་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9657">Saṅkāśa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="66afc256-6782-4f56-887f-80af508d5da7" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_l555anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.660</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Home of Geese</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ngang pa’i gnas</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ངང་པའི་གནས།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of four parks that surround the city of <span data-ref="UT22084-068-021-9605"><span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9605">Radiant</span></span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="5989be66-5746-4f15-b3bb-6a05ec401d79" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_l5d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.661</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Honey River</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sbrang rtsi ’bab pa’i chu bo</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྦྲང་རྩི་འབབ་པའི་ཆུ་བོ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9072">Enjoyment of Scents</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="c10bb025-08bf-4460-a5f4-7aaf9197b91d" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_l5l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.662</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Honey Water Forest</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sbrang rtsi’i chu’i tshal</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྦྲང་རྩིའི་ཆུའི་ཚལ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9027">Dwelling in One Direction</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="cdba9148-bafc-4c4c-976f-551b4c855d21" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_l5t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.663</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Horse Cloud Forest</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rta’i sprin</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྟའི་སྤྲིན།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8989">Deer Abode</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="b0f10fa6-eb5d-4102-8361-051ffb783c24" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_l655anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.664</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">horse-faced people</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rta gdong can</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྟ་གདོང་ཅན།</span></li><li class="italic">turaṃgavadana</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A type of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9967">kinnara</span> that has a horse face and the body of a horse.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="1f479f49-55e6-44ab-896d-c38debe895d8" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_l6d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.665</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">House of Refined Gold</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gser phug gi khang pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གསེར་ཕུག་གི་ཁང་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">tapanīyagṛha</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A realm in the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9276">Heaven of the Thirty-Three</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="4af8234b-7f95-41ab-9f21-9349852596fa" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_l6l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.666</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Hovering Bees</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bung ba rkang drug rjes su rgyu ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བུང་བ་རྐང་དྲུག་རྗེས་སུ་རྒྱུ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A lotus pool on the banks of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9131">Flow of Beauty</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="fe914433-6a45-467b-8c07-27e81522a03b" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_l6t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.667</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Howling Like a Jackal</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">wa ltar sgra ’byin, wa skad ’byin</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཝ་ལྟར་སྒྲ་འབྱིན།, ཝ་སྐད་འབྱིན།</span></li><li class="italic">jambukanināda</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of sixteen realms that surround the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9279">Hell of Ultimate Torment</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="7a28c7f9-6d3d-47c6-bf8c-14375613c412" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_l755anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.668</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Howling, Howling Hell</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ngu ’bod</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ངུ་འབོད།</span></li><li class="italic">raurava</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of the eight hot hells.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="2bc9402b-e92e-42e9-a806-d8a14809c7ac" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_l7d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.669</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Huluhulu</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">hu lu hu lu</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཧུ་ལུ་ཧུ་ལུ།</span></li><li class="italic">huluhulu</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">An unvirtuous <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8562">nāga</span> king.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="a4254b29-93b5-4af9-a1fe-d4190600bc41" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_l7l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.670</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Hundred Arches</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rta babs brgya pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྟ་བབས་བརྒྱ་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A city in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9209">Godānīya</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="3ead9fd1-1b49-42e1-87d1-c79b48106604" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_l7t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.671</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Hundred Peaks</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">parba brgya pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">པརྦ་བརྒྱ་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9209">Godānīya</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="a6900b41-d734-4078-b5bf-ecc0144bdfe6" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_l855anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.672</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Ikṣvāku</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bu ram shing pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བུ་རམ་ཤིང་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">ikṣvāku</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition"><span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-10026">Śākyamuni</span>’s family line.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="6276adee-879f-4e8b-af6c-c11d910d5aaa" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_l8d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.673</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">ill will</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gnod sems</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གནོད་སེམས།</span></li><li class="italic">vyāpāda</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">The second among the three mental misdeeds.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="4c60d2fe-c13a-454a-92ee-6915b748f683" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_l8l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.674</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Illuminating the Surroundings</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">nye ’khor kun tu snang ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཉེ་འཁོར་ཀུན་ཏུ་སྣང་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9413">Living by Rājanina</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="c0eaa32a-7049-49b9-8783-3a21c22eb8cb" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_l8t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.675</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Illumination</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’od snang</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འོད་སྣང་།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9672">Shining in Manifold Ways</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="85800438-ce3f-45bb-820a-d2b76101f8d0" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_l955anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.676</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Immeasurable</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gzhal du med pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གཞལ་དུ་མེད་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river in the northern continent of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9398">Kuru</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="3c129cb0-629a-41da-ba29-c0f8b5497049" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_l9d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.677</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Immortal One</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mi ’chi</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མི་འཆི།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A previous ruler of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9276">Heaven of the Thirty-Three</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="e4511fe9-5ba4-46c7-9a1f-bdc2ba1cd818" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_l9l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.678</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Immovable</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mi g.yo ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མི་གཡོ་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">acalā</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">The fourth level of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8489">asuras</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="84ba497a-d239-482b-ac98-66a40da1dc21" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_l9t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.679</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Immutable One</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mi ’gyur</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མི་འགྱུར།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A previous ruler of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9276">Heaven of the Thirty-Three</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="2ae09034-d18d-4db9-a506-5da413314e1f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_la55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.680</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">imperceptible form</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rnam par rig byed ma yin pa, rnam par rig byed ma yin pa’i gzugs</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྣམ་པར་རིག་བྱེད་མ་ཡིན་པ།, རྣམ་པར་རིག་བྱེད་མ་ཡིན་པའི་གཟུགས།</span></li><li class="italic">avijñaptirūpa</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">Entities, such as vows, that are categorized as form composed of the physical <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9921">elements</span> yet remain imperceptible. </p></div></div></div></div><div id="34afc2a4-84bd-4ab2-8b0d-a55e288cd00d" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_lad5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.681</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Impossible to Die</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gsod med</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གསོད་མེད།</span></li><li class="italic">nirmarmara</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of sixteen realms that surround the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9298">Howling Hell</span>. Also known as <span><span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9533">No Death</span></span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="d85f0cbf-ef86-4bff-8212-214ef3ece3f0" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_lal5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.682</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">In Tune with All Pleasures</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’dod pa thams cad rjes su ’thun pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འདོད་པ་ཐམས་ཅད་རྗེས་སུ་འཐུན་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9672">Shining in Manifold Ways</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="08103cda-89bd-4ca8-ab1b-e1ea12aef6f0" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_lat5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.683</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Incense River</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">spos chu</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྤོས་ཆུ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river in the realm of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8526">Four Great Kings</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="15ad3e40-2f7e-4f47-adb4-ee01f86306dc" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_lb55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.684</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Incessantly Intense Pain</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">tshor ba rtag tu ’dus pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཚོར་བ་རྟག་ཏུ་འདུས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">samāhṛta­vedana</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A realm that neigbors the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8846">Black Line Hell</span>.</p><p class="definition">(The term <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">Samāhṛtavedana</em> is reading, on the authority of the Tib., <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">samāhūta˚</em> as <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">samāhṛta˚</em>)</p></div></div></div></div><div id="be70d498-69c9-41ee-b016-d2c2203a7cca" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_lbd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.685</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Incomparable</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dpe med pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དཔེ་མེད་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest at <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9734">Sudharma</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="e6a5a71c-dbbd-425a-9f3b-8da38fd52437" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_lbl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.686</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Incomparable Harm</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gnod pa dpe med pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གནོད་པ་དཔེ་མེད་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">pīḍānupama</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of sixteen realms that surround the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9235">Great Howling Hell</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="0854ae78-30a4-425c-84fe-a3d3d295f00f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_lbt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.687</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">incorrect mental engagement</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">tshul bzhin ma yin pa’i yid la byed pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཚུལ་བཞིན་མ་ཡིན་པའི་ཡིད་ལ་བྱེད་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">ayoniśomanas­kara</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">Identifications and discernments that run counter to the actual nature of things.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="c52d23d8-82bd-4352-9da7-b279eb213441" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_lc55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.688</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Indra</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dbang po</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དབང་པོ།</span></li><li class="italic">indra</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">Another name of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8738">Śakra</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="0e6e477c-fd44-4606-a6f2-4225f2ac780a" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_lcd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.689</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Infatuation with One’s Body</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rang lus kyi rgyags pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རང་ལུས་ཀྱི་རྒྱགས་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of the twenty-seven realms in the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9266">Heaven Free from Strife</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="3e684255-b7af-4208-9406-96c0d10b4584" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_lcl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.690</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Infinite Flow</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dpag tu med pa ’bab pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དཔག་ཏུ་མེད་པ་འབབ་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9657">Saṅkāśa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="ddf242fb-b642-4427-862f-e8328ea37f11" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_lct5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.691</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Infinite Pain</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">tshor ba mtha’ yas</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཚོར་བ་མཐའ་ཡས།</span></li><li class="italic">anantaduḥkha, anantavedana</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of sixteen realms that surround the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9235">Great Howling Hell</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="41a6c5c1-2684-4410-a300-f88b41c77aa7" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ld55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.692</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Infinite Shores</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mtha’ yas pha rol</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མཐའ་ཡས་ཕ་རོལ།</span></li><li class="italic">anantapārā</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river in hell.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="f2af2ab1-a478-4289-b63e-443f0772f20e" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ldd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.693</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Infinite Sinking into the Ground</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sar ’bying mtha’ yas</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སར་འབྱིང་མཐའ་ཡས།</span></li><li class="italic">ananta­majjana­bhūmi</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of the sixteen realms that surround the <span><span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9277">Hell of Heat</span></span>. </p></div></div></div></div><div id="5b7abad9-0824-413a-b972-d628ab4a56f1" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ldl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.694</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Infinite Torture</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">tshor ba tshad med pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཚོར་བ་ཚད་མེད་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">mahāpramāṇa­vedana</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of sixteen realms that surround the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8975">Crushing Hell</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="1f51ca70-4a66-47e5-b569-053433e43739" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ldt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.695</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Infinitely Long Torture</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sdug bsngal mtha’ yas mang ba, tshor ba mtha’ med ring</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཚོར་བ་མཐའ་མེད་རིང་།, སྡུག་བསྔལ་མཐའ་ཡས་མང་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">apāra­dīrgha­vedana</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of sixteen realms that surround the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9279">Hell of Ultimate Torment</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="50fa40e7-20b6-40ea-8ca4-13875b6e622b" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_le55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.696</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Inner Vastness</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">nang yangs pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ནང་ཡངས་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A lake in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9753">Supreme Strength</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="4e1837f3-c77b-4e2d-bac3-5eafbaa7a4b7" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_led5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.697</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Insatiable</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ngoms mi myong</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ངོམས་མི་མྱོང་།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9035">Dwelling on Summits</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="dd19cf68-69ee-4f3b-bb5f-2c47fbe86706" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_lel5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.698</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">insight</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">shes rab</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཤེས་རབ།</span></li><li class="italic">prajñā</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">Transcendent or discriminating awareness; the mind that sees the ultimate truth. One of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-10035">six perfections</span> of the bodhisattva.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="2f5be259-ed5f-46db-b858-f35798e7d03d" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_let5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.699</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Instant Revival Upon Death</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">shi ma thag tu ’tsho ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཤི་མ་ཐག་ཏུ་འཚོ་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">sama­mṛtyu­jīvita</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of sixteen realms that surround the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9235">Great Howling Hell</span>. Alternatively referred to as <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9404">Life Isochronous with Death</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="9622934b-1291-4137-bb53-78f7436a38f0" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_lf55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.700</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Insuperable</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">zil gyis mi non pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཟིལ་གྱིས་མི་ནོན་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A king of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9272">Heaven of Making Use of Others’ Emanations</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="752d2fa3-ca32-4a0e-9b2c-312e8697b070" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_lfd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.701</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Intense Harm</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gnod pa drag pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གནོད་པ་དྲག་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">caṇḍaghora</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of sixteen realms that surround the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9630">Reviving Hell</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="b541559c-622d-467e-954e-3691e871531f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_lfl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.702</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Intense Heat from All Directions</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">phyogs thams cad rab tu sreg pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཕྱོགས་ཐམས་ཅད་རབ་ཏུ་སྲེག་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">sarva­dikpratāpa</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A realm that neighbors the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9278">Hell of Intense Heat</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="fc73433d-2ee7-43b2-8aa6-8dc85bda78d7" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_lft5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.703</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Intoxicating Abode</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">myos gnas</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མྱོས་གནས།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9008">Distinguished in Many Colorful Ways</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="1c765f9f-f27c-4469-a603-ce0fb3f38bc2" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_lg55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.704</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Invisible</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mi mthong ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མི་མཐོང་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9101">Eye Garland</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="472abb80-21b7-4980-a0e3-f5075bce449a" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_lgd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.705</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Invisible Summit</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rtse rtse mi snang</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྩེ་རྩེ་མི་སྣང་།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain near the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8489">asura</span> city <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9012">Double Pleasure</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="347238a7-8b77-42e8-a604-774af1d160ef" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_lgl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.706</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Iron Plates</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">lcags gleg, lcags snam</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ལྕགས་གླེག, ལྕགས་སྣམ།</span></li><li class="italic">ayaspaṭṭa</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of sixteen realms that surround the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9279">Hell of Ultimate Torment</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="18599e16-22c3-424a-a949-18b700934522" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_lgt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.707</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Iron Vase</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">lcags kyi bum pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ལྕགས་ཀྱི་བུམ་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">ayaskumbha</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of the sixteen realms that surround the <span><span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9277">Hell of Heat</span></span>. </p></div></div></div></div><div id="1f6ff524-3643-4e7a-978c-29a45f253d83" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_lh55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.708</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Iron Wilderness</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">lcags tshal dgon pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ལྕགས་ཚལ་དགོན་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">ayovanakāntāra</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of sixteen realms that surround the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9298">Howling Hell</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="bb06c8b2-7e47-4933-9bd1-90451ee2c294" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_lhd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.709</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Isle of Jewels, Jewel Islands</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rin po che’i gling, rin po che’i gling</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རིན་པོ་ཆེའི་གླིང་།, རིན་པོ་ཆེའི་གླིང་།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain in the sea far beyond <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span></p></div></div></div></div><div id="f668e516-539c-4acf-81b3-0ee35c0a0792" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_lhl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.710</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Isle of Jewels, Jewel Islands</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rin po che’i gling, rin po che’i gling</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རིན་པོ་ཆེའི་གླིང་།, རིན་པོ་ཆེའི་གླིང་།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">An ocean off <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="df808ea3-f5c8-4222-9063-4479d741f88e" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_lht5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.711</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Isolated Highlands</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’brog tu rnam par chad pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འབྲོག་ཏུ་རྣམ་པར་ཆད་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A city in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9847">Videha</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="b92ef609-438c-4143-aa43-dd6b8a4de777" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_li55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.712</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Jagaddala</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dza gad+dA la</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཛ་གདྡཱ་ལ།</span></li><li class="italic">jagaddala</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">An important Buddhist monastery located in Bengal (modern day Bangladesh), founded by King <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8734">Rāmapāla</span> (ruled 1077–1120 <span class="small-caps">ᴄᴇ</span>).</p></div></div></div></div><div id="674f564a-d9ff-4357-a660-2bbdee7e0874" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_lid5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.713</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Jambha</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’dzam bha</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འཛམ་བྷ།</span></li><li class="italic">jambha</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">An <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8489">asura</span>. </p></div></div></div></div><div id="e1ae34b2-901c-4afb-8cd1-96c09d04e789" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_lil5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.714</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Jambu</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’dzam bu</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འཛམ་བུ།</span></li><li class="italic">jambu</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river famed for its excellent gold</p></div></div></div></div><div id="5351bc6b-0b65-4dd1-90e0-85e8aab15862" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_lit5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.715</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Jaṃbu Forest</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’jam bu’i tshal</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འཇམ་བུའི་ཚལ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A peak on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9739">Sumeru</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="be5ccc20-147a-488c-a8e8-2634b4f12caf" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_lj55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.716</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Jambudvīpa</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’dzam bu gling</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འཛམ་བུ་གླིང་།</span></li><li class="italic">jambudvīpa</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p>The name of the southern continent in Buddhist cosmology, which can signify either the known human world, or more specifically the Indian subcontinent, literally “the <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">jambu</em> island/continent.” Jambu is the name used for a range of plum-like fruits from trees belonging to the genus <em class="foreign">Szygium</em>, particularly <em class="foreign">Szygium jambos</em> and <em class="foreign">Szygium cumini</em>, and it has commonly been rendered “rose apple,” although “black plum” may be a less misleading term. Among various explanations given for the continent being so named, one (in the <cite class="title break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">Abhidharmakośa</cite>) is that a jambu tree grows in its northern mountains beside Lake Anavatapta, mythically considered the source of the four great rivers of India, and that the continent is therefore named from the tree or the fruit. Jambudvīpa has the Vajrāsana at its center and is the only continent upon which buddhas attain awakening.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="6077e6cb-cd7f-4fbb-bfc4-036f45f6b973" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ljd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.717</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Jambudvīpa Garland</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’dzam bu’i gling gi phreng ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འཛམ་བུའི་གླིང་གི་ཕྲེང་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">An island to the north of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="40f7b47a-f44f-4de1-96d6-df7de8d1da3c" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ljl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.718</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Janaka</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">skyed pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྐྱེད་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">janaka</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A virtuous <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8562">nāga</span> king.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="0ba0b573-2b87-4a8d-a4da-5b6c1aa1bdff" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ljt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.719</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Jewel Forest</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">nor bu’i nags, rin po che’i nags</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ནོར་བུའི་ནགས།, རིན་པོ་ཆེའི་ནགས།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">(1) A forest in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9059">Endowed with Migration</span> (<em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">nor bu’i nags</em>). (2) A forest on the upper level of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9417">Living on the Peak</span> (<em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">rin po che’i nags</em>).</p></div></div></div></div><div id="49be8436-77b6-4bb9-8379-0ded3d7d9a9f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_lk55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.720</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Jewel Friends</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rin po che’i grogs po</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རིན་པོ་ཆེའི་གྲོགས་པོ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain between <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9398">Kuru</span> and <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9209">Godānīya</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="035c5f97-378f-4fe2-9ec9-eb11f786c767" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_lkd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.721</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Jewel Platforms</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">nor bu’i stegs bu</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ནོར་བུའི་སྟེགས་བུ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A lake in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9796">Total Pleasure</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="90227339-1134-4473-8766-f0bf92510cf2" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_lkl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.722</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Jewel Rocks</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rin po che’i rdo ba dang ldan pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རིན་པོ་ཆེའི་རྡོ་བ་དང་ལྡན་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">An island in the vicinity of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="0bf6bced-4856-452e-b3f1-08094fd39ae0" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_lkt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.723</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Jewel Shore</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rin po che’i ’gram</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རིན་པོ་ཆེའི་འགྲམ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9753">Supreme Strength</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="dc7ba6e6-0ba6-47d3-bbab-3426dbad021f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ll55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.724</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">jewel summit</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ri’i gtsug na nor bu</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རིའི་གཙུག་ན་ནོར་བུ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A bird in the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9266">Heaven Free from Strife</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="a8eabd6c-a047-4ea5-8a8e-feefd72644b8" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_lld5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.725</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Jewel-Water Keeper</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">nor bu’i chu can rnams kyis ’dzin pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ནོར་བུའི་ཆུ་ཅན་རྣམས་ཀྱིས་འཛིན་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9657">Saṅkāśa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="58644a1c-c015-40cc-9b0c-b6b01b294b81" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_lll5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.726</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Joy of the Vidyādharas</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rig pa ’dzin pa dga’ ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རིག་པ་འཛིན་པ་དགའ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A lake on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9078">Equal Peaks</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="c7e1a615-dcde-4518-9fb0-4cc7f559843c" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_llt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.727</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Joyful Garland</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dgod phreng</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དགོད་ཕྲེང་།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A peak on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9739">Sumeru</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="eed6d421-7ed3-4e0c-8763-7237f8f03520" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_lm55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.728</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Joyful Gods</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">lha rnams dga’ ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ལྷ་རྣམས་དགའ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A pond in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8956">Continuous Movement</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="51f99672-f56e-462b-974c-b922384423a9" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_lmd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.729</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Joyless Thought</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bsam pa dga’ med</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བསམ་པ་དགའ་མེད།</span></li><li class="italic">ānandanirāśa</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of sixteen realms that surround the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9235">Great Howling Hell</span>. Alternatively referred to as <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9534">No Hope of Joy</span> (<em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">kun dga’ la re ba med pa</em>) in the Tibetan text.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="20076dd2-1891-4fd9-b165-0e50cf89d013" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_lml5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.730</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Joyous</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rab tu spro ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རབ་ཏུ་སྤྲོ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A virtuous <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8562">nāga</span> king.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="62c28d7d-210a-41d5-b188-364bf708326f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_lmt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.731</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Joyous</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">kun dga’</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀུན་དགའ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest at <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9734">Sudharma</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="105c34c2-c0b2-4f4f-a0b2-6d7b7ca9bb63" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ln55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.732</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Joyous Birds</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bya rnam par dga’ ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བྱ་རྣམ་པར་དགའ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">(1) A forest in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8956">Continuous Movement</span> (<em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">bya rnam par dga’ ba</em>). (2) A pond in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8956">Continuous Movement</span> (<em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">bya mngon par dga’ ba</em>).</p></div></div></div></div><div id="065ed27d-7c7f-4b97-a338-eb1d68180e48" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_lnd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.733</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Joyous Birdsong</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bya’i sgra mngon par dga’ ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བྱའི་སྒྲ་མངོན་པར་དགའ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A part of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9153">Forest of Joy</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="c1e05e57-26da-4517-93ba-c67be6fb7329" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_lnl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.734</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Joyous Flow</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dga’ bar ’bab pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དགའ་བར་འབབ་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river in the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9764">Swan Forest</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="f6af9959-1063-47a7-a1f4-cd81b6a0bf32" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_lnt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.735</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Joyous Forest</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">kun dga’ ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀུན་དགའ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8989">Deer Abode</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="2a9f7cf6-8f17-4b12-86ac-a96ad2f1b027" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_lo55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.736</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Joyous Garland of Jambu Gold</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rab tu dga’ ba’i ’dzam bu’i phreng ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རབ་ཏུ་དགའ་བའི་འཛམ་བུའི་ཕྲེང་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8529">gandharva</span> colony on Mount <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9659">Sāra</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="206724d3-b509-43d7-bef4-8de9ecfcb300" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_lod5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.737</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Joyous Gods</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">lha dga’ ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ལྷ་དགའ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A lake on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9078">Equal Peaks</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="3afac35d-397e-48d7-86c0-9345117268f3" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_lol5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.738</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Joyous Grove</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dga’ ba’i tshal</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དགའ་བའི་ཚལ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest on the southern face of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9739">Sumeru</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="be8d0823-100a-4831-948a-32e881d3aa11" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_lot5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.739</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Joyous Higher Realms</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mtho ris dga’ ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མཐོ་རིས་དགའ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river that flows between the two <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8811">Anūna</span> mountains.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="0f9e1668-f2d1-4f5c-a572-53e640f4af97" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_lp55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.740</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Joyous Imagination</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">kun brtags par dga’ ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀུན་བརྟགས་པར་དགའ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">Alternative name of the lake <span><span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9095">Expansive</span></span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="a492b88c-6bf8-4f48-b059-343baf16aa8b" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_lpd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.741</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Joyous in All Regards</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mngon dga’</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མངོན་དགའ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9035">Dwelling on Summits</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="c5d56649-a18a-4b71-a967-26b828479368" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_lpl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.742</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Joyous Magnetizer of All</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dbang du ma gyur pa ma yin pas yid mngon par dga’ ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དབང་དུ་མ་གྱུར་པ་མ་ཡིན་པས་ཡིད་མངོན་པར་དགའ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A ruler of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9266">Heaven Free from Strife</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="10a677b9-bd80-44d1-a930-5856a6ba0f1d" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_lpt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.743</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Joyous Mountain</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dga’i ba’i ri’i nags</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དགའི་བའི་རིའི་ནགས།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9823">Upward Ocean</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="5ede84f5-63b5-476c-84f9-345a89c26b35" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_lq55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.744</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Joyous Movement</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dga’ bas ’jug pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དགའ་བས་འཇུག་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9657">Saṅkāśa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="6a4e70ff-0c92-4d43-a2c0-c9f64907e530" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_lqd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.745</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Joyous Nāga Girls</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">klu’i bu mo mngon par dga’ ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀླུའི་བུ་མོ་མངོན་པར་དགའ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9657">Saṅkāśa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="9682da9c-c109-42bf-bef9-e5cd8b24f176" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_lql5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.746</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Joyous Play</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rtsed mo dga’ ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྩེད་མོ་དགའ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9260">Heap in the Stream</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="09c9df51-4840-472d-a298-0e071e5327a3" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_lqt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.747</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Joyous Smoke</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">du ba dga’ ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དུ་བ་དགའ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9142">Forest Garlands</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="47224e15-d2b4-4540-9668-fa24384c41c6" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_lr55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.748</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Joyous Summit Visitor</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rtse mo la ’jug par dga’ ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྩེ་མོ་ལ་འཇུག་པར་དགའ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9657">Saṅkāśa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="b00a2e90-56b8-479b-ac0a-d15e51e10f48" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_lrd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.749</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Joyous to Behold</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mthong na dga’ ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མཐོང་ན་དགའ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">Pools that surround the summit of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8801">All Worlds</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="fdfab364-9489-4c85-8e52-b51a0eace7d4" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_lrl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.750</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Joyous Women</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bud med dga’ ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བུད་མེད་དགའ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest at <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9734">Sudharma</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="76286c0f-e42e-4bd4-9436-f801c188ac79" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_lrt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.751</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Just Like Milk</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’o ma dang mtshungs par ’jug pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འོ་མ་དང་མཚུངས་པར་འཇུག་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A land to the north of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="866a919d-a29b-48d9-8ff8-6025e75fa61d" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ls55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.752</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Kāberi</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">kA be ri</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀཱ་བེ་རི།</span></li><li class="italic">kāberi</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river in the south of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="c972a212-bf0c-4b7f-a676-ff895121ec1b" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_lsd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.753</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Kābīra</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">kA bI ra</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀཱ་བཱི་ར།</span></li><li class="italic">kābīra</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9601">Promotion</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="5106fa70-e112-49e1-8c8d-c969266d6d77" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_lsl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.754</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Kailāśa</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ti se</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཏི་སེ།</span></li><li class="italic">kailāśa</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain in the north of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="cda6967c-d0f6-49c1-9a61-ddc6004ccb90" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_lst5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.755</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Kailāśa Horn</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ti se’i rwa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཏི་སེའི་རྭ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain north of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="f2457bfd-2bfc-40be-b0f7-038cbb56cb20" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_lt55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.756</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Kāla</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">nag po</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ནག་པོ།</span></li><li class="italic">kāla</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">An unvirtuous <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8562">nāga</span> king.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="3e9f5fb3-f861-4757-aac5-848d744cf086" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ltd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.757</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Kālaka</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">kA la ko</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀཱ་ལ་ཀོ</span></li><li class="italic">kālaka</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">An island in the sea west of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="7efaaf8e-0744-4ca0-b258-48fa13dc0ad0" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ltl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.758</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">kālakūṭa</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">kA la ku Ta</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀཱ་ལ་ཀུ་ཊ།</span></li><li class="italic">kālakūṭa</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A deadly poison that originated when the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8531">gods</span> and <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8489">asuras</span> churned the oceans to create the nectar of immortality.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="8b09a86f-030e-48b6-a2f7-32387be173f8" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ltt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.759</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Kamboja</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">kam po dzI</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀམ་པོ་ཛཱི།</span></li><li class="italic">kamboja</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A land to the north of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>, corresponding to the northern Afghanistan</p></div></div></div></div><div id="22ed69b2-7e51-4f3d-a4a9-e61d967dfd3c" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_lu55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.760</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Kanakamuni</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gser thub</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གསེར་ཐུབ།</span></li><li class="italic">kanakamuni</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">The name of a previous buddha.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="9f5ca546-6149-44fb-8ac3-81d8067885b3" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_lud5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.761</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Kaṇṭhamāla</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mgul phreng</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མགུལ་ཕྲེང་།</span></li><li class="italic">kaṇṭhamāla</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">King of the “<span><span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8564">necklaces</span></span>” (a class of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8489">asuras</span>).</p></div></div></div></div><div id="3f828789-569b-475e-936d-f593aa04c57d" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_lul5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.762</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">karada</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ka ra da</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀ་ར་ད།</span></li><li class="italic">karada</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A bird of a red color whose voice has been described as like thunder or the sound of a drum.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="2b16e93c-570a-49f0-a0a9-2fcd483b50e3" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_lut5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.763</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">karketana</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ke ke ru</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀེ་ཀེ་རུ།</span></li><li class="italic">karketana</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A stone sometimes identified as cat’s eye.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="44394edb-98b3-4e82-b0d6-d9fa66ff4226" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_lv55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.764</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Karmapa III, Rangjung Dorjé</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rang ’byung rdo rje</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རང་འབྱུང་རྡོ་རྗེ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">(1284–1339). An important master in the Karma Kagyu lineage of Tibetan Buddhism (<em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">karma bka’ brgyud</em>). He is considered the third master in the lineage to have the title of Karmapa.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="5cb1014d-c618-472e-928d-0be854478200" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_lvd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.765</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">karmic actions to be experienced in other lives</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">lan grangs gzhan la myong bar ’gyur ba’i las</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ལན་གྲངས་གཞན་ལ་མྱོང་བར་འགྱུར་བའི་ལས།</span></li><li class="italic">apara­paryāya­vedanīya</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of the three types of karma whose results are experience neither in the present nor the next, but the subsequent lives. The other two types are the “karma that ripens in this life” (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">dṛṣṭa­dharma­vipāka</em> or <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">dṛṣṭa­dharma­vedanīya</em>) and the “karma that is to be experienced in the immediately following life” (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">upapadya­vedanīya</em>).</p></div></div></div></div><div id="9dbb7f4f-7b7f-4173-a879-c90f7203c679" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_lvl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.766</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Karṇika</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">kar+N+Ni ka</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀརྞྞི་ཀ</span></li><li class="italic">karṇika</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A land in the east of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="39e256f1-6af9-440b-b3f5-91d28a413331" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_lvt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.767</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">kāsa</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ka sa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀ་ས།</span></li><li class="italic">kāsa</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">The grass <em class="foreign">Saccharum spontaneum</em>, native to Indian subcontinent.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="16af352f-99c6-4b59-bb18-15e65eee3728" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_m055anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.768</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Kāśī</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">kA shi, ka shi, ka shi ka</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀ་ཤི་ཀ, ཀ་ཤི།, ཀཱ་ཤི།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">Ancient name for <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-10019">Vārāṇasī</span>, the holy city on the banks of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9182">Gaṅgā</span>, this name can be applied also to the surrounding country or district. It lies in modern day Uttar Pradesh, India.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="a7964590-bdae-4ad7-9f3a-29bf9f4c739d" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_m0d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.769</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Kāśyapa</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’od srung</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འོད་སྲུང་།</span></li><li class="italic">kāśyapa</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A previous buddha.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="cc862b30-e334-4f17-a19f-cc1988720588" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_m0l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.770</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Kaṭuka</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ka Tu ka</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀ་ཊུ་ཀ</span></li><li class="italic">kaṭuka</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A land to the north of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="08802354-443b-48ab-aad8-39eae60f5ae5" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_m0t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.771</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Kauśika</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">kau shi ka</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀཽ་ཤི་ཀ</span></li><li class="italic">kauśika</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p>“One who belongs to the Kuśika lineage.” An epithet of the god Śakra, also known as Indra, the king of the gods in the Trāyastriṃśa heaven. In the Ṛgveda, Indra is addressed by the epithet Kauśika, with the implication that he is associated with the descendants of the Kuśika lineage (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">gotra</em>) as their aiding deity. In later epic and Purāṇic texts, we find the story that Indra took birth as Gādhi Kauśika, the son of Kuśika and one of the Vedic poet-seers, after the Puru king Kuśika had performed austerities for one thousand years to obtain a son equal to Indra who could not be killed by others. In the Pāli <cite class="title break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">Kusajātaka</cite> (Jāt V 141–45), the Buddha, in one of his former bodhisattva lives as a Trāyastriṃśa god, takes birth as the future king Kusa upon the request of Indra, who wishes to help the childless king of the Mallas, Okkaka, and his chief queen Sīlavatī. This story is also referred to by Nāgasena in the <cite class="title break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">Milindapañha</cite>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="76003ac3-63be-4327-a186-11ef40e44ce2" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_m155anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.772</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Kauśika</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">kau shi ka</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀཽ་ཤི་ཀ</span></li><li class="italic">kauśika</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">(1) A river in the east of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>. (2) A river in the ephemeral hell known as <span><span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9619">Red</span></span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="9e163b3f-fe78-471e-9e97-fa87f44ca9ca" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_m1d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.773</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Kauśikama</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">kau shi ka ma</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀཽ་ཤི་ཀ་མ།</span></li><li class="italic">kauśikama</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9085">Excellence of Exquisite Intelligence</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="bd459fdd-0416-4a33-b86c-c59237f07f5b" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_m1l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.774</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Kāverī</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">kA be rI</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀཱ་བེ་རཱི།</span></li><li class="italic">kāverī</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="1a7a86ce-09af-4399-92d2-251a02233de0" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_m1t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.775</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Kekāpino</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ke kA pi no</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀེ་ཀཱ་པི་ནོ།</span></li><li class="italic">kekāpino</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A land to the west of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="a6a62b65-59ca-4366-9bac-616d6232a41a" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_m255anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.776</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Ketaka</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ke ta ka</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀེ་ཏ་ཀ</span></li><li class="italic">ketaka</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">An island in the vicinity of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="2dc1ae81-1288-41cf-a92d-4c7064ba81a8" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_m2d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.777</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Ketaka Fragrance</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ke ta ka’i dris bsgos pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀེ་ཏ་ཀའི་དྲིས་བསྒོས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">ketaka</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9657">Saṅkāśa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="a261dbab-fb40-488d-b5a2-4d35f5df825d" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_m2l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.778</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Ketako</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ke ta ko</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀེ་ཏ་ཀོ</span></li><li class="italic">ketako</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A land in the south of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="2e61277c-5f01-48fd-8e84-577b4f0a222d" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_m2t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.779</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Ketu</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mjug rings</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མཇུག་རིངས།</span></li><li class="italic">ketu</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One among the nine heavenly bodies.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="5db60fb5-cbc1-48df-987b-d829d3546b01" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_m355anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.780</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Khārā</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">khA rA</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཁཱ་རཱ།</span></li><li class="italic">khārā</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A land to the north of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="765a595f-12c6-4f20-9dfc-8c1d9d2bb9b2" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_m3d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.781</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">killing</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">srog gcod pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྲོག་གཅོད་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">prāṇātipāta</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">The first among the three physical misdeeds.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="896e3c80-1174-4998-af8b-15c8fb938189" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_m3l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.782</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">kimpāka</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">kim pa ka</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀིམ་པ་ཀ</span></li><li class="italic">kimpāka</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A fruit that is attractive to behold and has a delicious taste, but is poisonous when eaten.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="3041df5b-bafd-45ed-a138-aeea6bf86668" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_m3t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.783</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">kiṃśuka</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">keng shu ka, king shu ka</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀིང་ཤུ་ཀ, ཀེང་ཤུ་ཀ</span></li><li class="italic">kiṃśuka</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition"><em class="foreign">Butea frondosa</em>, also known as flame of the forest; a tree with bright red flowers.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="6e06763e-0df8-40f7-ab9d-ff79e8ce0ab6" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_m455anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.784</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Kinkikirāta</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">kin+ki ki rA tA</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀིནྐི་ཀི་རཱ་ཏཱ།</span></li><li class="italic">kinkikirāta</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A barbaric people in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="f2532450-2fb0-46a0-ad02-7f0c7d162e13" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_m4d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.785</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">kinnara</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mi’am ci</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མིའམ་ཅི།</span></li><li class="italic">kinnara</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p>A class of nonhuman beings that resemble humans to the degree that their very name‍—which means “is that human?”‍—suggests some confusion as to their divine status. Kinnaras are mythological beings found in both Buddhist and Brahmanical literature, where they are portrayed as creatures half human, half animal. They are often depicted as highly skilled celestial musicians.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="4aed9612-012e-4aa5-848e-14c3895573a4" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_m4l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.786</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Kokālika</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ko ka li ka</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀོ་ཀ་ལི་ཀ</span></li><li class="italic">kokālika</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A monk who joined <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8655">Devadatta</span>’s plot against the Buddha.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="9b7db420-9bc9-4913-8b5c-41c9b8bcc5a0" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_m4t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.787</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Koraṇḍo</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ko raN+Do</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀོ་རཎྜོ།</span></li><li class="italic">koraṇḍo</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A land in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9209">Godānīya</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="005deba6-ec56-493e-a560-12cf132cc4c4" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_m555anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.788</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Kosala</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">kau sha la, ko sa la</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀོ་ས་ལ།, ཀཽ་ཤ་ལ།</span></li><li class="italic">kosala, kośala</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">An ancient kingdom, northwest of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9441">Magadha</span>, abutting Kāśi, whose capital was Śrāvastī. During the Buddha’s time it was ruled by King Prasenajit.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="80ce0e64-27ed-416d-9821-d0733cf76d3c" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_m5d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.789</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Kośalā</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ko sha lA</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀོ་ཤ་ལཱ།</span></li><li class="italic">kośalā</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river in the east of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="49216566-97a4-4065-8cef-61e41a7ddc0e" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_m5l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.790</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Kourava, Kuru</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ko’u ra ba, sgra mi snyan</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀོའུ་ར་བ།, སྒྲ་མི་སྙན།</span></li><li class="italic">kourava, kuru</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A land in the east of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="b3717cc9-12bc-4b61-964a-1e6e73962aae" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_m5t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.791</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Kourava, Kuru</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ko’u ra ba, sgra mi snyan</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀོའུ་ར་བ།, སྒྲ་མི་སྙན།</span></li><li class="italic">kourava, kuru</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">(1) The continent to the north of Mount <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9739">Sumeru</span>. (2) A land to the north of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="095dcda0-40d2-4f26-a3af-0dd3c4348593" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_m655anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.792</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Kouṭubha</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">kau Tub+haH</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀཽ་ཊུབྷཿ།</span></li><li class="italic">kouṭubha</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A lake on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9078">Equal Peaks</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="2ffeb775-acbb-4487-b368-d6acde810828" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_m6d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.793</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Krakucchanda</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’khor ba ’jig</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འཁོར་བ་འཇིག</span></li><li class="italic">krakucchanda</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">The first buddha of the Fortunate Eon (our current eon).</p></div></div></div></div><div id="47334c46-7c4f-41af-92d0-c2e610451a2f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_m6l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.794</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">kṣatriya</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rgyal rigs</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྒྱལ་རིགས།</span></li><li class="italic">kṣatriya</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p>The ruling caste in the traditional four-caste hierarchy of India, associated with warriors, the aristocracy, and kings.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="e280c857-4bb7-44c1-affe-be4c6b2ae1b9" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_m6t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.795</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Kṣoṇo</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">Sho No</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཥོ་ཎོ།</span></li><li class="italic">kṣoṇo</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="96580f3b-7f7f-458e-ae1d-ddfc26ce5bc0" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_m755anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.796</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Kubala Grove</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ku ba la’i tshal</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀུ་བ་ལའི་ཚལ།</span></li><li class="italic">kubala</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A grove in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9601">Promotion</span></p></div></div></div></div><div id="27ebaa2f-c880-40dd-b99a-3df1ffaf6c54" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_m7d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.797</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Kubera</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ku be ra</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀུ་བེ་ར།</span></li><li class="italic">kubera</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">Also known as Vaiśravaṇa. One among the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8526">Four Great Kings</span>, guardian of the north.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="64552daf-e76a-4dfb-b696-89fd3823c422" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_m7l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.798</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Kukkuṭācīra</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">kuk+ku TA tsI ra</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀུཀྐུ་ཊཱ་ཙཱི་ར།</span></li><li class="italic">kukkuṭācīra</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9142">Forest Garlands</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="ccede45f-433c-4fc9-a193-04b848759a56" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_m7t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.799</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Kulakā</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ku la kA</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀུ་ལ་ཀཱ།</span></li><li class="italic">kulakā</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8581">rākṣasī</span> living in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9613">Ramayo</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="38d41952-812d-4b63-9936-637e5df335af" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_m855anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.800</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Kumāra</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gzhon nu</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གཞོན་ནུ།</span></li><li class="italic">kumāra</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">Another name for the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8531">god</span> Skandha.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="1e2966da-80fb-4f8b-96c9-0d1c17655cda" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_m8d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.801</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">kumbhāṇḍa</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">grul bum</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གྲུལ་བུམ།</span></li><li class="italic">kumbhāṇḍa</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">Dwarf-like beings.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="5bcaee0a-5adc-4e91-93bb-8d6cdb3c080b" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_m8l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.802</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Kumuda Flowers</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">me tog ku mu da</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མེ་ཏོག་ཀུ་མུ་ད།</span></li><li class="italic">kumuda</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9035">Dwelling on Summits</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="e0ae589a-9f1d-4a7a-97d9-705f42cddbd1" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_m8t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.803</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Kuṇḍalin</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’khyil pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འཁྱིལ་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">kuṇḍalin</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A virtuous <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8562">nāga</span> king.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="b0b45858-c7c1-49e5-a12b-8859649a4f47" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_m955anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.804</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Kuñjaro</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">kuny+dza ro</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀུཉྫ་རོ།</span></li><li class="italic">kuñjaro</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain in the sea south of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="dc2764e0-1718-45b7-a355-08d92162cd41" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_m9d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.805</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">kuśika</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ku shi kA</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀུ་ཤི་ཀཱ།</span></li><li class="italic">kuśika</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A class of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8622">vidyādharas</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="86d5b9d6-a912-4d8b-89a8-d40147f1ad5d" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_m9l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.806</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Land of Kuṭa Fruits</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ku Ta’i ’bras bu pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀུ་ཊའི་འབྲས་བུ་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A land to the north of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="5c2e8a8b-b315-4868-9cf4-2b9ecff06851" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_m9t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.807</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Land of No Mercy</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">snying rje med pa’i sa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྙིང་རྗེ་མེད་པའི་ས།</span></li><li class="italic">nirdayabhūmi</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A realm that neighbors the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9278">Hell of Intense Heat</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="44ba2510-8dd6-440d-a931-20af5d436734" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ma55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.808</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Land of the Good</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bzang po pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བཟང་པོ་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A land to the north of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="8a96e7ef-b641-4f85-a34c-232afdb56f19" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mad5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.809</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Laṅkapuri Rākṣasas</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">lang ka’i grong khyer na nges par gnas pa’i srin po</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ལང་ཀའི་གྲོང་ཁྱེར་ན་ངེས་པར་གནས་པའི་སྲིན་པོ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">An island in the vicinity of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="bd0bdcfa-1c67-4fcf-932a-0998fafc9575" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mal5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.810</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Lateral</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mtha’ la gnas pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མཐའ་ལ་གནས་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A realm inhabited by <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8530">garland-bearer gods</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="692068af-1a15-4a01-b04d-632a2c9103bf" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mat5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.811</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Life Isochronous with Death</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">srog ’chi ba dang bcas pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྲོག་འཆི་བ་དང་བཅས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">samṛtyujīvita</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of sixteen realms that surround the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9235">Great Howling Hell</span>. Alternatively referred to as <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9322">Instant Revival Upon Death</span> (<em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">shi ma thag tu ’tsho ba</em>) in the Tibetan text.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="e3f97620-0fcd-42dd-961a-bb267558e584" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mb55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.812</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Light Ray Peak</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’od zer gyis rtse mo</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འོད་ཟེར་གྱིས་རྩེ་མོ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest on the lower level of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9417">Living on the Peak</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="49b4ef56-6ef5-4922-b8ee-132168668795" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mbd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.813</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Light Rays of Joy</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’od zer mngon par dga’ ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འོད་ཟེར་མངོན་པར་དགའ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9796">Total Pleasure</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="bc5624e6-a362-49b1-bf5a-904698979f5e" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mbl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.814</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Light Rays of the Forest</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">nags tshal ’od zer</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ནགས་ཚལ་འོད་ཟེར།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of the twenty-seven realms in the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9266">Heaven Free from Strife</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="a89f35aa-0b57-4b8e-a490-da1298f11b9a" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mbt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.815</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">lightning wielder</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">glog ’khyug par byed pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གློག་འཁྱུག་པར་བྱེད་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A class of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8622">vidyādharas</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="297220bc-dc7d-4fb6-9966-e4bb537de4da" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mc55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.816</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Like Stacks of Dry Wood</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">shing skam bsdus pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཤིང་སྐམ་བསྡུས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">dārusaṃvartaka</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A realm that neighbors the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9278">Hell of Intense Heat</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="eacc1865-d8a6-48f8-8898-7903049f2721" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mcd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.817</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Like Unopened Flowers</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">me tog kha ma bye ba lta bu</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མེ་ཏོག་ཁ་མ་བྱེ་བ་ལྟ་བུ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of sixteen realms that surround the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9279">Hell of Ultimate Torment</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="e98fa054-af96-490f-ad83-3b93938e8bdc" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mcl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.818</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Limited Light</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’od chung</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འོད་ཆུང་།</span></li><li class="italic">parīttābha</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">The lowest level of the form realm’s second <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9969">concentration</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="bccbcc58-dd2e-4953-b058-4fc10bc02a54" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mct5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.819</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Limitless Flow</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mtha’ med ’bab</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མཐའ་མེད་འབབ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9000">Delighting in Flower Garlands</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="7ae0ebe8-8f7c-46c9-a27f-967bc0f225d8" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_md55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.820</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Limitless Light</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">tshad med ’od</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཚད་མེད་འོད།</span></li><li class="italic">apramāṇābhā</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">The second level within the form realm’s second <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9969">concentration</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="9066537a-492a-4a0f-b7bb-79ac1bddcede" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mdd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.821</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Living by Rājanina</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rA dza ni na rgyu ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རཱ་ཛ་ནི་ན་རྒྱུ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of the twenty-seven realms of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9266">Heaven Free from Strife</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="9fced6de-6e6a-45d3-a2ad-a83a4c6db0ba" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mdl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.822</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Living in Forests and Parks</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">tshal dang nye ba’i tshal na gnas pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཚལ་དང་ཉེ་བའི་ཚལ་ན་གནས་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A realm inhabited by <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8530">garland-bearer gods</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="c3feaa3c-fbab-4c43-94d9-69652d10eb06" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mdt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.823</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Living in Kuttāṃgati</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">kuD+TAM ga ti na gnas pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀུཌྚཱཾ་ག་ཏི་ན་གནས་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">An area in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9398">Kuru</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="1830193e-268b-4152-abc9-5f61d5ebf7ad" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_me55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.824</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Living in Mountain Ranges</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ri’i klung na kun tu spyod pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རིའི་ཀླུང་ན་ཀུན་ཏུ་སྤྱོད་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">An area in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9398">Kuru</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="e20096e6-c6ec-4e81-bac0-b155eb12c5b5" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_med5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.825</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Living on the Peak</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">brtsegs pa rgyu ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བརྩེགས་པ་རྒྱུ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of the twenty-seven realms of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9266">Heaven Free from Strife</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="ec4ac521-3fcf-422e-a3f5-b54213547acd" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mel5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.826</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Lofty Abode</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mtho bar gnas</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མཐོ་བར་གནས།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A realm of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8516">ever-infatuated gods</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="9e54b2c0-cdf2-483d-a375-7835c8319761" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_met5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.827</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Lofty Heaps of Silver</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dngul mthon por brtsegs pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དངུལ་མཐོན་པོར་བརྩེགས་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9771">Tamer of Deer Enemies</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="b26bf7c7-09c3-4606-8e0d-0b0949e5aa81" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mf55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.828</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Lofty Mound</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mtho brtsegs</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མཐོ་བརྩེགས།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">(1) A peak upon Mount <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9739">Sumeru</span>. (2) A mountain in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9197">Garland of Splendor</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="22ee3722-232e-40c6-b432-9abead7c7975" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mfd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.829</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Lofty Peak</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mtho bar brtsegs pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མཐོ་བར་བརྩེགས་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest on the lower level of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9417">Living on the Peak</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="c3dd3c44-d6e7-49e9-bf2b-d43286b55433" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mfl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.830</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Lofty Summit</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mtho bar brtsegs pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མཐོ་བར་བརྩེགས་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9398">Kuru</span>. Also known as Covered by Lotuses (<em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">pad ma dmar pos kun tu khyab pa</em>).</p></div></div></div></div><div id="74b4a35d-810e-4fc9-874e-ce26aa48f87a" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mft5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.831</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Long</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ring pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རིང་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9657">Saṅkāśa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="d73db578-8b2b-4c51-8a01-1940b3a05afe" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mg55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.832</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Long-Lasting Agony</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">tshor ba ring ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཚོར་བ་རིང་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">pratāntavedana</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of sixteen realms that surround the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9235">Great Howling Hell</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="6afba4f5-27d7-4d13-8f35-09c9709ed4c7" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mgd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.833</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Longing for Smell</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’dri ’dod</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འདྲི་འདོད།</span></li><li class="italic">gandhakambala</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of sixteen realms that surround the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9279">Hell of Ultimate Torment</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="a3b4cd95-dbc3-4f96-9202-7508acf469d1" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mgl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.834</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Lord of Death</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gshin rje, ’chi bdag</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གཤིན་རྗེ།, འཆི་བདག</span></li><li class="italic">yama</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">Ruler of the hells.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="411a4a60-0d8e-46f3-a763-7edc09d98191" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mgt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.835</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Lotus Pool of Sparkling Waters</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rnam par bkra ba’i chu’i pad ma’i rdzing bu</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྣམ་པར་བཀྲ་བའི་ཆུའི་པད་མའི་རྫིང་བུ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9796">Total Pleasure</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="0dd24075-e659-4d61-935e-0cb149451b7f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mh55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.836</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Lotuses Resembling Sunlight</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">pad ma’i nyi ma’i ’od lta bu</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">པད་མའི་ཉི་མའི་འོད་ལྟ་བུ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A lotus pond in the forest known as <span><span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9310">Incomparable</span></span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="bcafb8a2-0ae8-44db-8fec-8e7844f03fe2" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mhd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.837</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Lovely</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">yid ’ong</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཡིད་འོང་།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9066">Engaging in Clarification</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="39535a7e-3301-49a8-a129-6c01446290b7" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mhl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.838</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Lovely Girl</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bud med sdug</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བུད་མེད་སྡུག</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A lotus pool in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9403">Lateral</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="1e24936e-5f72-435b-9ef2-acdbc05e684e" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mht5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.839</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Lovely Pleasure Garden</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">skyed mos tshal dga’</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྐྱེད་མོས་ཚལ་དགའ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8489">asuras</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="1db96a05-0d09-4bf4-9520-985079d215dc" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mi55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.840</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Lovely Scent</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">spos kun ldan</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྤོས་ཀུན་ལྡན།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A queen of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8731">Rāhu</span>, king of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8489">asuras</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="e73e65d2-449a-49de-b09a-fb58c393db23" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mid5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.841</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Lovely Voice</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">skad kyi dbyangs can</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྐད་ཀྱི་དབྱངས་ཅན།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9657">Saṅkāśa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="88d3321b-b29c-4272-87f1-3d9064d10639" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mil5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.842</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Low River</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dma’ ba’i chu</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དམའ་བའི་ཆུ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9657">Saṅkāśa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="6342377a-11e1-4705-a933-e63be56e45cd" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mit5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.843</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Luminosity</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’od gsal ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འོད་གསལ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9025">Dwelling in Excellent View</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="714e9c50-24c8-400e-b6ec-2299b4ba0c8d" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mj55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.844</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Luminosity</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’od gsal</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འོད་གསལ།</span></li><li class="italic">ābhāsvara</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">The uppermost level of the second <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9969">concentration</span> in the form realm.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="abb2e06b-b025-44cc-9750-f81139e65e45" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mjd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.845</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Luminous</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rab tu gsal ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རབ་ཏུ་གསལ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A previous ruler of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9276">Heaven of the Thirty-Three</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="2c0da599-6fbd-479a-8100-e1d23a72c420" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mjl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.846</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Luminous Formation</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rab chags gsal</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རབ་ཆགས་གསལ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of the seven golden mountains that surround Mount <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9739">Sumeru</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="f9b07d1c-4266-4b61-ac24-824463e5f6ec" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mjt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.847</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Luminous Jewels</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rin po che ’od ’byin</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རིན་པོ་ཆེ་འོད་འབྱིན།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9606">Radiant Streams</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="9d9ddb6c-fc25-472b-8d22-bd6defd1b514" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mk55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.848</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">lying</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rdzun du smra ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྫུན་དུ་སྨྲ་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">mṛṣā­vāda</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">The first among the four verbal misdeeds.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="23211661-2eca-4827-b6a7-6a7af55f7c02" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mkd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.849</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Madrā</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ma drA</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མ་དྲཱ།</span></li><li class="italic">madrā</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A land in the south of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="cf08ee1f-e77c-4a13-b08a-f040e67b81fb" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mkl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.850</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Madtakaṭama</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mad ta ka Ta ma</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མད་ཏ་ཀ་ཊ་མ།</span></li><li class="italic">madtakaṭama</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A peak upon Mount <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9739">Sumeru</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="6009bd60-d95a-407a-a59e-f556ec44614f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mkt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.851</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Magadha</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ma ga dhA</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མ་ག་དྷཱ།</span></li><li class="italic">magadha</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p>An ancient Indian kingdom that lay to the south of the Ganges River in what today is the state of Bihar. Magadha was the largest of the sixteen “great states” (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">mahājanapada</em>) that flourished between the sixth and third centuries <span class="small-caps">ʙᴄᴇ</span> in northern India. During the life of the Buddha Śākyamuni, it was ruled by King Bimbisāra and later by Bimbisāra's son, Ajātaśatru. Its capital was initially Rājagṛha (modern-day Rajgir) but was later moved to Pāṭaliputra (modern-day Patna). Over the centuries, with the expansion of the Magadha’s might, it became the capital of the vast Mauryan empire and seat of the great King Aśoka.</p><p>This region is home to many of the most important Buddhist sites, including Bodh Gayā, where the Buddha attained awakening; Vulture Peak (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">Gṛdhra­kūṭa</em>), where the Buddha bestowed many well-known Mahāyāna sūtras; and the Buddhist university of Nālandā that flourished between the fifth and twelfth centuries <span class="small-caps">ᴄᴇ</span>, among many others.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="69f474dd-b4c3-4a71-8bfd-c3d90d47c194" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ml55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.852</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Mahādeva</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">lha chen po</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ལྷ་ཆེན་པོ།</span></li><li class="italic">mahādeva</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">An epithet of Śiva.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="d77643b2-2f79-4c1c-ab03-9941e6dee0f3" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mld5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.853</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Maheśvara, Īśvara</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dbang phyug, dbang phyug chen po</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དབང་ཕྱུག, དབང་ཕྱུག་ཆེན་པོ།</span></li><li class="italic">maheśvara, īśvara</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">Literally “lord,” this term is an epithet for the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8531">god</span> Śiva, but functions more generally in Buddhist texts as a generalized “supreme being” to whom the creation of the universe is attributed.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="492db183-b469-4056-a2c7-840f2a3b8e1d" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mll5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.854</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Maheśvara, Īśvara</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dbang phyug, dbang phyug chen po</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དབང་ཕྱུག, དབང་ཕྱུག་ཆེན་པོ།</span></li><li class="italic">maheśvara, īśvara</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">Another name for the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8531">god</span> Śiva.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="0b1f57e7-ea4c-4276-9feb-ac5f4be0c6aa" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mlt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.855</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Mahikṣikā</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ma hi ShI kA</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མ་ཧི་ཥཱི་ཀཱ།</span></li><li class="italic">mahikṣikā</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A land to the north of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="1e7a4db5-55f0-4aa5-9687-a6dc58721575" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mm55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.856</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">mahoraga</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">lto ’phye chen po</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ལྟོ་འཕྱེ་ཆེན་པོ།</span></li><li class="italic">mahoraga</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p>Literally “great serpents,” mahoragas are supernatural beings depicted as large, subterranean beings with human torsos and heads and the lower bodies of serpents. Their movements are said to cause earthquakes, and they make up a class of subterranean geomantic spirits whose movement through the seasons and months of the year is deemed significant for construction projects.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="478983bd-1f03-4a1a-a6e0-c5bb1bc8582e" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mmd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.857</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Maitreya</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">byams pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བྱམས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">maitreya</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p>The bodhisattva Maitreya is an important figure in many Buddhist traditions, where he is unanimously regarded as the buddha of the future era. He is said to currently reside in the heaven of Tuṣita, as Śākyamuni’s regent, where he awaits the proper time to take his final rebirth and become the fifth buddha in the Fortunate Eon, reestablishing the Dharma in this world after the teachings of the current buddha have disappeared. Within the Mahāyāna sūtras, Maitreya is elevated to the same status as other central bodhisattvas such as Mañjuśrī and Avalokiteśvara, and his name appears frequently in sūtras, either as the Buddha’s interlocutor or as a teacher of the Dharma. <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">Maitreya</em> literally means “Loving One.” He is also known as Ajita, meaning “Invincible.”</p><p>For more information on Maitreya, see, for example, the introduction to <cite class="title text-en" lang="en"><a target="_blank" href="/entity/passage/ed4cf305-d6eb-4835-a5cf-7483eb4b4396" title="Maitreya’s Setting Out">Maitreya’s Setting Out</a></cite> (Toh 198).</p></div></div></div></div><div id="e0133a81-a3ee-412d-b012-b099286c29aa" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mml5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.858</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Majestic Trees</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">shing ’gying ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཤིང་འགྱིང་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest at <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9673">Shining Jewel Light</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="35027c89-a863-4edd-98a6-53d1d1266be7" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mmt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.859</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Making the Hair of All Beings Stand on End</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sems can thams cad spu zing</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སེམས་ཅན་ཐམས་ཅད་སྤུ་ཟིང་།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A place in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9279">Ultimate Torment</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="a50078ab-0efc-4acd-a012-147dc70d1023" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mn55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.860</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">mākṣāḍa</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mA ShA Da</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མཱ་ཥཱ་ཌ།</span></li><li class="italic">mākṣāḍa</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A class of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8622">vidyādharas</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="cdca17d8-1369-4996-8b3f-c306c15af834" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mnd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.861</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Malaya dweller</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ma la ya gnas pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མ་ལ་ཡ་གནས་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A class of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8622">vidyādharas</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="fb7c1a26-6346-4bed-b5e6-72a1a878a5d7" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mnl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.862</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Malaya, Malaya Mountains</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ma la ya, ri ma la ya</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མ་ལ་ཡ།, རི་མ་ལ་ཡ།</span></li><li class="italic">malaya, malayagiri</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain in the south of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="8f7bff6a-d3c3-4b63-b0f6-059d39acda75" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mnt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.863</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Malaya, Malaya Mountains</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ma la ya, ri ma la ya</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མ་ལ་ཡ།, རི་མ་ལ་ཡ།</span></li><li class="italic">malaya, malayagiri</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain range in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="48449b7a-3d1c-4800-8f8d-c0dfd878154f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mo55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.864</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Mālikā</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mA li kA gling</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མཱ་ལི་ཀཱ་གླིང་།</span></li><li class="italic">mālikā</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">An island in the vicinity of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="7acd55f6-3e92-4658-9b8a-23a131ba4255" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mod5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.865</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Mālikagaṅkara Forest</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mA li ka gang+ka ra’i nags</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མཱ་ལི་ཀ་གངྐ་རའི་ནགས།</span></li><li class="italic">mālikagaṅkara</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9241">Great Slope</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="a2443a26-92ae-4e4f-838c-6619d37bd72e" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mol5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.866</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Mānadehā</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mAn de hA</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མཱན་དེ་ཧཱ།</span></li><li class="italic">mānadehā</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8581">rākṣasī</span> living on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8813">Ardhamaru</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="8f9565d3-0b26-4df0-b3d5-b30d88392e86" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mot5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.867</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Mānasaṅkalpa</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">yid kyis brtags pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཡིད་ཀྱིས་བརྟགས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">mānasaṅkalpa</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">City in the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9269">Heaven of Joy</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="bf5ffa70-bca8-4ac1-9f1a-cae886cbd063" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mp55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.868</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Mānasarovara</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ma pham</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མ་ཕམ།</span></li><li class="italic">mānasarovara</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A lake in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="7f1bc107-5ac8-4980-ab0c-7f52f195dd70" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mpd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.869</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Maṇḍala</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">maN+DalaM</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མཎྜལཾ།</span></li><li class="italic">maṇḍala</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9128">Flocking Peacocks</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="afd80c4d-047d-4ee1-b710-fbe85b6b1761" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mpl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.870</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">mandārava</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">man dA ra ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མན་དཱ་ར་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">mandārava</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p>One of the five trees of Indra’s paradise, its heavenly flowers often rain down in salutation of the buddhas and bodhisattvas and are said to be very bright and aromatic, gladdening the hearts of those who see them. In our world, it is a tree native to India, <em class="foreign">Erythrina indica</em> or <em class="foreign">Erythrina variegata</em>, commonly known as the Indian coral tree, mandarava tree, flame tree, and tiger’s claw. In the early spring, before its leaves grow, the tree is fully covered in large flowers, which are rich in nectar and attract many birds. Although the most widespread coral tree has red crimson flowers, the color of the blossoms is not usually mentioned in the sūtras themselves, and it may refer to some other kinds, like the rarer <em class="foreign">Erythrina indica alba</em>, which boasts white flowers.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="8152559b-d070-40e5-bacd-cfd12f6dc574" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mpt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.871</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Mandārava Forest</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">me tog man dA ra ba’i tshal</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མེ་ཏོག་མན་དཱ་ར་བའི་ཚལ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9513">Moving Mind</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="63721b5d-fdc4-4776-828b-253957e9de62" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mq55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.872</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Mandehā</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">man de ha</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མན་དེ་ཧ།</span></li><li class="italic">mandehā</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8581">rākṣasī</span> living in <span><span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8862">Blue Waters</span></span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="6c7892ae-49ba-4028-907e-119344ced8f9" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mqd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.873</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Māndhāta</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">nga las nu</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ང་ལས་ནུ།</span></li><li class="italic">māndhāta</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">(1) A powerful king whose good deeds lent splendor to the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9584">Pleasure Grove Park</span>. (2) A universal monarch.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="d6f71c61-9391-4d6e-8ffa-c319aec86f6f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mql5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.874</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Maṅgalā</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bkra shis ma</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བཀྲ་ཤིས་མ།</span></li><li class="italic">maṅgalā</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A queen of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8731">Rāhu</span>, king of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8489">asuras</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="67197407-c29e-43ce-988d-6ea39c66b554" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mqt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.875</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Manifest Karmic Action</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">las mngon sum</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ལས་མངོན་སུམ།</span></li><li class="italic">karmasākṣin</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain range surrounding the hell of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9043">Embers Within</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="6643cf9c-da10-4c9b-984a-d6c3a71badae" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mr55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.876</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Manifold Chariots</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">shing rta sna tshogs pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཤིང་རྟ་སྣ་ཚོགས་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9417">Living on the Peak</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="b8bb81b5-c0e7-4736-aefa-811ac138394d" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mrd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.877</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Mañjuśrī</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’jam dpal</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འཇམ་དཔལ།</span></li><li class="italic">mañjuśrī</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p>Mañjuśrī is one of the “eight close sons of the Buddha” and a bodhisattva who embodies wisdom. He is a major figure in the Mahāyāna sūtras, appearing often as an interlocutor of the Buddha. In his most well-known iconographic form, he is portrayed bearing the sword of wisdom in his right hand and a volume of the <cite class="title break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">Prajñā­pāramitā­sūtra</cite> in his left. To his name, Mañjuśrī, meaning “Gentle and Glorious One,” is often added the epithet Kumārabhūta, “having a youthful form.” He is also called Mañjughoṣa, Mañjusvara, and Pañcaśikha.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="afc4ebec-4e96-44c8-8ad0-a5a56071db25" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mrl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.878</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Mansion of Great Joy</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">khang bzangs rab tu dga’ bar gnas pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཁང་བཟངས་རབ་ཏུ་དགའ་བར་གནས་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mansion in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9734">Sudharma</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="2082c93b-a97d-4661-9d3b-aee0ed86447b" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mrt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.879</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Mansion of the Mirror of Karmic Actions</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">me long gi khang pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མེ་ལོང་གི་ཁང་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mansion within one of the trees in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9547">Pair of Śāla Trees</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="be33ec74-6b07-494d-b35c-c7fde200b8ac" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ms55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.880</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">māra</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bdud</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བདུད།</span></li><li class="italic">māra</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">(1) A demonic being often bearing the epithet of the “Evil One” (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">pāpīyān</em>, <em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">sdig can</em>), sometimes said to be the principal deity in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9272">Heaven of Making Use of Others’ Emanations</span>, the highest paradise in the desire realm; also one of the names of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8531">god</span> of desire, Kāma in the Vedic tradition. He is portrayed as attempting to prevent the Buddha’s enlightenment. In early soteriological religions, the principal deity in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9884">saṃsāra</span>, such as <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9910">Indra</span>, would attempt to prevent anyone’s realization that would lead to such a liberation.</p><p class="definition">(2) The devas ruled over by <span class="ignore">Māra</span> and assisting his attempts to prevent the Buddha’s enlightenment; they do not wish any being to escape from <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9884">saṃsāra</span>. More generally, they are symbolic of the defects within a person that prevent enlightenment. These four personifications are the <span class="ignore">māra</span> of the sons of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8531">gods</span> (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">devaputramāra</em>, <em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">lha’i bu’i bdud</em>), which is the distraction of pleasures; the <span class="ignore">māra</span> of death (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">mṛtyumāra</em>, <em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">’chi bdag gi bdud</em>); the <span class="ignore">māra</span> of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9925">aggregates</span> (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">skandhamāra</em>, <em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">phung po’i bdud</em>), which is the body; and the <span class="ignore">māra</span> of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9942">afflictions</span> (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">kleśamāra</em>, <em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">nyon mongs pa’i bdud</em>).</p></div></div></div></div><div id="d0dcc2b9-18f5-48c0-b606-6a658208ebae" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_msd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.881</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">marvels</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rmad du byung ba’i sde</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྨད་དུ་བྱུང་བའི་སྡེ།</span></li><li class="italic">adbhutadharma</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One among the twelve sections of scripture.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="6dbef67d-afe5-443c-9e7c-08386a3c5b2a" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_msl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.882</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Massaged and Touched with the Palm of the Hand</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">lag mthil gyis byug cing reg pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ལག་མཐིལ་གྱིས་བྱུག་ཅིང་རེག་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river in the realm of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8531">gods</span> in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9035">Dwelling on Summits</span> within the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9276">Heaven of the Thirty-Three</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="6d10c1c9-c879-41b9-bfb7-524ecb3f6d80" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mst5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.883</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Masses of Vajra-Like Bones</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rus pa rdo rje lta bu ’byung</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རུས་པ་རྡོ་རྗེ་ལྟ་བུ་འབྱུང་།</span></li><li class="italic">vajrāsthi­patana­sampāta</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of the sixteen realms that surround the <span><span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9277">Hell of Heat</span></span>. </p></div></div></div></div><div id="84b76845-d969-4b3b-8875-99ab6c4b157b" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mt55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.884</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Matala</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ma ta la</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མ་ཏ་ལ།</span></li><li class="italic">matala</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A grove in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9752">Supreme Splendor</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="cd15cec2-3d4a-4b5d-b7fa-a985ba4742c7" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mtd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.885</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Mātali</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ma ta li</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མ་ཏ་ལི།</span></li><li class="italic">mātali</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition"><span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8738">Śakra</span>’s elephant driver.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="4539b2cd-7eb2-408c-a237-13f851ed7e37" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mtl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.886</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Meghalati</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">me g+ha la ti</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མེ་གྷ་ལ་ཏི།</span></li><li class="italic">meghalati</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="2fb5c95c-5369-4fbb-9234-026295882568" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mtt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.887</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Meghamālin</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sprin phreng, sprin phreng can</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྤྲིན་ཕྲེང་།, སྤྲིན་ཕྲེང་ཅན།</span></li><li class="italic">meghamālin</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A virtuous <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8562">nāga</span> king. </p></div></div></div></div><div id="5115e735-0440-4084-a1b9-75a56a1fe0f2" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mu55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.888</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Mekala Source</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">me ka la ’byung ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མེ་ཀ་ལ་འབྱུང་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">mekala</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">An island in the vicinity of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="1e6e9f0e-c465-4016-826e-a39a24df106e" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mud5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.889</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Melako</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">me la ko</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མེ་ལ་ཀོ</span></li><li class="italic">melako</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A land in the south of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="a867dd71-2e7d-4fa7-b425-a5ab88c85c7f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mul5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.890</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Melodious</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dbyangs snyan pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དབྱངས་སྙན་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9657">Saṅkāśa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="aca274a6-9baf-4b88-8416-2b5930d2ffbb" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mut5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.891</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Melodious Experience</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">snyan pa spyod pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྙན་པ་སྤྱོད་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A location in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9519">Mutual Liking</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="02bd7ac1-47d5-418a-80ad-998f2aa21c76" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mv55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.892</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">mendicant</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dge sbyong</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དགེ་སྦྱོང་།</span></li><li class="italic">śramaṇa</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">An ordained Buddhist practitioner. Pairs often with <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8491">brahmin</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="23f3da2a-72ec-4ffe-a3f6-0b66dbe9d18f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mvd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.893</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">mending ritual</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gso sbyong</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གསོ་སྦྱོང་།</span></li><li class="italic">poṣadha</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">The monastic procedure for confession of misdeeds and the restoration of vows.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="e6d35472-9267-48b9-864f-d9312dd65121" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mvl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.894</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Menko</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">men ko</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མེན་ཀོ</span></li><li class="italic">menko</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain to the north of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="7b35c64c-1a8a-4ff3-8a8e-62ddd8230adc" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_mvt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.895</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Mental Stain</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sems kyi dri ma</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སེམས་ཀྱི་དྲི་མ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A land in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9209">Godānīya</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="f00b0ece-b052-4c8e-a9b0-dfd6c372359e" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_n055anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.896</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Merging</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’dres pa’i tshal</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འདྲེས་པའི་ཚལ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A grove in the forest known as <span><span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9310">Incomparable</span></span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="badea4b7-0223-4bcd-a5c3-f7872755d6c6" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_n0d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.897</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Merging of the Sindhū and the Sea</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sin+d+hu dang rgya mtsho gnyis ’dre ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སིནྡྷུ་དང་རྒྱ་མཚོ་གཉིས་འདྲེ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">An area to the west of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="eaa9aab0-8f8b-4cc2-8c4d-d8cec3c0ba51" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_n0l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.898</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Metallic Fire</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">lcags kyi me</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ལྕགས་ཀྱི་མེ།</span></li><li class="italic">ayo’gninaraka</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of sixteen realms that surround the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8975">Crushing Hell</span>. Alternatively referred to as <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9263">Heap of Live Coals of Iron-dust</span> (<em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">lcags kyi phye ma me ma dag gi ra ba</em>).</p></div></div></div></div><div id="5a0621d5-98e5-4cbf-acc9-51c8bfab2400" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_n0t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.899</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Milky River</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’o ma’i chu</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འོ་མའི་ཆུ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9657">Saṅkāśa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="b6df2a34-9630-47f7-94dd-6bb953c62a49" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_n155anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.900</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Milky Sea</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’o ma’i chu</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འོ་མའི་ཆུ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">An ocean between <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9209">Godānīya</span> and <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9847">Videha</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="5a7a5f4f-6982-48a2-ad69-75ff219a8700" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_n1d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.901</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Milky Waters</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’o ma’i chu</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འོ་མའི་ཆུ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A sea to the north of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="ced33a35-87c3-4bb9-846e-812f008e2373" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_n1l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.902</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Minced up by Raining Loops of Wire</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">srad bu’i rgyud dkrugs pa, srad bu’i rgyud ’dre ba dud pa ltar ’khrigs pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྲད་བུའི་རྒྱུད་དཀྲུགས་པ།, སྲད་བུའི་རྒྱུད་འདྲེ་བ་དུད་པ་ལྟར་འཁྲིགས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">tantu­varṣa­māloddhṛta</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A realm that neighbors the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9278">Hell of Intense Heat</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="63977472-a6f0-4a0d-8076-b13dc1ba4310" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_n1t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.903</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Mirror Forest</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">me long tshal</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མེ་ལོང་ཚལ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">Forest upon <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9575">Mount Playful</span> in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9734">Sudharma</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="22d67e6b-ebbe-4098-8172-23e29c94cacf" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_n255anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.904</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Mirror Lake</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">kun mthong</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀུན་མཐོང་།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A lake in the realm of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8489">asuras</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="b1149d35-3fbc-4f91-bcf4-a7314383147a" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_n2d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.905</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Misperception</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’du shes log pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འདུ་ཤེས་ལོག་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A “ruler of the world” who belongs to the class of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8553">māras</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="96d5d04b-7224-423f-8752-9ee9bc241a72" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_n2l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.906</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Misunderstanding</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">log par rnam par lta ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ལོག་པར་རྣམ་པར་ལྟ་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">vitathadarśana</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A place in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9279">Ultimate Torment</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="b2e229e5-a364-4cbd-8a31-57583e81964a" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_n2t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.907</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Mithila</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mi thi la</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མི་ཐི་ལ།</span></li><li class="italic">mithila</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A land in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9209">Godānīya</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="96437a7c-c2a6-4d06-bcfa-31a1688ccac8" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_n355anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.908</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Mithila Grove</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mi thi la’i tshal</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མི་ཐི་ལའི་ཚལ།</span></li><li class="italic">mithila</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A Buddhist temple in a previous time period.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="00f7f907-25da-4cfb-88f3-00fca89b01fe" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_n3d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.909</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Mixed</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">kun tu ’dres pa, yongs su ’dres pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀུན་ཏུ་འདྲེས་པ།, ཡོངས་སུ་འདྲེས་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">(1) A forest on the northern face of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9739">Sumeru</span> (<em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">yongs su ’dres pa</em>). (2) A river in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9209">Godānīya</span> (<em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">kun tu ’dres pa</em>).</p></div></div></div></div><div id="f203901d-4b54-437c-9a73-f50881380923" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_n3l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.910</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Mixture</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’dres pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འདྲེས་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest on the third <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8489">asura</span> level, <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9087">Excellent Abode</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="637d9313-03ef-4c96-a355-4d05151a1c2d" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_n3t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.911</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Molten Red</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dmar po rnam par zhu</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དམར་པོ་རྣམ་པར་ཞུ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river in the ephemeral hell known as <span><span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9619">Red</span></span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="d5a294a3-d80f-4cab-91d6-c6c8c37e4bf2" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_n455anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.912</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">monastic administrator</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">zhal ta pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཞལ་ཏ་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">vaiyāpṛtyakara</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">The officer who receives and administers donations on behalf of the Saṅgha.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="505c49fc-794f-420b-b98f-362c9b81a644" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_n4d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.913</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Moon Body</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">zla ba’i lus</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཟླ་བའི་ལུས།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A lake on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9078">Equal Peaks</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="1a4ff720-0124-404b-81bb-3b3318a6aa7d" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_n4l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.914</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Moon Garland</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">zla ba’i phreng ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཟླ་བའི་ཕྲེང་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">candramālā</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A realm below that of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8731">Rāhu</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="a1033eb4-03d2-4089-a8df-787c0f48e13a" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_n4t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.915</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Moon Joy</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">zla ba dga’ ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཟླ་བ་དགའ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A lake on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9078">Equal Peaks</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="585a3325-011e-4ed7-84b6-be1156e5e3ea" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_n555anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.916</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Moon Mountain</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ri bo zla ba, zla ba’i ri bo</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཟླ་བའི་རི་བོ།, རི་བོ་ཟླ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">(1) A mountain to the north of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span> (<em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">zla ba’i ri bo</em>). (2) A mountain upon which the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8531">gods</span> of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8526">Four Great Kings</span> will take position while awaiting the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8489">asura</span> army (<em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">ri bo zla ba</em>).</p></div></div></div></div><div id="2463368c-e009-4fb8-a02f-2041fda2d0c4" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_n5d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.917</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Moon Power</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">zla ba’i shugs</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཟླ་བའི་ཤུགས།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9209">Godānīya</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="cd35a278-b707-45b9-a2f9-98059aae894e" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_n5l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.918</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Moon-Like</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">zla ba ’dra</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཟླ་བ་འདྲ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9035">Dwelling on Summits</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="428be836-d592-47ad-91e9-3bac232d55d0" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_n5t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.919</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">most humble</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">shin tu dud pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཤིན་ཏུ་དུད་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A class of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8622">vidyādharas</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="2db5307a-2de4-447b-b155-7a7da2ed32f6" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_n655anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.920</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Mount Illuminator</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">kun tu snang byed</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀུན་ཏུ་སྣང་བྱེད།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9398">Kuru</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="f2c2e7b7-1470-44a4-b6a7-77817c9ad034" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_n6d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.921</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Mount Playful</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ri rtse ba, rtse ba’i ri</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རི་རྩེ་བ།, རྩེ་བའི་རི།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">(1) A mountain in the forest of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9369">Joyous Women</span>. (2) A mountain in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9283">High Conduct</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="f46512e5-d2f2-4668-8b9b-db805bd020e6" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_n6l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.922</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Mount Sky Reacher</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ri mkha’ thug</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རི་མཁའ་ཐུག</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain in <span><span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9580">Pleasant Sound</span></span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="b7a65a66-5229-4807-b21f-5d924c750bbd" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_n6t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.923</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Mount Stainless</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ri grib med</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རི་གྲིབ་མེད།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain in <span><span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9580">Pleasant Sound</span></span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="d4c4a9f8-994f-43c4-914b-e7af688cdb84" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_n755anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.924</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Mount Universal Joy</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ri thams cad dga’</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རི་ཐམས་ཅད་དགའ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain in <span><span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9580">Pleasant Sound</span></span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="5d7b53dd-d38d-4bbb-957d-72a02a8ab36e" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_n7d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.925</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Mount Wish-Fulfilling Emanation</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ri yid bzhin sprul</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རི་ཡིད་བཞིན་སྤྲུལ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain in <span><span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9580">Pleasant Sound</span></span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="55ab255a-dd1e-448a-ba41-b9c3f8722782" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_n7l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.926</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">mountain based</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ri rnams la kun tu chags pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རི་རྣམས་ལ་ཀུན་ཏུ་ཆགས་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A class of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8622">vidyādharas</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="6b9eab82-5c17-4292-b46c-87e00986540e" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_n7t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.927</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Mountain Dwellings</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ri la nges par gnas pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རི་ལ་ངེས་པར་གནས་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">An island in the vicinity of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="207bf0ea-60a0-4cb5-a4f4-3d4fec36e67d" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_n855anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.928</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">mountain mansion dwellers</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">lhun po’i khang na gnas pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ལྷུན་པོའི་ཁང་ན་གནས་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A class of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8489">asuras</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="4e840803-e1e9-46fe-9d98-4733dff99457" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_n8d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.929</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Mountain of Play</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rtsed mo’i ri bo</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྩེད་མོའི་རི་བོ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9056">Endowed with Increasing Bliss</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="e731440c-62b4-4a24-859c-237936d196c9" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_n8l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.930</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Mountain Stream</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ri bo la rgyu ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རི་བོ་ལ་རྒྱུ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9657">Saṅkāśa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="51d47446-f5e6-4184-b5d5-587f60e36b5d" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_n8t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.931</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Mountainous Environs</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ri’i nye ’khor</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རིའི་ཉེ་འཁོར།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A part of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9495">Mountainous Garland</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="a9d9168d-cd5d-44c1-8bee-16830aabd252" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_n955anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.932</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Mountainous Garland</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ri’i phreng ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རིའི་ཕྲེང་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8958">Controlled Movement</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="b802f5dc-425e-47c3-9894-6664ea218dfa" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_n9d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.933</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Mountainous Joy</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ri’i khrod dga’ ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རིའི་ཁྲོད་དགའ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9796">Total Pleasure</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="91d71c7c-9077-40ba-ad8c-6b3f80001fdb" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_n9l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.934</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Mountainous Light Garland</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ri’i ’od phreng</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རིའི་འོད་ཕྲེང་།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A peak on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9739">Sumeru</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="98bccc88-36ca-487c-b3b0-665e5e014c66" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_n9t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.935</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Moved</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">g.yos pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གཡོས་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">An area in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9398">Kuru</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="7ed307b5-a3fb-47b9-b631-0b9c3fda0711" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_na55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.936</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Movement</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">kun tu rgyu</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀུན་ཏུ་རྒྱུ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A lake near <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9734">Sudharma</span>. </p></div></div></div></div><div id="504d4c23-875b-44a7-97f6-39ae75531116" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_nad5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.937</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Movement Everywhere</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">thams cad ’gro ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཐམས་ཅད་འགྲོ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A city in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9847">Videha</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="2e00900c-3667-4729-b498-08e410429c8f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_nal5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.938</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Movement of Wind</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rlung gi rgyu, rlung gi rgyu ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རླུང་གི་རྒྱུ་བ།, རླུང་གི་རྒྱུ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">(1) Alternative name for <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9068">Enjoying the Wind</span> (<em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">rlung gi rgyu</em>). (2) One of the twenty-seven realms in the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9266">Heaven Free from Strife</span> (<em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">rlung gi rgyu ba</em>).</p></div></div></div></div><div id="ab14f848-514d-41f8-9925-0aa5e7e10bb8" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_nat5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.939</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Moving among Eyes</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mig la kun tu rgyu ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མིག་ལ་ཀུན་ཏུ་རྒྱུ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">An area in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9398">Kuru</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="3b0d50f6-a7df-43ca-ada8-6ce02f740509" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_nb55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.940</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Moving Flowers</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">me tog rgyu ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མེ་ཏོག་རྒྱུ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9657">Saṅkāśa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="31fe7a8c-5cf5-4da4-bbe6-4c0b2e2ad6c0" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_nbd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.941</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Moving Fragrance</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dri rgyu ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དྲི་རྒྱུ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">An area in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9398">Kuru</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="65268843-d7fe-44df-8d5a-499b651cf8d7" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_nbl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.942</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Moving in Gatherings</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">tshogs pa rgyu ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཚོགས་པ་རྒྱུ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of the twenty-seven realms of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9266">Heaven Free from Strife</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="57219428-93cc-47d0-a79b-eeacf410a910" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_nbt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.943</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Moving in Mixed Environments</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rab tu rnam par ’dres pa’i khor yug na rgyu ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རབ་ཏུ་རྣམ་པར་འདྲེས་པའི་ཁོར་ཡུག་ན་རྒྱུ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of the twenty-seven realms of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9266">Heaven Free from Strife</span>, possibly the same as <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8956">Continuous Movement</span> (<em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">rgyun gyis rgyu ba</em>).</p></div></div></div></div><div id="6a3c4387-f8d5-47e8-a99b-324314566aa0" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_nc55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.944</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Moving in Mountain Ranges</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ri’i tshogs na rgyu ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རིའི་ཚོགས་ན་རྒྱུ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of the twenty-seven realms in the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9266">Heaven Free from Strife</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="f6798504-7081-42bf-8a64-0aac06b42905" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ncd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.945</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Moving in One’s Land</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rang gi yul bar rgyu ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རང་གི་ཡུལ་བར་རྒྱུ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of the twenty-seven realms in the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9266">Heaven Free from Strife</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="e3886a2a-4608-4297-8449-161597724110" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ncl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.946</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Moving in the Stream</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rgyun gyi gnas na rnam par rgyu ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྒྱུན་གྱི་གནས་ན་རྣམ་པར་རྒྱུ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of the twenty-seven realms of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9266">Heaven Free from Strife</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="71d882ef-cdb8-4fc9-a848-74daf9e05d86" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_nct5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.947</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Moving in the Wink of an Eye</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mig phye zhing ’gro ba btsums nas ’gro ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མིག་ཕྱེ་ཞིང་འགྲོ་བ་བཙུམས་ནས་འགྲོ་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">nimeṣonmeṣa­gatī</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A realm in the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9276">Heaven of the Thirty-Three</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="e7d0d16d-942c-4c23-8c14-8c9e0c159ebf" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_nd55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.948</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Moving in Vast Environments</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rgya chen po’i khor yug na rgyu ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྒྱ་ཆེན་པོའི་ཁོར་ཡུག་ན་རྒྱུ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of the twenty-seven realms of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9266">Heaven Free from Strife</span>, presumably the same as <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9506">Moving in Mixed Environments</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="6305dfbd-1e36-4cbb-ac0c-6569790502c8" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ndd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.949</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Moving Like the Moon</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">zla ba’i gnas ltar rgyu ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཟླ་བའི་གནས་ལྟར་རྒྱུ་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">candrāyaṇacāra</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A realm in the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9276">Heaven of the Thirty-Three</span>. Also called <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9627">Resembling the Full Moon</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="348382dc-3074-4fb3-a514-f23a378782ec" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ndl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.950</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Moving Mind</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">yid g.yo ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཡིད་གཡོ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A realm inhabited by <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8530">garland-bearer gods</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="c02e9815-604b-4dc5-a8ee-29a1fabd385e" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ndt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.951</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Moving Moon</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">zla ba rgyu ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཟླ་བ་རྒྱུ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9657">Saṅkāśa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="3dc335b1-19ac-4b70-b968-99d8515d89c8" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ne55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.952</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Moving on Springy Ground</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dma’ ba dang mtho ba na rgyu ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དམའ་བ་དང་མཐོ་བ་ན་རྒྱུ་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">nimnonnatā­cāriṇī</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A realm in the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9276">Heaven of the Thirty-Three</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="59acec3a-ea32-4a6e-9148-58f4a051988f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ned5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.953</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">moving without delay</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’gor ba med par ’gro ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འགོར་བ་མེད་པར་འགྲོ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A class of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8622">vidyādharas</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="47f6a541-68e6-42f1-b856-15dde9d7fa25" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_nel5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.954</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Multicolor</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’dres pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འདྲེས་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain on the continent of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9398">Kuru</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="8b6f4a70-ae8d-47c6-a7c7-8d7c250bda4c" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_net5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.955</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">musāragalva</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mu sA ra gal ba, mu sA ra gal+ba, mu sa ra, spug</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མུ་ས་ར།, མུ་སཱ་ར་གལ་བ།, མུ་སཱ་ར་གལྦ།, སྤུག</span></li><li class="italic">musāragalva</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">Musāragalva is fossilized coral that has undergone transformation under millions of years of underwater pressure. It appears in one version of the list of seven precious materials. The Tibetan tradition describes it as being formed from ice over a long period of time. It can also refer to tridacna (<em class="foreign">Tridacnidae</em>) shell, which is also presently referred to by the name musaragalva. Attempts to identify musāragalva have included sapphire, cat’s eye, red coral, conch, and amber.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="b6357997-e45e-4bbe-bc0c-0c16104deb5f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_nf55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.956</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Musulundha</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mu su lun dha</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མུ་སུ་ལུན་དྷ།</span></li><li class="italic">musulundha</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">King of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8531">gods</span> in the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9266">Heaven Free from Strife</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="a38ef4c0-9af9-4971-b8fb-4159020f9cbd" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_nfd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.957</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Mutation</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gzhan du ’gyur ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གཞན་དུ་འགྱུར་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">anyathā­parivarta</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">(1) One of sixteen realms that surround the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9235">Great Howling Hell</span>. (2) One of sixteen realms that surround the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9630">Reviving Hell</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="245442f8-7254-4beb-aa77-7e8c8c49aaa7" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_nfl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.958</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Mutilation by Iron</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">lcags kyis bsgyur ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ལྕགས་ཀྱིས་བསྒྱུར་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">ayaḥ­parivartaka</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of sixteen realms that surround the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9630">Reviving Hell</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="ef01787d-7848-4ab7-9912-d6f0e9b2e79a" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_nft5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.959</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Mutual Harm</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">phan tshun gnod pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཕན་ཚུན་གནོད་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">paraspara­pīḍā­saṃvarta</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of sixteen realms that surround the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9235">Great Howling Hell</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="67f3257e-94a4-43ae-95ea-77377a4d92b8" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ng55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.960</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Mutual Liking</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">phan tshun dga’</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཕན་ཚུན་དགའ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A realm of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8617">triple-lute-bearer gods</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="90cb0864-69bd-4721-b137-0150b05ab596" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ngd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.961</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Nāḍoḍina</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">nA Do DI na</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ནཱ་ཌོ་ཌཱི་ན།</span></li><li class="italic">nāḍoḍina</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9209">Godānīya</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="5257b1aa-f3bc-4c93-8534-df210ad1bb3f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ngl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.962</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">nāga</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">klu</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀླུ།</span></li><li class="italic">nāga</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A serpentine class of beings associated with intelligence and wealth.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="8fd5d912-9e12-4ea9-9be3-2586e472941f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ngt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.963</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Nāga Beru</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">klu’i be ruH</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀླུའི་བེ་རུཿ།</span></li><li class="italic">beru</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A lake on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9078">Equal Peaks</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="da834c04-0fd6-433c-966e-3f6d0f390d86" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_nh55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.964</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Nāga River</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">klu’i chu</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀླུའི་ཆུ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9241">Great Slope</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="dd80abf7-2957-4964-8197-6da89a367383" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_nhd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.965</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Nālandā</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ba len+d+ra</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བ་ལེནྡྲ།</span></li><li class="italic">nālanda</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A renowned monastic complex in India.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="47ddecbd-4962-438a-8eec-33c5c48b2fa1" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_nhl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.966</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Nālati</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">na lA ti, na la ti</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ན་ལ་ཏི།, ན་ལཱ་ཏི།</span></li><li class="italic">nālati</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A town in ancient India where this <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9986">sūtra</span> is taught.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="4300f796-5f74-4d62-8620-40a39163c90d" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_nht5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.967</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Nārāyaṇa</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sred med kyi bu</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྲེད་མེད་ཀྱི་བུ།</span></li><li class="italic">nārāyaṇa</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">Another name for the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8531">god</span> <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8778">Viṣṇu</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="75fd9127-ed3e-4b29-bd4e-07d917692999" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ni55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.968</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Narmadā</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">nar ma dA</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ནར་མ་དཱ།</span></li><li class="italic">narmadā</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river to the south of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="c6c29a80-97f1-4af1-8ea2-b64be53627de" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_nid5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.969</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">narratives</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rtogs pa brjod pa’i sde</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྟོགས་པ་བརྗོད་པའི་སྡེ།</span></li><li class="italic">avadāna</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One among the twelve sections of scripture.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="1705f2d6-1c3d-4957-96d8-d65abd2c674f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_nil5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.970</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Nature of Precious Bliss</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bde ba rin po che’i rang bzhin</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བདེ་བ་རིན་པོ་ཆེའི་རང་བཞིན།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9840">Vast Garlands of Bliss</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="38b7666a-ade2-483b-8d4c-f2104ff7e720" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_nit5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.971</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">necklace</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mgul phreng</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མགུལ་ཕྲེང་།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A class of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8489">asuras</span> ruled by <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8695">Kaṇṭhamāla</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="d55e87c5-7853-4992-b6cc-fa43f115a67b" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_nj55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.972</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Nectar Flow</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bdud rtsi ’bab pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བདུད་རྩི་འབབ་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A lake on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9078">Equal Peaks</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="9e3427ab-a502-4895-8c2d-f5e1dfca91d3" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_njd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.973</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Needle Eye</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">khab kyi kha</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཁབ་ཀྱི་ཁ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain off <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9847">Videha</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="a131748a-fd92-42f4-8aa1-7d5b58ce9783" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_njl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.974</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Net Garland</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dra ba’i phreng ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དྲ་བའི་ཕྲེང་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9025">Dwelling in Excellent View</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="412acae7-3059-4d87-99ef-3ed08d9d1771" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_njt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.975</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Neutralization of Nāga Poison</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">klu’i dug bcom</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀླུའི་དུག་བཅོམ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">An ocean between <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9209">Godānīya</span> and <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9847">Videha</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="7277eda9-5208-409a-a325-ae1de301b065" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_nk55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.976</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Niculundha Flow</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ni tsu lun+da ’bab pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ནི་ཙུ་ལུནྡ་འབབ་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">niculundha</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9128">Flocking Peacocks</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="4906a791-09c3-445d-a8c8-aa7928a788d1" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_nkd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.977</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Nimi</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ni mi</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ནི་མི།</span></li><li class="italic">nimi</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A king who built stupas.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="e407c462-bf1a-4b2b-b6ae-a01645f912bd" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_nkl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.978</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Nirāsravarati</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">zag pa med par ’gro ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཟག་པ་མེད་པར་འགྲོ་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">nirāsravarati</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">The mansion within the city of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9449">Mānasaṅkalpa</span> in the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9269">Heaven of Joy</span> in which the bodhisattva <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8711">Maitreya</span> lives.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="557a71a2-09ff-40e8-9705-0e92ea6f11ee" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_nkt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.979</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">nirvāṇa without any remainder, nirvāṇa without remainder</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">lhag med myang ’das</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ལྷག་མེད་མྱང་འདས།</span></li><li class="italic">nirupadhiśeṣa­nirvāṇa</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">The cessation of karma and <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9942">affliction</span> within which no residue of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9925">aggregates</span> remains.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="385874ab-d0db-4cdc-95b5-c5ff7b339121" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_nl55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.980</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">nirvāṇa, transcendence of suffering</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mya ngan las ’das pa, mya ngan las ’das pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མྱ་ངན་ལས་འདས་པ།, མྱ་ངན་ལས་འདས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">nirvāṇa, nirvāṇa</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">The ultimate cessation of suffering. Also translated here as “<span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9946">transcendence of suffering</span>.”</p></div></div></div></div><div id="ac32bc5b-668a-4237-964c-e794eb68dfc9" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_nld5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.981</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">nirvāṇa, transcendence of suffering</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mya ngan las ’das pa, mya ngan las ’das pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མྱ་ངན་ལས་འདས་པ།, མྱ་ངན་ལས་འདས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">nirvāṇa, nirvāṇa</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">The ultimate cessation of suffering. Also rendered here as “<span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8565">nirvāṇa</span>.”</p></div></div></div></div><div id="7b73bb25-bce3-47c5-b8e2-9d0c8f89ef4f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_nll5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.982</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">No Death</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’chi med</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འཆི་མེད།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of sixteen realms that surround the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9298">Howling Hell</span>. Alternatively referred to as <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9306">Impossible to Die</span> (<em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">gsod med</em>) in the Tibetan text.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="b9c8a0b8-8354-4352-b199-46a4cf272950" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_nlt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.983</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">No Hope of Joy</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">kun dga’ la re ba med pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀུན་དགའ་ལ་རེ་བ་མེད་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of sixteen realms that surround the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9235">Great Howling Hell</span>. Appears to be identical with <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9350">Joyless Thought</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="987be809-b467-4a7f-b459-d24c1f78fb97" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_nm55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.984</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">No Lack of Embankments</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’jug ngogs med pa ma yin pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འཇུག་ངོགས་མེད་པ་མ་ཡིན་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A location in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9266">Heaven Free from Strife</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="ca7df710-3427-4c3e-bd6a-9c13c28182ae" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_nmd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.985</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">No Shadows</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">grib ma med pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གྲིབ་མ་མེད་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9840">Vast Garlands of Bliss</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="02f4d334-0e69-4600-a543-0dcea128cf23" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_nml5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.986</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">non-Buddhist</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mu stegs can</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མུ་སྟེགས་ཅན།</span></li><li class="italic">tīrthika</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p>Those of other religious or philosophical orders, contemporary with the early Buddhist order, including Jains, Jaṭilas, Ājīvikas, and Cārvākas. Tīrthika (“forder”) literally translates as “one belonging to or associated with (possessive suffix <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">–ika</em>) stairs for landing or for descent into a river,” or “a bathing place,” or “a place of pilgrimage on the banks of sacred streams” (Monier-Williams). The term may have originally referred to temple priests at river crossings or fords where travelers propitiated a deity before crossing. The Sanskrit term seems to have undergone metonymic transfer in referring to those able to ford the turbulent river of saṃsāra (as in the Jain tīrthaṅkaras, “ford makers”), and it came to be used in Buddhist sources to refer to teachers of rival religious traditions. The Sanskrit term is closely rendered by the Tibetan <em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">mu stegs pa</em>: “those on the steps (<em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">stegs pa</em>) at the edge (<em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">mu</em>).”</p></div></div></div></div><div id="7b9b6940-c5ab-4cca-97c2-bb0dd6e22faa" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_nmt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.987</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Non-Intoxication</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">myos pa med pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མྱོས་པ་མེད་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river in the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9764">Swan Forest</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="c353222b-8713-4848-938a-dc0b6f0fd4db" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_nn55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.988</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Non-perception of Time</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dus mi mthong</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དུས་མི་མཐོང་།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A lotus pool in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9403">Lateral</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="94d8406a-bac9-4175-907c-5a3a958b0b08" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_nnd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.989</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">non-returner</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">phyir mi ’ong ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཕྱིར་མི་འོང་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">anāgāmin</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">The third level of noble ones when practicing the path of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8536">hearers</span> (bound to never be reborn in the realm of desire).</p></div></div></div></div><div id="af00cf53-d390-4394-8f1d-d62c69523d02" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_nnl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.990</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Numerous Celestial Bodies</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rgyu skar mang po</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྒྱུ་སྐར་མང་པོ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain beyond <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9847">Videha</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="ae28bd69-0411-4c35-956b-180a1d0796b1" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_nnt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.991</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Numerous Joys</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dga’ ba du ma</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དགའ་བ་དུ་མ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A lake near <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9131">Flow of Beauty</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="37d90a5d-890e-452f-b745-42633597ca08" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_no55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.992</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Numerous Leaves</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">lo ’dab mang ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ལོ་འདབ་མང་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A town in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9847">Videha</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="9170c823-cda9-4af6-92a6-2a38e653e409" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_nod5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.993</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">once-returner</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">lan cig phyir ’ong ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ལན་ཅིག་ཕྱིར་འོང་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">sakṛdāgāmin</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">The second level of noble ones when practicing the path of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8536">hearers</span> (having only one remaining birth in the realm of desire).</p></div></div></div></div><div id="6921cebe-b9c4-4193-b9a8-3ab413cbeb2a" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_nol5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.994</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">One League of Cool Water</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bsil ba’i chu ni rgyar dpag tshad du gyur pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བསིལ་བའི་ཆུ་ནི་རྒྱར་དཔག་ཚད་དུ་གྱུར་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9657">Saṅkāśa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="abb40cb9-59e5-481c-a3ef-c23d16a2f12a" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_not5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.995</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">One That Arouses Great Pity</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">snying rje chen po</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྙིང་རྗེ་ཆེན་པོ།</span></li><li class="italic">mahākaruṇa</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A realm that neighbors the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9278">Hell of Intense Heat</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="62318ec6-1f6d-4839-bb99-004abc17c344" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_np55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.996</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Ornament of the Mind</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">yid kyi rgyan</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཡིད་ཀྱི་རྒྱན།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of the twenty-seven realms of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9266">Heaven Free from Strife</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="248c00de-0a31-4d9c-ae4f-a141db45fb51" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_npd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.997</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Overflow</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rgyu mthun pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྒྱུ་མཐུན་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9288">Holder of Joy</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="326363e3-7696-4ffc-a844-53e8b58cfcd9" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_npl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.998</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Overjoyed</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rab dgod, rab tu spro ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རབ་ཏུ་སྤྲོ་བ།, རབ་དགོད།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition"><span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8489">Asura</span> king of the fourth level, <span><span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9305">Immovable</span></span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="509807dd-caa2-487e-b34a-e90dc05b5194" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_npt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.999</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Pain Incarnate</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">shar gyur pa thams cad sdug bsngal</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཤར་གྱུར་པ་ཐམས་ཅད་སྡུག་བསྔལ།</span></li><li class="italic">sarvāmiṣa­bhūta­vedana</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A realm that neighbors the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9278">Hell of Intense Heat</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="846bfed1-4702-44a1-a540-2bb00f5f3d34" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_nq55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1000</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Pair of Śāla Trees</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">shing sA la zung</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཤིང་སཱ་ལ་ཟུང་།</span></li><li class="italic">yamanaśālā</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A realm in the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9276">Heaven of the Thirty-Three</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="796f3432-d65d-4534-af3c-2eedbe7252da" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_nqd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1001</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Pakṣu</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">pak+Shu</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">པཀྵུ།</span></li><li class="italic">pakṣu</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="8b8ca529-2dc1-4aa8-b656-78581cf41ee5" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_nql5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1002</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Palanquin Houses</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">khyogs kyi khang bu</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཁྱོགས་ཀྱི་ཁང་བུ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">Refers to <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9705">Spacious Palanquin Houses</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="db50a533-2a81-4848-a032-0346e1637501" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_nqt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1003</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Palatial Mountain</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gzhal yas khang gi ri</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གཞལ་ཡས་ཁང་གི་རི།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9796">Total Pleasure</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="fe29caf7-ba48-40cd-928d-c7b564375742" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_nr55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1004</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">paṇḍita</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">paN+Di ta</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">པཎྜི་ཏ།</span></li><li class="italic">paṇḍita</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">An accomplished scholar.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="51710dbf-49d1-46e5-b5fa-a517bb165d9e" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_nrd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1005</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">parables</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">de lta bu byung ba’i sde</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དེ་ལྟ་བུ་བྱུང་བའི་སྡེ།</span></li><li class="italic">itivṛttaka</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One among the twelve sections of scripture.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="b98acce4-f93d-4a96-9303-db8bacb68b6e" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_nrl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1006</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Pāraṭā</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">pA ra tA</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">པཱ་ར་ཏཱ།</span></li><li class="italic">pāraṭā</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">An area to the west of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="b0fb5468-2bf4-46e5-90cf-651aa5ac1c57" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_nrt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1007</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Pārijāta</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">yongs ’du</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཡོངས་འདུ།</span></li><li class="italic">pārijāta</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A heavenly tree on Mount <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9739">Sumeru</span> (<em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">yongs ’du</em>).</p></div></div></div></div><div id="f29dcd91-297e-4887-aa58-3183241cf3e6" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ns55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1008</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Pārijāta Mountains</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ri yongs ’du</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རི་ཡོངས་འདུ།</span></li><li class="italic">pārijāta</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain range. </p><p class="definition">(We have been unable to identify this mountain, or mountain range. However, since <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">yongs ’du</em> is a translation of “<span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9551">pārijāta</span> tree,” we have opted for this translation. Perhaps it refers to the mountains where the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9551">pārijāta</span> tree grows?)</p></div></div></div></div><div id="a80ab03a-4f55-422a-a81c-3a1777991822" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_nsd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1009</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Park of Golden Shade</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gser gyi grib ma’i tshal</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གསེར་གྱི་གྲིབ་མའི་ཚལ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A park in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8820">Attached to That</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="46f5d233-5510-4509-8fa5-98b26ccd7350" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_nsl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1010</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Park of Passion</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rgyags pa’i kun dga’ ra ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྒྱགས་པའི་ཀུན་དགའ་ར་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of four parks that surround the city of <span data-ref="UT22084-068-021-9605"><span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9605">Radiant</span></span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="22005d0f-ea22-4b04-800a-c38653ae314f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_nst5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1011</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Park of the Cuckoo Birds</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">khu byug gi kun dga’ ra ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཁུ་བྱུག་གི་ཀུན་དགའ་ར་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of four parks that surround the city of <span data-ref="UT22084-068-021-9605"><span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9605">Radiant</span></span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="30e70bbc-b072-453d-b33c-cd0e22b91b4d" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_nt55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1012</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Part of the Assembly</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ris mthun pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རིས་མཐུན་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">nikāyabhāginī</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A realm in the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9276">Heaven of the Thirty-Three</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="0fb68cee-8d0a-4e50-8daa-a57eec96e648" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ntd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1013</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Pāruṣika</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rtsub ’gyur</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྩུབ་འགྱུར།</span></li><li class="italic">pāruṣika</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest on the western face of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9739">Sumeru</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="8081fef6-7221-4e9e-9306-1b87f4235403" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ntl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1014</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Passionate Conduct</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">yang dag chags spyod</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཡང་དག་ཆགས་སྤྱོད།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A realm of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8617">triple-lute-bearer gods</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="54c2ebb6-1906-4cbc-b993-f8f3bc4a6e85" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ntt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1015</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">past-life stories</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">skyes pa rabs kyi sde</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྐྱེས་པ་རབས་ཀྱི་སྡེ།</span></li><li class="italic">jātaka</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One among the twelve sections of scripture.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="5326689d-97db-4c80-b715-c82ad9426bdd" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_nu55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1016</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Pāṭaliputra</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">pA TA li pu tra</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">པཱ་ཊཱ་ལི་པུ་ཏྲ།</span></li><li class="italic">pāṭaliputra</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A city in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>; present day Patna.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="a520d09f-0cab-429d-9dea-46460cc85598" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_nud5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1017</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Patshap</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">pa tshab</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">པ་ཚབ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">The name of a Tibetan family to which belonged the renowned translator Patshap Nyima Drakpa.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="06eeafb3-6e7a-45a9-a148-46d8a8e4fd64" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_nul5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1018</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Patshap Tsultrim Gyaltsen, Tsultrim Gyaltsen</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">pa tshab tshul khrims rgyal mtshan</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">པ་ཚབ་ཚུལ་ཁྲིམས་རྒྱལ་མཚན།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">The primary translator of this scripture.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="3eeb7f6a-2dcd-4030-89bd-df482de901b4" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_nut5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1019</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">paurva</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">pau rwa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">པཽ་རྭ།</span></li><li class="italic">paurva</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A class of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8622">vidyādharas</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="43e192de-5bce-49dd-ba69-485cefe0f4bf" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_nv55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1020</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Peacock Call</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rma bya’i sgra</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྨ་བྱའི་སྒྲ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">An area in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9398">Kuru</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="039ba75c-bc93-454a-94f0-9fa26b2fed0b" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_nvd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1021</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Peacock Forest</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rma bya’i nags</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྨ་བྱའི་ནགས།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">An island in the vicinity of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="1f964bff-73e5-429a-a211-94ce0a9df997" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_nvl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1022</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Pearl</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mu tig</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མུ་ཏིག</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">An island in the vicinity of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="02ac1e5e-243d-4bc8-bd26-7c36ccc266f8" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_nvt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1023</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Pearl Stream</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mu tig ’bab pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མུ་ཏིག་འབབ་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9519">Mutual Liking</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="bc6e0567-0267-443c-88e8-1946f51adfd2" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_o055anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1024</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Pearly Sand</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mu tig gi bye ma dang ldan pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མུ་ཏིག་གི་བྱེ་མ་དང་ལྡན་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9657">Saṅkāśa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="c5ae4358-5887-4fb1-ab8b-fbb95298da6b" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_o0d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1025</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Peripheral</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">zur la gnas pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཟུར་ལ་གནས་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A realm inhabited by <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8530">garland-bearer gods</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="c56f12f3-a1a3-4d11-8f28-cc820090a120" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_o0l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1026</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">pervasive attachment</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">kun tu khyab pa’i zhen pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀུན་ཏུ་ཁྱབ་པའི་ཞེན་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A class of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8622">vidyādharas</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="28520a62-5ad3-4f69-92a1-92605be7ca2c" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_o0t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1027</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Pervasive Fragrance</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dri ’thul ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དྲི་འཐུལ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9796">Total Pleasure</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="a1478969-2a92-4ec9-9a37-9683889b7748" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_o155anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1028</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Pervasive Waters</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">chus khyab pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཆུས་ཁྱབ་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">An ocean between <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9398">Kuru</span> and <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9209">Godānīya</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="6af4c99a-3f38-484d-88d3-e794470f9260" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_o1d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1029</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Pinnacle</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rtse mo, rtse mo can</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྩེ་མོ་ཅན།, རྩེ་མོ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">(1) A river on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9657">Saṅkāśa</span> (<em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">rtse mo</em>). (2) One of four parks that surround the city of <span data-ref="UT22084-068-021-9605"><span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9605">Radiant</span></span> (<em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">rtse mo can</em>).</p></div></div></div></div><div id="02559a9d-b6dd-4119-bc9a-77e18e40ec84" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_o1l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1030</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">piśāca</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sha za</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཤ་ཟ།</span></li><li class="italic">piśāca</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p>A class of nonhuman beings that, like several other classes of nonhuman beings, take spontaneous birth. Ranking below rākṣasas, they are less powerful and more akin to pretas. They are said to dwell in impure and perilous places, where they feed on impure things, including flesh. This could account for the name <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">piśāca</em>, which possibly derives from <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">√piś</em>, to carve or chop meat, as reflected also in the Tibetan <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">sha za</em>, “meat eater.” They are often described as having an unpleasant appearance, and at times they appear with animal bodies. Some possess the ability to enter the dead bodies of humans, thereby becoming so-called <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">vetāla</em>, to touch whom is fatal.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="cdfd2eff-b741-4e12-aa20-969dc1406d7e" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_o1t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1031</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Place for Austerities</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dka’ thub dang ’brel ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དཀའ་ཐུབ་དང་འབྲེལ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">An island in the vicinity of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="3f67ccea-bbfb-4447-b081-548187a245e4" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_o255anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1032</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Place Where the Water is Enjoyed</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">chu la spyod pa’i sa gzhi</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཆུ་ལ་སྤྱོད་པའི་ས་གཞི།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A pond on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9078">Equal Peaks</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="738faba5-ea80-4801-a489-91963dc9c1bc" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_o2d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1033</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">player</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rtse ba la gnas pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྩེ་བ་ལ་གནས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">krīḍāvihārin</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A class of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8489">asuras</span> ruled by <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8729">Puṣpamāla</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="f1f5d279-930f-47d1-a9b9-4295dd9b69df" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_o2l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1034</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Playful Abandon</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bag med rnams rtse ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བག་མེད་རྣམས་རྩེ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A pond on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9078">Equal Peaks</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="fe1d2c9c-7c99-4898-9f85-df79fd1e949e" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_o2t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1035</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Playful Frolicking</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rtse dga’</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྩེ་དགའ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A lake near <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9734">Sudharma</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="20dc9819-c4d0-476f-8dcb-2294d1168c33" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_o355anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1036</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Playing the Vīṇā</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">pi wang gis rtse ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">པི་ཝང་གིས་རྩེ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A lotus grove in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8853">Blazing Splendor</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="7a74624f-e5ae-4c30-b282-1bf2d12fe822" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_o3d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1037</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Pleading</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rgyob shig pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྒྱོབ་ཤིག་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of sixteen (or seventeen) realms that surround the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8975">Crushing Hell</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="0dd3971a-ff03-4e65-9965-db9af7ffe744" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_o3l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1038</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Pleasant Breeze</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rlung bde</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རླུང་བདེ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8489">asuras</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="e72618cf-0c99-4624-abcb-d21036a17aef" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_o3t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1039</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Pleasant Humming of Bees</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bung ba’i sgra snyan</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བུང་བའི་སྒྲ་སྙན།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A realm of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8621">vessel-bearer gods</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="dff32921-7440-4bc5-94e5-7374135d8dd2" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_o455anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1040</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Pleasant Sound</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sgra snyan pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྒྲ་སྙན་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A realm of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8617">triple-lute-bearer gods</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="5e7fdc5f-3791-48d5-b8be-b0c6d4594544" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_o4d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1041</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Pleasurable Water</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’dod pa’i chu</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འདོད་པའི་ཆུ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river in the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9764">Swan Forest</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="c15cbc77-107d-455e-8bec-4a024780db97" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_o4l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1042</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Pleasure Grove of Song</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">glu dbyangs len pa’i kun dga’ ra ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གླུ་དབྱངས་ལེན་པའི་ཀུན་དགའ་ར་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A grove in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9197">Garland of Splendor</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="bb439188-c93d-4314-b068-ef82e0ddac26" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_o4t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1043</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Pleasure Grove of the Moon Vision</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">zla ba mthong bar ’dod pa’i tshal</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཟླ་བ་མཐོང་བར་འདོད་པའི་ཚལ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of the twenty-seven realms in the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9266">Heaven Free from Strife</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="b7f35561-a482-4fb9-917c-0c019255ce91" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_o555anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1044</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Pleasure Grove Park</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">kun dga’ ra ba’i skyed mos tshal</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀུན་དགའ་ར་བའི་སྐྱེད་མོས་ཚལ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A park in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9296">House of Refined Gold</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="83a23d1e-0be2-482f-8e03-c4a688a16c1d" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_o5d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1045</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Plow</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gshol mda’ ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གཤོལ་མདའ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">An island in the vicinity of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="6a33f0b0-eb6f-4616-8c57-4f07202d0d7f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_o5l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1046</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Plumes of Fire</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">me’i spyi gtsug lta bu</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མེའི་སྤྱི་གཙུག་ལྟ་བུ།</span></li><li class="italic">agnicūḍaka</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A realm that neighbors the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9278">Hell of Intense Heat</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="4305074b-9011-48f3-ba17-04283c99997c" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_o5t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1047</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Pond</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mtshe’u</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མཚེའུ།</span></li><li class="italic">taḍāga</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of sixteen realms that surround the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9630">Reviving Hell</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="8fe59660-30b9-48b3-941b-f502850c23e9" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_o655anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1048</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Pond Garland</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rdzing bu’i phreng ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྫིང་བུའི་ཕྲེང་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A lake on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9078">Equal Peaks</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="5f8626fa-958d-4a31-8548-e77a63672b5a" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_o6d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1049</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Ponds in Delightful Pleasure Gardens</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">kun dga’ ra ba bde bar gnas pa’i lteng ka</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀུན་དགའ་ར་བ་བདེ་བར་གནས་པའི་ལྟེང་ཀ</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9033">Dwelling on Forest Riverbanks</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="1b47e7db-8873-4df2-bb02-010692da6772" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_o6l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1050</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">ponds of beauty</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">lteng ka sdug gu</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ལྟེང་ཀ་སྡུག་གུ</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A class of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8489">asuras</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="89c7f5df-0697-46cf-bbc0-d7584779f852" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_o6t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1051</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Porridge</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">skyo ma</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྐྱོ་མ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">An ocean between <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9209">Godānīya</span> and <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9847">Videha</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="c0523575-c054-48f2-bcc1-f8142dea32b6" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_o755anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1052</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Possessor of Excellent Conduct</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">legs spyod ldan</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ལེགས་སྤྱོད་ལྡན།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A previous ruler of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9276">Heaven of the Thirty-Three</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="0bf49179-e886-4f69-b942-88121cfaeb15" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_o7d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1053</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Possessor of Reeds</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">be tra can</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བེ་ཏྲ་ཅན།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river to the south of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="6afc2d85-a870-4437-b60c-230254375bf8" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_o7l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1054</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Power of Past Smoke</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sngon gyi du ba’i stobs</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྔོན་གྱི་དུ་བའི་སྟོབས།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9657">Saṅkāśa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="e417830d-a2e5-492f-badc-05efdd96639f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_o7t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1055</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">power of space</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">nam mkha’i stobs</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ནམ་མཁའི་སྟོབས།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A class of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8622">vidyādharas</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="f9ba8f1c-1177-4b5f-9f30-7ed57f563955" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_o855anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1056</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Powerful</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">shugs dang ldan pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཤུགས་དང་ལྡན་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river to the south of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="4625703a-77a9-4162-95ae-c7bd2069f246" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_o8d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1057</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Powerful Luminous Retreat</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dben ’gro dbang po’i ’od</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དབེན་འགྲོ་དབང་པོའི་འོད།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A lake near <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9734">Sudharma</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="0d0effbc-b87e-4444-a79b-b87167dea4d3" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_o8l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1058</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Prabhāvatī</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’od dang ldan pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འོད་དང་ལྡན་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">prabhāvatī</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A previous ruler of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9276">Heaven of the Thirty-Three</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="649afa17-8a4b-4d36-aca2-eaecd9cc8547" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_o8t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1059</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Pramatha</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rab ’joms</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རབ་འཇོམས།</span></li><li class="italic">pramatha</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">An unvirtuous <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8562">nāga</span> king.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="af01dc52-d9b2-4ee3-a7f2-9a4e167de8b8" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_o955anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1060</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Praśānta</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rab tu zhi ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རབ་ཏུ་ཞི་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">praśānta</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">Lord of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9269">Heaven of Joy</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="82729ec9-de52-4245-ab08-27c8c3447e2c" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_o9d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1061</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">prātimokṣa</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">so sor thar pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སོ་སོར་ཐར་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">prātimokṣa</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition"> “<span class="ignore">Prātimokṣa</span>” is the name given to the code of conduct binding on monks and nuns. The term can be used to refer both to the disciplinary rules themselves and to the texts from the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9974">Vinaya</span> that contain them. There are multiple recensions of the <cite class="title break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN"><span class="ignore">Prātimokṣa</span></cite>, each transmitted by a different monastic fraternity in ancient and medieval India. Three remain living traditions, one of them the Mūlasarvāstivāda <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9974">Vinaya</span> of Tibetan Buddhism. Though the numbers of rules vary across the different recensions, they are all organized according to the same principles and with the same disciplinary categories. It is customary for monastics to recite the <cite class="title break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN"><span class="ignore">Prātimokṣa</span><span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9986"> Sūtra</span></cite><span class="ref-pending" data-href="https://read.84000.co/translation/toh2.html"/> fortnightly. </p></div></div></div></div><div id="3d8daf49-bcb5-46c6-9e6c-bd6756a1eb52" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_o9l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1062</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Precious Arch</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">nor bu’i rta babs</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ནོར་བུའི་རྟ་བབས།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9209">Godānīya</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="e2d5eac5-c830-45d8-acd6-2d31e96ed1ee" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_o9t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1063</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Precious Ground</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rin po che’i sa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རིན་པོ་ཆེའི་ས།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A grove in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9034">Dwelling on Mixed Riverbanks</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="86230d81-c385-45ed-b3d2-43038205ca9c" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_oa55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1064</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Precious Rain</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rin chen char ’bebs</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རིན་ཆེན་ཆར་འབེབས།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of the seven golden mountains that surround Mount <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9739">Sumeru</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="a42d7c04-a0c6-4f9e-9ffd-926245f81a6a" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_oad5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1065</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Precipices and Abysses</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ngam grog dang g.yang sa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ངམ་གྲོག་དང་གཡང་ས།</span></li><li class="italic">śvabhraprapāta</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A place in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9279">Ultimate Torment</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="3209b8f4-19b7-4b45-8a6d-a3d43473c1c2" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_oal5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1066</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Prikṣikā</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">pri Shi kA</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">པྲི་ཥི་ཀཱ།</span></li><li class="italic">prikṣikā</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A land to the north of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="c8e1b45b-2453-4581-b477-bebf2da33abe" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_oat5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1067</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Profound</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">zab pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཟབ་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">gambhīra</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">The residence of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8489">asura</span> king <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8729">Puṣpamāla</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="f2d79a05-6a80-4ca3-91f5-d3ab76fe3e95" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ob55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1068</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Promotion</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sbyor ba la ’jug pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྦྱོར་བ་ལ་འཇུག་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">yogāvaha</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A realm in the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9276">Heaven of the Thirty-Three</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="da7eb0c9-a0db-4215-baf1-1d4e1ce8c774" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_obd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1069</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">prophecies</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">lung du bstan pa’i sde</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ལུང་དུ་བསྟན་པའི་སྡེ།</span></li><li class="italic">vyākaraṇa</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One among the twelve sections of scripture.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="1d819a3f-14d5-4855-9685-222b8bf3a95f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_obl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1070</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Pulindo</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">pu lin do</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">པུ་ལིན་དོ།</span></li><li class="italic">pulindo</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A land to the north of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="e54c97e8-3076-4ffb-94c5-3d20dd673e44" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_obt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1071</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Pūraṇa</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rdzogs byed</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྫོགས་བྱེད།</span></li><li class="italic">pūraṇa</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">Extremist teacher at the time of the Buddha</p></div></div></div></div><div id="b45c9a7a-962e-4245-9e53-149deacfdbc6" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_oc55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1072</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">pure abodes</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gnas gtsang ma’i ris</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གནས་གཙང་མའི་རིས།</span></li><li class="italic">śuddhāvāsa</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">Realms associated the fourth <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9969">concentration</span> into which only noble beings are born.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="7219540f-f47d-40cc-a2b8-cad5b3fe17da" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ocd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1073</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">pure conduct</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">tshang par spyod pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཚང་པར་སྤྱོད་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">brahmacārya</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A celibate lifestyle focused on spiritual pursuits.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="4e2e5162-9d58-4d8f-8c26-559f3950bec4" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ocl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1074</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Pure Direction</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">phyogs gtsang ma</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཕྱོགས་གཙང་མ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9869">White Body</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="905c8581-c2a6-4f4f-979c-10eb3b0681a6" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_oct5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1075</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">purposeful expressions</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ched du brjod pa’i sde</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཆེད་དུ་བརྗོད་པའི་སྡེ།</span></li><li class="italic">udāna</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One among the twelve sections of scripture.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="a2cf5b1f-ef9d-4903-ac37-7b9ec62990df" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_od55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1076</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Puṣpamāla</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">me tog phreng</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མེ་ཏོག་ཕྲེང་།</span></li><li class="italic">puṣpamāla</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">King on the third level of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8489">asuras</span>, <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9087">Excellent Abode</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="6d782d24-6565-49f0-b921-2496b9634565" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_odd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1077</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Radiant</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’od can, ’od ’phro ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འོད་ཅན།, འོད་འཕྲོ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">(1) Celestial city occupied by <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8731">Rāhu</span>, king of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8489">asuras</span> (<em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">’od can</em>). (2) A forest on the lower level of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9417">Living on the Peak</span> (<em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">’od ’phro ba </em>).</p></div></div></div></div><div id="0e82cb06-c158-41b9-9e69-60026f01328a" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_odl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1078</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Radiant Streams</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">chu klung ’od ’byin</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཆུ་ཀླུང་འོད་འབྱིན།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9511">Moving in Vast Environments</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="7753a90f-1fbc-496c-a768-753a1a8f1412" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_odt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1079</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Rāhu</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sgra can, sgra gcan</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྒྲ་གཅན།, སྒྲ་ཅན།</span></li><li class="italic">rāhu</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">An <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8489">asura</span> king.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="06cfc474-eb9a-4a14-8928-77aca3e176e6" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_oe55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1080</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Rain of Burning Stones</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rdo me ’bar ba char ltar ’bab pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྡོ་མེ་འབར་བ་ཆར་ལྟར་འབབ་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of sixteen realms that surround the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9298">Howling Hell</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="f064b151-88cb-4ab1-9ede-d64a7a710654" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_oed5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1081</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Rain of Jambu Gold</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’dzam bu na da char ’bebs</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འཛམ་བུ་ན་ད་ཆར་འབེབས།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8866">Born in a Lap</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="6f3f7fc6-be4f-4826-893b-9c656936e0ab" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_oel5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1082</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Rain of Weapons</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mtshon ’bab pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མཚོན་འབབ་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">śastrasāmpāti</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of sixteen realms that surround the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9630">Reviving Hell</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="7cafc4d7-7e87-4f63-a54a-f0278790a80d" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_oet5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1083</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Rain River</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">char dang char gyi rjes su ’byung ba’i chu klung</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཆར་དང་ཆར་གྱི་རྗེས་སུ་འབྱུང་བའི་ཆུ་ཀླུང་།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9657">Saṅkāśa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="d1537ccc-2fde-4f33-82a7-ea483c9593d9" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_of55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1084</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Rainfall</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">char ’bebs</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཆར་འབེབས།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A virtuous <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8562">nāga</span> king.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="a5d6cdd3-67d3-4718-a63d-0028f40baee2" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ofd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1085</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Rājagṛha</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rgyal po’i khab</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྒྱལ་པོའི་ཁབ།</span></li><li class="italic">rājagṛha</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p>The ancient capital of Magadha prior to its relocation to Pāṭaliputra during the Mauryan dynasty, Rājagṛha is one of the most important locations in Buddhist history. The literature tells us that the Buddha and his saṅgha spent a considerable amount of time in residence in and around Rājagṛha‍—in nearby places, such as the Vulture Peak Mountain (Gṛdhrakūṭaparvata), a major site of the Mahāyāna sūtras, and the Bamboo Grove (Veṇuvana)‍—enjoying the patronage of King Bimbisāra and then of his son King Ajātaśatru. Rājagṛha is also remembered as the location where the first Buddhist monastic council was held after the Buddha Śākyamuni passed into parinirvāṇa. Now known as Rajgir and located in the modern Indian state of Bihar.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="49187835-c54b-429a-9eb0-87d756187fd9" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ofl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1086</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Rājanina</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rA dza ni na</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རཱ་ཛ་ནི་ན།</span></li><li class="italic">rājanina</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A lake in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9413">Living by Rājanina</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="b21f414a-955c-4574-a5e2-4dfc51ccfb88" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_oft5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1087</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">rākṣasa, rākṣasa/rākṣasī, rākṣasī</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">srin mo, srin po</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྲིན་པོ།, སྲིན་མོ།</span></li><li class="italic">rākṣasa, rākṣasī</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p>A class of nonhuman beings that are often, but certainly not always, considered demonic in the Buddhist tradition. They are often depicted as flesh-eating monsters who haunt frightening places and are ugly and evil-natured with a yearning for human flesh, and who additionally have miraculous powers, such as being able to change their appearance.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="4b8909e7-501c-4557-9629-a34e5f2a025d" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_og55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1088</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Rāmā</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rA ma</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རཱ་མ།</span></li><li class="italic">rāmā</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8581">rākṣasī</span> living on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8813">Ardhamaru</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="1dd25731-ca1a-41d6-8bc5-e3d2888ecfd0" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ogd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1089</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Rāmapāla</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ne bai pA la, rA ma phA la</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ནེ་བཻ་པཱ་ལ།, རཱ་མ་ཕཱ་ལ།</span></li><li class="italic">rāmapāla</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">(1) A king of the Pāla dynasty who ruled from 1077–1120 <span class="small-caps">ᴄᴇ</span> (<em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">rA ma phA la</em>). (2) The alternate spelling, <em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">ne bai pA la</em>, is tentatively identified to be the very same king of the Pāla dynasty. See <a href="end-notes.xhtml#UT22084-068-021-8447" data-pointer-type="id">n.640</a>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="77ab151e-ee21-426d-9fe3-826a2194d60f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ogl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1090</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Ramayo</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ra ma yo</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ར་མ་ཡོ།</span></li><li class="italic">ramayo</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A sea to the west of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="9b704838-9f50-4caa-a288-3efd9be9860c" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ogt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1091</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Raven Mouths</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bya rog kha</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བྱ་རོག་ཁ།</span></li><li class="italic">kākāsyaka</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of sixteen realms that surround the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9279">Hell of Ultimate Torment</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="04427c94-4845-458a-86d7-a0c73b723e8c" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_oh55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1092</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Raven’s Belly</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bya rog lto</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བྱ་རོག་ལྟོ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of sixteen realms that surround the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9279">Hell of Ultimate Torment</span>. Also called <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8845">Black Belly</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="76d0e7a3-9382-45c1-b5c2-9954ef579cdb" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ohd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1093</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Ravens with Vajra-Like Beaks</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">khwa’i chu rdo rje lta bu</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཁྭའི་ཆུ་རྡོ་རྗེ་ལྟ་བུ།</span></li><li class="italic">vajra­vāyasa­tuṇḍa</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of sixteen realms that surround the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9235">Great Howling Hell</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="ff8539fc-1f2d-4265-baad-8433a0b1dc30" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ohl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1094</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Ravens’ Peak</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">khwa spungs</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཁྭ་སྤུངས།</span></li><li class="italic">vāyasakūṭa</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain in the hell called <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9859">Wailer</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="0e1f9b7a-915d-4d6d-8123-4e54f6da60e0" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_oht5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1095</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">reality</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">de kho na nyid, de nyid</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དེ་ཁོ་ན་ཉིད།, དེ་ཉིད།</span></li><li class="italic">tattva</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">Literally “thatness.” This term refers to the ultimate nature of things, the way things are in <span class="ignore">reality</span>.</p><p class="definition">Note that the term “reality” has also been used to render terms of similar meaning such as <em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">yang dag nyid</em> and others.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="46a75ee1-0292-48b5-8944-e2558c4ca296" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_oi55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1096</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Red</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dmar po</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དམར་པོ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">(1) An ocean between <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9847">Videha</span> and <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>. (2) An ocean off <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>. (3) A river in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>. (4) An ephemeral hell to the north of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="019447fb-d77d-4fb5-8d90-3c08cf699525" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_oid5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1097</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Red City</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">grong khyer dmar gnas</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གྲོང་ཁྱེར་དམར་གནས།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A realm of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8516">ever-infatuated gods</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="b4cc6b7a-fb37-4274-a1d2-88750b8dd8f5" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_oil5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1098</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Red Conches and Pearls</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dung dang mu tig dmar po</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དུང་དང་མུ་ཏིག་དམར་པོ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">An island in the vicinity of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="677b43c5-d5e2-4ba8-b0fa-bfa64556f253" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_oit5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1099</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Red Forest</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">nags dmar po</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ནགས་དམར་པོ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9506">Moving in Mixed Environments</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="e77034fd-5d2d-4d56-8aa9-7bf223177bf1" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_oj55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1100</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Red Water</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">chu dmar pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཆུ་དམར་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">An ocean between <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9209">Godānīya</span> and <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9847">Videha</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="8d7dd6c3-88c2-41ba-bad0-71bed3ab21e0" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ojd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1101</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">red-eyed ones</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mig dpar ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མིག་དཔར་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A class of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8489">asuras</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="b429a3e3-6d29-43c4-9613-136ef5e7328d" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ojl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1102</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Relentless Torments</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gnod pa rnam par m zhi ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གནོད་པ་རྣམ་པར་མ་ཞི་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">kāraṇāvyuparama</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of sixteen realms that surround the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9630">Reviving Hell</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="4657a0df-c791-4246-bd5a-62253163d158" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ojt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1103</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Reliever of the Sweaty</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rngul ba ngal so ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྔུལ་བ་ངལ་སོ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A lake on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9078">Equal Peaks</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="e83236a1-afb3-4871-8501-751cafcef26e" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ok55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1104</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Resembling a Great Lotus</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">pad ma chen po lta bu</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">པད་མ་ཆེན་པོ་ལྟ་བུ།</span></li><li class="italic">kumuda, mahāpaduma</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of the sixteen realms that surround the <span><span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9277">Hell of Heat</span></span>. </p></div></div></div></div><div id="63e74d5f-68e6-4c08-a3d8-e17ab2406dd2" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_okd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1105</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Resembling the Full Moon</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">zla ba’i gnas ltar nya ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཟླ་བའི་གནས་ལྟར་ཉ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A realm in the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9276">Heaven of the Thirty-Three</span>. Also called <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9512">Moving Like the Moon</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="2b83c8a3-eb4b-4de6-b505-7aded3575fb3" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_okl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1106</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Resembling White Lotuses</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">pad ma dkar po lta bu</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">པད་མ་དཀར་པོ་ལྟ་བུ།</span></li><li class="italic">puṇḍarīka</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of the sixteen realms that surround the <span><span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9277">Hell of Heat</span></span>. </p></div></div></div></div><div id="70795082-a117-49c2-a932-914251905687" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_okt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1107</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Resplendent</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rnam par skra ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྣམ་པར་སྐྲ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">King of the peafowl.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="05169396-5cdc-4c4e-8bc7-c4aa94020847" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ol55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1108</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Retinue</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’khor</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འཁོར།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A realm of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8617">triple-lute-bearer gods</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="686b99cb-08b7-4221-bf62-e71f4c13780e" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_old5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1109</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Reviving, Reviving Hell</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">yang sos</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཡང་སོས།</span></li><li class="italic">saṃjīvana</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of the eight hot hells.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="388c3383-2287-4a0b-8b33-9c5870b98638" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_oll5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1110</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Rice-Milk Mud</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’o thug gi ’dam</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འོ་ཐུག་གི་འདམ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9657">Saṅkāśa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="5cfb4573-1d57-465b-a83d-b7973c3fb124" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_olt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1111</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Rich and Dark Shade</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">grib ma snum zhing nag pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གྲིབ་མ་སྣུམ་ཞིང་ནག་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8956">Continuous Movement</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="5c322113-8a21-40da-839e-19114069ab8d" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_om55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1112</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Ripe Vessel</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">smin pa’i snod</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྨིན་པའི་སྣོད།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A town in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9847">Videha</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="e6c5ad9a-9509-4706-9d6f-5fad607030a7" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_omd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1113</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">ripening</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rnam par smin pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྣམ་པར་སྨིན་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">vipāka</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">The resultant maturation of karmic actions and the manifestation of their effects. See also <a href="end-notes.xhtml#UT22084-068-021-614" data-pointer-type="id">n.60</a>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="667869f1-7457-4b0a-a70e-6fbec7091e66" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_oml5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1114</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Ripping of All Vital Points</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gnad dang gnad gcod pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གནད་དང་གནད་གཅོད་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">marma­marma­nikṛntana</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of sixteen realms that surround the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8975">Crushing Hell</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="681fc737-9ab7-46f9-805b-0ebdbe2869fd" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_omt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1115</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Rising</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">shar ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཤར་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain in the eastern sea beyond <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="16db1aad-7d27-4d90-80c4-60d0d8e2a055" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_on55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1116</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">River of a Thousand Flows</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">chu bo stong ’bab</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཆུ་བོ་སྟོང་འབབ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9031">Dwelling in the Lofty</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="4859c6a1-c35a-46a9-bc9a-40a203849657" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ond5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1117</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">River of Carelessness</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bag med pa’i chu</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བག་མེད་པའི་ཆུ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river in <span><span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9203">Garlands of Flowers</span></span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="d9d2aa00-059c-418e-b61f-4b9eca076ae2" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_onl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1118</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">River of Enjoyments</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">chu bo dga’ bcas</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཆུ་བོ་དགའ་བཅས།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9031">Dwelling in the Lofty</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="08d00dba-0310-4757-b621-8af09b62c473" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ont5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1119</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">River of Free Flow</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">chu bo gar dgar ’bab</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཆུ་བོ་གར་དགར་འབབ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9031">Dwelling in the Lofty</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="14b2796a-a665-4639-8789-56fc9150fbf0" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_oo55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1120</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">River of Great Enjoyments</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">chu bo dga’ bcas che</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཆུ་བོ་དགའ་བཅས་ཆེ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9031">Dwelling in the Lofty</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="5e7926a6-4718-47b5-9c11-dfa15d7b17fd" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ood5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1121</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">River of Layered Flows</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">chu bo brtsegs ’bab</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཆུ་བོ་བརྩེགས་འབབ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9031">Dwelling in the Lofty</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="8a626cd3-0bc7-43b7-b1e6-e3786ae9ab03" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ool5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1122</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">River of Strong Current</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">chu bo shugs chen ’bab</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཆུ་བོ་ཤུགས་ཆེན་འབབ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9031">Dwelling in the Lofty</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="46a1cdbe-908f-4716-82c3-906d48ebf117" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_oot5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1123</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">River of Strong Garlands</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">chu bo shugs phreng</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཆུ་བོ་ཤུགས་ཕྲེང་།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9031">Dwelling in the Lofty</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="a1dce162-1b67-4757-a509-528d0845ffd3" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_op55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1124</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">River of Sweet Taste</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">chu bo ro zhim</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཆུ་བོ་རོ་ཞིམ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9031">Dwelling in the Lofty</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="3d7dabcf-afe2-43f7-9be4-8156245c101e" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_opd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1125</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">River of Wine</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">chang ’bab chu bo</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཆང་འབབ་ཆུ་བོ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9072">Enjoyment of Scents</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="a1e55db0-4fc0-43b8-9e66-d72aceb3eb75" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_opl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1126</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Rivers and Flatlands</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">chu bo sman ljong</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཆུ་བོ་སྨན་ལྗོང་།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A peak upon Mount <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9739">Sumeru</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="fe0a864a-50ca-4095-a8ef-d4b7c5fe19a1" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_opt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1127</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Roadless</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">lam med pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ལམ་མེད་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">An island in the vicinity of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="23e1e1b4-9143-4b6a-93e7-573584170f6a" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_oq55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1128</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">roamers</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rab tu rgyug pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རབ་ཏུ་རྒྱུག་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A class of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8489">asuras</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="e89e642c-711c-4427-8222-b59b4f8124d8" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_oqd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1129</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Roaming Sumeru</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ri rab tu rgyu ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རི་རབ་ཏུ་རྒྱུ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A land in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9209">Godānīya</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="ae057bd0-ea71-4c06-8f06-84748e84a009" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_oql5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1130</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">roaming the cimiśa cave</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">tsi mi sha’i phug na rgyu ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཙི་མི་ཤའི་ཕུག་ན་རྒྱུ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A class of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8622">vidyādharas</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="c68ca57b-0dbb-4b5e-b448-ec860003b0a4" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_oqt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1131</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Roaring Flow</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’u ru ru’i sgras ’bab pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འུ་རུ་རུའི་སྒྲས་འབབ་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9657">Saṅkāśa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="6bfca0de-d3f4-4120-95bd-6d03ee9356c3" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_or55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1132</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Rohina</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ro hi na</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རོ་ཧི་ན།</span></li><li class="italic">rohina</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A virtuous <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8562">nāga</span> king.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="01a64432-0f60-4635-817c-7dc562ea7336" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ord5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1133</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Ruby Forest</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">pad ma rA ga’i nags</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">པད་མ་རཱ་གའི་ནགས།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9506">Moving in Mixed Environments</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="608b2867-1c5a-4410-b6f7-796329dea4c3" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_orl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1134</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">runners</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">kun tu rgyug pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀུན་ཏུ་རྒྱུག་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A class of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8489">asuras</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="79dc4f82-a092-4a67-a0e5-1d0d4043e9ae" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ort5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1135</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Śaci</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bde sogs</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བདེ་སོགས།</span></li><li class="italic">śaci</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">The wife of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8738">Śakra</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="9d0cd01b-53db-406e-ab5b-8a4facf5afd3" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_os55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1136</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">sage</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">drang srong</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དྲང་སྲོང་།</span></li><li class="italic">ṛṣi</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">Indian <span class="ignore">sage</span> or wise man, often a wandering ascetic or hermit; <em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">drang srong</em> is literally “the righteous one.” “Great <span class="ignore">sage</span>” is sometimes also used as a specific epithet of the buddhas.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="77d5f4a8-d3a2-4bf4-94a8-6cbf8d645d7e" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_osd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1137</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Sagely Joy</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">drang srong dga’ ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དྲང་སྲོང་དགའ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9128">Flocking Peacocks</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="64966d46-03d8-4b8e-959a-b9436ed44e97" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_osl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1138</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Śakā</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sh kA</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཤ་ཀཱ།</span></li><li class="italic">śakā</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A land to the north of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="c46473a9-c71c-4bc8-afb8-4c7b3d3f7bdb" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ost5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1139</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Śakra</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">brgya byin</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བརྒྱ་བྱིན།</span></li><li class="italic">śakra</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">The lord of the gods in the Heaven of the Thirty-Three (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">trāyastriṃśa</em>). Alternatively known as Indra, the deity that is called “lord of the gods” dwells on the summit of Mount Sumeru and wields the thunderbolt. The Tibetan translation <em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">brgya byin</em> (meaning “one hundred sacrifices”) is based on an etymology that <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">śakra</em> is an abbreviation of <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">śata-kratu</em>, one who has performed a hundred sacrifices. Each world with a central Sumeru has a Śakra. Also known by other names such as Kauśika, Devendra, and Śacipati. </p><p class="definition">Also mentioned in this text as <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8697">Kauśika</span> and as <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9910">Indra</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="3ec44d80-00e7-44f6-8e2b-c0a695dbf71e" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ot55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1140</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Śākya</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">shAkya</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཤཱཀྱ།</span></li><li class="italic">śākya</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p>Name of the ancient tribe in which the Buddha was born as a prince; their kingdom was based to the east of Kośala, in the foothills near the present-day border of India and Nepal, with Kapilavastu as its capital.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="42a1f95e-b362-4157-9e3d-02daeff06b02" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_otd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1141</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Śākya followers</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">shAkya pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཤཱཀྱ་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">In the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9986">sūtra</span> this term used by <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8567">non-Buddhists</span> to refer to Buddhists.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="aafd3f3f-d16d-4507-a177-f9eb18db6838" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_otl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1142</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Śākyamuni</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">shAkya thub pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཤཱཀྱ་ཐུབ་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">śākyamuni</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p>An epithet for the historical Buddha, Siddhārtha Gautama: he was a <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">muni</em> (“sage”) from the Śākya clan. He is counted as the fourth of the first four buddhas of the present Good Eon, the other three being Krakucchanda, Kanakamuni, and Kāśyapa. He will be followed by Maitreya, the next buddha in this eon.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="10359430-2efe-4d8d-b059-ec2dfc31c2d5" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ott5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1143</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Śakyarakṣita</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">shAkya rak+Shi ta</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཤཱཀྱ་རཀྵི་ཏ།</span></li><li class="italic">śakyarakṣita</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">An Indian <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8569">paṇḍita</span> involved in translating this <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9986">sūtra</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="990c20a5-fbc4-4679-b05d-ddf7419a9d05" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ou55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1144</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Salty</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">lan tshwa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ལན་ཚྭ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A sea between <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9847">Videha</span> and <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span></p></div></div></div></div><div id="f4046269-d811-4c4f-b3c9-e32a991c2b45" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_oud5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1145</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Sāmreḍā</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sA mre DA</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སཱ་མྲེ་ཌཱ།</span></li><li class="italic">sāmreḍā</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9241">Great Slope</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="fb9dab49-6166-48f2-acd9-5fa54afa2dfe" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_oul5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1146</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Sandy Stretch</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bye ma’i gnas skabs</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བྱེ་མའི་གནས་སྐབས།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">An area between <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9209">Godānīya</span> and <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9847">Videha</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="33bbef90-36f8-48a5-8674-e0dfe1b55ebe" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_out5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1147</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Saṅkāśa</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">saM kA sha, sang kA sha, sang kA sha kA</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སང་ཀཱ་ཤ་ཀཱ།, སང་ཀཱ་ཤ།, སཾ་ཀཱ་ཤ།</span></li><li class="italic">saṅkāśa</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9398">Kuru</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="30ed045a-ee86-4311-bb33-84f5a2b57370" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ov55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1148</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Śāntākaragupta</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">shAn+ta A ka ra gup+ta</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཤཱནྟ་ཨཱ་ཀ་ར་གུཔྟ།</span></li><li class="italic">śāntākaragupta</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">An Indian <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8569">paṇḍita</span> involved in translating this <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9986">sūtra</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="8bd7df56-011b-498d-9923-d82d6d986b03" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ovd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1149</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Sānu</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sA nu</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སཱ་ནུ།</span></li><li class="italic">sānu</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A lake on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9078">Equal Peaks</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="90595c27-647b-468e-ba6a-e97b46601b4b" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ovl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1150</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Sāra</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sA ra</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སཱ་ར།</span></li><li class="italic">sāra</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain in the sea west of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="b34f8e95-5fc9-44c9-8e45-f4587adea677" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ovt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1151</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Śāradvatīputra</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sha ra dwa ti’i bu</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཤ་ར་དྭ་ཏིའི་བུ།</span></li><li class="italic">śāradvatīputra</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">More widely known as Śāriputra‍—the contracted version of his name‍—he was one of the Buddha’s foremost <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8536">hearer</span> disciples. Renowned for his pure discipline and unparalleled knowledge of the teachings.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="274c6c83-54e4-4fda-8b1a-9c8d72bb3d2f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_p055anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1152</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Saumya</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">so’u myo</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སོའུ་མྱོ།</span></li><li class="italic">saumya</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A previous ruler of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9266">Heaven Free from Strife</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="3171d914-7e8c-4d8c-a95d-519ad15acad6" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_p0d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1153</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Scattered Stones</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rdo ba ’drim pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྡོ་བ་འདྲིམ་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9823">Upward Ocean</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="75fbb302-f811-4c27-9aaa-7a6d3ac18465" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_p0l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1154</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">scent of constant inebriation</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rtag tu myos pa’i dri</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྟག་ཏུ་མྱོས་པའི་དྲི།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A class of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8622">vidyādharas</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="2b7a536e-1376-4304-bde2-01295654a4cb" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_p0t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1155</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Scream</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sgra chen po</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྒྲ་ཆེན་པོ།</span></li><li class="italic">mahānināda</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of sixteen realms that surround the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9298">Howling Hell</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="5df25171-2a06-475b-ad9a-4715168560e3" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_p155anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1156</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Screams Everywhere</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">thams cad sgra ’byin pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཐམས་ཅད་སྒྲ་འབྱིན་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of sixteen realms that surround the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9298">Howling Hell</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="1beb40e8-4aff-4ddd-8569-9281860bd065" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_p1d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1157</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Seasonal Joy</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dus na dga’ ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དུས་ན་དགའ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9398">Kuru</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="092bc608-d468-45ba-845e-ce30f3367e19" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_p1l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1158</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Second China</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rgya nag gzhan</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྒྱ་ནག་གཞན།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A land to the north of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="7e8f3671-10b8-42cd-9b40-d1701f014516" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_p1t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1159</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Secret Play</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gsang ba rtse dga’ ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གསང་བ་རྩེ་དགའ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9657">Saṅkāśa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="55a5cbe4-e7d5-4984-9320-02d75975fbd9" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_p255anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1160</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Seeing the Head</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mgo bo mthong ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མགོ་བོ་མཐོང་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A pond on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9078">Equal Peaks</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="c7c2f448-a5d6-464d-bac9-fd6ce4df39bb" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_p2d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1161</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Seeing Thousands</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">stong du mthong ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྟོང་དུ་མཐོང་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A lotus pond on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9013">Draped in Light Rays</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="0e4a9e08-709e-4b7d-add1-f32fe3d31a3f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_p2l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1162</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">sense source</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">skye mched</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྐྱེ་མཆེད།</span></li><li class="italic">āyatana</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p>These can be listed as twelve or as six sense sources (sometimes also called sense fields, bases of cognition, or simply āyatanas).</p><p>In the context of epistemology, it is one way of describing experience and the world in terms of twelve sense sources, which can be divided into inner and outer sense sources, namely: (1–2) eye and form, (3–4) ear and sound, (5–6) nose and odor, (7–8) tongue and taste, (9–10) body and touch, (11–12) mind and mental phenomena.</p><p>In the context of the twelve links of dependent origination, only six sense sources are mentioned, and they are the inner sense sources (identical to the six faculties) of eye, ear, nose, tongue, body, and mind.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="5253918f-78fd-4377-8948-c53814d43175" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_p2t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1163</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Serene</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rab tu gtum pa ma yin pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རབ་ཏུ་གཏུམ་པ་མ་ཡིན་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A ruler of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9266">Heaven Free from Strife</span>. Also called <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8744">Serene Form</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="bedce585-a139-421e-8abe-18d597a67bf1" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_p355anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1164</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Serene Form</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rab tu gtum pa ma yin pa’i gzugs</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རབ་ཏུ་གཏུམ་པ་མ་ཡིན་པའི་གཟུགས།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">Alternative name for <span><span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8743">Serene</span></span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="10063a64-77fd-41a9-b9fa-f8620b9d7f70" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_p3d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1165</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">seven branches of awakening</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">byang chub kyi yan lag bdun</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བྱང་ཆུབ་ཀྱི་ཡན་ལག་བདུན།</span></li><li class="italic">saptabodhyaṅga</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">The seven factors that constitute the path of seeing, namely: mindfulness, investigation, diligence, joy, agility, absorption, and equanimity. These are further explained in this text; see <a href="UT22084-068-021-section-6.xhtml#UT22084-068-021-4039" data-pointer-type="id">4.B.1097</a>–<a href="UT22084-068-021-section-6.xhtml#UT22084-068-021-4043" data-pointer-type="id">4.B.1101</a>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="3da99f50-6694-4e86-af93-8ec6dc46b21f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_p3l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1166</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">seven precious substances</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rin po che’i rdzas bdun</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རིན་པོ་ཆེའི་རྫས་བདུན།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p>The set of seven precious materials or substances includes a range of precious metals and gems, but their exact list varies. The set often consists of gold, silver, beryl, crystal, red pearls, emeralds, and white coral, but may also contain lapis lazuli, ruby, sapphire, chrysoberyl, diamonds, etc. The term is frequently used in the sūtras to exemplify preciousness, wealth, and beauty, and can describe treasures, offering materials, or the features of architectural structures such as stūpas, palaces, thrones, etc. The set is also used to describe the beauty and prosperity of buddha realms and the realms of the gods.</p><p>In other contexts, the term <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">saptaratna</em> can also refer to the seven precious possessions of a cakravartin or to a set of seven precious moral qualities. </p></div></div></div></div><div id="2e584dd3-ca07-4474-8fa7-3d18dd382323" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_p3t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1167</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">seven sages</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">drang srong bdun</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དྲང་སྲོང་བདུན།</span></li><li class="italic">saptarṣi</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">Refers to the seven stars of the Big Dipper, the names of which are derived from the names of the <span class="ignore">seven sages</span> (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">saptarṣi</em>) of the Vedic tradition.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="2a14dc53-a31c-4b0a-99d8-368aae405a5a" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_p455anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1168</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">seven treasures</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rin po che sna bdun</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རིན་པོ་ཆེ་སྣ་བདུན།</span></li><li class="italic">saptaratna</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">Seven possessions of a universal monarch: the precious lady, precious jewel, precious wheel, precious elephant, precious horse, precious minister, and precious general or, as described in this text, precious master of the household. See also the detailed description in <a href="UT22084-068-021-chapter-1.xhtml#UT22084-068-021-145" data-pointer-type="id">1.96</a>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="fc4d8590-0236-437d-96f1-f2dd19ce9784" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_p4d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1169</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Seven-Headed</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mgo bdun pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མགོ་བདུན་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A virtuous <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8562">nāga</span> king. </p></div></div></div></div><div id="b9db826d-bfc2-49ef-a9b0-bbe70bf16d26" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_p4l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1170</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">sexual misconduct</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’dod pas log par g.yem pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འདོད་པས་ལོག་པར་གཡེམ་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">kāma­mithyā­caryā</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">The third among the three physical misdeeds.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="959530dc-b2ef-4c40-86d0-fb6988faee7d" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_p4t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1171</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Shaded by Garlands</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’phreng ba’i grib ma</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འཕྲེང་བའི་གྲིབ་མ།</span></li><li class="italic">mālācchāyā</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A realm in the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9276">Heaven of the Thirty-Three</span> and the name of a tree that grows there.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="2beaf127-2e4b-4d3d-90e8-a926d1724902" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_p555anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1172</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Shaded by Trees</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">shing gis g.yogs pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཤིང་གིས་གཡོགས་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A lake on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9078">Equal Peaks</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="c86a8e85-bfc0-450b-97d9-e4a70f31bc7a" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_p5d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1173</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">shadow players</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">grib ma’i rtse</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གྲིབ་མའི་རྩེ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A type of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8581">rākṣasī</span> living on an island called <span><span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9057">Endowed with Jewels</span></span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="59c8aaf9-9c7a-4afd-a0cc-366943ae4fda" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_p5l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1174</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Shaken by Fierce Winds</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rlung gtum pos g.yos pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རླུང་གཏུམ་པོས་གཡོས་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9417">Living on the Peak</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="8f95e55b-f8a2-4919-b4d8-9d4a2d5a9f29" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_p5t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1175</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Shang Buchikpa</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">zhang bu gcig pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཞང་བུ་གཅིག་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">An assistant translator and editor of this scripture.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="7f5108b5-df91-4b90-840b-cf367de1e97d" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_p655anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1176</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Sharp and Unbearable Pain</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">tshor ba rtsub cing tsha la bzod pa dka’ ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཚོར་བ་རྩུབ་ཅིང་ཚ་ལ་བཟོད་པ་དཀའ་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">khara­kaṭuka­duḥsaha­vedana</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of sixteen realms that surround the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9235">Great Howling Hell</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="8a835a20-fe45-4165-af64-50bd9470ae01" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_p6d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1177</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Sherap Ö</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">shes rab ’od</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཤེས་རབ་འོད།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">An assistant translator and editor of this scripture.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="0751fe52-94b8-4a34-a483-cc4cc94af31b" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_p6l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1178</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Shining</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rab spro</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རབ་སྤྲོ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A virtuous <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8562">nāga</span> king.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="95ba1c0c-4821-43aa-a89b-3bfd11850170" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_p6t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1179</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Shining in Manifold Ways</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rnam pa sna tshogs par rnam par bkra ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྣམ་པ་སྣ་ཚོགས་པར་རྣམ་པར་བཀྲ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of the twenty-seven realms of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9266">Heaven Free from Strife</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="19a09f62-203a-40ee-adec-771f8c5808d3" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_p755anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1180</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Shining Jewel Light</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">nor bu ’byin</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ནོར་བུ་འབྱིན།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9511">Moving in Vast Environments</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="cc400022-a69d-43dc-9a96-1f4a71c78a31" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_p7d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1181</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Śikhin</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gtsug tor can</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གཙུག་ཏོར་ཅན།</span></li><li class="italic">śikhin</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A previous buddha.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="18d9828d-5bcc-4f36-b5b5-fe5f4b8b0a19" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_p7l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1182</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Śīlabhadra</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">tshul khrims bzang po</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཚུལ་ཁྲིམས་བཟང་པོ།</span></li><li class="italic">śīlabhadra</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A king in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>, <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8720">Musulundha</span>’s rebirth.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="88537432-d49d-4a52-b60a-2fe12cc70d25" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_p7t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1183</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Silver Forest</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dngul gyi shing ljon pa’i tshal</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དངུལ་གྱི་ཤིང་ལྗོན་པའི་ཚལ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9869">White Body</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="857c13b8-42c3-4f10-a348-5a0e8649e823" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_p855anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1184</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Silver Hue</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dngul gyi mdog</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དངུལ་གྱི་མདོག</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9657">Saṅkāśa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="ab922da1-27cb-4ef6-bc72-5cc7bfa82833" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_p8d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1185</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Silvery Sands</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dngul dang bcas pa’i bye mas yongs su bskor ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དངུལ་དང་བཅས་པའི་བྱེ་མས་ཡོངས་སུ་བསྐོར་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">An island in the vicinity of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="af73b3a0-2f66-4f34-8262-e59c4596f87b" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_p8l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1186</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Siṃhala</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sing ha la</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སིང་ཧ་ལ།</span></li><li class="italic">siṃhala</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">The island of Lanka.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="92656fb7-c4f6-45ee-aebe-934fee0ba9fe" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_p8t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1187</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Sindh</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sin du’i yul</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སིན་དུའི་ཡུལ།</span></li><li class="italic">sindh</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">An area located in present day Pakistan.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="51c97550-e5e9-4813-99a7-e072f941af73" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_p955anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1188</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Sindhū</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sin+d+hu</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སིནྡྷུ།</span></li><li class="italic">sindhū</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river to the west of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="9577db14-9753-4174-bc76-6dd32fc6a38c" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_p9d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1189</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Single Face</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ngos gcig pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ངོས་གཅིག་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain in the eastern sea beyond <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="6111f740-d591-4d3c-a85f-545025cfc13b" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_p9l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1190</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Sitā, Sītā</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sI tA, si tA</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སཱི་ཏཱ།, སི་ཏཱ།</span></li><li class="italic">sitā, sītā</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="d633b9c0-ce14-448f-9094-95890724ef11" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_p9t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1191</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Sitā, Sītā</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sI tA, si tA</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སཱི་ཏཱ།, སི་ཏཱ།</span></li><li class="italic">sitā, sītā</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river to the north of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="01520621-e4fb-48d3-9572-143f8531fe91" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_pa55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1192</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Situ Paṇchen Chökyi Jungné</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">si tu paN chen chos kyi ’byung gnas</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སི་ཏུ་པཎ་ཆེན་ཆོས་ཀྱི་འབྱུང་གནས།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">The editor of the Degé Kangyur (1700–1774).</p></div></div></div></div><div id="1fa304dd-7897-42f3-8dc4-0d5b212dabf0" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_pad5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1193</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Situated by the End of Karaṇa</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ka ra na’i mtha’ na gnas pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀ་ར་ནའི་མཐའ་ན་གནས་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">An area in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9398">Kuru</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="90e9ae3c-c539-44e8-8090-8329a234ecca" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_pal5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1194</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">six objects</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">drug, yul drug</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དྲུག, ཡུལ་དྲུག</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">The six sense objects: forms, sounds, smells, tastes, textures, and mental objects.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="037ba07b-0395-4ab3-a1cb-0701adfd420c" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_pat5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1195</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">six perfections</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">pha rol tu phyin pa drug</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཕ་རོལ་ཏུ་ཕྱིན་པ་དྲུག</span></li><li class="italic">ṣaṭpāramitā</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">The six practices of the bodhisattva path: generosity (Tib. <em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">sbyin pa</em>; Skt. <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">dāna</em>), discipline (Tib. <em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">tshul khrims</em>; Skt. <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">śīla</em>), patience (Tib. <em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">bzod pa</em>; Skt. <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">kṣānti</em>), diligence (Tib. <em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">brtson ’grus</em>; Skt. <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">vīrya</em>), <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9969">concentration</span> (Tib. <em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">bsam gtan</em>; Skt. <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">dhyāna</em>), and <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-100012">insight</span> (Tib. <em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">shes rab</em>; Skt. <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">prajñā</em>).</p></div></div></div></div><div id="71487fe2-166f-4824-98cf-e90de15e2c41" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_pb55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1196</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">six seasons</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dus tshigs drug</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དུས་ཚིགས་དྲུག</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">The <span class="ignore">six seasons</span> are early winter, late winter, spring, summer, monsoon, and fall.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="1ba0abb9-5d3b-4f0f-b20a-b299beab5009" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_pbd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1197</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">six tastes</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ro drug</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རོ་དྲུག</span></li><li class="italic">ṣaḍrasa</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">According to Āyurveda, all foods can be categorized by <span class="ignore">six tastes</span>: sweet, sour, salty, bitter, pungent, and astringent.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="2a151855-70b5-4090-aa36-a608163dfe84" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_pbl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1198</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Sky Scent</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">nam mkha’i dri ma</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ནམ་མཁའི་དྲི་མ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A town in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9847">Videha</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="61d92e66-3f0c-4aa2-b2fc-ec551118929a" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_pbt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1199</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">sky traveler</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">nam mkha’ la rgyu bar byed pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ནམ་མཁའ་ལ་རྒྱུ་བར་བྱེད་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A class of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8622">vidyādharas</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="62c9b560-3f73-4baf-9de7-8fc80a4c0e66" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_pc55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1200</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Slab of Beryl</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bai DUr+ya’i rdo leb</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བཻ་ཌཱུརྱའི་རྡོ་ལེབ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A location in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9014">Draped with Jewels</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="47897fb0-4940-4e23-b189-085635edfe88" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_pcd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1201</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Slicing Like a Bottle-Gourd Fruit</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’bras bu a la bud lta bur gcod pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འབྲས་བུ་ཨ་ལ་བུད་ལྟ་བུར་གཅོད་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">alābucchedaka</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of sixteen realms that surround the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8975">Crushing Hell</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="50837f8d-52d6-4162-8b71-637b46ed3dfd" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_pcl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1202</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Sloping Banks</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gram sag gi chu</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གྲམ་སག་གི་ཆུ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9657">Saṅkāśa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="3876369c-fece-4e76-b960-2d8a6ddc2be4" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_pct5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1203</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Smoky</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">du ba pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དུ་བ་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9142">Forest Garlands</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="ceec186f-331b-4781-b555-c263a236807f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_pd55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1204</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Smoky Forest of Burning Embers</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">me mdag dud pa’i tshal</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མེ་མདག་དུད་པའི་ཚལ།</span></li><li class="italic">dhūmāṅgāravana</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of sixteen realms that surround the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9298">Howling Hell</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="0c5c378a-f945-4d91-a83b-77f4cb63c93c" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_pdd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1205</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Smoky Forest of Burning Plantains</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">chu shing bsregs pa’i tshal</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཆུ་ཤིང་བསྲེགས་པའི་ཚལ།</span></li><li class="italic">kadalī­dhūma­vana</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of sixteen realms that surround the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9298">Howling Hell</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="b22448b9-7edc-48ca-89a4-444850851c24" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_pdl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1206</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Smooth Ground</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gzhi ’jam pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གཞི་འཇམ་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A lotus pond on the fifth minor mountain on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9423">Lofty Summit</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="58e94588-7ba4-418c-8245-9d91b4947514" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_pdt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1207</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Snake</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sbrul</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྦྲུལ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain off <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9847">Videha</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="a2e859e5-49ad-43fc-9229-a09b7def929d" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_pe55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1208</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Snowy</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gangs yod pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གངས་ཡོད་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9657">Saṅkāśa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="35e8cdf1-5d3b-4e84-86d1-7ffea04a3779" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ped5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1209</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Snowy Regions</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">kha ba ’khor ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཁ་བ་འཁོར་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">An island in the vicinity of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="39b99638-ab2f-4eb5-b0c1-fe38cc77486f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_pel5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1210</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Sole Shadow</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">grib ma gcig pu pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གྲིབ་མ་གཅིག་པུ་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8956">Continuous Movement</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="f7587940-d7b8-45c1-b7b5-9034c0128c17" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_pet5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1211</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Solitary</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gcig pu ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གཅིག་པུ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="c1a27d3a-9591-4376-8678-41d3848a2125" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_pf55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1212</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">solitary buddha</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rang sangs rgyas</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རང་སངས་རྒྱས།</span></li><li class="italic">pratyekabuddha</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">An individual who attains a certain level of realization and liberation (different in some respects from those of an arhat and well short of those of a buddha) through understanding the nature of interdependent origination, without relying upon a teacher in that lifetime.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="421aaddb-8568-42a5-a8a6-c277f5c0bd50" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_pfd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1213</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">songs</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dbyangs kyis bsnyad pa’i sde</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དབྱངས་ཀྱིས་བསྙད་པའི་སྡེ།</span></li><li class="italic">geya</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One among the twelve sections of scripture.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="3e2bb631-9f4f-46bc-ad27-5510cd5d36d0" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_pfl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1214</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Sound of the Jambu Bird</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bya ’dzam pa skad ’byin</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བྱ་འཛམ་པ་སྐད་འབྱིན།</span></li><li class="italic">jambhāvitāra</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of sixteen realms that surround the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9279">Hell of Ultimate Torment</span>. This hell is the same as the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9699">Sound of Water</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="3fd961a2-da31-4921-b3ed-a455c378c70a" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_pft5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1215</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Sound of Water</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">chu sgra</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཆུ་སྒྲ།</span></li><li class="italic">jambhāvitāra</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of sixteen realms that surround the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9279">Hell of Ultimate Torment</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="3f5f366f-3c5d-4351-b5ee-80a342447819" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_pg55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1216</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Sounds of the Land</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">nye ’khor gyi sgra</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཉེ་འཁོར་གྱི་སྒྲ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A city in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9847">Videha</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="1937da97-3049-4822-8668-25799823aca9" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_pgd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1217</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Sounds of Water</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">chu sgra kun nas sgrogs pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཆུ་སྒྲ་ཀུན་ནས་སྒྲོགས་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9046">Encircled by White Clouds</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="707d9d83-ab66-49dd-9c19-b7df078cd97e" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_pgl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1218</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Source of Bodies</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">lus ’byung</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ལུས་འབྱུང་།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">Alternative name for <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8963">Copious Parasites in Marrow and Bones</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="2e34e88c-4042-4145-9e08-d4375d588fca" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_pgt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1219</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Source of Great Lotuses</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">pad ma che ’byung</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">པད་མ་ཆེ་འབྱུང་།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A lake near <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9734">Sudharma</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="6fc4fccc-e9e5-4a92-aa20-d78423916510" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ph55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1220</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Source of Joy</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dga’ ’byung</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དགའ་འབྱུང་།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A lake near <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9734">Sudharma</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="c36176d8-3292-4b49-8fa1-ad636ce7a95f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_phd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1221</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">space dwellers</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">nam mkha’ la gnas pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ནམ་མཁའ་ལ་གནས་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A class of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8489">asuras</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="c4ca379c-040b-4d03-bccc-17213c1a768a" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_phl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1222</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Spacious Palanquin Houses</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">khyogs kyi khang bu yangs pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཁྱོགས་ཀྱི་ཁང་བུ་ཡངས་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A park in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9509">Moving in the Stream</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="bc1b70a2-6986-47fd-9692-031ac45e6670" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_pht5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1223</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Spānāśetu</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">spA nA she tu</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྤཱ་ནཱ་ཤེ་ཏུ།</span></li><li class="italic">spānāśetu</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">An island in the vicinity of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="3c395441-8f07-4cee-90c6-bc62c5b8fb73" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_pi55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1224</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Sparkling with Brilliant Jewels</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">nor bu’i cha shas rnams kyis rnam par bkra ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ནོར་བུའི་ཆ་ཤས་རྣམས་ཀྱིས་རྣམ་པར་བཀྲ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9796">Total Pleasure</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="debae856-aca0-4625-b561-d8ebbf299fd5" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_pid5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1225</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Sparks and Parasites</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">me’i phye ma srin bu</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མེའི་ཕྱེ་མ་སྲིན་བུ།</span></li><li class="italic">asthicūrṇakṛmi</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of sixteen realms that surround the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9298">Howling Hell</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="c227fc1e-42f2-4f7d-9fa3-db47b82236a8" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_pil5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1226</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Special Drink</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">lhag pa thung ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ལྷག་པ་ཐུང་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9128">Flocking Peacocks</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="86fa38bf-c943-41e8-93d2-e412023b8c1c" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_pit5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1227</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">special insight</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">lhag mthong</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ལྷག་མཐོང་།</span></li><li class="italic">vipaśyanā</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">Refers to <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-100012">insight</span> into the nature of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9926">reality</span> or the practice of developing such <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-100012">insight</span>. One of the two basic forms of Buddhist meditation, the other being <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9922">calm abiding</span> (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">śamatha</em>, <em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">zhi gnas</em>).</p></div></div></div></div><div id="04cf3fd3-8b8d-4d86-90e3-6de8af7a1a8a" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_pj55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1228</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Special Joy</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">lhag par dga’ ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ལྷག་པར་དགའ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A realm of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8516">ever-infatuated gods</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="092556e7-8f9a-4edb-95a7-805880257ce2" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_pjd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1229</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Sphere Endowed with Diverse Music</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sil snyan rnam pa sna tshogs kyi sgra dang ldan pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སིལ་སྙན་རྣམ་པ་སྣ་ཚོགས་ཀྱི་སྒྲ་དང་ལྡན་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9066">Engaging in Clarification</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="ba502ae9-705c-468e-ac7b-9cbe4bc8ccf0" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_pjl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1230</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Splashing Swan Wings</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ngang pas’i gshog pas bcom pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ངང་པསའི་གཤོག་པས་བཅོམ་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A pond on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9078">Equal Peaks</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="fb8eab18-c2bd-4de6-84c5-8b736fcdc26b" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_pjt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1231</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Splendid</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gzi brjid dang ldan pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གཟི་བརྗིད་དང་ལྡན་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A ruler of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9266">Heaven Free from Strife</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="e179ba1f-9629-456e-9895-c88ca58a33b7" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_pk55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1232</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Splendor of the Signs of Pride</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">nga rgyal rtags kyi gzi brjid</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ང་རྒྱལ་རྟགས་ཀྱི་གཟི་བརྗིད།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of the twenty-seven realms in the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9266">Heaven Free from Strife</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="8fa2a2f3-7ab8-4f3d-b5db-82b587daf7e3" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_pkd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1233</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Sporting among Lotuses</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">pad ma’i nang na rgyu ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">པད་མའི་ནང་ན་རྒྱུ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A realm of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8621">vessel-bearer gods</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="fcabe0aa-0831-48f5-946e-4d9987ca4cf9" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_pkl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1234</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Sporting among Moving Groups</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">tshogs pa rgyu ba na rnam par rgyu ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཚོགས་པ་རྒྱུ་བ་ན་རྣམ་པར་རྒྱུ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A realm in the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9266">Heaven Free from Strife</span> (multiple slightly variant versions are extant in the Tibetan, making the term sound more like a description than a proper noun).</p></div></div></div></div><div id="e9548afc-a65e-4fba-b13c-334c3469543c" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_pkt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1235</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Spring Joy</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dpyid dga’ ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དཔྱིད་དགའ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9657">Saṅkāśa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="26030a72-9a50-47a6-8f81-bbf8babe44f0" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_pl55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1236</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Stable Water</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">chu brtan pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཆུ་བརྟན་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A lake on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9078">Equal Peaks</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="60bb14da-70fa-47a8-b973-aeb174728d97" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_pld5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1237</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">stage of no impediment</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mi lcog med pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མི་ལྕོག་མེད་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">The preparatory stage for the first <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9969">concentration</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="3162dff7-1fa7-4a80-bcf7-ee063df392c3" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_pll5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1238</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Stainless</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dri ma med pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དྲི་མ་མེད་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A pond on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9078">Equal Peaks</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="295b1256-0009-467a-b779-031c75d03e4a" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_plt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1239</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Stainless and Clear</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dri ma med par gsal ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དྲི་མ་མེད་པར་གསལ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A city in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9209">Godānīya</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="f9c5a1fb-b520-476f-bcb5-694bbafed39c" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_pm55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1240</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Star Garland</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">skar ’phreng</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྐར་འཕྲེང་།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">An <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8489">asura</span> city.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="84f73a9d-4c5c-400b-a557-976d1d6779b3" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_pmd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1241</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">starving spirit</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">yi dags</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཡི་དགས།</span></li><li class="italic">preta</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p>One of the five or six classes of sentient beings, into which beings are born as the karmic fruition of past miserliness. As the term in Sanskrit means “the departed,” they are analogous to the ancestral spirits of Vedic tradition, the <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">pitṛ</em>s, who starve without the offerings of descendants. It is also commonly translated as “hungry ghost” or “starving spirit,” as in the Chinese 餓鬼 <em class="foreign">e gui</em>.</p><p>They are sometimes said to reside in the realm of Yama, but are also frequently described as roaming charnel grounds and other inhospitable or frightening places along with piśācas and other such beings. They are particularly known to suffer from great hunger and thirst and the inability to acquire sustenance. Detailed descriptions of their realm and experience, including a list of the thirty-six classes of pretas, can be found in <cite class="title text-en" lang="en">The Application of Mindfulness of the Sacred Dharma</cite>, Toh 287, <a target="_blank" href="https://read.84000.co/translation/toh287.html#UT22084-068-021-1672" title="2.­1281">2.­1281</a>– <a target="_blank" href="https://read.84000.co/translation/toh287.html#UT22084-068-021-1902" title="2.1482">2.1482</a>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="c5b6b3ff-d4fa-44b2-97a8-c1fd5cae1112" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_pml5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1242</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Staṣkako</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">staSh+ka ko</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྟཥྐ་ཀོ</span></li><li class="italic">staṣkako</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8562">nāga</span> who visits <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9657">Saṅkāśa</span> Mountain.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="6dbe902c-49b4-4799-ab25-ac308d61ca4e" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_pmt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1243</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Steadfast One</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">brtan pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བརྟན་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A previous ruler of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9276">Heaven of the Thirty-Three</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="7169b9fd-d93b-43b7-af46-5708360b5712" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_pn55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1244</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">stealing, take what was not given, taking what is not given, taking what was not given</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ma byin par len pa, ma byin par len pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མ་བྱིན་པར་ལེན་པ།, མ་བྱིན་པར་ལེན་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">adattādāna, adattādāna</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">The second among the three physical misdeeds. Also rendered here as “<span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9902">stealing</span>.”</p></div></div></div></div><div id="9ad933f8-ddbc-4390-be33-dfde30d736b8" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_pnd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1245</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">stealing, take what was not given, taking what is not given, taking what was not given</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ma byin par len pa, ma byin par len pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མ་བྱིན་པར་ལེན་པ།, མ་བྱིན་པར་ལེན་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">adattādāna, adattādāna</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">The second among the three physical misdeeds. Also rendered here according to the literal meaning of <em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">ma byin par len pa</em>, “<span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8605">taking what was not given</span>.”</p></div></div></div></div><div id="ca9c49b7-be4f-43ca-b2b1-4d68f42d19eb" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_pnl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1246</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Stomach</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gsus pa nyid</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གསུས་པ་ཉིད།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">An area in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9398">Kuru</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="0a98e45a-a574-4af4-ac8b-f1736bbc0687" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_pnt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1247</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">stream enterer</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rgyun du zhugs pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྒྱུན་དུ་ཞུགས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">srotāpanna</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A person who has entered the “stream” of practice that leads to <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8565">nirvāṇa</span>. The first of the four attainments of the path of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8536">hearers</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="2006e1f3-ce9a-475b-9ffd-9913b31d814c" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_po55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1248</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Stream of Dark Foam</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dbu ba rog rog ’bab pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དབུ་བ་རོག་རོག་འབབ་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9072">Enjoyment of Scents</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="3ea5db32-4fd5-4a2f-aab7-0f365b22e3be" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_pod5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1249</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Stream of Gold</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gser ’bab</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གསེར་འབབ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9072">Enjoyment of Scents</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="bbac550f-18f0-4a65-bfff-1f9ccba2e25c" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_pol5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1250</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Stream of Jewel Pieces</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rin po che’i dum bu ’bab</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རིན་པོ་ཆེའི་དུམ་བུ་འབབ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9072">Enjoyment of Scents</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="48275cfe-719b-4af6-a348-bc57ed99c2e0" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_pot5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1251</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Stream of Jewels</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rin chen ’bab</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རིན་ཆེན་འབབ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9072">Enjoyment of Scents</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="18834090-6e97-4b6e-9a59-02f22e3ac2b9" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_pp55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1252</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Strewn Sand</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bye ma ’drim pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བྱེ་མ་འདྲིམ་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9241">Great Slope</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="2e9588bf-fe59-4719-8a6b-70e905dea588" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ppd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1253</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Strife</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’thab pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འཐབ་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A “ruler of the world” who belongs to the class of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8553">māras</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="c66b5ebf-eb68-47a5-bbd0-2466a777207a" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ppl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1254</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">strongly attached to pleasure</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bde ba la chags pa’i shugs</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བདེ་བ་ལ་ཆགས་པའི་ཤུགས།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A class of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8622">vidyādharas</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="222e67f9-f6a9-48f4-a01f-94f8bb0f27dc" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ppt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1255</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Studded with Kadambas</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ka dam+ba ’khod pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀ་དམྦ་འཁོད་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9657">Saṅkāśa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="1e8cbd5d-934e-4f00-97b3-8b33bf21c31c" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_pq55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1256</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Studded with Lotuses</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">pad mas bkab par gyur pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">པད་མས་བཀབ་པར་གྱུར་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A lake on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9078">Equal Peaks</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="06172a81-eb93-4c16-b32d-1a337cc89dc7" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_pqd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1257</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Studded with Mansions</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">khang bzangs dkrigs pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཁང་བཟངས་དཀྲིགས་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A pleasure grove in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9668">Shaded by Garlands</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="bab1d4f3-5413-41e2-9f59-bd02e83d46a6" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_pql5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1258</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Studded with Vidruma Trees</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bi dru ma’i shing dang ldan pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བི་དྲུ་མའི་ཤིང་དང་ལྡན་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9657">Saṅkāśa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="8f9e7977-2b92-4553-b1db-70aa85d65a51" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_pqt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1259</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Subhūticandra</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">su b+hU ti tsan+d+ra</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སུ་བྷཱུ་ཏི་ཙནྡྲ།</span></li><li class="italic">subhūticandra</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A translator of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9986">sūtra</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="a3102c09-5d38-4d42-837f-1e4706aaabf2" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_pr55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1260</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Sublime, Sublime Heaven</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gya nom snang</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གྱ་ནོམ་སྣང་།</span></li><li class="italic">sudarśana, sudṛśa</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">The third of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9927">five realms</span> associated with the fourth <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9969">concentration</span> into which only noble beings are born. </p></div></div></div></div><div id="eb660550-a7e0-47e6-8284-fad17f8d867a" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_prd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1261</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Subtle Engagement</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">shib tu spyod pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཤིབ་ཏུ་སྤྱོད་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">sūkṣmacarā</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A realm in the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9276">Heaven of the Thirty-Three</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="60a0cb08-994b-4a1d-ad5e-16beef14fe61" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_prl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1262</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Sudarśana</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">legs mthong, lta na sdug</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ལེགས་མཐོང་།, ལྟ་ན་སྡུག</span></li><li class="italic">sudarśana</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">(1) King who appears during the elephant <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8636">Airāvaṇa</span>’s previous life as a <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8491">brahmin</span> (<em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">legs mthong</em>). (2) The city of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8738">Śakra</span> (<em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">legs mthong</em> and <em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">lta na sdug</em>).</p></div></div></div></div><div id="de6d20f2-8d8a-4bb3-9cae-f97d019d4289" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_prt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1263</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Sudharma</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">chos bzang</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཆོས་བཟང་།</span></li><li class="italic">sudharma</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition"><span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8738">Śakra</span>’s assembly hall.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="e1be0ed7-b675-4282-8a91-a1a636e35f4f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ps55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1264</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Śukati Pearls</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mu tig gi shu ka ti</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མུ་ཏིག་གི་ཤུ་ཀ་ཏི།</span></li><li class="italic">śukati</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">An island between <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9398">Kuru</span> and <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9209">Godānīya</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="1ef3b19d-a55a-4719-b1e3-4bf2311c3fa3" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_psd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1265</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Sukhana</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">su kha na</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སུ་ཁ་ན།</span></li><li class="italic">sukhana</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain to the west of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="5efd7245-2f87-4581-b311-6ce5e8a6f8c8" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_psl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1266</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Śukti Realm</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">shuk+ti’i gnas</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཤུཀྟིའི་གནས།</span></li><li class="italic">śukti</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">An island in the vicinity of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="22a54d38-181b-4b0a-a5c1-eca5bc803cd0" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_pst5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1267</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Sumanyu</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">su ma n+yum</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སུ་མ་ནྱུམ།</span></li><li class="italic">sumanyu</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A previous ruler of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9276">Heaven of the Thirty-Three</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="ec554dcc-896f-47fc-befa-ed29ccc75a6f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_pt55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1268</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Sumegha</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">su me gho</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སུ་མེ་གྷོ།</span></li><li class="italic">sumegha</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain in the sea west of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="2014c001-ec4d-45a4-ba8c-d283853d6949" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ptd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1269</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Sumeru</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ri rab, ri rab lhun po</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རི་རབ་ལྷུན་པོ།, རི་རབ།</span></li><li class="italic">sumeru</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p>According to ancient Buddhist cosmology, this is the great mountain forming the axis of the universe. At its summit is Sudarśana, home of Śakra and his thirty-two gods, and on its flanks live the asuras. The mount has four sides facing the cardinal directions, each of which is made of a different precious stone. Surrounding it are several mountain ranges and the great ocean where the four principal island continents lie: in the south, Jambudvīpa (our world); in the west, Godānīya; in the north, Uttarakuru; and in the east, Pūrvavideha. Above it are the abodes of the desire realm gods. It is variously referred to as Meru, Mount Meru, Sumeru, and Mount Sumeru.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="5bd87759-fd74-42a8-8949-e54dfbd90110" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ptl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1270</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Sumeru dweller</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ri rab lhun po la gnas pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རི་རབ་ལྷུན་པོ་ལ་གནས་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A class of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8622">vidyādharas</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="f184f2a7-fe3e-4199-831b-753ad0c8887d" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ptt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1271</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Sumeru Rival</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ri rab lhun po la ’gran pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རི་རབ་ལྷུན་པོ་ལ་འགྲན་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain to the north of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="cc4063d1-0adb-4ca6-bf06-cd650c8c8acf" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_pu55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1272</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Summer Joy</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dbyar dga’ ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དབྱར་དགའ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9657">Saṅkāśa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="89b4d3b0-be3b-477b-b703-383d5c0e408d" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_pud5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1273</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Summit Encircler</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rtse mo la ’khor ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྩེ་མོ་ལ་འཁོར་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9142">Forest Garlands</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="ac5610b8-3a1a-426c-ae11-80e3b4f22203" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_pul5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1274</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Summit Net</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rtse mo’i g.seb</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྩེ་མོའི་གསེབ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A lake on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9078">Equal Peaks</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="44c2d2aa-2873-4ee3-98b2-dd5ed92190ba" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_put5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1275</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Sun Enjoyer</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">nyi ma sten pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཉི་མ་སྟེན་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A lotus pond on the fifth minor mountain on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9423">Lofty Summit</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="37431cfb-dd26-4043-9348-3eb937bcfaec" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_pv55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1276</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Sunny</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">nyi ma ldan</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཉི་མ་ལྡན།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain in the sea south of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="2be3346e-88f6-4bba-a23d-168682b274f6" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_pvd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1277</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Sunshine</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">nyin mor byed pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཉིན་མོར་བྱེད་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9260">Heap in the Stream</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="f2b68628-e470-4aea-bdd7-ac27a6a1adc0" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_pvl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1278</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Superior</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bla lhag pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བླ་ལྷག་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain off <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9847">Videha</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="f6b95b7d-8ec6-4055-bd35-c1cdd0696842" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_pvt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1279</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Superior Harm</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gnod pa mtho ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གནོད་པ་མཐོ་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">ūrdhvakāraṇa</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of sixteen realms that surround the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9630">Reviving Hell</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="cfa5cc1c-0a27-4b7d-9d90-e75d4cbf21a9" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_q055anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1280</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">supreme ketaka garland bearer</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ke ta ka’i phreng ba mchog dang ldan pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀེ་ཏ་ཀའི་ཕྲེང་བ་མཆོག་དང་ལྡན་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A class of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8622">vidyādharas</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="02fda338-02ea-4bd6-8297-a2ac4e58ce58" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_q0d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1281</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Supreme Lake</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mtsho mchog</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མཚོ་མཆོག</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A lake on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9078">Equal Peaks</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="617b2942-38ee-440e-8adf-a5fb54318e18" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_q0l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1282</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Supreme Pleasure Grove</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">skyed mos tshal gyi mchog</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྐྱེད་མོས་ཚལ་གྱི་མཆོག</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of the twenty-seven realms in the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9266">Heaven Free from Strife</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="f120d261-1449-4b3c-903e-6048f7d21e8c" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_q0t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1283</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Supreme Splendor</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gzi brjid mchog</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གཟི་བརྗིད་མཆོག</span></li><li class="italic">tejomukha</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A realm in the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9276">Heaven of the Thirty-Three</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="276335c0-277e-446a-a194-071c8f1fc1d0" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_q155anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1284</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Supreme Strength</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rab kyi shugs, rab kyi shugs kyi bdag</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རབ་ཀྱི་ཤུགས་ཀྱི་བདག, རབ་ཀྱི་ཤུགས།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of the twenty-seven realms of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9266">Heaven Free from Strife</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="3486e635-0221-48dd-999d-dc34168f9c40" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_q1d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1285</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Surrounded by Nakra Crocodiles</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">chu srin na kras bskor ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཆུ་སྲིན་ན་ཀྲས་བསྐོར་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9657">Saṅkāśa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="2e95ec85-ff97-429c-b743-0776a9a5d3c0" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_q1l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1286</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Surrounded by Nyaronya</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">nya ro hi ’khor ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཉ་རོ་ཧི་འཁོར་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9657">Saṅkāśa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="e7bb511d-8964-4f44-ba8a-859bc3039c59" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_q1t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1287</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Suśīmo</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">su shI mo</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སུ་ཤཱི་མོ།</span></li><li class="italic">suśīmo</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain in the sea west of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="1d039d99-48ab-4d08-8328-d5981259cd9a" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_q255anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1288</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Sustained by Fruition</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’bras bus nye bar ’tsho ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འབྲས་བུས་ཉེ་བར་འཚོ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A realm inhabited by <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8530">garland-bearer gods</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="26d538b0-50c4-41e6-ae57-cd785d47ba44" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_q2d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1289</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Sustained by the Finest Tastes</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ro brgya mchog gis bsten pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རོ་བརྒྱ་མཆོག་གིས་བསྟེན་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A grove in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9820">Unmixed</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="9e0171e8-23fa-46cb-8835-a71798ac4b91" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_q2l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1290</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Susthali</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sus tha li</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སུས་ཐ་ལི།</span></li><li class="italic">susthali</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A land to the north of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="643935d0-63fb-47fc-8abc-2bc1b02a1331" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_q2t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1291</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Sūtra</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mdo</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མདོ།</span></li><li class="italic">sūtra</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">In Buddhism it refers to the Buddha’s teachings, whatever their length, and in terms of the three divisions of the Buddha’s teachings, it is the category of teachings other than those on the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9974">Vinaya</span> and <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9985">Abhidharma</span>. It is also used as a category to contrast with the tantra teachings. Another very specific meaning is when it is classed as one of the nine or twelve aspects of the Dharma. In that context <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN"><span class="ignore">sūtra</span></em> means “discourse.”</p></div></div></div></div><div id="b04744cc-c072-44a3-813e-4300a50532da" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_q355anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1292</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">sūtras</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mdo’i sde</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མདོའི་སྡེ།</span></li><li class="italic">sūtra</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One among the twelve sections of scripture. See also entry on the term “<span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9986">sūtra</span>.“</p></div></div></div></div><div id="360ac958-8bd5-478a-a636-bf6febad0963" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_q3d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1293</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Suvarṇadvīpa</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gser gling</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གསེར་གླིང་།</span></li><li class="italic">suvarṇadvīpa</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A region of Southeast Asia visited by Indians.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="913084ba-555f-4dd5-941a-b37d80557442" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_q3l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1294</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Suvelang Forest</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">su be lang gi nags</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སུ་བེ་ལང་གི་ནགས།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9241">Great Slope</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="27fc3666-d4c8-49c1-b53f-a8500096d0d3" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_q3t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1295</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Suvīra</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">su bI ro</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སུ་བཱི་རོ།</span></li><li class="italic">suvīra</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A land to the west of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="611b54aa-1905-48da-a467-c8c460db3a0b" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_q455anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1296</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Swamp of Filth</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mi gtsang ba’i ’dam</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མི་གཙང་བའི་འདམ།</span></li><li class="italic">amedhyamṛttikā</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of sixteen realms that surround the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9630">Reviving Hell</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="54870d2a-b6de-4996-a4a3-7019aae30381" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_q4d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1297</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">swan chariot</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ngang pa’i shing rta</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ངང་པའི་ཤིང་རྟ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A class of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8622">vidyādharas</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="18ca8088-2846-4cfb-bab1-14e97cdd0bfd" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_q4l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1298</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Swan Charioteer</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ngang pa’i shing rta</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ངང་པའི་ཤིང་རྟ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">An epithet of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8647">Brahmā</span>, who rides a swan.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="a07cadf3-671e-4e58-892d-f2080d3a13fe" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_q4t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1299</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Swan Forest</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ngang pa’i nags</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ངང་པའི་ནགས།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">(1) A forest in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9059">Endowed with Migration</span>. (2) A lake to the north of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="f1973100-45d9-4c40-b5ba-86432ed1d01d" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_q555anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1300</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Swan Lotus Forest</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ngang pa’i pad ma’i tshal</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ངང་པའི་པད་མའི་ཚལ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A lotus grove in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9556">Part of the Assembly</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="bf6b981a-e404-484e-97bd-e5805a83ba85" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_q5d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1301</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Swan Waters</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ngang pa’i chu</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ངང་པའི་ཆུ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A lake on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9078">Equal Peaks</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="11e49797-c6cb-45f4-a719-d880da0ab4a7" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_q5l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1302</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Swift Current</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">myur ba’i chu</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མྱུར་བའི་ཆུ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9657">Saṅkāśa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="1f3c8605-3cc1-4f57-8ee3-55a5200b77cd" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_q5t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1303</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Swift Movement</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’gro mgyogs pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འགྲོ་མགྱོགས་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A realm inhabited by <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8530">garland-bearer gods</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="e500a3ec-a56d-4481-85af-4698f28fc144" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_q655anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1304</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Swimming Like Fish in Molten Copper</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">zangs bzhus bar nya ’khyug pa lta bu</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཟངས་བཞུས་བར་ཉ་འཁྱུག་པ་ལྟ་བུ།</span></li><li class="italic">tāmra­lohita­mīnāvarta</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of the sixteen realms that surround the <span><span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9277">Hell of Heat</span></span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="a6accc2e-e23e-47ff-aa1b-33d886038596" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_q6d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1305</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">tailed creature</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">lang ku di ka</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ལང་ཀུ་དི་ཀ</span></li><li class="italic">lāṅgulika</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A monster in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9812">Unbearably Terrifying</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="33b7e50c-8c3e-48db-875b-2e3f67eb5fce" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_q6l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1306</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Ṭakaśobho</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">Ta ka sho bho</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཊ་ཀ་ཤོ་བྷོ།</span></li><li class="italic">ṭakaśobho</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="5925ce89-dce3-4af3-823c-054f414b9438" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_q6t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1307</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Takṣaka</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’jog po</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འཇོག་པོ།</span></li><li class="italic">takṣaka</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A virtuous <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8562">nāga</span> king. </p></div></div></div></div><div id="64795d8d-8e2e-462a-9010-004e8868b97f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_q755anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1308</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Tamer of Deer Enemies</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ri dags kyi dgra dul ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རི་དགས་ཀྱི་དགྲ་དུལ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9398">Kuru</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="37261716-d4fb-4915-bc80-5bdee6dbb1f8" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_q7d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1309</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Tamer of Madness</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">myos ’gro ’dul</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མྱོས་འགྲོ་འདུལ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A pleasure garden in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9074">Enraptured by and Attached to Song</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="84a1e89f-256e-4326-a327-15193cb00c08" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_q7l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1310</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Tangled Forest</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ral pa can</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རལ་པ་ཅན།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8989">Deer Abode</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="7b66bf3c-1d0a-4628-a5e9-d19a16462412" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_q7t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1311</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Teeming with Snakes</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sbrul ’khyil ba lta bu</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྦྲུལ་འཁྱིལ་བ་ལྟ་བུ།</span></li><li class="italic">nāgāvarta</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of the sixteen realms that surround the <span><span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9277">Hell of Heat</span></span>. </p></div></div></div></div><div id="e419cc7e-5be4-4725-ab1c-535706f0cd40" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_q855anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1312</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">ten powers</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">stobs bcu</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྟོབས་བཅུ།</span></li><li class="italic">daśabala</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">Ten wisdom powers unique to a tathāgata: (1) the knowledge of what is possible and not possible, (2) the knowledge of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8583">ripening</span> of karma, (3) the knowledge of the variety of aspirations, (4) the knowledge of the variety of natures, (5) the knowledge of the different levels of capabilities, (6) the knowledge of the destinations of all paths, (7) the knowledge of various states of meditation, (8) the knowledge of remembering previous lives, (9) the knowledge of deaths and rebirths, and (10) the knowledge of the cessation of defilements.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="2685de11-0a58-401f-b1dd-5bf713c9ac7d" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_q8d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1313</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">ten virtues, ten virtuous actions</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dge ba bcu</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དགེ་བ་བཅུ།</span></li><li class="italic">daśakuśala</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">Abstaining from <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8545">killing</span>, <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8605">taking what is not given</span>, <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8593">sexual misconduct</span>, <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9903">lying</span>, uttering <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8508">divisive talk</span>, speaking <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8535">harsh words</span>, <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8494">chatter</span>, <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8501">covetousness</span>, <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8539">ill will</span>, and <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8628">wrong views</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="86d4d0e2-5580-4ec8-80f5-d8cb4e02bcbc" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_q8l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1314</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Terrible Dangling of Battered Bodies</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">lus zhum mi bzad ’phyang</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ལུས་ཞུམ་མི་བཟད་འཕྱང་།</span></li><li class="italic">vilīna­gātrāvakaṭu­lamba</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of sixteen realms that surround the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9279">Hell of Ultimate Torment</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="51863c7b-89be-40cd-aae8-b9a2492a9d69" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_q8t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1315</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Terrifying Inferno with Swarms of Crocodiles</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">srin bu na kra dang ’khor lo dang me ’jigs ’jigs ltar skyes pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྲིན་བུ་ན་ཀྲ་དང་འཁོར་ལོ་དང་མེ་འཇིགས་འཇིགས་ལྟར་སྐྱེས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">nakra­cakra­bhairavāgni­jāla</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of the sixteen realms that surround the <span><span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9277">Hell of Heat</span></span>. </p></div></div></div></div><div id="2f9a0751-7693-44a8-927f-9744f095c991" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_q955anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1316</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Terrifying Nightmares</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rmi lam ’jigs byed ston</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྨི་ལམ་འཇིགས་བྱེད་སྟོན།</span></li><li class="italic">svapna­bhairava­darśana</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of sixteen realms that surround the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9279">Hell of Ultimate Torment</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="cec3017f-b66b-4848-a67e-e001ca52f65d" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_q9d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1317</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Terrifying Sight</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’jigs par lta ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འཇིགས་པར་ལྟ་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">bhairava­darśana</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of sixteen realms that surround the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8975">Crushing Hell</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="814ea9c4-9068-46d5-822a-504a3060ec71" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_q9l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1318</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Terrifying Slope</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mtha’ drag</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མཐའ་དྲག</span></li><li class="italic">ghorataṭa</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of the sixteen realms that surround the <span><span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9277">Hell of Heat</span></span>. </p></div></div></div></div><div id="1996ec92-2dbc-49a5-9b9b-6cc26a3e8e34" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_q9t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1319</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Terror of Being Eaten by Birds</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bya ’jigs ’jigs ltar ’dug pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བྱ་འཇིགས་འཇིགས་ལྟར་འདུག་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">pakṣi­bhairava­bhakṣa</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A place in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9279">Ultimate Torment</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="1d51b032-f0ab-460e-ae97-369c0e384cdb" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qa55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1320</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Terror of Enormous Screaming Bodies</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">lus chen po shin tu sgra ’byin ’jigs ’jigs ltar ’dug pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ལུས་ཆེན་པོ་ཤིན་ཏུ་སྒྲ་འབྱིན་འཇིགས་འཇིགས་ལྟར་འདུག་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">mahā­kāya­sunāda­bhairava</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A realm that neighbors the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9278">Hell of Intense Heat</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="ec44adbf-d2d0-4e02-ac0c-fec29586dc9c" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qad5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1321</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">the constantly infatuated</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rtag tu rgyags pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྟག་ཏུ་རྒྱགས་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition"><span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8529">Gandharvas</span> who live on the island of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9339">Jambudvīpa Garland</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="c9c39259-cfd0-4503-a2d2-537714c44849" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qal5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1322</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">The Essence of All</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">thams cad kyi snying po</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཐམས་ཅད་ཀྱི་སྙིང་པོ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9056">Endowed with Increasing Bliss</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="fb5dc0f5-a61d-4449-bf52-64e602f3e7f5" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qat5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1323</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">The Hour of Death</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gnod skyes</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གནོད་སྐྱེས།</span></li><li class="italic">kālavelā</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">An acid river in the hell <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9147">Forest of Continuous Flames</span></p></div></div></div></div><div id="3ca24a3c-4440-4ccf-95c1-3fb32b044edd" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qb55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1324</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Thick Smoke</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">du bas ’khrigs pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དུ་བས་འཁྲིགས་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9558">Passionate Conduct</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="52ad144f-9159-4c68-9c89-b73ab696ad96" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qbd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1325</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Thorough Joy upon Hearing</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">thos na mi dga’ ba med pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཐོས་ན་མི་དགའ་བ་མེད་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A location in the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9269">Heaven of Joy</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="3b8e78d9-8721-49a4-a483-1c99e8ae6cd0" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qbl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1326</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Thoroughly Enjoyable</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">kun nas bde ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀུན་ནས་བདེ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A park in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9757">Sustained by Fruition</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="bda38038-6baf-4e2f-8076-99748be93e43" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qbt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1327</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Thoroughly Joyous</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">kun nas mngon par dga’ ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀུན་ནས་མངོན་པར་དགའ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">Alternative name for <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8760">Thoroughly Joyous Form</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="58eaa238-bee7-4753-9b95-3e29ac2e0bed" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qc55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1328</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Thoroughly Joyous Form</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gzugs kun nas mngon par dga’ ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གཟུགས་ཀུན་ནས་མངོན་པར་དགའ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A ruler of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9266">Heaven Free from Strife</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="cfbbab6c-97ba-4eab-9107-27058ce2ed4d" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qcd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1329</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">those fond of causing disease</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">nad gtong ba la dga’ ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ནད་གཏོང་བ་ལ་དགའ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A class of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8489">asuras</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="934bda54-7b49-47b9-9d4e-3d606db94e4c" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qcl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1330</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">those who swarm like bees</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bung ba ltar ’khyil pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བུང་བ་ལྟར་འཁྱིལ་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A class of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8489">asuras</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="a6031d3f-aeb6-47d4-a9a9-d5a84d626504" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qct5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1331</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">those with secret incantations</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sngags gsang ba pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྔགས་གསང་བ་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A class of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8622">vidyādharas</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="038055bd-38fa-4c6f-b28b-9612085b1e30" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qd55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1332</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Thousand-Eyed One</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mig stong</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མིག་སྟོང་།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A previous ruler of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9276">Heaven of the Thirty-Three</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="0bc58393-21d9-4ea5-8636-75636d0886c6" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qdd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1333</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Thousandfold Light</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">stong snang</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྟོང་སྣང་།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A previous ruler of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9276">Heaven of the Thirty-Three</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="16cbf474-f661-435d-8265-3f84f1efa72f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qdl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1334</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">three factors</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">chos gsum</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཆོས་གསུམ།</span></li><li class="italic">tridharma</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">Object, sense faculty, and consciousness. </p></div></div></div></div><div id="204aafed-5b5c-4e34-ad19-877d123066bb" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qdt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1335</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">three flaws</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">nyes pa gsum</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཉེས་པ་གསུམ།</span></li><li class="italic">doṣa-traya</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">Desire, anger, and delusion.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="29ab9fa8-cc03-4a4d-8452-d95a452ff546" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qe55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1336</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Three Horns</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rwa gsum pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྭ་གསུམ་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9209">Godānīya</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="d74740fc-80b1-4f01-b5fe-d0fa8d7a8e59" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qed5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1337</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">three kinds of awakening</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">byang chub gsum</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བྱང་ཆུབ་གསུམ།</span></li><li class="italic">tribodhi</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">The three levels of awakening that are respectively achieved by <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8536">hearers</span>, <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8595">solitary buddhas</span>, and perfect buddhas.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="04a1b256-f69d-4139-b693-3692fcc6ed1f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qel5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1338</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">three realms</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">khams gsum, srid pa gsum</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཁམས་གསུམ།, སྲིད་པ་གསུམ།</span></li><li class="italic">tribhuvana, tridhātu</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">The desire realm, the form realm, and the formless realm of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8589">cyclic existence</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="13f5ca5d-5372-4b5c-8e07-c82f44129374" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qet5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1339</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">three stains</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dri ma gsum</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དྲི་མ་གསུམ།</span></li><li class="italic">trimala</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">Anger, desire, and ignorance.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="95f93edf-339f-43dc-bd37-c78a1bd33e68" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qf55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1340</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">thus-gone, thus-gone one</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">de bzhin gshegs pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དེ་བཞིན་གཤེགས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">tathāgata</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p>A frequently used synonym for <em class="emph">buddha</em>. According to different explanations, it can be read as <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">tathā-gata</em>, literally meaning “one who has thus gone,” or as <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">tathā-āgata</em>, “one who has thus come.” <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">Gata</em>, though literally meaning “gone,” is a past passive participle used to describe a state or condition of existence. <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">Tatha­(tā)</em>, often rendered as “suchness” or “thusness,” is the quality or condition of things as they really are, which cannot be conveyed in conceptual, dualistic terms. Therefore, this epithet is interpreted in different ways, but in general it implies one who has departed in the wake of the buddhas of the past, or one who has manifested the supreme awakening dependent on the reality that does not abide in the two extremes of existence and quiescence. It is also often used as a specific epithet of the Buddha Śākyamuni.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="fb1801da-eed9-4437-a4ab-556e231d93b2" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qfd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1341</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Tiger Ear Star</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">stag rna’i rgyu skar</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྟག་རྣའི་རྒྱུ་སྐར།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">Unidentified figure connected to a prophetic discourse.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="d2769128-4909-4ea7-a15d-4d2e437ca049" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qfl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1342</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Timely Flow</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dus su ’bab pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དུས་སུ་འབབ་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9657">Saṅkāśa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="33206ea7-78b1-4b9f-97fc-6fa7796ae3cb" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qft5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1343</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Timely Moving Lotuses</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">pad ma dus su rgyu ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">པད་མ་དུས་སུ་རྒྱུ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A lotus pond on the fifth minor mountain on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9423">Lofty Summit</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="9362bc16-fdc4-4213-9584-1071554c787f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qg55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1344</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Timely Water</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dus kyi chu</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དུས་ཀྱི་ཆུ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A town in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9847">Videha</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="ba212295-5de3-4933-bb38-00cb13c18b19" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qgd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1345</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Tormented by All Suffering</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sdug bsngal kun gyis nyen</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྡུག་བསྔལ་ཀུན་གྱིས་ཉེན།</span></li><li class="italic">sarva­duḥkhāvarta</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of sixteen realms that surround the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9279">Hell of Ultimate Torment</span>. This hell is the same as <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9877">Wrapped in Every Possible Pain</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="1a7ba69b-ea63-422a-9453-bcd08af2f297" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qgl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1346</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Tormenting Armor of Vajra-Like Flies</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bung ba rdo rje lta bus gnod pa’i go cha</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བུང་བ་རྡོ་རྗེ་ལྟ་བུས་གནོད་པའི་གོ་ཆ།</span></li><li class="italic">vajra­bhramara­pīḍā­saṃnāha</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of the sixteen realms that surround the <span><span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9277">Hell of Heat</span></span>. </p></div></div></div></div><div id="c2f2e0c6-4474-4642-b651-394b9e6b8064" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qgt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1347</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Total Darkness</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">thams cad mun pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཐམས་ཅད་མུན་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">sarvāndhakāra</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of sixteen realms that surround the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9235">Great Howling Hell</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="ebad79a4-53bc-448c-be43-38d8a85a7fc5" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qh55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1348</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Total Pleasure</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gcig tu dga’ ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གཅིག་ཏུ་དགའ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of the twenty-seven realms of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9266">Heaven Free from Strife</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="9c6720bd-b000-4495-b353-8c729e194e60" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qhd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1349</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">transient collection</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’jig tshogs</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འཇིག་ཚོགས།</span></li><li class="italic">satkāya</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">The transitory collection of the five <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9925">aggregates</span>, the basis for the view of a self or that which belongs to a self.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="26111e83-281f-4bf6-bfbe-ebcf10e95666" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qhl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1350</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Traveling Fragrance</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dri rgyu ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དྲི་རྒྱུ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest on the lower level of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9417">Living on the Peak</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="492dbc16-adbc-4c17-b8d2-703c5acd669e" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qht5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1351</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Traveling on Great Mounts</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bzhon pa rgya che ba la rnam par rgyu ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བཞོན་པ་རྒྱ་ཆེ་བ་ལ་རྣམ་པར་རྒྱུ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of the twenty-seven realms of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9266">Heaven Free from Strife</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="4c5144ac-c262-442a-95ed-ade898ede93b" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qi55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1352</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Tree Made of Anthers</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ze’u ’bru’i lus kyi shing</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཟེའུ་འབྲུའི་ལུས་ཀྱི་ཤིང་།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A town in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9847">Videha</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="f90c8a87-32a0-4a18-abb2-e800b8d01186" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qid5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1353</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Triple Beauty</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gsum mdzes</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གསུམ་མཛེས།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9027">Dwelling in One Direction</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="138b0323-0fa5-40a7-abae-f1fd30f631ce" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qil5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1354</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Triple Circle</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">thig le gsum pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཐིག་ལེ་གསུམ་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9823">Upward Ocean</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="f48e66ae-2e7c-4a3c-afad-fa931f3f60ef" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qit5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1355</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Triple Horns</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rwa gsum pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྭ་གསུམ་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">(1) A mountain in the sea south of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>. (2) A river on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9823">Upward Ocean</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="53711d8f-dbe8-416b-85a4-de0dc5405614" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qj55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1356</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Triple Summits</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rwa gsum pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྭ་གསུམ་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">An island in the vicinity of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="a82d487c-402b-4d47-81d9-2b401157e577" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qjd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1357</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">triple-lute bearer, triple-lute-bearer, triple-lute-bearer gods</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">pi bang can gsum pa lha</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">པི་བང་ཅན་གསུམ་པ་ལྷ།</span></li><li class="italic">vīṇātṛtīyaka</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A class of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8531">gods</span> associated with the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8526">Four Great Kings</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="c231e807-ddc0-49b4-b626-23fcc7246825" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qjl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1358</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Tsokala</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">tso ka la</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཙོ་ཀ་ལ།</span></li><li class="italic">tsokala</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A land in the south of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="67bbe94b-d1e4-4c34-9154-604aa5094713" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qjt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1359</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Tsontva</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">tson twa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཙོན་ཏྭ།</span></li><li class="italic">tsontva</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A land in the south of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="818b5e43-c694-44ee-b0c4-668d2fc9f548" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qk55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1360</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Turning Away from Pride</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">nga rgyal ldog pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ང་རྒྱལ་ལྡོག་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of the twenty-seven realms in the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9266">Heaven Free from Strife</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="9400772c-2f9d-4de4-952b-a975b113f6a7" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qkd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1361</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Twelve Mountains</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ri bcu gnyis la nges par gnas pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རི་བཅུ་གཉིས་ལ་ངེས་པར་གནས་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">An island in the vicinity of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="ea1f16e6-a979-4f91-99d3-152e71e6d64a" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qkl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1362</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">two truths</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bden pa gnyis</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བདེན་པ་གཉིས།</span></li><li class="italic">dvayasatya</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">The truths of the way things seem to be and the way they actually are.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="1e2f1637-542d-48fc-9a6e-80ca7124f1af" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qkt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1363</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Unbearable Harm</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gnod pa mi bzad pa, gnod pa mi bzod pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གནོད་པ་མི་བཟད་པ།, གནོད་པ་མི་བཟོད་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">kāraṇāprasaha</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of sixteen realms that surround the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8975">Crushing Hell</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="62fa3afc-b6a8-42ed-9414-c66c0ddb6d1d" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ql55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1364</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Unbearably Terrifying</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rab tu mi bzad cing mchog tu ’jigs pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རབ་ཏུ་མི་བཟད་ཅིང་མཆོག་ཏུ་འཇིགས་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river in the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9630">Reviving Hell</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="c4637911-3dc2-4cde-a4bb-8bb7b8b825eb" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qld5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1365</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Undefeatable</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mi ’joms pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མི་འཇོམས་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A virtuous <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8562">nāga</span> king. </p></div></div></div></div><div id="4ed71e4c-858a-402a-a193-0ee0f9723ce8" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qll5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1366</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Undulating</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rlabs rab tu ’jug pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རླབས་རབ་ཏུ་འཇུག་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9657">Saṅkāśa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="317d75eb-8649-4042-97ad-36eca630d950" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qlt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1367</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Universal Delight</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">kun mthong yid ’ong</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀུན་མཐོང་ཡིད་འོང་།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9008">Distinguished in Many Colorful Ways</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="86c97e6e-e51c-4a7d-b5f4-004f4455e296" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qm55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1368</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Universal Disease</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">nad thams cad pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ནད་ཐམས་ཅད་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">sarvavyādhika</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of sixteen realms that surround the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9630">Reviving Hell</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="db781941-4ed2-4ea9-85d5-4c911aaf64ac" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qmd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1369</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Universal Growth</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">thams cad skye ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཐམས་ཅད་སྐྱེ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8956">Continuous Movement</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="c36618c5-0f2e-4b1a-8e75-c994467c2f3f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qml5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1370</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Universal Illumination</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">kun snang</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀུན་སྣང་།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A pleasure grove in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9668">Shaded by Garlands</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="56e6f292-db60-4eae-8386-0ac67d495f9e" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qmt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1371</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Universal Joy</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">kun nas dga’ ba, thams cad rab tu dga’ bar gnas pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀུན་ནས་དགའ་བ།, ཐམས་ཅད་རབ་ཏུ་དགའ་བར་གནས་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">(1) A realm inhabited by <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8530">garland-bearer gods</span> (<em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">thams cad rab tu dga’ bar gnas pa</em>). (2) A mountain in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9601">Promotion</span> (<em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">kun nas dga’ ba</em>).</p></div></div></div></div><div id="8e8a98bb-0c0c-4cf9-bb39-4f3b0568ffbf" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qn55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1372</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Universal Observer</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">kun tu mig</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀུན་ཏུ་མིག</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A previous ruler of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9276">Heaven of the Thirty-Three</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="41e261c3-3623-4152-b23b-3f602e411b66" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qnd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1373</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Universally Blissful</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">kun bde</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀུན་བདེ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A previous ruler of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9276">Heaven of the Thirty-Three</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="c724589a-dafe-4be4-994c-9982ab37136a" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qnl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1374</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Unlofty, Unlofty Heaven</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mi che ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མི་ཆེ་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">abṛha, avṛha</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">The first of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9927">five realms</span> associated with the fourth <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9969">concentration</span> into which only noble beings are born.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="fa3a1bf7-0fb2-4489-8a73-c8ee32808207" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qnt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1375</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Unmixed</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ma ’dres pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མ་འདྲེས་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A realm in the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9276">Heaven of the Thirty-Three</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="98f5e434-21c8-4984-9350-7500b12a8eb3" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qo55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1376</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Untouched Sunrise</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">nyi ma shar bar gyur bas mi reg pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཉི་མ་ཤར་བར་གྱུར་བས་མི་རེག་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9657">Saṅkāśa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="2c1833c0-e880-45cd-bd26-410a03ea9f7b" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qod5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1377</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Unwavering</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mi g.yo ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མི་གཡོ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A lotus pond on the fifth minor mountain on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9423">Lofty Summit</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="d83249c1-bc76-4e65-9285-a4051ffcd22b" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qol5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1378</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Upward Ocean</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rgya mtsho gyen du ’gro ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྒྱ་མཚོ་གྱེན་དུ་འགྲོ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9847">Videha</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="1657ce1b-9a85-472c-9744-5e337cf6e6f1" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qot5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1379</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Utpala Colors</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ud pa la’i mdog</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཨུད་པ་ལའི་མདོག</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A realm of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8516">ever-infatuated gods</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="31fe22a3-5674-414b-84ba-e5e8c2c2ef51" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qp55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1380</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Utpala Gift</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ud pa la sbyin</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཨུད་པ་ལ་སྦྱིན།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A merchant in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>, later to be reborn as <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8641">Auspicious Time</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="c77032b7-9b2c-49cf-8ada-21f24f6fff58" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qpd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1381</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Uttara</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ud ta ra</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཨུད་ཏ་ར།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain to the north of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="549a5e07-9795-4ccc-99a9-4d4a8a337fdc" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qpl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1382</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Utter Joy</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rab tu dga’ ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རབ་ཏུ་དགའ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">(1) An emanated forest created upon the shoulders of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8636">Airāvaṇa</span>. (2) A lake near <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9734">Sudharma</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="1f4a0381-4ee4-41f5-9855-091cbe5d9c3a" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qpt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1383</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Utter Purity</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rab tu gtsang ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རབ་ཏུ་གཙང་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain range in the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9266">Heaven Free from Strife</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="6a434708-dc78-47bd-91b9-a43fa2a833eb" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qq55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1384</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Utter Vastness</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">shin tu yangs pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཤིན་ཏུ་ཡངས་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A pool in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9764">Swan Forest</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="fc6a7aad-9906-437b-a1d5-ceded9f551a6" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qqd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1385</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Utterly Delightful to Behold</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">kun nas mthong na dga’ ba, mthong na kun dga’ ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀུན་ནས་མཐོང་ན་དགའ་བ།, མཐོང་ན་ཀུན་དགའ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">(1) A lotus pond in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9413">Living by Rājanina</span> (<em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">mthong na kun dga’ ba</em>). (2) A mountain on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9840">Vast Garlands of Bliss</span> (<em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">kun nas mthong na dga’ ba</em>).</p></div></div></div></div><div id="913fd0f5-36a2-4150-bcb6-6ec8f9d2dbf3" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qql5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1386</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Utterly Dreadful</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">kun du mi dga’ ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀུན་དུ་མི་དགའ་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">nirānanda</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of sixteen realms that surround the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9630">Reviving Hell</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="5e6bb59e-e75e-4965-9bd5-77e905969f1a" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qqt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1387</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Utterly Lofty</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rab tu mtho ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རབ་ཏུ་མཐོ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of the twenty-seven realms in the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9266">Heaven Free from Strife</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="f54ee6cf-ddbf-4b5c-9d85-4fc5bb266a72" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qr55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1388</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Utterly Unborn</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">shin tu ma skyes pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཤིན་ཏུ་མ་སྐྱེས་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9142">Forest Garlands</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="fd2e7f85-7150-4873-98ac-5c9faa241eba" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qrd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1389</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Vaiśālī</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">yangs pa can</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཡངས་པ་ཅན།</span></li><li class="italic">vaiśālī</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9209">Godānīya</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="9c19ce62-8cf4-43e0-8880-bbc8136fc2f6" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qrl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1390</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Vaitaraṇī</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rab med</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རབ་མེད།</span></li><li class="italic">vaitaraṇī</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river in hell.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="f8b5db35-6cf1-45c2-9fba-f5ae74049a84" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qrt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1391</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Vajra Seat</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rdo rje’i gdan</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྡོ་རྗེའི་གདན།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">The site of the Buddha’s ultimate awakening.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="3179ad59-28ad-40a3-b464-8c7101a74525" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qs55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1392</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Vārāṇasī</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bA rA Na sI</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བཱ་རཱ་ཎ་སཱི།</span></li><li class="italic">vārāṇasī</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A city in North India, on the banks of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9182">Gaṅgā</span>, where the Buddha gave his first sermon; this name can be applied also to the surrounding country or district. It lies in modern day Uttar Pradesh, India. The name is rendered elsewhere in this translation as its older name, “<span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9378">Kāśī</span>.”</p></div></div></div></div><div id="e78c83d7-91a4-4f9a-bf70-6a23eec2d04f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qsd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1393</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Variation</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rnam pa sna tsogs</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྣམ་པ་སྣ་ཙོགས།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river in <span><span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9443">Majestic Trees</span></span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="8720c5ae-f8fe-4d27-b24d-1ea9962dafb5" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qsl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1394</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Various Chariots</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">shing rta sna tshogs</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཤིང་རྟ་སྣ་ཚོགས།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">See “<span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9032">Dwelling in Various Chariots</span>.”</p></div></div></div></div><div id="e4746ace-483a-438a-9091-40f64fdcd99e" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qst5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1395</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Varitavaṭṭānang</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ba ri ta baT+Ta nang</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བ་རི་ཏ་བཊྚ་ནང་།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8622">vidyādhara</span> site on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9375">Kālaka</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="99d42510-9f47-496b-a1a7-5b492c17ac4a" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qt55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1396</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Vast Forest of the Seasons</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dus kyi tshal rgya che</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དུས་ཀྱི་ཚལ་རྒྱ་ཆེ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9033">Dwelling on Forest Riverbanks</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="e3131a4c-0f84-4a71-97f9-6319cafe0d68" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qtd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1397</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Vast Garlands of Bliss</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bde ba’i phreng ba rgya chen po</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བདེ་བའི་ཕྲེང་བ་རྒྱ་ཆེན་པོ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9506">Moving in Mixed Environments</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="ea8688c5-ce0e-49e2-8868-39e813b09116" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qtl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1398</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Vast Sky</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">nam mkha’ ring ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ནམ་མཁའ་རིང་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">An area in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9102">Eyes Beyond the World</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="9bd01e83-b58c-4b7d-a56c-4ab51860fec4" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qtt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1399</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Vast Space</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bar yangs pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བར་ཡངས་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain range in the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9266">Heaven Free from Strife</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="49484145-4bd1-4375-83c4-5613551a4fc9" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qu55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1400</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Vastness</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rnam par yangs pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྣམ་པར་ཡངས་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">(1) An old <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8531">god</span> approached by <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8720">Musulundha</span>. (2) A lotus pool in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9764">Swan Forest</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="ad1846dd-8ad9-4b9a-9699-96492a3d20c5" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qud5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1401</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Vāsuki</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bA su ki, nor rgyas kyi bu</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ནོར་རྒྱས་ཀྱི་བུ།, བཱ་སུ་ཀི</span></li><li class="italic">vāsuki</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">(1) A virtuous <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8562">nāga</span> king (<em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">nor rgyas kyi bu</em>). (2) A <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8562">nāga</span> who visits <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9657">Saṅkāśa</span> Mountain (<em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">bA su ki</em>).</p></div></div></div></div><div id="cbc5749a-b2a7-4076-8bbb-2dffe04f4120" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qul5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1402</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Veil of Complete Darkness</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rab rib kun bsags pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རབ་རིབ་ཀུན་བསགས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">sarva­tamastimira­nikara</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of sixteen realms that surround the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9298">Howling Hell</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="26d352d4-c412-4155-bd5d-d8e9b6ab7fc0" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qut5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1403</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Vemacitrin</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">thags bzangs ris</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཐགས་བཟངས་རིས།</span></li><li class="italic">vemacitrin</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">An <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8489">asura</span> king.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="944185e2-bd54-4713-8c14-b5b47f0f5d2a" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qv55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1404</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Venomous Fangs</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mche ba’i dug</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མཆེ་བའི་དུག</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8562">nāga</span> who visits <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9657">Saṅkāśa</span> Mountain.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="497db3c3-853f-4a1e-9bcf-36558ab6be94" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qvd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1405</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">verses</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">tshigs su bcad pa’i sde</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཚིགས་སུ་བཅད་པའི་སྡེ།</span></li><li class="italic">gāthā</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One among the twelve sections of scripture.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="8aec7917-2f9b-4406-905e-88c1b008745d" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qvl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1406</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Very Violent</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rab tu mi bzad pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རབ་ཏུ་མི་བཟད་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">pracaṇḍa</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A realm that neighbors the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8846">Black Line Hell</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="b6ac5f01-fcb7-4115-9494-0fc28b902fee" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_qvt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1407</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">vessel bearer, vessel-bearer gods</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">yol go thogs pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཡོལ་གོ་ཐོགས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">karoṭapādaka</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A class of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8531">gods</span> associated with the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8526">Four Great Kings</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="77a43437-33b0-416b-8b24-5f106b01a8b1" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_r055anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1408</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Victorious Supreme Movement</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rgyal ba mchog ’gro</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྒྱལ་བ་མཆོག་འགྲོ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mansion upon the mountain Playful in the forest Joyous Wisdom.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="de0c838c-b599-413b-8afe-10bde09d7a07" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_r0d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1409</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Videha</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">lus ’phags po</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ལུས་འཕགས་པོ།</span></li><li class="italic">videha</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">The continent to the east of Mount <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9739">Sumeru</span>. </p></div></div></div></div><div id="dcd28351-43fb-434a-9eed-4bf4de0b6781" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_r0l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1410</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Vidhyādhara Celebration</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rig pa ’dzin pa rtse dga’ bas gnas pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རིག་པ་འཛིན་པ་རྩེ་དགའ་བས་གནས་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A stream on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9657">Saṅkāśa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="c3cbb027-67f8-4d7d-a0db-d8cc75d28f1e" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_r0t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1411</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Vidruma</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bi dru ma</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བི་དྲུ་མ།</span></li><li class="italic">vidruma</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain between <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9209">Godānīya</span> and <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9847">Videha</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="cd95b18d-3416-4f1b-9a31-c7962ea9ee79" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_r155anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1412</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">vidyādhara</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rig pa ’dzin pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རིག་པ་འཛིན་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">vidyādhara</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A class of semi-divine beings that are famous for wielding (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">dhara</em>) spells (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">vidyā</em>). Loosely understood as “sorcerers,” these magical beings are frequently petitioned through dhāraṇī and kriyātantra ritual to grant magical powers to the supplicant. The later Buddhist tradition, playing on the dual valences of <em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">vidyā</em> as “spell” and “knowledge,” began to apply this term to realized figures in the Buddhist pantheon.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="2bc29893-6085-42d1-958b-51e516268a65" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_r1d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1413</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Viewing</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">kun tu lta ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀུན་ཏུ་ལྟ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A realm of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8621">vessel-bearer gods</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="71c477d7-26a5-4379-a115-28a05113726e" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_r1l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1414</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Vikramaśīla</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bi kra ma shI la</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བི་ཀྲ་མ་ཤཱི་ལ།</span></li><li class="italic">vikramaśīla</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A renowned monastic complex in India.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="5f282b3e-2104-4c5c-b471-eb70cf7247af" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_r1t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1415</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">vīṇā</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">pi wang</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">པི་ཝང་།</span></li><li class="italic">vīṇā</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A family of Indian chordophone instruments.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="ad5f08e4-7bfc-4cad-aafb-7052b213eca9" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_r255anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1416</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Vinaya</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’dul ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འདུལ་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">vinaya</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">The Buddha’s teachings that lay out the rules and disciplines for his followers.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="d0a268c1-1774-4c2d-a898-ebf4f2308b1a" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_r2d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1417</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Vindhya, Vindhya Range, Vindhyas</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’bigs byed, ’bigs byed</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འབིགས་བྱེད།, འབིགས་བྱེད།</span></li><li class="italic">vindhya, vindhya</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain in the south of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="1e9d9556-55d2-46d7-8e54-e49609076636" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_r2l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1418</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Vindhya, Vindhya Range, Vindhyas</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’bigs byed, ’bigs byed</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འབིགས་བྱེད།, འབིགས་བྱེད།</span></li><li class="italic">vindhya, vindhya</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">An Indian mountain chain.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="16977813-7b26-4fe9-a276-122798c83a06" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_r2t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1419</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Vipaśyin</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rnam par gzigs</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྣམ་པར་གཟིགས།</span></li><li class="italic">vipaśyin</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A previous buddha.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="f375ae9a-0fe6-41d2-b176-247cb9e0e807" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_r355anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1420</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Virūḍhaka</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’phags skye po</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འཕགས་སྐྱེ་པོ།</span></li><li class="italic">virūḍhaka</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8526">Four Great Kings</span>, guardian of the south.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="a22448ce-e4c6-4085-a8e6-69a7ecaff72d" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_r3d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1421</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Virūpākṣa</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mig mi bzang</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མིག་མི་བཟང་།</span></li><li class="italic">virūpākṣa</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One among the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8526">Four Great Kings</span>, guardian of the west.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="16e9fa77-0503-4acd-9453-88cddbdea147" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_r3l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1422</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Vīryākaraśānti</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bIr+ya A ka ra shAn+ti</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བཱིརྱ་ཨཱ་ཀ་ར་ཤཱནྟི།</span></li><li class="italic">vīryākaraśānti</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">An Indian <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8569">paṇḍita</span> involved in translating this <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9986">sūtra</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="d752c637-f6f2-435e-9925-f0d9db758296" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_r3t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1423</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Vision of Vast Bliss</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bde ba rgya chen po dmigs pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བདེ་བ་རྒྱ་ཆེན་པོ་དམིགས་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9506">Moving in Mixed Environments</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="44a14e25-173b-4d53-a1e0-504b4fd6a5ed" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_r455anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1424</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Viṣkaṭā</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">biSh+ka TA</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བིཥྐ་ཊཱ།</span></li><li class="italic">viṣkaṭā</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A town in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9847">Videha</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="8acf2902-aec6-4e39-8b67-e38eefceb677" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_r4d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1425</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Viṣṇu</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">khyab ’jug</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཁྱབ་འཇུག</span></li><li class="italic">viṣṇu</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of the principal deities in the Hindu pantheon.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="2f1e3997-caca-4547-a745-622c43212c65" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_r4l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1426</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Viśvabhū</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">thams cad skyob</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཐམས་ཅད་སྐྱོབ།</span></li><li class="italic">viśvabhū</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A previous buddha.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="56b0a86d-eb4b-424b-8058-9dfffaebb2c0" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_r4t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1427</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Vrikṣīrang</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bri k+ShI rang</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བྲི་ཀྵཱི་རང་།</span></li><li class="italic">vrikṣīraṅ</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A town in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9847">Videha</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="c0b907e5-ca6c-446b-b792-74cad63e66f2" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_r555anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1428</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Vulture Friendship</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bya rgod dang nye ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བྱ་རྒོད་དང་ཉེ་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">gṛdhrasāmanta</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain in the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8975">Crushing Hell</span></p></div></div></div></div><div id="a8760233-d1ba-49dc-806e-a083dff7af6f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_r5d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1429</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Vulture Terrors</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bya rgod kyi ’jigs pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བྱ་རྒོད་ཀྱི་འཇིགས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">gṛdhrabhairava</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A realm that neigbors the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8846">Black Line Hell</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="918dd6ec-a05a-42be-b643-4e81d42ade38" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_r5l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1430</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Wailer</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">kyi hud zer ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀྱི་ཧུད་ཟེར་བ།</span></li><li class="italic">hāhārava</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of sixteen realms that surround the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8975">Crushing Hell</span>. Literally, “Cries of Woe” or “Lamenting.”</p></div></div></div></div><div id="d26a7ba2-ef7c-4aa2-be38-c70b957da543" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_r5t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1431</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">wakefulness</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ye shes</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཡེ་ཤེས།</span></li><li class="italic">jñāna</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">Also known as “wisdom,” “gnosis,” or the like. Typically refers to a nonconceptual or unobscured state of knowledge.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="ee22c650-69cc-4e2e-9d5c-2edc3e08bda8" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_r655anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1432</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">wandering</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">kun tu rgyu ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀུན་ཏུ་རྒྱུ་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A class of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8531">gods</span> associated with the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8526">Four Great Kings</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="c01ba3bd-0eed-4ee6-9e43-5299d6fd0515" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_r6d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1433</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Warm</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dron mo</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དྲོན་མོ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">An ocean between <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9209">Godānīya</span> and <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9847">Videha</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="d6c1a033-11d6-407d-a9c6-4e542bbc46e6" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_r6l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1434</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">water dwellers</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">chu na gnas pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཆུ་ན་གནས་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A class of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8489">asuras</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="b5a887b0-e718-45d2-9780-33f1def83488" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_r6t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1435</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Water Lily Mansion</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">me tog ku ba la ya’i khyim</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མེ་ཏོག་ཀུ་བ་ལ་ཡའི་ཁྱིམ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mansion in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9066">Engaging in Clarification</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="fec0cade-87b5-4270-93fe-001f13eb13ec" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_r755anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1436</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Water of Joy</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dga’ ba’i chu, rab tu dga’ bar gyur pa’i chu</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དགའ་བའི་ཆུ།, རབ་ཏུ་དགའ་བར་གྱུར་པའི་ཆུ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">(1) A lake on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9078">Equal Peaks</span> (<em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">dga’ ba’i chu</em>). (2) A river on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9657">Saṅkāśa</span> (<em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">rab tu dga’ bar gyur pa’i chu </em>).</p></div></div></div></div><div id="91327e0d-fbbd-434b-a50c-6330510a937a" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_r7d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1437</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Water That One Never Tires Of</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ngoms pa med pa’i chu</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ངོམས་པ་མེད་པའི་ཆུ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A pond in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8956">Continuous Movement</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="5276714e-5708-4cc6-bb8f-e205628b98bd" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_r7l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1438</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Waters Always Mingled with the Moon</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rtag tu zla ba dang ’dres pa’i chu</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རྟག་ཏུ་ཟླ་བ་དང་འདྲེས་པའི་ཆུ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A lake on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9078">Equal Peaks</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="fde8faa8-43b3-4d6e-92de-97f866be0f90" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_r7t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1439</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Waves of the Seas of Jambudvīpa</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’dzam bu’i gling gi rgya mtsho’i rlabs</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འཛམ་བུའི་གླིང་གི་རྒྱ་མཚོའི་རླབས།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">An ocean far off the coast of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="a82dfe9e-1893-433e-8bf5-1674ef2f50ab" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_r855anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1440</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Wavy</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rlabs ldan, rlabs rab tu ’jug pa, rlabs ’byung ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རླབས་འབྱུང་བ།, རླབས་རབ་ཏུ་འཇུག་པ།, རླབས་ལྡན།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">(1) A lake on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9078">Equal Peaks</span> (<em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">rlabs rab tu ’jug pa</em>). (2) A river to the south of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span> (<em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">rlabs ldan</em>). (3) A river on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9657">Saṅkāśa</span> (<em class="foreign text-wy" lang="bo-LATN">rlabs ’byung ba</em>).</p></div></div></div></div><div id="d882b417-ed09-40d5-8495-272f37e18892" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_r8d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1441</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Well-Consumed</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">legs par zos pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ལེགས་པར་ཟོས་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain between <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9398">Kuru</span> and <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9209">Godānīya</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="acdf373f-9e69-4448-b086-15d140b4c33d" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_r8l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1442</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Well-Endowed</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rab sbyor</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རབ་སྦྱོར།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of the seven golden mountains that surround Mount <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9739">Sumeru</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="5763e542-6c29-456b-b615-8af8550f1dfc" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_r8t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1443</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">well-gone one</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bde bar gshegs pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བདེ་བར་གཤེགས་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">sugata</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">An epithet of the buddhas meaning “one who has gone to bliss.” The Sanskrit term literally means “faring well.”</p></div></div></div></div><div id="fc27bc24-cdbe-4071-85dd-3f64ce29fc49" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_r955anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1444</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">White</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dkar po</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དཀར་པོ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A previous ruler of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9276">Heaven of the Thirty-Three</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="863f4eaf-9553-4490-aa08-c3c579b9da31" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_r9d5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1445</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">White Body</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">lus dkar</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ལུས་དཀར།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A realm of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8617">triple-lute-bearer gods</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="adfff97b-888b-48b0-8235-a928e35463dd" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_r9l5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1446</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">White Cloud</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sprin dkar po</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྤྲིན་དཀར་པོ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9657">Saṅkāśa</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="c7e56661-2c0e-40c7-9ac0-5f0f252168ca" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_r9t5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1447</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">White Cloud Keeper</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sprin dkar po ’dzin pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྤྲིན་དཀར་པོ་འཛིན་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A mountain in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9398">Kuru</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="74002374-68df-4117-a708-c91304ad64cb" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ra55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1448</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">White Gambhīra</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gam bhi ro dkar</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གམ་བྷི་རོ་དཀར།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A lake in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9209">Godānīya</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="efad7f47-72fe-4d65-a542-3844cd7939bb" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_rad5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1449</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">White Water</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">chu dkar</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཆུ་དཀར།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A peak on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9739">Sumeru</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="3b3be5b7-c257-4d34-8363-f98d11564ab4" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_ral5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1450</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Wild Water</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">shin tu grol bar gyur pa’i chu</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཤིན་ཏུ་གྲོལ་བར་གྱུར་པའི་ཆུ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8989">Deer Abode</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="fc8a014a-35db-4927-8cc5-f06aa5f723ed" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_rat5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1451</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">wind</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">rlung</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">རླུང་།</span></li><li class="italic">prāṇa, vāyu</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of the four <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9921">elements</span> that constitute all matter, or one of the three primary humors (<em class="foreign break text-sa" lang="sa-LATN">doṣa</em>) of the body.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="d23c6bcd-6c91-480e-a362-89a3ed8a3ea6" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_rb55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1452</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">wine drinker</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">chang ba rnams kyis btung ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཆང་བ་རྣམས་ཀྱིས་བཏུང་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A class of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8622">vidyādharas</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="54c05bad-9582-403a-b922-d9463069f1ce" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_rbd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1453</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Wish-Fulfilling Waters</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ji ltar ’dod pa’i chu</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཇི་ལྟར་འདོད་པའི་ཆུ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river in <span><span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9443">Majestic Trees</span></span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="3297ddc1-1e7a-44dc-8453-4d609cb449df" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_rbl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1454</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">woman craver</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">bud med la sred pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">བུད་མེད་ལ་སྲེད་པ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A class of <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8622">vidyādharas</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="b58c9481-32a9-4586-a2e1-b08870bc187f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_rbt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1455</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">worm</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">srin bu</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྲིན་བུ།</span></li><li class="italic">kṛmi</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">When refering to the human body, these are creatures that inhabit it and may either harm or contribute to its health. Note that this term can also mean insects and <span class="ignore">worm</span>s in general.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="314cbb1a-5c42-435d-a3b3-c3cd3d14e01f" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_rc55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1456</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Worrisome</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">kun du rtog byed</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཀུན་དུ་རྟོག་བྱེད།</span></li><li class="italic">saṅkalpakāraṇa</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of sixteen realms that surround the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9298">Howling Hell</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="69eec99c-d322-425f-bc83-85bb4b1e65ae" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_rcd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1457</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">worthy one</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">dgra bcom pa</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">དགྲ་བཅོམ་པ།</span></li><li class="italic">arhat</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A person who has accomplished the final fruition of the path of the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-8536">hearers</span> and is liberated from <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9884">saṃsāra</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="70267edc-1d77-489a-943a-c280d386c636" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_rcl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1458</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Wrapped in Every Possible Pain</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">sdug bsngal kun dkris</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">སྡུག་བསྔལ་ཀུན་དཀྲིས།</span></li><li class="italic">sarvaduḥkhāvarta</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">One of sixteen realms that surround the <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9279">Hell of Ultimate Torment</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="5b457f37-2050-4b7a-a1bd-a4844678591e" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_rct5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1459</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">wrong view</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">log lta</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ལོག་ལྟ།</span></li><li class="italic">mithyā-dṛṣṭi</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">The third among the three mental misdeeds.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="9d3bfc42-ac48-41d3-b11a-e2ae12b0ad5c" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_rd55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1460</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">yakṣa</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">gnod sbyin</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">གནོད་སྦྱིན།</span></li><li class="italic">yakṣa</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p>A class of nonhuman beings who inhabit forests, mountainous areas, and other natural spaces, or serve as guardians of villages and towns, and may be propitiated for health, wealth, protection, and other boons, or controlled through magic. According to tradition, their homeland is in the north, where they live under the rule of the Great King Vaiśravaṇa.</p><p> Several members of this class have been deified as gods of wealth (these include the just-mentioned Vaiśravaṇa) or as bodhisattva generals of yakṣa armies, and have entered the Buddhist pantheon in a variety of forms, including, in tantric Buddhism, those of wrathful deities.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="996fe086-2cf2-4228-9cd7-88b80aa7dd10" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_rdd5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1461</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Yamunā</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ya mu nA, ya mu na</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཡ་མུ་ན།, ཡ་མུ་ནཱ།</span></li><li class="italic">yamunā</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A river in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9338">Jambudvīpa</span>, still called by the same name today.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="24cee0e6-a6c4-4496-aeb0-bb146ca90f8a" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_rdl5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1462</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Yavana</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">ya ba na</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">ཡ་བ་ན།</span></li><li class="italic">yavana</li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">Indian term used in reference to Greeks, or foreign barbarians in general.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="8b82ad5d-96e6-486d-821c-a45620d2464d" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_rdt5anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1463</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Yielding All Fruits</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">’bras bu kun phyed</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">འབྲས་བུ་ཀུན་ཕྱེད།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A park in <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9757">Sustained by Fruition</span>.</p></div></div></div></div><div id="46ed4626-7a6a-412e-b39a-8d08bc5e6dee" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_re55anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">g.1464</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="flex gap-1 flex-col p-0 @c/sidebar:-mt-0.5"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Yielding to Pressure and Bouncing Back</div><ul class="ml-4 list-disc"><li class="italic">mnan na nem la bteg na ’phar ba</li><li class="pt-1"><span class="font-tibetan text-base">མནན་ན་ནེམ་ལ་བཏེག་ན་འཕར་བ།</span></li></ul><div class="glossary-instance-definition"><p class="definition">A forest on <span data-glossary-id="UT22084-068-021-9771">Tamer of Deer Enemies</span>.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-state="inactive" data-orientation="horizontal" role="tabpanel" aria-labelledby="radix-_R_2npftt6btb_-trigger-bibliography" id="radix-_R_2npftt6btb_-content-bibliography" tabindex="0" data-slot="tabs-content" class="mt-2 ring-offset-background focus-visible:outline-none focus-visible:ring-2 focus-visible:ring-ring focus-visible:ring-offset-2 pb-8 data-[state=inactive]:hidden"><div class="flex flex-col w-full"><div id="bibliography" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_2nanpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4 @c/sidebar:mt-5 mt-6">b.</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><h2 class="font-serif font-light text-primary scroll-m-20 text-xl @c/sidebar:mt-4 mt-6 @c/sidebar:pb-2 pb-3 @c/sidebar:text-left text-center section-title">Bibliography</h2></div></div><div class="mt-3 flex flex-col gap-6"><div class="flex flex-col gap-4"><div id="Bibliography-0" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_2t7anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4 @c/sidebar:mt-0.5 mt-4">b.1</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div class="text-secondary font-sans text-base font-bold">Bibliography</div></div></div><div id="13a7a914-bd19-4f41-b832-b82b0dbf3b8b" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_23d7anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">b.1.1</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div><p><em>’phags pa dam pa’i chos dran pa nye bar gzhag pa</em>. Toh 287, Degé Kangyur vol. 68 (mdo sde, ya), folios 82a–318a; vol. 69 (mdo sde, ra), folios 1.b–307.a; vol. 70 (mdo sde, la), folios 1.b–312.a; and vol. 71 (mdo sde, sha), folios 1.b–229.b.</p></div></div></div><div id="636e0cbf-9272-4f9c-b0f9-b3d658bb623c" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_25d7anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">b.1.2</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div><p><em>’phags pa dam pa’i chos dran pa nye bar gzhag pa</em>. bka’ ’gyur (dpe bsdur ma) [Comparative Edition of the Kangyur], krung go’i bod rig pa zhib ’jug ste gnas kyi bka’ bstan dpe sdur khang (The Tibetan Tripitaka Collation Bureau of the China Tibetology Research Center). 108 volumes. Beijing: krung go’i bod rig pa dpe skrun khang (China Tibetology Publishing House), vol. 68, 238–842; vol. 69, 3–828; vol. 70, 3–821; and vol. 71, 3–603.</p></div></div></div><div id="36bc5042-9cf7-42bd-b892-cccd0f102dcb" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_27d7anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">b.1.3</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div><p><em>’phags pa dam pa’i chos dran pa nye bar gzhag pa</em>. Stok Palace Kangyur, vol. 82 (mdo sde, ki), folios 1.b–378; vol. 83 (mdo sde, khi), folios 1.b–370.b; vol. 84 (mdo sde, gi), folios 1.b–383.b; and vol. 85 (mdo sde, ghi), folios 1.b–419.b.</p></div></div></div><div id="412f24b7-4f2f-4e2e-b004-99f584d914b4" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_29d7anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">b.1.4</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div><p><em>Zhengfa nianchu jing</em> <em>正法念處經</em>. In Taishō Tripiṭaka. Edited by Junjirō Takakusu and Kaigyoku Watanabe. Vol. 17, no. 721.</p></div></div></div><div id="40b462b0-ae49-454b-aa27-5d026a61f192" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_2bd7anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">b.1.5</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div><p>Cabezón, José Ignacio. <em>Sexuality in Classical South Asian Buddhism</em>. Sommerville, MA: Wisdom Publications, 2017.</p></div></div></div><div id="c3d99b6d-965c-44c8-ac0c-a921a7243b18" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_2dd7anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">b.1.6</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div><p>Demoto, Mitsuyo (2009). “Die 128 Nebenhöllen nach dem Saddharmasmṛ- tyupasthānasūtra.” <em>Pāsādikadānam: Festschrift für Bhikkhu Pāsādika</em>, edited by Martin Straube, Roland Steiner, Jayandra Soni, Michael Hahn, and Mitsuyo Demoto. Marburg: Indica et Tibetica Verlag, 2009: 61–88.</p></div></div></div><div id="c46a5e3e-72ce-40aa-b3ee-00f33ea73b40" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_2fd7anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">b.1.7</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div><p>Demoto, Mitsuyo, ed. <em>Saddharma­smṛtyupasthāna­sūtra</em>: Critical Edition of Ch. 3. Unpublished draft, last modified July 2012. PDF file.</p></div></div></div><div id="602990c5-92a3-4fbf-a396-bf44cadc88e3" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_2hd7anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">b.1.8</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div><p>Denkarma (<em>pho brang stod thang ldan [/ lhan] dkar gyi chos ’gyur ro cog gi dkar chag</em>). Degé Tengyur, vol. 206 (sna tshogs, jo), folios 294.b–310.a.</p></div></div></div><div id="5983928d-054e-40f9-8672-301a86f760ab" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_2jd7anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">b.1.9</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div><p>Herrmann-Pfandt, Adelheid. <em>Die lHan kar ma: ein früher Katalog der ins Tibetische übersetzten buddhistischen Texte</em>. Vienna: Verlag der österreichischen Akademie der Wissenschaften, 2008. </p></div></div></div><div id="3abfca81-e489-48ab-82ea-58d0bf38ad7e" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_2ld7anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">b.1.10</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div><p>Kritzer, Robert (Forthcoming). “Worms in <em>Saddharma­smṛtyupasthāna­sūtra</em>.” In <em>Memorial Volume for Helmut Krasser</em>. Cambridge: Harvard University Press.</p></div></div></div><div id="43c0e73f-e964-42dd-ba08-e0647bba8eea" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_2nd7anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">b.1.11</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div><p>Kritzer, Robert (2020). “Meditation on the Body in Chapter 7 of <em>Saddharma­smṛtyupasthāna­sūtra</em>.” <em>Religions</em> 11, no. 6 (2020): 283.</p></div></div></div><div id="8ef82ddf-bf4e-4c6c-9e96-71ada3524ba6" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_2pd7anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">b.1.12</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div><p>Lin, Li-kuoung, &amp; P. Demiéville. <em>L’aide-mémoire de la vraie loi</em>. Paris: Adrien-Maisonneuve, 1949. </p></div></div></div><div id="4942be26-0037-4771-aa26-18995e88ddf7" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_2rd7anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">b.1.13</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div><p>Mizuno, Kogen. “On the Ārya-saddharmasmrtyupasthāna-sūtra.” <em>Journal of Indian and Buddhist Studies</em> (<em>Indogaku Bukkyogaku Kenkyu</em>) 12 (September 1964): 38–47.</p></div></div></div><div id="15a6470b-e99a-46dd-b6e5-2447d2d4f42b" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_2td7anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">b.1.14</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div><p>Moretti, Costantino. “The Thirty-six Categories of ‘Hungry Ghosts’ Described in the Sūtra of the Foundations of Mindfulness of the True Law.” <em>Fantômes dans l’Extrême-Orient D’hier et D’aujourd’hui</em>. Edited by Vincent Durand Dastès, 43–69. Paris: INALCO, 2017.</p></div></div></div><div id="6b55a216-a61d-457c-941d-9ca6c468bc98" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_2vd7anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">b.1.15</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div><p>Rangjung Dorjé (rang byung rdo rje). <em>dam pa’i chos dran pa nye bar bzhag pa’i mdo yi don snang bar byed pa’i bstan bcos</em>. Lhasa: bod ljongs mi dmangs dpe skrun khang, 2010.</p></div></div></div><div id="b7b32fa7-fdd5-4036-904e-fc2d9ce2571d" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_31d7anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">b.1.16</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div><p>Stuart, Daniel M. (2012). “A Less Traveled Path: Meditation and Textual Practice in the Saddharmasmṛtyupasthāna(sūtra).” PhD diss., University of California, Berkeley.</p></div></div></div><div id="85b7245b-3804-413d-a890-bb81c4147bae" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_33d7anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">b.1.17</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div><p>Stuart, Daniel M. (2015a). <em>A Less Traveled Path: Saddharmasmṛtyupasthānasūtra Chapter 2, Critically edited with A Study on Its Structure and Significance for the Development of Buddhist Meditation</em>. Sanskrit Texts from the Tibetan Autonomous Region (STTAR) 18. Beijing and Vienna: China Tibetology Publishing House and Austrian Academy of Sciences Press, 2015.</p></div></div></div><div id="397941dd-74f3-4a0e-b35b-e3b477d332d3" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_35d7anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">b.1.18</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div><p>Stuart, Daniel M. (2015b). “Power in Practice: Cosmic Sovereignty Envisioned in Buddhism’s Middle Period.” <em>The Critical Review for Buddhist Studies</em> 18 (2015): 165–96.</p></div></div></div><div id="eec65810-2844-46e3-8f84-44d99a4723d0" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_37d7anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">b.1.19</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div><p>Stuart, Daniel M. (2017a). “Yogācāra Substrata? Precedent Frames for Yogācāra Thought among Third-Century Yoga Practitioners in Greater Gandhāra.” <em>Journal of Indian Philosophy</em> 46 (October 2017): 193–240.</p></div></div></div><div id="e3276c79-b5b2-4a32-a78c-c81f40c996b8" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_39d7anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">b.1.20</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div><p>Stuart, Daniel M. (2017b). “Unmanifest Perceptions: Mind-Matter Interdependence and Its Consequences in Buddhist Thought and Practice.” In <em>Śrāvakabhūmi and Buddhist Manuscripts</em>, edited by Jundo Nagashima and Seongcheol Kim, 109–71. Tokyo: Nombre, 2017.</p></div></div></div><div id="4e5b3f43-c884-4e6a-8a58-33f11aeb8b63" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_3bd7anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">b.1.21</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div><p>Stuart, Daniel M. (2019). “<a href="https://doi.org/10.3390/rel10060363">Becoming Animal: Karma and the Animal Realm Envisioned through an Early Yogācāra Lens</a>.” <em>Religions</em> 10, no. 6 (2019): 363.</p></div></div></div><div id="87104957-9eb0-4fdd-af68-c18d0879e793" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_3dd7anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">b.1.22</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div><p>van der Kuijp, Leonard W. J. “On the Vicissitudes of Subhūticandra’s <em>Kāmadhenu</em> Commentary on the <em>Amarakoṣa</em> in Tibet.” <em>Journal of the International Association of Tibetan Studies</em>, no. 5 (December 2009): 1–105.</p></div></div></div><div id="effb588f-c504-4587-9d30-cf221156f62e" class="relative scroll-mt-20"><button type="button" id="radix-_R_3fd7anpftt6btb_" aria-haspopup="menu" aria-expanded="false" data-state="closed" class="absolute labeled -left-16 w-16 text-end hover:cursor-pointer whitespace-pre-line leading-4">b.1.23</button><div class="passage pl-6 @c/sidebar:pl-4"><div><p>Wallace, Vesna A., ed. <em>Saddharma­smṛtyupasthāna­sūtra</em>: Critical Edition of Ch. 1. Unpublished draft, last modified May 10, 2020. PDF file.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><script>$RS("S:5","P:5")</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,"57:I[916077,[\"/_next/static/chunks/2fb4b456dae69409.js?dpl=dpl_C4kSSWFdt51TZQpmuYtxXgHAunY1\",\"/_next/static/chunks/6165fecb8e0eae36.js?dpl=dpl_C4kSSWFdt51TZQpmuYtxXgHAunY1\",\"/_next/static/chunks/1cfd6a6ab8fe5d2f.js?dpl=dpl_C4kSSWFdt51TZQpmuYtxXgHAunY1\",\"/_next/static/chunks/15d7387d42764915.js?dpl=dpl_C4kSSWFdt51TZQpmuYtxXgHAunY1\"],\"ReaderBodyPanel\"]\n"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,"17:[\"$\",\"$L57\",null,{\"titles\":[{\"uuid\":\"88611b7f-1cbf-4e13-83e3-131a6410e0dd\",\"title\":\"The Application of Mindfulness of the Sacred Dharma\",\"language\":\"en\",\"type\":\"mainTitle\"},{\"uuid\":\"b1116e3d-54d5-4481-ba72-9567df624e2a\",\"title\":\"Saddharma­smṛtyupasthāna\",\"language\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"type\":\"mainTitle\"},{\"uuid\":\"7c1b65d2-c5bb-46dc-9b8b-9f0657c711b4\",\"title\":\"dam pa’i chos dran pa nye bar gzhag pa\",\"language\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"type\":\"mainTitle\"},{\"uuid\":\"95936891-12df-4c3e-b633-bc71ed74b6e6\",\"title\":\"དམ་པའི་ཆོས་དྲན་པ་ཉེ་བར་གཞག་པ།\",\"language\":\"bo\",\"type\":\"mainTitle\"},{\"uuid\":\"e104d207-b8e7-4a30-b73c-673dfae369d9\",\"title\":\"Toh 287\",\"language\":\"en\",\"type\":\"toh\"},{\"uuid\":\"6b27356e-2627-4b84-90f7-fc7bd897dc2f\",\"title\":\"dam chos dran pa nyer bzhag\",\"language\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"type\":\"otherTitle\"},{\"uuid\":\"3efda650-c833-46b2-b176-6e5681929be7\",\"title\":\"《正法念處經》\",\"language\":\"zh\",\"type\":\"otherTitle\"},{\"uuid\":\"fb39d14a-2846-459d-951a-f64586e2c518\",\"title\":\"The Noble Application of Mindfulness of the Sacred Dharma\",\"language\":\"en\",\"type\":\"longTitle\"},{\"uuid\":\"1c61c226-d6e0-422b-89f8-2b278d724afc\",\"title\":\"Ārya­saddharma­smṛtyupasthāna\",\"language\":\"Sa-Ltn\",\"type\":\"longTitle\"},{\"uuid\":\"ec03a0f8-ab95-44c7-86eb-a62ddd2449a5\",\"title\":\"’phags pa dam pa’i chos dran pa nye bar gzhag pa\",\"language\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"type\":\"longTitle\"},{\"uuid\":\"3daf048a-b20b-42be-8508-fc66cd9248ea\",\"title\":\"འཕགས་པ་དམ་པའི་ཆོས་དྲན་པ་ཉེ་བར་གཞག་པ།\",\"language\":\"bo\",\"type\":\"longTitle\"}],\"frontMatter\":[{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"4b28412a-ab96-485a-824a-d01b0a0686d5\",\"sort\":2,\"type\":\"summaryHeader\",\"label\":\"s.\",\"alignments\":{}},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"heading\",\"attrs\":{\"level\":2,\"start\":0,\"end\":7,\"uuid\":\"10a09bab-b93f-49b7-8713-5cc4034a8d81\",\"class\":\"section-title\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Summary\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":7}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"efbdaa49-31e4-4021-ab94-98210f1cf2f9\",\"sort\":4,\"type\":\"summary\",\"label\":\"s.1\",\"alignments\":{}},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":1306,\"uuid\":\"efbdaa49-31e4-4021-ab94-98210f1cf2f9\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"While on the way to \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":20}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Rājagṛha\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":20,\"end\":28},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"a5d6cdd3-67d3-4718-a63d-0028f40baee2\",\"uuid\":\"69251f3c-d669-4a1d-a7fc-407fcae1aa1b\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" to collect \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":28,\"end\":40}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"alms\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":40,\"end\":44},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"04bccafd-3cc4-42b2-a249-07b6649932ba\",\"uuid\":\"5bab7d16-daeb-482d-80e4-5b9f16188935\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", a group of newly ordained monks are approached by some \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":44,\"end\":101}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"non-Buddhists\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":101,\"end\":114},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"02f4d334-0e69-4600-a543-0dcea128cf23\",\"uuid\":\"1d465c9f-d5b2-48ff-9bbf-94d7ed30da11\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", who suggest that their doctrine is identical to that of the Buddha, since everyone agrees that misdeeds of body, speech, and mind are to be given up. The monks do not know how to reply, and when they later return to the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":114,\"end\":336}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"brahmin\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":336,\"end\":343},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"d2beaf90-2596-4dcc-b765-8064c0cba1f3\",\"uuid\":\"ef7be384-5567-47f1-a902-d328ee30072e\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" town of \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":343,\"end\":352}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Nālati\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":352,\"end\":358},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"47ddecbd-4962-438a-8eec-33c5c48b2fa1\",\"uuid\":\"b3add1bb-16e7-4363-9d17-6dadd26f5547\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", where the Buddha is residing, \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":358,\"end\":390}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Śāradvatīputra\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":390,\"end\":404},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"b34f8e95-5fc9-44c9-8e45-f4587adea677\",\"uuid\":\"1cb9abc5-b8d4-4463-a674-626debf55cee\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" therefore encourages them to seek clarification from the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":404,\"end\":462}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Blessed One\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":462,\"end\":473},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"096407a8-2631-4818-90b7-90d522c2f84b\",\"uuid\":\"a96890bd-e42c-4ed4-b720-496dfe1f3b29\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" himself. In response to the monks’ request, the Buddha delivers a comprehensive discourse on the effects of virtuous and unvirtuous actions, explaining these matters from the perspective of an adept practitioner of his teachings, who sees and understands all this through a process of personal discovery. As the teaching progresses, the Buddha presents an epic tour of the realm of desire‍—from the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":473,\"end\":873}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Hell of Ultimate Torment\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":873,\"end\":897},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"8f5efab1-1d55-410b-b89a-af49ca7d6f7d\",\"uuid\":\"b70e2b15-45b7-4f54-80ce-21c194cdadd4\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" to the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":897,\"end\":905}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Heaven Free from Strife\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":905,\"end\":928},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"51ea6bef-2574-4728-a987-a2d2c53e8fd3\",\"uuid\":\"d8cfd2f2-810c-4890-914a-655a253f5dc3\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"‍—all the while introducing the specific human actions and attitudes that cause the experience of such worlds and outlining the ways to remedy and transcend them. In the final section of the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":928,\"end\":1119}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"sūtra\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1119,\"end\":1124},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"643935d0-63fb-47fc-8abc-2bc1b02a1331\",\"uuid\":\"1acb03e8-e8d6-4a1b-be7d-1489bc050297\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", which is presented as an individual scripture on its own, the focus is on mindfulness of the body and the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1124,\"end\":1232}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ripening\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1232,\"end\":1240},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"e6c5ad9a-9509-4706-9d6f-5fad607030a7\",\"uuid\":\"f4c00204-7609-46ea-b5e4-8746681c8e79\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" of karmic actions that is experienced among humans in particular.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1240,\"end\":1306}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"1cd7b6a0-bc0d-4ca6-81a0-25ee8a6bcd97\",\"sort\":28,\"type\":\"acknowledgmentHeader\",\"label\":\"ac.\",\"alignments\":{}},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"heading\",\"attrs\":{\"level\":2,\"start\":0,\"end\":16,\"uuid\":\"81adeb2b-6291-4ba2-be78-c60a2f64aea5\",\"class\":\"section-title\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Acknowledgements\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":16}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"98e433cd-1857-44fa-8d82-daa878403f57\",\"sort\":30,\"type\":\"acknowledgment\",\"label\":\"ac.1\",\"alignments\":{}},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":726,\"uuid\":\"085c7155-5805-40b0-9b7d-eb452cf0748d\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Translated by the Dharmachakra Translation Committee under the supervision of Chokyi Nyima Rinpoche. The translation was produced by Thomas Doctor with help from Benjamin Collet-Cassart and Timothy Hinkle. Thomas also wrote the introduction. Andreas Doctor checked the translation against the Tibetan and edited the text. The 84000 editorial team subsequently reviewed the translation and made further edits. Wiesiek Mical assisted by reviewing numerous passages against the available Sanskrit sources. Robert Kritzer generously shared several unpublished articles on the text with us, and Vesna Wallace and Mitsuyo Demoto kindly gave us access to drafts of their critical Sanskrit editions of chapters 1 and 3, respectively. \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":726}}]},{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":726,\"end\":838,\"uuid\":\"0cb17121-0812-49d0-b4fb-1714868e9b07\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The translation was completed under the patronage and supervision of 84000: Translating the Words of the Buddha.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":726,\"end\":838}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"bd492c05-4a23-4def-b71f-2fc7e5043b46\",\"sort\":33,\"type\":\"acknowledgment\",\"label\":\"ac.2\",\"alignments\":{}},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":158,\"uuid\":\"bd492c05-4a23-4def-b71f-2fc7e5043b46\",\"hasLeadingSpace\":true,\"leadingSpaceUuid\":\"3b2516b1-c231-442b-a607-38eb48fe51e9\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The generous sponsorship of Sun Ping, Tian Xingwen, and Sun Fanglin, which helped make the work on this translation possible, is most gratefully acknowledged.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":158}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"0bd9034c-6bb8-4995-ab39-ea65cf50bb72\",\"sort\":35,\"type\":\"introductionHeader\",\"label\":\"i.\",\"alignments\":{}},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"heading\",\"attrs\":{\"level\":2,\"start\":0,\"end\":12,\"uuid\":\"49331be1-bbaa-40d8-b3a7-0bc8f187aacf\",\"class\":\"section-title\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Introduction\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":12}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"b38ba171-d4f4-44b2-a83e-9473109bc328\",\"sort\":37,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"label\":\"i.1\",\"alignments\":{}},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":1017,\"uuid\":\"b38ba171-d4f4-44b2-a83e-9473109bc328\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The epic discourse of \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":22}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The Application of Mindfulness of the Sacred Dharma \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":22,\"end\":74},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"a0dbd59b-2034-4434-ad8c-cca64f2d683b\",\"lang\":\"en\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"(AMSD) unfolds as a single, sustained reply to a short question that is put to the Buddha \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":74,\"end\":164}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Śākyamuni\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":164,\"end\":173},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"aafd3f3f-d16d-4507-a177-f9eb18db6838\",\"uuid\":\"24589911-caec-4442-ba6f-533f27ca712b\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" as the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":173,\"end\":181}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"sūtra\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":181,\"end\":186},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"643935d0-63fb-47fc-8abc-2bc1b02a1331\",\"uuid\":\"dd55fbd1-20cc-406d-9c69-3858b3333ee1\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" opens. A group of newly ordained monks have been challenged by the members of another religious group, who suggest that the Buddha’s teachings are indistinguishable from those of their own teacher. Not knowing how to reply, the monks request that the Buddha explain how the path of the sacred Dharma is unlike any other. As the Buddha responds to the monks, he describes the path from the perspective of an adept meditating monk, who applies the Dharma teachings correctly and so discovers the truths of the Dharma. In an account that spans the full spectrum of life in \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":186,\"end\":757}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"saṃsāra\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":757,\"end\":764},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"35bde4db-33ca-4dba-8414-ff2df3723581\",\"uuid\":\"6c0c4c79-9e95-4694-9a29-afa6d6ace7c3\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", from the horrifying misery and intense pain of the lower realms to the enrapturing beauty and bliss in the heavens, the Buddha explains how different kinds of physical, verbal, and mental behavior of humans lead to rebirth in such realms of existence.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":764,\"end\":1017}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"5dea2aae-da63-4226-9e9c-bef69e9323d5\",\"sort\":47,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"label\":\"i.2\",\"alignments\":{}},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":1034,\"uuid\":\"5dea2aae-da63-4226-9e9c-bef69e9323d5\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The generic and unnamed monk, from whose perspective the Buddha explains the subject matter, witnesses the myriad realms of existence from the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":143}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Hell of Ultimate Torment\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":143,\"end\":167},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"8f5efab1-1d55-410b-b89a-af49ca7d6f7d\",\"uuid\":\"112c3271-2579-4298-9e89-389c030e25ca\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" to the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":167,\"end\":175}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Heaven Free from Strife\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":175,\"end\":198},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"51ea6bef-2574-4728-a987-a2d2c53e8fd3\",\"uuid\":\"b465fa08-e561-4e04-8c9a-a4634f914461\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", sometimes by means of the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":198,\"end\":226}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"divine eye\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":226,\"end\":236},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"bfe4d6ca-3e0f-4dde-a8bb-7c5149937f8b\",\"uuid\":\"55694f95-9bc8-4d99-a264-2b897c6d8736\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" that is accomplished through meditation, and at other times through the eye of \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":236,\"end\":316}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"insight\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":316,\"end\":323},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"dd19cf68-69ee-4f3b-bb5f-2c47fbe86706\",\"uuid\":\"72807edd-5002-45fc-bae9-d1f897b0a32d\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" that is acquired through hearing the teachings. In this way, the monk comes to directly recognize the matrix of causes and effects that keeps the wheel of \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":323,\"end\":479}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"cyclic existence\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":479,\"end\":495},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"7f9b4269-ecf7-4226-9cbd-3ff52a609edb\",\"uuid\":\"f3335e0d-008a-439f-a408-a35795282d05\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" turning, and he realizes with full clarity how, throughout all this, life and beings’ experiences are utterly impermanent and always determined by their own past actions. A very substantial part of the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":495,\"end\":698}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"sūtra\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":698,\"end\":703},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"643935d0-63fb-47fc-8abc-2bc1b02a1331\",\"uuid\":\"68d01922-b702-4e68-ba94-a052d00984fd\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" describes the ravishing sceneries and amazing events that take place in the heavens. In the midst of these breathtaking descriptions, the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":703,\"end\":842}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"sūtra\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":842,\"end\":847},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"643935d0-63fb-47fc-8abc-2bc1b02a1331\",\"uuid\":\"9cd1f9d1-8560-4bd2-af3d-8fb77e2bff6b\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" frequently presents pithy teachings of the Dharma, typically given in verses that may be spoken by \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":847,\"end\":947}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"gods\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":947,\"end\":951},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"001a0a5f-1d64-4686-98cb-d50f70cca517\",\"uuid\":\"49414cf3-e8e4-476e-9dac-d28cee2a6dfd\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", such as \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":951,\"end\":961}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Śakra\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":961,\"end\":966},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"c46473a9-c71c-4bc8-afb8-4c7b3d3f7bdb\",\"uuid\":\"fef789f4-a1c4-4338-afe0-720715839f5c\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", or by divine birds, such as the king of swans or the peacock king.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":966,\"end\":1034},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"endNoteLink\",\"attrs\":{\"notes\":[{\"endNote\":\"6130ae22-fd9a-42bb-b7ea-0062cf779b73\",\"label\":\"1\",\"uuid\":\"546ca672-9365-4310-b8e4-f2b8401c08dc\",\"start\":1034,\"end\":1034,\"location\":\"end\",\"toh\":null}]}}]}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"d9c91fea-2c94-48df-813b-843717a7b5ad\",\"sort\":68,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"label\":\"i.3\",\"alignments\":{}},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":1415,\"uuid\":\"d9c91fea-2c94-48df-813b-843717a7b5ad\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The account of the heavens and the actions that lead to rebirth there comes to an abrupt end in the midst of the descriptions of the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":133}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Heaven Free from Strife\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":133,\"end\":156},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"51ea6bef-2574-4728-a987-a2d2c53e8fd3\",\"uuid\":\"2154f329-24ef-4ae2-a5af-d936ec077ed1\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". Instead follows, for the remainder of the scripture, a teaching on mindfulness of the body. This latter teaching, which functions mostly as an independent part of the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":156,\"end\":325}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"sūtra\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":325,\"end\":330},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"643935d0-63fb-47fc-8abc-2bc1b02a1331\",\"uuid\":\"e8349fb3-9c09-4027-8fab-086bf1bd3c78\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", presents mindfulness of the body within the framework of the “internal” human body and the “external” body of the outer world. This latter section includes an elaborate description of the human realm according to Buddhist cosmology.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":330,\"end\":564},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"endNoteLink\",\"attrs\":{\"notes\":[{\"endNote\":\"b21f2e9e-9c85-49c4-ad64-a134cc842e77\",\"label\":\"2\",\"uuid\":\"a26ffeb8-c21c-458a-8c53-1b0708dddfe4\",\"start\":564,\"end\":564,\"location\":\"end\",\"toh\":null}]}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" Given the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":564,\"end\":575}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"sūtra\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":575,\"end\":580},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"643935d0-63fb-47fc-8abc-2bc1b02a1331\",\"uuid\":\"cfd813ac-18f2-470d-814d-2f4445f87ae3\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"’s sudden stop in the middle of the presentation of the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":580,\"end\":636}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Heaven Free from Strife\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":636,\"end\":659},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"51ea6bef-2574-4728-a987-a2d2c53e8fd3\",\"uuid\":\"42389375-3962-4231-966d-1297ab5d17e8\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", it seems quite likely that an earlier version of the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":659,\"end\":714}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"sūtra\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":714,\"end\":719},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"643935d0-63fb-47fc-8abc-2bc1b02a1331\",\"uuid\":\"3c229878-c81e-4edc-ab78-4be52104ae2d\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" might have been significantly longer than the present version and that only a partial version was available to the Tibetan translators. If so, the missing material must, however, have been lost at a very early point in the text’s history, since the Chinese translation,\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":719,\"end\":989},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"endNoteLink\",\"attrs\":{\"notes\":[{\"endNote\":\"eafd7071-b1dc-4111-96c7-c05487fee160\",\"label\":\"3\",\"uuid\":\"54fbf989-8f50-4f96-a955-f8313c93e760\",\"start\":989,\"end\":989,\"location\":\"end\",\"toh\":null}]}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" which was produced earlier, during the early sixth century,\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":989,\"end\":1049},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"endNoteLink\",\"attrs\":{\"notes\":[{\"endNote\":\"ff3b5861-4efd-4532-9af1-63c088315be2\",\"label\":\"4\",\"uuid\":\"74fc5851-b553-4b75-bb37-2abab6ff3da2\",\"start\":1049,\"end\":1049,\"location\":\"end\",\"toh\":null}]}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" features the same disjointed topical transition. In spite of this awkward end to the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1049,\"end\":1135}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"sūtra\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1135,\"end\":1140},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"643935d0-63fb-47fc-8abc-2bc1b02a1331\",\"uuid\":\"699a40d1-e4f4-4afc-b0cf-c552f60bcb26\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"’s description of the heavenly realms, the discourse of the AMSD as it remains today is a vast treasury of Dharma, a rich presentation of the realms of \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1140,\"end\":1292}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"saṃsāra\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1292,\"end\":1299},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"35bde4db-33ca-4dba-8414-ff2df3723581\",\"uuid\":\"3e93bdfb-85e0-4aff-95c7-109ac796cb13\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", and a splendid piece of world literature that stands out as one of the greatest literary works of classical India.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1299,\"end\":1415}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"63d08d5a-8388-403f-8d6f-de0bc7f9c5de\",\"sort\":90,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"label\":\"i.4\",\"alignments\":{}},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":1072,\"uuid\":\"63d08d5a-8388-403f-8d6f-de0bc7f9c5de\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"With its 2158 Tibetan pages, the AMSD is the largest scripture within the general \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":82}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"sūtra\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":82,\"end\":87},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"643935d0-63fb-47fc-8abc-2bc1b02a1331\",\"uuid\":\"b99d9b35-025a-4877-8299-fe7c7272bc49\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" section of the Degé Kangyur,\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":87,\"end\":116},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"endNoteLink\",\"attrs\":{\"notes\":[{\"endNote\":\"6428fb04-6b6e-4bbb-a243-74532f948431\",\"label\":\"5\",\"uuid\":\"cf6bf8b5-a9a6-485f-b5a3-147b0e3d250e\",\"start\":116,\"end\":116,\"location\":\"end\",\"toh\":null}]}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" where the text is placed as the first scripture within the collection of Hīnayāna scriptures. This placement among the Hīnayāna \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":116,\"end\":245}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"sūtras\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":245,\"end\":251},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"643935d0-63fb-47fc-8abc-2bc1b02a1331\",\"uuid\":\"5073c69b-8ced-4661-af71-c4e0b93cbce5\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" has been a topic of some debate among Tibetans, since one finds frequent occurrences of the term “Mahāyāna” within the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":251,\"end\":371}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"sūtra\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":371,\"end\":376},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"643935d0-63fb-47fc-8abc-2bc1b02a1331\",\"uuid\":\"485346bb-7d93-4c32-ab46-cc91a2093808\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"’s later sections. Notably, however, the term is only found in the Tibetan translation of the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":376,\"end\":470}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"sūtra\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":470,\"end\":475},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"643935d0-63fb-47fc-8abc-2bc1b02a1331\",\"uuid\":\"8b1c744c-fcb1-405a-befb-7ce653b60eb7\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", not in the Chinese translation.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":475,\"end\":508},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"endNoteLink\",\"attrs\":{\"notes\":[{\"endNote\":\"209961ce-6d75-4f1a-8a90-44d5e4d80dce\",\"label\":\"6\",\"uuid\":\"bf0ccc81-c038-413d-ae70-56d7b7494f21\",\"start\":508,\"end\":508,\"location\":\"end\",\"toh\":null}]}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" Moreover, the Tibetan translator of the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":508,\"end\":549}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"sūtra\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":549,\"end\":554},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"643935d0-63fb-47fc-8abc-2bc1b02a1331\",\"uuid\":\"f14235e6-4d04-49b1-bfe4-7f7efb6f6d31\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":554,\"end\":556}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Patshap Tsultrim Gyaltsen\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":556,\"end\":581},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"06eeafb3-6e7a-45a9-a148-46d8a8e4fd64\",\"uuid\":\"c415f80f-2c4c-44f3-93fd-81000932d114\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (eleventh–twelfth c.), himself classified the text as a Mahāyāna scripture in his colophon to the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":581,\"end\":680}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"sūtra\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":680,\"end\":685},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"643935d0-63fb-47fc-8abc-2bc1b02a1331\",\"uuid\":\"143d1a5f-5a86-425d-8c4e-9af2e40b4947\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". Still, the editor of the Degé Kangyur, \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":685,\"end\":726}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Situ Paṇchen Chökyi Jungné\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":726,\"end\":752},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"01520621-e4fb-48d3-9572-143f8531fe91\",\"uuid\":\"d288941b-882d-4fe5-9695-a8ca28f472d9\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (1700–1774) classified the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":752,\"end\":780}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"sūtra\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":780,\"end\":785},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"643935d0-63fb-47fc-8abc-2bc1b02a1331\",\"uuid\":\"0f9e73e2-5cb4-42fc-90af-0c28e3a92d5c\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" as belonging to the Hīnayāna, basing himself on the earlier classification of \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":785,\"end\":864}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Butön Rinchen Drup\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":864,\"end\":882},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"fb5c71d3-c33c-4d7a-8c17-3c952d6de664\",\"uuid\":\"dc0aeaad-8079-4f0d-ba44-3a0907857148\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (1290–1364), the famous compiler of the Kangyur. \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":882,\"end\":932}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Butön\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":932,\"end\":937},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"fb5c71d3-c33c-4d7a-8c17-3c952d6de664\",\"uuid\":\"3d5d1eba-8a78-4ca7-bdf3-9e1bf8de030c\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" in turn seems to have relied on the Denkarma inventory (compiled in 812), which likewise classifies the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":937,\"end\":1042}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"sūtra\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1042,\"end\":1047},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"643935d0-63fb-47fc-8abc-2bc1b02a1331\",\"uuid\":\"192275f2-6f8b-4140-b433-1156696d4089\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" as a Hīnayāna scripture.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1047,\"end\":1072},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"endNoteLink\",\"attrs\":{\"notes\":[{\"endNote\":\"c91aa30e-2bbd-4477-8871-566659d2d4c7\",\"label\":\"7\",\"uuid\":\"0ffecf1a-5dab-4039-bee4-a1d5ae820eb8\",\"start\":1072,\"end\":1072,\"location\":\"end\",\"toh\":null}]}}]}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"ca5f1caf-13a7-4d8e-803d-78bced912557\",\"sort\":121,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"label\":\"i.5\",\"alignments\":{}},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":1531,\"uuid\":\"ca5f1caf-13a7-4d8e-803d-78bced912557\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"According to its lengthy and very informative colophon, the Tibetan translation of the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":87}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"sūtra\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":87,\"end\":92},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"643935d0-63fb-47fc-8abc-2bc1b02a1331\",\"uuid\":\"c4f123ff-8466-47a2-8df9-6eaa0747eb12\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" that is preserved in the Degé Kangyur was produced during the reign of the Indian king \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":92,\"end\":180}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Rāmapāla\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":180,\"end\":188},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"1dd25731-ca1a-41d6-8bc5-e3d2888ecfd0\",\"uuid\":\"8692ca5e-7866-4330-aed3-78d1a87d26ac\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (ca. 1077–1120). In his colophon, the Tibetan translator \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":188,\"end\":246}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Tsultrim Gyaltsen\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":246,\"end\":263},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"06eeafb3-6e7a-45a9-a148-46d8a8e4fd64\",\"uuid\":\"6bf428ed-75f9-4a29-ac8c-71da04cab298\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" mentions that the translation is based on several earlier incomplete draft translations. At least some of these had been produced already, during the earlier Tibetan translation efforts of the eighth and ninth centuries, as attested by the text’s inclusion in the Denkarma inventory. \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":263,\"end\":548}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Tsultrim Gyaltsen\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":548,\"end\":565},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"06eeafb3-6e7a-45a9-a148-46d8a8e4fd64\",\"uuid\":\"a65d55f4-bb20-46f2-9344-f46bc8e3bdf0\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" further mentions that he worked on the translation together with a large team of Indian \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":565,\"end\":654}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"paṇḍitas\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":654,\"end\":662},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"fe29caf7-ba48-40cd-928d-c7b564375742\",\"uuid\":\"e04ae3df-1ca8-4279-ab2c-bbc94ad9bc9d\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", among whom he makes specific mention of \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":662,\"end\":704}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Śāntākaragupta\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":704,\"end\":718},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"30ed045a-ee86-4311-bb33-84f5a2b57370\",\"uuid\":\"62f88200-c606-446a-8630-5f6a73fbe78d\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":718,\"end\":720}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Abhayākaragupta\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":720,\"end\":735},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"7114b873-5be9-4a36-a988-e6af036a6bf2\",\"uuid\":\"fc029876-edd9-4683-b87f-91c5ddd7057f\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":735,\"end\":737}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Śakyarakṣita\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":737,\"end\":749},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"10359430-2efe-4d8d-b059-ec2dfc31c2d5\",\"uuid\":\"86ebdc3c-b733-4beb-a19e-880691b86c16\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":749,\"end\":751}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Vīryākaraśānti\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":751,\"end\":765},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"16e9fa77-0503-4acd-9453-88cddbdea147\",\"uuid\":\"4c6de47c-83ee-4f63-9e7f-f451d3d5e6ed\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":765,\"end\":767}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Subhūticandra\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":767,\"end\":780},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"8f9e7977-2b92-4553-b1db-70aa85d65a51\",\"uuid\":\"cd5894b0-1b70-4d12-adb1-69879d7cfc44\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", and \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":780,\"end\":786}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Aḍitacandra\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":786,\"end\":797},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"b59b805c-4cb5-4883-a807-21fe6012f460\",\"uuid\":\"924b0b87-8000-4191-a8a6-f77cd5b4d3dd\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". He also says that he was further assisted by two other Tibetan scholars, \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":797,\"end\":872}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Shang Buchikpa\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":872,\"end\":886},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"8f95e55b-f8a2-4919-b4d8-9d4a2d5a9f29\",\"uuid\":\"2755f516-ddd0-494e-b29f-7268038bcf8b\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" and \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":886,\"end\":891}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Sherap Ö\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":891,\"end\":899},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"8a835a20-fe45-4165-af64-50bd9470ae01\",\"uuid\":\"3759a571-f4d7-436c-9add-4e7b008b0b6a\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\". In spite of his prominent role in producing this translation of the AMSD, \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":899,\"end\":975}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Patshap Tsultrim Gyaltsen\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":975,\"end\":1000},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"06eeafb3-6e7a-45a9-a148-46d8a8e4fd64\",\"uuid\":\"e3330364-2e59-4b51-8166-cdd2dd60b676\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" does not appear to have translated any other texts contained in the Kangyur. We do, however, find a \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1000,\"end\":1101}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Tsultrim Gyaltsen\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1101,\"end\":1118},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"06eeafb3-6e7a-45a9-a148-46d8a8e4fd64\",\"uuid\":\"61133c08-95ee-4dc8-9ac9-c8c8bbee8439\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", who may very likely be the same person, listed as the translator of a number of tantric practice manuals contained in the Tengyur, at times working with the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1118,\"end\":1277}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"paṇḍita\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1277,\"end\":1284},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"fe29caf7-ba48-40cd-928d-c7b564375742\",\"uuid\":\"a74dd905-5c95-4156-9c8a-8fcee29dd256\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" named \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1284,\"end\":1291}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Abhayākaragupta\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1291,\"end\":1306},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"7114b873-5be9-4a36-a988-e6af036a6bf2\",\"uuid\":\"518d1254-6cb6-4bfc-b6eb-8e3952fe3054\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (who we just saw was involved in the translation of the AMSD). Apart from such brief listings of his name, however, we sadly have no other information available about this important figure in the history of Tibetan Buddhism.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1306,\"end\":1531}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"3f815b58-9aaa-4b12-88f0-8c2c9bbe6667\",\"sort\":157,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"label\":\"i.6\",\"alignments\":{}},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":1177,\"uuid\":\"3f815b58-9aaa-4b12-88f0-8c2c9bbe6667\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"The single extant Sanskrit manuscript of the AMSD is supposedly kept today at the Norbulingka in Lhasa, although no official information is available about this and physical access to the manuscript appears to be highly restricted. Photographs of the manuscript have recently been shared among a small group of scholars in the West, but these photos are also not freely accessible at present. According to Daniel Stuart, the date of composition of the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":452}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"sūtra\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":452,\"end\":457},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"643935d0-63fb-47fc-8abc-2bc1b02a1331\",\"uuid\":\"b3d2c159-0a83-4133-8741-0dfcb6363d37\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" in India can be established to be somewhere between 150 and 400 \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":457,\"end\":522}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ᴄᴇ\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":522,\"end\":524},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"smallCaps\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":522,\"end\":524,\"uuid\":\"417a8614-6981-40a2-bac7-28d59d63e67e\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"small-caps\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", whereas the dating of the only extant Sanskrit manuscript in Tibet has been suggested, by Stuart, to a much later period: circa the eleventh to thirteenth centuries \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":524,\"end\":691}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ᴄᴇ\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":691,\"end\":693},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"smallCaps\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":691,\"end\":693,\"uuid\":\"050d8d02-3759-409a-866b-8c5e44e24805\",\"type\":\"span\",\"textStyle\":\"small-caps\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\".\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":693,\"end\":694},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"endNoteLink\",\"attrs\":{\"notes\":[{\"endNote\":\"b54d6d7c-b662-4b45-a74c-4acd813b7825\",\"label\":\"8\",\"uuid\":\"100e01ff-1fcc-4db7-a089-11befb5e2520\",\"start\":694,\"end\":694,\"location\":\"end\",\"toh\":null}]}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" The extant Sanskrit manuscript largely parallels the Degé Tibetan edition up to the discussion of the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":694,\"end\":797}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Heaven Free from Strife\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":797,\"end\":820},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"51ea6bef-2574-4728-a987-a2d2c53e8fd3\",\"uuid\":\"e43342c6-8789-48e1-a931-09c2146f7070\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (near the end of the second Tibetan volume), at which point the text ends. The Sanskrit manuscript is a partial copy that only covers approximately half of the text as contained in the Chinese and Tibetan translations. Notably, as Stuart has shown, the surviving Sanskrit manuscript and the Chinese and Tibetan translations all transmit the same recension.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":820,\"end\":1177},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"endNoteLink\",\"attrs\":{\"notes\":[{\"endNote\":\"91edf2bd-a24d-43d6-874f-2dc5db59fe78\",\"label\":\"9\",\"uuid\":\"41381cdd-a071-4431-aa62-5a8aab55e430\",\"start\":1177,\"end\":1177,\"location\":\"end\",\"toh\":null}]}}]}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"792d7001-99d4-45f1-ac3e-376729469673\",\"sort\":170,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"label\":\"i.7\",\"alignments\":{}},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":925,\"uuid\":\"792d7001-99d4-45f1-ac3e-376729469673\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"A critical edition and English translation of the Sanskrit text pertaining to the first part of chapter 2 (according to the Tibetan chapter structure) has been published by Stuart.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":180},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"endNoteLink\",\"attrs\":{\"notes\":[{\"endNote\":\"ec751a9e-0c2a-4992-a2e6-cad9c6741fb9\",\"label\":\"10\",\"uuid\":\"a1334609-19a3-4311-b6bb-a364700a931a\",\"start\":180,\"end\":180,\"location\":\"end\",\"toh\":null}]}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" Critical editions of chapter 1 and the section on the hell realms in the latter part of chapter 2 are currently being prepared by Vesna Wallace and Mitsuyo Demoto, respectively.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":180,\"end\":358},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"endNoteLink\",\"attrs\":{\"notes\":[{\"endNote\":\"a7fe81a5-8ce8-4919-b34d-eb3e7cf832eb\",\"label\":\"11\",\"uuid\":\"816fd6ef-3618-4a6d-8059-78ed3178eaa8\",\"start\":358,\"end\":358,\"location\":\"end\",\"toh\":null}]}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" As we prepared this English translation we consulted Stuart’s critical Sanskrit edition and English translation of that section of the text, which proved to be very beneficial for our translation. Wallace and Demoto also both kindly shared their draft Sanskrit editions with us, which likewise was very helpful for our work. For a detailed discussion of the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":358,\"end\":717}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"sūtra\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":717,\"end\":722},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"643935d0-63fb-47fc-8abc-2bc1b02a1331\",\"uuid\":\"e8903b03-fb03-4ad6-beea-93527044f9eb\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"’s textual history and the Sanskrit, Chinese, and Tibetan manuscripts, we refer the interested reader to Stuart’s doctoral thesis on the AMSD (2012) and his later published version of his thesis (2015a).\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":722,\"end\":925}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"93bd509d-754e-44d3-ae64-8eaa672ab29f\",\"sort\":178,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"label\":\"i.8\",\"alignments\":{}},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":1448,\"uuid\":\"93bd509d-754e-44d3-ae64-8eaa672ab29f\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Short references to the AMSD, its teaching on impermanence, and its calls to renunciation are quite frequent in the Tibetan scholarly tradition. Most notably, \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":159}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Karmapa III, Rangjung Dorjé\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":159,\"end\":186},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"44394edb-98b3-4e82-b0d6-d9fa66ff4226\",\"uuid\":\"94df60ee-0878-4ea6-8491-dd7487c75497\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" (1284–1339), produced a large compendium to the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":186,\"end\":235}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"sūtra\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":235,\"end\":240},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"643935d0-63fb-47fc-8abc-2bc1b02a1331\",\"uuid\":\"e7d939f2-18f3-4ad3-8dc6-2949f9156870\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\".\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":240,\"end\":241},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"endNoteLink\",\"attrs\":{\"notes\":[{\"endNote\":\"e5a4315a-12ec-4c5b-aa3a-11850275cf9e\",\"label\":\"12\",\"uuid\":\"34d9f1b3-7d6f-4040-9dfc-e799f26dada8\",\"start\":241,\"end\":241,\"location\":\"end\",\"toh\":null}]}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" Modern scholarship on the AMSD was first undertaken by Lin and Demiéville (1949) but has recently been greatly advanced through the publications of Stuart (2012, 2015a, 2015b, 2017a). Stuart’s recent work provides a wealth of information regarding the available textual witnesses and analysis of some of the heterogeneous doctrinal developments that find expression in the AMSD. In addition to her forthcoming critical Sanskrit edition of chapter 3, Demoto (2009) has also published a study of the names of the various hell realms that occur in this chapter. Robert Kritzer is currently preparing a Tibetan critical edition and English translation of the final (autonomous) section of the AMSD, which concerns mindfulness of the body (chapter 7 according to the Chinese chapter division). Kritzer also kindly shared his unpublished paper (forthcoming) on the AMSD’s complex presentation of “\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":241,\"end\":1133}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"worms\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1133,\"end\":1138},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"b58c9481-32a9-4586-a2e1-b08870bc187f\",\"uuid\":\"9060c294-42b4-466e-a0fc-a23a6b724eec\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"” that are described in the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1138,\"end\":1166}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"sūtra\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1166,\"end\":1171},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"643935d0-63fb-47fc-8abc-2bc1b02a1331\",\"uuid\":\"6fb765fa-6169-4b27-8bca-1e043e1bd366\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" as inhabiting the human body.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1171,\"end\":1201},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"endNoteLink\",\"attrs\":{\"notes\":[{\"endNote\":\"6a779139-3306-466d-9d7d-ae477b5d7544\",\"label\":\"13\",\"uuid\":\"0dfdf664-6a25-4bc3-be5d-3ff67f3b7b73\",\"start\":1201,\"end\":1201,\"location\":\"end\",\"toh\":null}]}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" Recently, in his book on sexuality in Indian Buddhism, José Cabezón has also discussed the lengthy presentation of the hells that we find in the AMSD, where several hells are described as the ripened results of various forms of \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1201,\"end\":1430}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"sexual misconduct\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1430,\"end\":1447},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"b9db826d-bfc2-49ef-a9b0-bbe70bf16d26\",\"uuid\":\"6d8e47a6-fd9d-4d72-8ae0-cff7f660bc6c\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\".\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1447,\"end\":1448},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"endNoteLink\",\"attrs\":{\"notes\":[{\"endNote\":\"87f684d3-3484-4c1f-bc75-c2735f0d4d45\",\"label\":\"14\",\"uuid\":\"05bc81d7-d4e6-4319-a8ce-d4709bebfec7\",\"start\":1448,\"end\":1448,\"location\":\"end\",\"toh\":null}]}}]}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"31e05502-bbec-404b-a406-018030734a07\",\"sort\":195,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"label\":\"i.9\",\"alignments\":{}},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":1367,\"uuid\":\"31e05502-bbec-404b-a406-018030734a07\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"In producing this English translation, we have based our work on the Degé xylograph while consulting the Comparative Edition (\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":126}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"dpe bsdur ma)\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":126,\"end\":139},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"italic\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"f791d666-db3d-4d62-bb49-d3f39872ea88\",\"lang\":\"Bo-Ltn\",\"type\":\"inlineTitle\"}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\", as well as the Stok Palace manuscript. It goes without saying that we do not see our translation as definitive, or final, in any way. As the publications of Stuart, Kritzer, and Demoto have clearly demonstrated, there is a dizzying amount of philological detail to consider in the Sanskrit, Chinese, and Tibetan witnesses of the AMSD. As our aim has been to produce a complete English translation of the more than 2100 pages contained in the Tibetan text, we have unfortunately not been able to study these textual details of the \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":139,\"end\":671}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"sūtra\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":671,\"end\":676},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"643935d0-63fb-47fc-8abc-2bc1b02a1331\",\"uuid\":\"5ea95068-c3e0-4f45-815e-35e23ae951de\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" to the degree that learned scholars would otherwise expect. We therefore sincerely apologize for any errors and shortcomings this English translation may contain. We nevertheless hope that, in spite of its imperfections, this publication may prove useful for scholars, as well as members of the general public, who wish to explore and study this amazing discourse. As further studies on this \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":676,\"end\":1069}},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"sūtra\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1069,\"end\":1074},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"glossaryInstance\",\"attrs\":{\"glossary\":\"643935d0-63fb-47fc-8abc-2bc1b02a1331\",\"uuid\":\"51c64320-d7d7-4a34-a61c-921e91303a98\",\"toh\":null}}]},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\" are published in the future, the present translation surely also stands to benefit. With its poetic beauty, philosophical profundity, and gripping presentation of the world as perceived by Buddhists in early medieval India, the AMSD certainly deserves the attention of the contemporary world.\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":1074,\"end\":1367}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"3e56caba-c28c-4a83-856a-d6ab4da36172\",\"sort\":202,\"type\":\"introductionHeader\",\"label\":\"\",\"alignments\":{}},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"heading\",\"attrs\":{\"level\":3,\"start\":0,\"end\":28,\"uuid\":\"70d7581c-c853-4236-9bfb-5f9bc814e085\",\"class\":\"section-title\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Detailed Outline of the Text\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":28}}]}]},{\"type\":\"passage\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"b0028da6-76c7-4ff9-b65d-4c4a237c5dfb\",\"sort\":204,\"type\":\"introduction\",\"label\":\"i.10\",\"alignments\":{}},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"bulletList\",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":5841,\"uuid\":\"3aad05ae-8915-4737-b4ce-2cc4ac7b2495\",\"spacing\":\"vertical\"},\"content\":[{\"type\":\"listItem\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"I. Chapter 1 (Vol. 68) \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":23},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"internalLink\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"99cb7a6f-5b92-4ad7-99d1-65ae878feb7b\",\"href\":\"/entity/passage/d58ca9d4-56f4-42fe-8f1d-ac8245bb641a\",\"entity\":\"d58ca9d4-56f4-42fe-8f1d-ac8245bb641a\",\"type\":\"passage\",\"toh\":null,\"isSameWork\":true,\"subtype\":\"translation\"}}]}],\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":23}},{\"type\":\"bulletList\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"listItem\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"A. The Ten Virtuous Courses of Action \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":23,\"end\":61},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"internalLink\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"04ef2f19-4a5e-43d6-9505-af1c8bdbd699\",\"href\":\"/entity/passage/d58ca9d4-56f4-42fe-8f1d-ac8245bb641a\",\"entity\":\"d58ca9d4-56f4-42fe-8f1d-ac8245bb641a\",\"type\":\"passage\",\"toh\":null,\"isSameWork\":true,\"subtype\":\"translation\"}}]}],\"attrs\":{\"start\":23,\"end\":61,\"uuid\":\"5b0d119b-ae9e-49d7-b3b2-d808c0af6bcc\"}}],\"attrs\":{\"start\":23,\"end\":61,\"uuid\":\"5b0d119b-ae9e-49d7-b3b2-d808c0af6bcc\"}}],\"attrs\":{\"start\":23,\"end\":61,\"uuid\":\"56906567-0489-487a-8d3f-c23e95f54680\",\"spacing\":\"horizontal\"}}],\"attrs\":{\"start\":0,\"end\":61,\"uuid\":\"053b38de-13c6-468b-9c23-c982fa93f2d6\"}},{\"type\":\"listItem\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"II. Chapter 2 \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":61,\"end\":75},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"internalLink\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"67c17cd2-7a4f-4b1d-ad0a-dcb203c3052f\",\"href\":\"/entity/passage/de849aff-59a3-453a-9658-7cf5cf58b42e\",\"entity\":\"de849aff-59a3-453a-9658-7cf5cf58b42e\",\"type\":\"passage\",\"toh\":null,\"isSameWork\":true,\"subtype\":\"translation\"}}]}],\"attrs\":{\"start\":61,\"end\":75}},{\"type\":\"bulletList\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"listItem\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"B. The Eighteen Grounds \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":75,\"end\":99},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"internalLink\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"0471d245-e19b-4dd8-beaa-674115efd63b\",\"href\":\"/entity/passage/de849aff-59a3-453a-9658-7cf5cf58b42e\",\"entity\":\"de849aff-59a3-453a-9658-7cf5cf58b42e\",\"type\":\"passage\",\"toh\":null,\"isSameWork\":true,\"subtype\":\"translation\"}}]}],\"attrs\":{\"start\":75,\"end\":99}},{\"type\":\"bulletList\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"listItem\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"1. The First Ground \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":99,\"end\":119},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"internalLink\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"64c52fd7-715c-4e88-93d2-8bab50d72d2d\",\"href\":\"/entity/passage/3433d812-77f6-4b84-8fb4-d9e641eacaa1\",\"entity\":\"3433d812-77f6-4b84-8fb4-d9e641eacaa1\",\"type\":\"passage\",\"toh\":null,\"isSameWork\":true,\"subtype\":\"translation\"}}]}],\"attrs\":{\"start\":99,\"end\":119,\"uuid\":\"e828cc64-5384-4ae4-b92e-4b456569155f\"}}],\"attrs\":{\"start\":99,\"end\":119,\"uuid\":\"e828cc64-5384-4ae4-b92e-4b456569155f\"}},{\"type\":\"listItem\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"2. The Second Ground \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":119,\"end\":140},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"internalLink\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"46226a63-8477-4df7-9b8f-36bbb6264a4a\",\"href\":\"/entity/passage/b7befc2a-2caf-4d35-8420-ae25260f0939\",\"entity\":\"b7befc2a-2caf-4d35-8420-ae25260f0939\",\"type\":\"passage\",\"toh\":null,\"isSameWork\":true,\"subtype\":\"translation\"}}]}],\"attrs\":{\"start\":119,\"end\":140,\"uuid\":\"faf52e82-833d-4c5f-aa65-b200db2a578e\"}}],\"attrs\":{\"start\":119,\"end\":140,\"uuid\":\"faf52e82-833d-4c5f-aa65-b200db2a578e\"}},{\"type\":\"listItem\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"3. The Third Ground \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":140,\"end\":160},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"internalLink\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"e75b5f3a-63cc-4952-8d2a-49d6b55e0e0b\",\"href\":\"/entity/passage/a1eaa3bf-af4c-406c-8358-68e172c8b810\",\"entity\":\"a1eaa3bf-af4c-406c-8358-68e172c8b810\",\"type\":\"passage\",\"toh\":null,\"isSameWork\":true,\"subtype\":\"translation\"}}]}],\"attrs\":{\"start\":140,\"end\":160,\"uuid\":\"982b5c24-74c4-46bf-ad9b-f3479bc6a999\"}}],\"attrs\":{\"start\":140,\"end\":160,\"uuid\":\"982b5c24-74c4-46bf-ad9b-f3479bc6a999\"}},{\"type\":\"listItem\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"4. The Fourth Ground \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":160,\"end\":181},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"internalLink\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"fef7034b-a8e8-4144-8fe0-0fbd032d2a7d\",\"href\":\"/entity/passage/5d9c542f-1afb-4448-a81c-c29a5c4e6262\",\"entity\":\"5d9c542f-1afb-4448-a81c-c29a5c4e6262\",\"type\":\"passage\",\"toh\":null,\"isSameWork\":true,\"subtype\":\"translation\"}}]}],\"attrs\":{\"start\":160,\"end\":181,\"uuid\":\"e6a13538-eec1-482f-b192-63fd2c05cd6f\"}}],\"attrs\":{\"start\":160,\"end\":181,\"uuid\":\"e6a13538-eec1-482f-b192-63fd2c05cd6f\"}},{\"type\":\"listItem\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"5. The Fifth Ground \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":181,\"end\":201},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"internalLink\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"70da1cec-3057-49e3-a8cd-5bb29c801cc7\",\"href\":\"/entity/passage/19731907-003e-48ac-a0c1-fc6f73541fb5\",\"entity\":\"19731907-003e-48ac-a0c1-fc6f73541fb5\",\"type\":\"passage\",\"toh\":null,\"isSameWork\":true,\"subtype\":\"translation\"}}]}],\"attrs\":{\"start\":181,\"end\":201,\"uuid\":\"4964e554-30eb-4abd-9cfc-a89d352e0ef0\"}}],\"attrs\":{\"start\":181,\"end\":201,\"uuid\":\"4964e554-30eb-4abd-9cfc-a89d352e0ef0\"}},{\"type\":\"listItem\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"6. The Sixth Ground \",\"attrs\":{\"start\":201,\"end\":221},\"marks\":[{\"type\":\"internalLink\",\"attrs\":{\"uuid\":\"fe4a79fe-b5fb-4112-a1ac-5d00a1d4cfc3\",\"href\":\"/entity/passage/1b8a34cc-9662-430e-81a2-c6a536084bb5\",\"entity\":\"1b8a34cc-9662-430e-81a2-c6a536084bb5\",\"type\":\"passage\",\"toh\":null,\"isSameWork\":true,\"subtype\":\"translation\"}}]}],\"attrs\":{\"start\":201,\"end\":221,\"uuid\":\"b1e7c1cf-559a-4651-ba25-ff107346eee5\"}}],\"attrs\":{\"start\":201,\"end\":221,\"uuid\":\"b1e7c1cf-559a-4651-ba25-ff107346eee5\"}},{\"type\":\"listItem\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"paragraph\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"